	<item>
		<title>About Me</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/about</link>
		<pubDate>Sun, 24 Jan 2010 17:26:41 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/?page_id=2</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[I've got 3 words to define my art. Dramatic, emotional, classic and close, ok that was 4, but the last one isn't as cool, but totally describes my style. I think pictures are for capturing expressions in the faces we love. I take my job very seriously, and need to take pictures as much as I need to breath. It's my art, my way of expression, and an important part of my livelihood. When I'm taking a picture, I'm at my very best. I love it!I love the light. I love the click of the camera. I love trying to find the perfect angle. And most of all, I love the people.I want my clients to feel good having their pictures taken, both during and after their shoot. I feel so lucky to get to do what I love everyday.If my style of photography fits your style, please let me help you feel good becoming art.]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Q&amp;A</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/qa</link>
		<pubDate>Sun, 31 Jan 2010 20:31:29 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/?page_id=244</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="qaQuestion"></div>
<div class="qaQuestion">What ages are best to get pictures taken in the first year?</div>
<div class="qaQuestion">It's best to schedule your newborn shoot within the first 2 weeks, then it's every three months for the first year.</div>
<div class="qaQuestion">What should I wear?</div>
<div class="qaAnswer">Solid colors that are either darker or lighter tend to photograph the best. Loud patterns can be distracting to the eye. Black is ideal for newborn pictures. Little girls in white dresses are also a favorite of mine. Ultimately, I think what's most important is that you feel comfortable. It's not about your clothes, it's all about you and your family. If you're planning a boudoir session, just contact me and we can chat.</div>
<div class="qaQuestion">How long will the shoot last?</div>
<div class="qaAnswer">Typically my shoots last about an hour, but I'm very flexible.  I work with and around my client.  If they're happy and having fun, I'll shoot as long as they let me.  I don't want tears, picture day is supposed to be fun.  It's all about having fun.</div>
<div class="qaQuestion">How many pictures can I expect?</div>
<div class="qaQuestion">It really depends, but typically between 50-80</div>
<div class="qaQuestion">What should I bring?</div>
<div class="qaAnswer">I'm not a really big "prop" photographer, but if you have something that is sentimental definitely bring it.  Meaningful stuffed animals, blankets, family heirloms, and cute hats are awesome.  Bring a couple outfits if you're unsure, but mostly I like the naked babies and all their rolls.</div>
<div class="qaQuestion">How will I proof the photos after the session?</div>
<div class="qaAnswer">A couple days after the shoot, I will post the pics to your very own web page for you to view and share with friends and family.  You'll be able to view the images in color, black and white, and sepia.  You'll also have pricing and ordering information on that page.</div>
<div class="qaQuestion">How did you get started doing photography, and how long have you been doing it?</div>
<div class="qaAnswer">I've been taking pictures as long as I can remember.  I traveled a lot when I was young and I always had my little Kodak camera with me.  I would take several rolls of 110 film every trip.  Film...haha.
I guess I was just born with a love for photography, because I never stopped.  I took classes in high school and college.  Then I walked into my basement one day 5 years ago and my dream became a reality.  I still open the door turn on the lights and sigh.</div>
<div class="qaQuestion">What kind of touch up do you do?</div>
<div class="qaQuestion">Any and all, I can take stretch marks out, remove acne, and darkness under the eyes. I may not make all the fine touch ups on the proofs, but I do on the prints, and CD if you choose to order it.</div>
<div class="qaQuestion">How long do I have to order?</div>
<div class="qaAnswer">I like for my clients to try to get their order in 2 weeks after having them put on the web.  They will stay up for a month.  I find if I give people longer and they can't decide they just procrastinate.  I know I do.</div>
<div class="qaQuestion">Once I place an order, how long until I receive them?</div>
<div class="qaAnswer">Typically about a week, but of course I can rush the pics if you need me too.  That usually takes 4 days.</div>
<div class="qaQuestion">Do you do announcements?</div>
<div class="qaAnswer">I did announcements for a while but found I couldn't compete with the web in terms of cost, so now I offer my clients a killer deal.  Basically, you can get whatever images you want for your announcements for $30.</div>
<div class="qaQuestion">What other types of products can I get?</div>
<div class="qaAnswer">Canvases, collages, jewelry, albums, books, you name it I can create it!</div>
<div class="qaQuestion">Do you photograph dogs?</div>
<div class="qaAnswer">I love dogs, absolutely.</div>
<div class="qaQuestion">In fact do you have pets?</div>
<div class="qaAnswer">Lucy and Layla are my little rat terriers.  They will bark at you when you come over, just ignore them.  They're all bark.  I also have a horse named Diamond.  She's perfect!</div>
<div class="qaQuestion">Do you only do studio photography?</div>
<div class="qaAnswer">No way, I need some fresh air every now and then.  I especially love the fall that's my favorite time to go outside.  I do charge a $30 travel fee, but you can come back and do studio pics too.  If you don't want to go somewhere we can just do some in my backyard, my house backs up to Burr Oak Woods.</div>
<div class="qaQuestion">What's your favorite thing to photograph?</div>
<div class="qaAnswer">I love to see the world, so travel photography is my favorite.  People in exotic places, that's where my heart is.  But the people here are pretty awesome too.</div>
<div class="qaQuestion">Can other family members order pictures?</div>
<div class="qaAnswer">Sure, no problem.  They can place an order independently as well, so don't feel like you have to coordinate.</div>
<div class="qaQuestion">How do we get the pictures when they come in?</div>
<div class="qaAnswer">I can mail them to you for $5, or you can arrange a time to come pick them up.</div>
<div class="qaQuestion">Where is your studio?</div>
<div class="qaAnswer">My studio is in my basement. I love having an in house studio. I wouldn't have it any other way.  If you're ever running late, don't worry, I'm just doing laundry or watching TV.  That's a lie, I'm always working.  My wonderful husband/assistant, Jon, is doing the laundry.</div>
<div class="qaQuestion">When should I book my appointment?</div>
<div class="qaAnswer">I would recommend at least a month in advance.  However, if you need a quick appointment, I can usually squeeze you in. Just give me a call and we can work something out.</div>
<div class="qaQuestion">Do you have any tips for shoots with babies?</div>
<div class="qaAnswer">Babies do really well full and rested.  I know the rest thing doesn't always happen, but try to feed your baby before you come over.  If we need to take a break so you can feed them in the middle of the shoot that's fine too.  Another tip would be to schedule your shoot when you find your baby is at their best.  Some babies like the morning some like the afternoon and some are night owls like myself.  Finally don't worry about getting your baby to smile in all the pictures, we want ALL the cute faces, even sour ones.</div>
<div class="qaQuestion">What do you love about your job?</div>
<div class="qaAnswer">Technically speaking I love the light!  I'm an artist and people are my canvas, light is my paint and my camera is my brush.  But really I love the relationships I have developed with my clients.  A lot of my clients have become close friends.  I get to watch their children grow up, and be there to capture it.  I love that my photography is what my clients have to help them remember.  It's an honor I take very seriously.</div>]]></content:encoded>

		<content:encoded><![CDATA[]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>
		<wp:post_id>445</wp:post_id>

	<item>
		<title>Children photography~ Kansas City</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?page_id=1139</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 01 Jan 1970 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?page_id=1139</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">Adorable....nuff said!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1140" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?attachment_id=1140"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1140" title="glas1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/glas1.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is Annie, and she is just about as perfect as perfect can be. As you can see she's super photogenic, but what you can't see is that she is so patient, understanding, and willing to do everything her mom Melissa and I asked.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1144" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?attachment_id=1144"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1144" title="glas5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/glas5.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">She is also super good with her little brother Sam. Sam is quiet and patient too, but he wasn't last time we took pics. Last time he was scared, this time he was perfect just like his sister. I mean it was really too easy. Picking pics to share with you was a real challenge.</p>


<a rel="attachment wp-att-1143" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?attachment_id=1143"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1143" title="glas4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/glas4.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">And then Sam gave me this little jewel. He's a serious little boy by nature, but he also loves to laugh. I was just changing up my lights and he just stood waiting. I feel like I can see right into his soul in this picture.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1142" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?attachment_id=1142"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1142" title="glas3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/glas3.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">I said Annie is good with her brother, but I didn't tell you that Sam loves his sister!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1145" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?attachment_id=1145"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1145" title="glas6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/glas6.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">See what I mean...</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1141" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?attachment_id=1141"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1141" title="glas2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/glas2.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>Melissa I always love our time together! I hope Ben loved his father's day gift as much as I liked taking them!</p>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>It&#039;s time....</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/4</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 16 Jun 2008 01:49:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/4</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://bp3.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SFXMqtN-UnI/AAAAAAAAAA8/ab8Nz0e-V9Q/s1600-h/DSC_0354.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://bp3.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SFXMqtN-UnI/AAAAAAAAAA8/ab8Nz0e-V9Q/s320/DSC_0354.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5212297177815994994" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://bp1.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SFXMtPFudlI/AAAAAAAAABE/5SG03zYdpxI/s1600-h/DSC_0398.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://bp1.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SFXMtPFudlI/AAAAAAAAABE/5SG03zYdpxI/s320/DSC_0398.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5212297221267945042" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://bp3.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SFXIhdeToyI/AAAAAAAAAAM/677CF9UnQZM/s1600-h/DSC_0429.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://bp3.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SFXIhdeToyI/AAAAAAAAAAM/677CF9UnQZM/s320/DSC_0429.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5212292620924199714" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://bp1.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SFXIhmcEkbI/AAAAAAAAAAU/2af2x4a8Gho/s1600-h/DSC_0363.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://bp1.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SFXIhmcEkbI/AAAAAAAAAAU/2af2x4a8Gho/s320/DSC_0363.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5212292623330742706" /></a><br /><span class="Apple-style-span"  style="font-family:'trebuchet ms';">It's time for me to jump into the world of blogging. I've been reading blogs now for awhile, but never thought it was for me. With my growing photography business I feel it's time to make time. So here I am. I will try to make this entertaining with pictures and funny stories, but we'll see. Here are some pictures I took this weekend in St. Louis. My brother-in-law got married and we had a blast spending a weekend on the other side of the state. Happy to be home now though.</span>]]></content:encoded>

She was trying to be the good little obedient dog she always is, while Lucy wanted nothing to do with me. Notice Lucy's expression. Pretty funny. It's been beautiful outside and I've really enjoyed taking some green pictures. ]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Weird Weather</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/7</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 20 Jun 2008 03:44:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/7</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://bp0.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SFsraI8bsWI/AAAAAAAAAB8/mG0CRS5AKYQ/s1600-h/sunset.jpg"><img style="float:left; margin:0 10px 10px 0;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://bp0.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SFsraI8bsWI/AAAAAAAAAB8/mG0CRS5AKYQ/s320/sunset.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5213808721689031010" /></a><br />Today was a beautiful day. Warm but breezy enough to sit comfortably outside and read a book. Then at about 6 a front blew in, and with it cool air that felt amazing. I didn't think about weather in Missouri except to complain. Until I met someone that spent their whole life on the west coast. They said their favorite thing about living in Missouri is watching the fronts blow in. To them the unpredictable nature of our weather is exciting. Now I too appreciate the constant change. <div>So tonight I was driving to the gym and as I was leaving my neighborhood I saw this amazing sunset happening in the middle of the storm front. I had to go home and get my camera. Of course by the time I got back it had changed. I really wanted to capture the pink puffy clouds catching some beautiful sun light, I thought it looked like cotton candy in the sky. What I got is a lot darker and a little eerie. I actually didn't do any work on this in photoshop. It is what you see. Everywhere else in the sky it was a hazy gray color. It was like someone ripped open the sky right in front of me. I hope you got to enjoy a similar sunset on your own.</div><div><br /></div>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>America&#039;s Pastime</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/8</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 23 Jun 2008 01:52:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/8</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://bp3.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SF8DQyiX4fI/AAAAAAAAACE/AfqnjoGcrAw/s1600-h/86c.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://bp3.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SF8DRGiuySI/AAAAAAAAACc/XU5xSehmNDk/s320/86f.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5214890485867268386" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://bp0.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SF8DRTy2TiI/AAAAAAAAACk/EbEKH8gqVCw/s1600-h/86d.jpg"><img style="display:block; It was hot, but the light was golden and I couldn't help taking a few pics.  The boys let me take some shots around the dugout. I was a little worried about a ball flying in there and hitting me or my best friend. As you can imagine I wasn't paying much attention to the game. Baseball is a boring game, I'm not going to lie, but it's also one of my favorite summer memories. I look forward to capturing some more images later this summer. Maybe even Jon's swing. He told me he was glad I didn't take pictures of his swing tonight because it was bad. Whatever that means. Oh yah they won the game at the last inning! </span></span>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>contrast and composition</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/9</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 25 Jun 2008 19:36:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/9</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://bp3.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SGKeb-UU4TI/AAAAAAAAACs/xOFInb6ziIM/s1600-h/87.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://bp3.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SGKeb-UU4TI/AAAAAAAAACs/xOFInb6ziIM/s320/87.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5215905521870364978" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://bp1.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SGKecIAZ6JI/AAAAAAAAAC0/ckF7rt-iFkc/s1600-h/87a.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://bp1.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SGKecIAZ6JI/AAAAAAAAAC0/ckF7rt-iFkc/s320/87a.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5215905524471163026" /></a><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">  </span>Some of my friends and family have taken to taking pictures. I think it's awesome. Photography is a great artistic outlet because it doesn't require years of practice to master the camera as it does other artistic tools. My good friend Cara recently encouraged me to start using my blog to help people make their pictures better, more artistic. I think you'll be surprised how a few simple rules can really make your pictures look more professional. I don't really know where to start I'll probably be pretty random actually depending on the pictures I take. <div><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>The above pictures have two composition concepts working for them. The first is called the rule of thirds. Long story short, don't put things right in the middle of the frame. Give the eye somewhere to go as it studies the picture. If the hat were right in the middle your eye would stop there. In these pictures you'll find your eye wondering. That's a good thing.</div><div><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>The second thing they have going for them is they both have strong lines going through the frame. I used the contrast in shadows to make the hat and light lines pop. Start to look around you and notice the differences in light. You'll be surprised what you see! Enjoy and happy shooting.<br /></div>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Future Andy Roddick, and maybe Nadal?</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=23</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 01 Jan 1970 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/?p=23</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SL9Ypln0voI/AAAAAAAAAKM/4HQ-Y2LeZ_Q/s1600-h/carter1.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SL9Ypln0voI/AAAAAAAAAKM/4HQ-Y2LeZ_Q/s320/carter1.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5242005962779573890"></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SL9Yp2BjlXI/AAAAAAAAAKU/1jRV56FyB1I/s1600-h/carter2.jpg"><img style="display:block; 		<title>The Workshop</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/the-workshop</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 22 Jul 2010 17:36:04 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?page_id=1104</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Fabulous Photography Workshop 101 (The Basic)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Here's the skinny!</em></p>
<strong>Who</strong>: This is for amateur or hobby photographers looking to improve their skills.

<strong>When</strong>: Saturday, April 30th from 10:30 am - 4:30 pm

<strong>Where: </strong>Gallery 325 @ 325 Southwest Boulevard, Kansas City, MO 64108

<strong>What to expec</strong>t:  This workshop will focus on the basics of digital photography.  In other words, how to really use your camera, exposure, composition, gear, and much much more.

<strong>What do I need</strong>:  A digital SLR.  If you have no idea what I'm talking about, but know that you want to take better pictures, and invest in a new camera. Just give me a ring I'll help you find a great camera that fits in your budget.  Beware: a good SLR camera is an investment and will cost you more than your typical point and shoot.

<strong>How much for the day</strong>:  $150 with a fabulous lunch included

<strong>How many are in the workshop?</strong> This class is limited to 20 people.
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>A few more quick details:</em></p>
Come a little early grab a doughnut, a good spot, and chat it up with your new photog friends.

After the workshop we're going to head to Nara for happy hour if anyone wants to join me for more fab photography discussions!

Bring your camera charged and ready to shoot, we will be taking pictures. Oh and bring your manual, lesson one always carry your manual.

SIGN UP HERE!  By submitting the Registration Form, you are agreeing to pay the $150 workshop fee via PayPal or check if a seat is available. You will receive a confirmation email within 24 hours solidifying your seat.
<div>816-830-2127</div>
<h3>Register here...</h3>

	<item>
		<title>Children Photography</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1234</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 01 Jan 1970 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1234</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1235" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?attachment_id=1235"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1235" title="hope1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/hope1.jpg" alt="" width="467" height="700" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Since having my aha moment last week my focus is now going to be on capturing emotion, so I guess I need to also work on showing the emotion I capture. I'm going to be sharing pictures on my blog not because they're the best, or cutest, or most technically perfect. I'm going to show them because they make me feel when I look at them. What a more perfect family to start with than the Sims family. They are so full of emotions, our shoot had laughter, more laughter, sweet kisses, and lots of love.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1238" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?attachment_id=1238"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1238" title="hope4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/hope4.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1236" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?attachment_id=1236"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1236" title="hope2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/hope2.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="467" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1240" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?attachment_id=1240"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1240" title="hope6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/hope6.jpg" alt="" width="467" height="700" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1237" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?attachment_id=1237"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1237" title="hope3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/hope3.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="467" /></a></p>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>lake trip</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/11</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 09 Jul 2008 21:43:00 +0000</pubDate>

margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://bp0.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SHUxxBIVxdI/AAAAAAAAAD0/MiceinqKzfM/s320/llama.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5221134061192725970" /></a>I'm home! After 11 wonderful relaxing days at the lake I'm happy to be home and back to blogging.  We had lots of adventures at the lake one of which was going to a drive through zoo outside of Eureka Springs. They had lots of cool animals it was really fun. One of the first animals we saw were these huge bison. They gave us food to feed them and I wanted to get a good picture of it. So I just threw some food at him hoping he would turn to look. Little did I know he would trot right over to the truck and stick his head in. I tried to feed him, but his mouth was so big and slobbery. Then there were the <span class="blsp-spelling-corrected" id="SPELLING_ERROR_0">ostriches</span>who literally would peck at you for food. They were so prehistoric looking it was really creepy. The last picture is for the llamas in the world. I love llamas!]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Eureka Springs</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/12</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 10 Jul 2008 20:55:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/12</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://bp3.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SHZ6O-tcTMI/AAAAAAAAAEE/-GmhYj5bccE/s1600-h/es2.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://bp3.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SHZ6O-tcTMI/AAAAAAAAAEE/-GmhYj5bccE/s320/es2.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5221495215753022658" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://bp1.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SHZ6POBdo1I/AAAAAAAAAEM/oWX0fs_iCSI/s1600-h/es3.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://bp1.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SHZ6POBdo1I/AAAAAAAAAEM/oWX0fs_iCSI/s320/es3.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5221495219863528274" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://bp0.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SHZ6PavvdvI/AAAAAAAAAEU/ZnkSE_cUTvU/s1600-h/es4.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://bp0.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SHZ6PavvdvI/AAAAAAAAAEU/ZnkSE_cUTvU/s320/es4.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5221495223278860018" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://bp1.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SHZ6PppzXsI/AAAAAAAAAEc/We1Lo-tQER4/s1600-h/es5.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://bp1.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SHZ6PppzXsI/AAAAAAAAAEc/We1Lo-tQER4/s320/es5.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5221495227280481986" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://bp1.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SHZ6P2oW-uI/AAAAAAAAAEk/gHhFAwMKUbc/s1600-h/es7.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://bp1.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SHZ6P2oW-uI/AAAAAAAAAEk/gHhFAwMKUbc/s320/es7.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5221495230764088034" /></a><br />Most of the time when we go to the lake we just go to the lake. However this year we managed to make not one trip, but three trips to Eureka Springs. I didn't mind, I love the city, and it's just a short 45 minutes from the lake house. We went shopping, went to the zoo, and got massages. It's a wonderful little city and if you're looking for a romantic and fun weekend getaway it's perfect. It's very eclectic with the artists, homosexuals, and of course Christians. One weekend it might be a gay pride festival, and the next a huge group of Christians come into town for The Great Passion Play. Did you like the big white jesus? Up close he actually looks Asian with a mop on top. My mom says the real deal in Brazil is much more impressive, but if you don't want to go too far south, just head to Arkansas for the next best thing. I personally go for the spas! There are plenty of places for relaxation and that's what I'm all about. This is starting to sound like a travel brochure, I better stop before I start describing the ancient hotels, with quaint cobble stone roads. I'm not going to lie it's a great getaway!]]></content:encoded>

		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>

		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://bp0.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SHj-D7ETKjI/AAAAAAAAAE8/ID0rhuBJ9eI/s1600-h/bkaliandpaige.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://bp0.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SHj-D7ETKjI/AAAAAAAAAE8/ID0rhuBJ9eI/s320/bkaliandpaige.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5222203111284877874" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://bp3.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SHj-EJWNx2I/AAAAAAAAAFE/-Ybu1TEz_h0/s1600-h/bpaige.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://bp3.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SHj-EJWNx2I/AAAAAAAAAFE/-Ybu1TEz_h0/s320/bpaige.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5222203115118118754" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://bp1.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SHj-EAZDNLI/AAAAAAAAAFM/inAfo_YCj0M/s1600-h/bpool.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://bp1.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SHj-EAZDNLI/AAAAAAAAAFM/inAfo_YCj0M/s320/bpool.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5222203112714089650" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://bp1.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SHj-ETYi2kI/AAAAAAAAAFU/Bxh4GIRBTMU/s1600-h/bpool2.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://bp1.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SHj-ETYi2kI/AAAAAAAAAFU/Bxh4GIRBTMU/s320/bpool2.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5222203117812243010" /></a><br />On Thursday I got to go watch one of my former third graders compete in a suburban league swim meet.Kali and Paige are both in the top picture and Paige is in the second. Kali my student is in the last picture thinking about her race. I shot these with my little point and shot cannon, I was really wishing I had my real camera, the speed wasn't there enough to get them swimming.<div>I have to admit being back at the pool really flooded my mind with memories. The smell of the chlorine, the anticipation of the coming race. It really took me back. Thanks again Kali for inviting me, it was great to see you!</div>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Kansas City Power and LIght</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/15</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 12 Jul 2008 19:24:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/15</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://bp0.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SHkGDCgZi9I/AAAAAAAAAFc/-78S4W8ghjI/s1600-h/bpl.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://bp0.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SHkGDCgZi9I/AAAAAAAAAFc/-78S4W8ghjI/s320/bpl.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5222211892194937810" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://bp3.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SHkGDfK7ZUI/AAAAAAAAAFk/X_Au7A18ylU/s1600-h/bpl3.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://bp3.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SHkGDfK7ZUI/AAAAAAAAAFk/X_Au7A18ylU/s320/bpl3.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5222211899889509698" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://bp2.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SHkGDW5mIhI/AAAAAAAAAFs/sJxKDGamG1k/s1600-h/bpl4.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://bp2.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SHkGDW5mIhI/AAAAAAAAAFs/sJxKDGamG1k/s320/bpl4.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5222211897669329426" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://bp0.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SHkGDo-PdGI/AAAAAAAAAF0/-9cjBr4KjMw/s1600-h/b2pl.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://bp0.blogger.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SHkGDo-PdGI/AAAAAAAAAF0/-9cjBr4KjMw/s320/b2pl.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5222211902520652898" /></a>Last night Jon and I made another <span class="blsp-spelling-corrected" id="SPELLING_ERROR_0">appearance</span>at our favorite hang out, The Power and Light District. We love to just sit in the Live Block and listen to a band, or people watch. Trust me there are plenty of interesting people out to watch. I snapped these off with my Cannon. One of these days I'll go down there at night with my Nikon and try to get some really fantastic shots. It's really a lot more impressive at night. If you haven't had time to go down there, find time, you'll feel like you're in another city!]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Paradise</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/16</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 09 Aug 2008 21:25:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/16</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SJ4LtVF67mI/AAAAAAAAAF8/yAZeXEJOAzQ/s1600-h/6.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SJ4LtVF67mI/AAAAAAAAAF8/yAZeXEJOAzQ/s320/6.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5232632690435092066" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SJ4LtbFpVTI/AAAAAAAAAGE/qxNmtnNePeE/s1600-h/2.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SJ4LtbFpVTI/AAAAAAAAAGE/qxNmtnNePeE/s320/2.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5232632692044551474" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SJ4Lth_tT3I/AAAAAAAAAGM/ZR2df9fTDdU/s1600-h/3.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SJ4Lth_tT3I/AAAAAAAAAGM/ZR2df9fTDdU/s320/3.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5232632693898694514" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SJ4Ltr9i-3I/AAAAAAAAAGU/5vQjbJgZxmM/s1600-h/4.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SJ4Ltr9i-3I/AAAAAAAAAGU/5vQjbJgZxmM/s320/4.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5232632696573983602" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SJ4Lt4L_9BI/AAAAAAAAAGc/cg__EjJpJng/s1600-h/5.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SJ4Lt4L_9BI/AAAAAAAAAGc/cg__EjJpJng/s320/5.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5232632699855827986" /></a>Well I'm home from paradise and have tons of photos to share with everyone. This set is of the resort itself. We stayed at Barcelo Maya Palace in the Maya Riviera. It was stunning, and I enjoyed every moment! We would start the day at about 9:00 with a big breakfast. Jon always had an omelet made. Then we would find some chairs in the shade on the beach until lunch time. Sometimes we would get up and walk down the beach or play beach volleyball, but most of the time we people watched and listened to the waves. In the afternoon we sat at the pool, took a nap and went to dinner. It was a rough time let me tell you. I can't wait to share more photos from the trip. ]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Beautiful Wedding!</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/19</link>
		<pubDate>Sun, 10 Aug 2008 02:19:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/19</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SJ5QhRhp5cI/AAAAAAAAAH0/Ds0BOOGQJDE/s1600-h/21.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SJ5QhRhp5cI/AAAAAAAAAH0/Ds0BOOGQJDE/s320/21.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5232708349621560770" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SJ5Qhks0abI/AAAAAAAAAH8/9H0UwcDpIGg/s1600-h/22.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SJ5Qhks0abI/AAAAAAAAAH8/9H0UwcDpIGg/s320/22.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5232708354768660914" /></a><br /><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SJ5QjGF6k9I/AAAAAAAAAIM/mE14208u6IM/s1600-h/25.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SJ5QjGF6k9I/AAAAAAAAAIM/mE14208u6IM/s320/25.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5232708380912161746" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SJ5QjNi8THI/AAAAAAAAAIU/NTKZHslBuqY/s1600-h/24.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SJ5QjNi8THI/AAAAAAAAAIU/NTKZHslBuqY/s320/24.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5232708382912957554" /></a>Jon and I had a wonderful time in Mexico, but our most memorable day was the day Jackie, and Jason (aka Smitty) got married. It couldn't have been a more perfect day. Warm and breezy with the perfect golden light. They stood just a few feet from the ocean and vowed to each other to always be there. They wrote their own vows so it was absolutely perfect. I felt honored to witness such a beautiful act of love.<div>In terms of photography, most of you know that weddings are not my specialty. Mostly because I don't have enough control of light, but I really enjoyed shooting their wedding. I've decided destination weddings are allll right! You really have to work hard to take a bad picture. I wish Jackie and Jason the best of luck they are a perfect pair and I know they will share many years of love. </div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Fuego Latino</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/21</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 13 Aug 2008 01:29:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/21</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SKI5Xv0jF4I/AAAAAAAAAJE/QDXsyL86sZ4/s1600-h/28.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SKI5Xv0jF4I/AAAAAAAAAJE/QDXsyL86sZ4/s320/28.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5233808797094582146" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SKI5XpDb6UI/AAAAAAAAAJM/wJ498bBHOlI/s1600-h/32.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SKI5XpDb6UI/AAAAAAAAAJM/wJ498bBHOlI/s320/32.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5233808795277977922" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SKI5YBHjRwI/AAAAAAAAAJU/l2sxzMeBw8g/s1600-h/31.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SKI5YBHjRwI/AAAAAAAAAJU/l2sxzMeBw8g/s320/31.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5233808801737688834" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SKI5YM-YnwI/AAAAAAAAAJc/x-q83Zc4bpw/s1600-h/29.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SKI5YM-YnwI/AAAAAAAAAJc/x-q83Zc4bpw/s320/29.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5233808804920467202" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SKI5YQUAa6I/AAAAAAAAAJk/OrQAoHWob70/s1600-h/30.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SKI5YQUAa6I/AAAAAAAAAJk/OrQAoHWob70/s320/30.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5233808805816462242" /></a>These are the last of the Mexico pictures I promise. The second one is of a show we saw at the resort. The name of the show was Fuego Latino. Every time a song would end Smitty would yell Fuego Latino. It was pretty funny, and the choreography was similar to the star steppers. (my high school drill team) The last one is of a little crab on the beach. He was actually hard to see Jon just happened to catch his little eyeballs as he scurried up and down the beach. I think he might have been stuck on the beach he couldn't seem to get past the surf. He stopped so I could take this picture he's pretty cute really. ]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Gross...</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/22</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 22 Aug 2008 02:52:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/22</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SK4qTi49M5I/AAAAAAAAAJs/OI30eWcUVuI/s1600-h/35.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SK4qTi49M5I/AAAAAAAAAJs/OI30eWcUVuI/s320/35.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5237169931950044050" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SK4qToXarKI/AAAAAAAAAJ0/1A9Ddc-KaC8/s1600-h/34.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SK4qToXarKI/AAAAAAAAAJ0/1A9Ddc-KaC8/s320/34.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5237169933419981986" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SK4qT0NBKPI/AAAAAAAAAJ8/uVJy_sCKIJM/s1600-h/36.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SK4qT0NBKPI/AAAAAAAAAJ8/uVJy_sCKIJM/s320/36.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5237169936597592306" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SK4qUF-IoeI/AAAAAAAAAKE/KwdHWDn8bqA/s1600-h/37.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SK4qUF-IoeI/AAAAAAAAAKE/KwdHWDn8bqA/s320/37.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5237169941367005666" /></a>This is a really creepy post. I took these at a public park. I think I've seen a similar scene in a horror movie. Seriously who wants to go to the bathroom in these? Not only are the stalls missing doors and toilet paper, but when I was taking the picture I got close enough to notice that they don't even have toilet seats. Probably because they don't encourage people to sit down. And then my mind wandered in a different direction no toilet paper, and no leaves anywhere nearby. What exactly do the poor people do if drip dry isn't an option. Sketchy thats all I have to say. Does anyone have any solutions? Maybe we should pose this question to our future president. Mr. President what exactly do you plan on doing about all the public restrooms in the world?]]></content:encoded>

margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SL9ZUBJHiMI/AAAAAAAAALM/ftChC2dN0Jw/s320/jud2.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5242006691721480386" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SL9ZUVQXOBI/AAAAAAAAALU/61Ikad2TvnU/s1600-h/jud1.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SL9ZUVQXOBI/AAAAAAAAALU/61Ikad2TvnU/s320/jud1.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5242006697120577554" /></a>Jon and I spent a relaxing weekend at the lake over labor day. We ate, slept, skied, watched tennis and played tennis. We've really taken to tennis this year and play pretty regularly, so it's no surprise that for the first time we actually want to watch tennis with my parents when we're at the lake. It's always some big match over the holidays and every other year we dreaded having to endure the matches. This year was different though, I've really enjoyed getting to watch the Americans move up the bracket. Someday I hope to go to the US open and see it in person, maybe I'll be able to watch one of my nephews play. Carter does look like Andy, and Judson, well Judson looks like he's having fun!<div><br /></div>]]></content:encoded>

It was a real shock considering just this summer we were at his brother Matt's wedding dancing the night away with him. We made the trip to St. Louis to say our goodbyes, and support Jon's mom Dianne while she morned the loss of her only sibling. David will live on in our memories forever, and be missed dearly.]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Catholic Church</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/26</link>
		<pubDate>Sun, 07 Sep 2008 22:52:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/26</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SMRbotY9IZI/AAAAAAAAAL8/4EhH7oq-hZc/s1600-h/church1.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SMRbotY9IZI/AAAAAAAAAL8/4EhH7oq-hZc/s320/church1.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5243416621103260050" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SMRbo77YDRI/AAAAAAAAAME/31H4IKjwVKA/s1600-h/church2.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SMRbo77YDRI/AAAAAAAAAME/31H4IKjwVKA/s320/church2.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5243416625005726994" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SMRbpAUIQSI/AAAAAAAAAMM/Om9f0ngwc5M/s1600-h/church3.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SMRbpAUIQSI/AAAAAAAAAMM/Om9f0ngwc5M/s320/church3.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5243416626183291170" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SMRbpbWvSDI/AAAAAAAAAMU/j8o9p7Qh8a0/s1600-h/church4.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SMRbpbWvSDI/AAAAAAAAAMU/j8o9p7Qh8a0/s320/church4.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5243416633441994802" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SMRbpp02sgI/AAAAAAAAAMc/zlkj8cKKP_I/s1600-h/church5.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SMRbpp02sgI/AAAAAAAAAMc/zlkj8cKKP_I/s320/church5.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5243416637326406146" /></a>I'm not a super religious person, but I have to say I love an old Catholic Church. They are all so unique, yet so much the same. While I don't really think God cares what your place of worship looks like it sure makes a difference to me. Maybe sometime soon I'll try to get in a more modern Catholic church iow a 70's looking church. I wonder what happened? Why did they all of a sudden decide orange carpet and wood panelling would look better than marble, and hard wood. Ok so it's more practical, but you know what I mean. They could at least go for timeless instead of stylish. Stylish and churches shouldn't really be in the same sentence. I mean really look at the robes the priests wear. ]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>beautiful boy</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/27</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 10 Sep 2008 02:15:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/27</guid>
		<description></description>

		<title>Beautiful Horses</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/28</link>
		<pubDate>Sun, 21 Sep 2008 12:37:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>

margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SNZB8R9lQQI/AAAAAAAAANw/TAn1O-VKYeE/s320/horseb2.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5248454919616545026" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SNZB8kelqNI/AAAAAAAAAN4/eu835jWNNCo/s1600-h/horseb5.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SNZB8kelqNI/AAAAAAAAAN4/eu835jWNNCo/s320/horseb5.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5248454924586821842" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SNZB8-FJLZI/AAAAAAAAAOA/DuctFa1eIm4/s1600-h/horseb3.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SNZB8-FJLZI/AAAAAAAAAOA/DuctFa1eIm4/s320/horseb3.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5248454931459419538" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SNZAPtgGFkI/AAAAAAAAANg/UynpIna-y3Q/s1600-h/horseb4.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SNZAPtgGFkI/AAAAAAAAANg/UynpIna-y3Q/s320/horseb4.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5248453054403319362" /></a><br />Yesterday Jon, Diamond, and I went to a Dressage show in Bonner Springs. It was a lot of fun. Jon was a great assistant, following me around with grooming wipes, my tests to practice, and reminding me to give him one of my whips before going in the show arena. Diamond improved as the day progressed. Believe it or not she was a little spunky. By our last test she got a 58% and a blue ribbon. Not too shabby for our first time doing the test. Go Diamond! The pics are of Joe Nash one of the riders at the show. He was riding the level 3-3 test. His horse was a big beautiful Dutch Warmblood. 18 hands! Even bigger than D. I'll try to get Jon to take some pics of D and I in the clinic today to post tomorrow<div>.<div><br /></div></div>]]></content:encoded>

Something like that anyway. We actually went to the Kansas City Ren Festival. It was a great time, we watched some shows, and lots of people. I think these pics pretty much say it all! If you haven't gotten the chance to go this year I would highly recommend it! It's one of my favorite fall traditions.]]></content:encoded>

His name was Pete and he's from New Zealand. After 40 years away Pete made the trip halfway across the world to visit his American family. I'm so happy I got the opportunity to meet Pete. He's a wonderful person and he truly feels like a part of our family. We chatted about New Zealand's culture, American politics, and life in general. It was a wonderful evening, and Jon and I look forward to many more memories with Pete. New Zealand here we come.<div>Oh and I threw some pics of my beautiful niece and nephews. I used my new lens, man I love this lens it's amazing. f 2.8 24-70</div>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>I love fall colors</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/33</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 09 Oct 2008 02:23:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/33</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SO1rYwlZ__I/AAAAAAAAASo/Yvz-DJOZzM4/s1600-h/b1.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SO1rYwlZ__I/AAAAAAAAASo/Yvz-DJOZzM4/s320/b1.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5254974413314064370" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SO1rY_DIglI/AAAAAAAAASw/TnBD_sh5RGc/s1600-h/b2.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SO1rY_DIglI/AAAAAAAAASw/TnBD_sh5RGc/s320/b2.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5254974417196843602" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SO1rZKfJXTI/AAAAAAAAAS4/qNG2nsE8Mck/s1600-h/b3.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SO1rZKfJXTI/AAAAAAAAAS4/qNG2nsE8Mck/s320/b3.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5254974420267130162" /></a>It's fall and with fall comes the vibrant and bright colors I absolutely love. This week the fall colors came out in full effect. I will be trying to capture those colors the next few weeks. I hope all of you are enjoying your fall as well.<div><br /></div>]]></content:encoded>

margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SPKpW-CvIEI/AAAAAAAAATY/vuQX-WFSZow/s320/golf4.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5256449927171481666" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SPKpXId-dmI/AAAAAAAAATg/CDb8-xSn9vI/s1600-h/golf6.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SPKpXId-dmI/AAAAAAAAATg/CDb8-xSn9vI/s320/golf6.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5256449929970087522" /></a>Today Jon and I went out golfing with my dad and uncle Rich at Tiffany Greens. Despite the wind it was an absolutely gorgeous day! The light was wonderful and I'm really glad I brought my camera to catch a few shots. I actually hit the ball pretty well too. I won't tell you my score because it's pretty high, but it was close to 100. Good enough for me. I have just really enjoyed this fall I can't believe we've been so lucky! We need to remember to thank mother nature every single amazing day!]]></content:encoded>

margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SQfd2fxAOtI/AAAAAAAAAVI/Ql0zOMRiWDY/s320/sr4.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5262418617915423442" /></a><br />I'm not so good about posting pics from my shoots on here. I started my blog to get myself out of the studio refining my art, but I'm going to make an effort to find a balance. Anyway, these are some pics I recently shot of Ashlie, she's a senior this year. We had so much fun working together. Ashlie is a photography enthusiast like myself and feels more comfortable behind the camera, but she did a stunning job.<div>I know I'm a baby belly photographer, but I have to admit it was kind of fun working with a client that actually listened to me. If you have any seniors that you know need pictures still, have them give me a call soon, the fall foliage is unbeatable. And can you believe the weather we've gotten? WOW!!!!!</div>]]></content:encoded>

margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SREM0v2WI-I/AAAAAAAAAWA/8bMh25UPQpI/s320/funeral3.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5265003539709961186" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SREM0TqUMKI/AAAAAAAAAV4/R_A1vc0exhg/s1600-h/funeral2.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SREM0TqUMKI/AAAAAAAAAV4/R_A1vc0exhg/s320/funeral2.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5265003532143308962" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SREM0M5KQII/AAAAAAAAAVw/afNUpmR7eqg/s1600-h/funeral1.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 213px; height: 320px;" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SREM0M5KQII/AAAAAAAAAVw/afNUpmR7eqg/s320/funeral1.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5265003530326524034" /></a>Jon and I made yet another sad journey across the state of Missouri last weekend. Jon's grandma Nana passed away peacefully 2 weeks ago. She was living in Wisconsin with her daughter Mary Lisa and their family. Before her passing her 4 children came together in Wisconsin to say their goodbyes, and share in the joy of their mom. What a wonderful way to go. It was Nana's wishes that she be cremated and placed in the earth above her husband Joe's grave, where she will naturally return to the Earth. It was a moving funeral for me, as I looked down the table at dinner for 30 I couldn't help thinking about how one couple could create such a large group of wonderful people. Grandma Nana made her difference in this world. She will always be remembered and missed dearly.]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Holiday Season</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/38</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 19 Nov 2008 02:41:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/38</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[While I find it hard to believe that Christmas is so quickly approaching, in truth it is just around the corner. Walmart has had their decorations out now for weeks, and Hobby Lobby months! I usually won't allow myself to get excited about Christmas until after Thanksgiving my favorite holiday, but this year Christmas is a good thing. It's a break from politics, economy, and oh my the election that has so consumed my life for the last few months. I'm starting to feel the tingle of holiday excitement. I am a Christmas lover despite the fact that Jon is a bit of a grinch. This year even Jon is starting to feel the holiday excitement. Anyway that's really not why I wrote this. I really wanted to let everyone know that I have updated my pics on my website. New songs, and new beautiful babies. I hope everyone enjoys the site, and don't forget to take a minute to sit down and take a break. Happy Holidays!!!!!!!<div><br /></div><div><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com">www.allisoncarenza.com</a></div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div>]]></content:encoded>

margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 214px; height: 320px;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SSoIh4kIX_I/AAAAAAAAAXI/uT0U-zTDXTQ/s320/wedding5.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5272035692003221490" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SSoIhicG19I/AAAAAAAAAXA/7vALyVzmyK8/s1600-h/wedding6.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 213px; height: 320px;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SSoIhicG19I/AAAAAAAAAXA/7vALyVzmyK8/s320/wedding6.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5272035686063986642" /></a><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: 'lucida grande';">Pretty much everyone knows babies are my specialty when it comes to photography, but this weekend I had the honor of taking pictures of Ryan and Amy's wedding reception. They got back from Jamaica the day before and celebrated their wedding with family and friends Friday night. Amy is the daughter of my teaching buddy Linda. The reception was at Californo's in Westport. Congrats Amy and Ryan, I hope you have many wonderful years together! The flowers and decorations were awesome, and Jon and I had a great time, but it made me appreciate my work with babies in the studio. I love being an assistant photographer at weddings, but it's not my passion as it is for some. Speaking of amazing wedding photographers check out my very good friend Maggie's website. She is currently working out of Ft. Lauderdale Florida, and St. Louis, but might be expanding her cliental to Kansas City. She's been featured in the Knot several times, and is flown all over the country for weddings. If you're shopping for wedding photographer she is your girl!!!! </span><a href="www.maggiestolzberg.com"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: 'lucida grande';">www.maggiestolzberg.com</span></a><div><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: 'lucida grande';">I can't say enough wonderful things about her work, truly an artist! </span></div><div><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: 'lucida grande';">Until we meet again keep checking the blog this week I had a very busy weekend and have lots of fun pictures to share. </span></div>]]></content:encoded>

margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SSzZLDKpfeI/AAAAAAAAAX4/8CDIyPUYTCk/s320/trober2.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5272828047595765218" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SSzZK3PSrmI/AAAAAAAAAXw/fOYBxYq4j-E/s1600-h/trober1.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 213px;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SSzZK3PSrmI/AAAAAAAAAXw/fOYBxYq4j-E/s320/trober1.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5272828044394016354" /></a><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: 'lucida grande';">I've been blissfully busy lately. With the holidays right around the corner everyone is in a rush to get those beautiful family pictures done for Christmas cards. I personally happen to be horrible at getting Christmas cards out on time, maybe because I'm busy helping everyone else get there's ready. I've made it in time once, then there were some new year's cards, and one year I even considered sending out an Easter card. That didn't happen, this year I've already got my card designed and it's ready to go to the printer. Can't wait to get it out on time, and maybe even before Christmas. WOW! The pictures above are of some really fantastic kids! They were so much fun and as you can see very photogenic! I had a great time working with them, and they had a great time playing with Lucy and Layla. Go figure. Whatever keeps them happy. If I don't have time to blog before Thanksgiving, I hope everyone has a happy turkey day!</span>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Thanksgiving Fireworks?</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/41</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 27 Nov 2008 16:03:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/41</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SS7Fj_wt1sI/AAAAAAAAAZY/LYCxJ2X-OQE/s1600-h/fireworks1.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SS7Fj7JZp9I/AAAAAAAAAZQ/Rd6b2Zpr5Xw/s320/fireworks2.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5273369434660644818" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SS7FjBPyDvI/AAAAAAAAAZI/um0PL78c5dM/s1600-h/fireworks3.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 214px; height: 320px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SS7FjBPyDvI/AAAAAAAAAZI/um0PL78c5dM/s320/fireworks3.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5273369419118153458" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SS7Fi7LxwLI/AAAAAAAAAZA/qoedfbnATFk/s1600-h/fireworks4.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SS7Fi7LxwLI/AAAAAAAAAZA/qoedfbnATFk/s320/fireworks4.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5273369417490743474" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SS7Fh3K5PuI/AAAAAAAAAY4/OqvnEPnOFbo/s1600-h/firework5.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SS7Fh3K5PuI/AAAAAAAAAY4/OqvnEPnOFbo/s320/firework5.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5273369399233429218" /></a>Last night Jon and I went to watch Thanksgiving fireworks with some of our friends. Apparently at <span class="blsp-spelling-error" id="SPELLING_ERROR_0">Longview</span> park in Lees Summit they shoot off fireworks to kick off the holiday season, and the opening of their Christmas light display. There were hundreds of cars lining Valley View Road. I was shocked and pleasantly surprised to find we got a decent spot, and it was only a little chilly. I took some shots before the action began to give you an idea of where we were and how many people were there. The fireworks themselves were pretty impressive and were <span class="blsp-spelling-corrected" id="SPELLING_ERROR_1">choreographed</span> with xmas music on KUDL. As you can see some trees were in our view, but I kinda liked it. I hope everyone has a wonderful Thanksgiving!]]></content:encoded>

Thursday we went to my Aunt Martha's house where she cooked up an awesome bird. We spent most of the evening watching the little ones entertain themselves with the pool table. The last picture is my favorite! The rest of the week I got to spend with Jon's family and we went bowling and ate out. It was a lot of fun. This evening I got out our Christmas decorations and put them up, the holidays are now in full swing. With such a short amount of time between now and Christmas I need to slow down and enjoy the season. For now it's back to work for a few weeks anyway. I hope everyone else had a relatively peaceful Thanksgiving, if not I'd love to hear the story.]]></content:encoded>

The art of photography is such an adventure and I just love it!]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Beautiful newborn</title>

I just love newborns!!!!!]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Downtown sunset</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/46</link>

margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SUXQ3mZ7viI/AAAAAAAAAc4/0X2f7-YGQJk/s320/dt3.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5279855791782477346" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SUXQ3vsVQqI/AAAAAAAAAcw/KZy357bkur8/s1600-h/dt2.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 240px; height: 320px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SUXQ3vsVQqI/AAAAAAAAAcw/KZy357bkur8/s320/dt2.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5279855794275566242" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SUXQ3JnBGNI/AAAAAAAAAco/7E8Tdbf3Sbc/s1600-h/dt1.jpg"><br /><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 240px;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SUXQ3JnBGNI/AAAAAAAAAco/7E8Tdbf3Sbc/s320/dt1.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5279855784052725970" /></a>So I was downloading some images off of my little Cannon Snapshot and found these. I had totally forgotten about this moment. This fall a group of Llamas (thats what we call our group of friends) decided to go enjoy some awesome sushi at a new restaurant downtown called Nara. It was great, but in the middle of the meal I looked out the window and noticed this beautiful light hitting the city. Luckily my little Cannon lives in my purse for moments like this! I grabbed it and excused myself from the table. Jon came with me to see what I was doing and maybe help me get into a spot that is really out of my reach. He has to do that sometimes. I think it might embarrass him, but he just nods his head and gives me a leg up. Such a good partner. Anyway...I might have to post more pictures from the past this week considering it's going to be 10 degrees all week, man I'm missing the summer sun! Bundle up!!!!!]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Still digging...</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/48</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 19 Dec 2008 00:35:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/48</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SUrszz14KQI/AAAAAAAAAfI/JbQ-HAD26L8/s1600-h/c9.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 214px; height: 320px;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SUrszz14KQI/AAAAAAAAAfI/JbQ-HAD26L8/s320/c9.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5281293887878998274" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SUrszXiFTpI/AAAAAAAAAfA/KpJHDVgNad4/s1600-h/c8.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SUrszXiFTpI/AAAAAAAAAfA/KpJHDVgNad4/s320/c8.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5281293880279781010" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SUrszJrHSlI/AAAAAAAAAe4/E6BEeiyTYDE/s1600-h/c7.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 240px;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SUrszJrHSlI/AAAAAAAAAe4/E6BEeiyTYDE/s320/c7.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5281293876559563346" /></a>This was the 5th and second to last winery we hit one day. Wow drinking wine can be work.<br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SUrsp8DT2EI/AAAAAAAAAew/0SOB9FP2yYY/s1600-h/c6.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SUrsp8DT2EI/AAAAAAAAAew/0SOB9FP2yYY/s320/c6.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5281293718284130370" /></a>Jon and I after an amazing dinner. Some of the best steak and wine I've ever had!<br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SUrsptUSGsI/AAAAAAAAAeo/vcohGyrb5k0/s1600-h/c4.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SUrsptUSGsI/AAAAAAAAAeo/vcohGyrb5k0/s320/c4.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5281293714328787650" /></a>Golden Gate Bridge-of course everyone has THAT shot so I tried something different.<br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SUrspRtmpKI/AAAAAAAAAeg/8WxxkAKQpuc/s1600-h/c3.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SUrspRtmpKI/AAAAAAAAAeg/8WxxkAKQpuc/s320/c3.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5281293706918798498" /></a><div style="text-align: center;">Big Sur!<br /></div><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SUrspBMqqAI/AAAAAAAAAeY/JUY5IOQs_vQ/s1600-h/c2.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SUrspBMqqAI/AAAAAAAAAeY/JUY5IOQs_vQ/s320/c2.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5281293702485682178" /></a><div style="text-align: center;">This was right out in front of our hotel, amazing view, and there weren't even that many people there. Once in a lifetime sunset.<br /></div><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SUrspMLyCVI/AAAAAAAAAeQ/_5qb7vYb1as/s1600-h/c1.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SUrspMLyCVI/AAAAAAAAAeQ/_5qb7vYb1as/s320/c1.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5281293705434761554" /></a>I'm having a blast looking through my old pics! I came across my California file yesterday.  The summer of 2007 Jon, Cara, Scott and I went on a trip up the coast of Cali. We flew into San Diego and drove all the way up the PCH, stopping in LA, Monterey, San Fran., and finally wine country. I loved Sonoma and dream of someday owning a winery there. I know I know, but I tell my kids to dream big so I have to too! It was one of those trips that you miss the moment you get home, but probably didn't appreciate enough when you were in the moment. It was an amazing experience and I'm glad I was a part of it before Cali drops off into the ocean. I'll keep digging, there are some really funny pics too!]]></content:encoded>
