margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SVVUQ11kamI/AAAAAAAAAfQ/JNwVIiB-6Ns/s320/d7.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5284222386095549026" /></a><br />Today I got up and went out to ride D for the first time in a week and a half! It's been so cold and with the holidays she's really been neglected. She was great despite the fact that she hasn't been turned out in a few days, I just love Diamond. She's sweet, but hard working. <div>Then I came home and took down all the decorations for Christmas. I love Christmas and get my decorations out right after Thanksgiving, but as soon as it's over I want to get on with life. Especially the xmas tree. We get a real tree every year and it can make a real mess when it dries out. I'll be finding pine needles in July. It's worth it for now anyway, someday I might just have to give in to the artificial tree. I hope everyone had a wonderful Christmas! Enjoy the next few days and have a wonderful new years!</div>]]></content:encoded>

Above are a few shots of the Plaza I took a few days after Christmas. I hope everyone has a great week. ]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Ouch...everyone has to grow up</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/53</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 16 Jan 2009 01:23:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/53</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SW_h2DaJMnI/AAAAAAAAAh0/EiPTDT19u5o/s1600-h/g3.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SW_h2DaJMnI/AAAAAAAAAh0/EiPTDT19u5o/s320/g3.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5291696405927768690" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SW_h2OKDFAI/AAAAAAAAAhs/eS3hK_W1yw4/s1600-h/g2.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SW_h2OKDFAI/AAAAAAAAAhs/eS3hK_W1yw4/s320/g2.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5291696408813048834" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SW_h11mUevI/AAAAAAAAAhk/j722oaT22VQ/s1600-h/g1.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 213px;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SW_h11mUevI/AAAAAAAAAhk/j722oaT22VQ/s320/g1.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5291696402220743410" /></a>Do you remember what it was like to be a kid? I remember caring a lot about candy, Christmas and making my parents proud. Despite my simple life there was always something to worry about, like who I was friends with, getting good grades, and what people thought of me. Then in college it's the same thing, I didn't take the time to really appreciate the freedom of the moment. I was so worried about the things I had to do, I didn't take time to appreciate what I didn't have to do. For example sitting around for hours watching TLC, taking naps, and not having to worry about cooking anything, or cleaning it up for that matter. Life was good for me. Now I'm an adult and I don't so much worry about those things, or anything for that matter. Maybe it's a right of passage, but growing up is tough! ]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>
		<wp:post_id>53</wp:post_id>

margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SXuLaKMC6zI/AAAAAAAAAjE/hxItb5mfqtY/s320/i1.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5294979068431887154" /></a>Last weekend I took a trip down to Ft. Lauderdale to visit my precious friend Maggie. Mags made the move down to Florida last March. She wanted to expand her wedding photography business particularly to destination weddings. Her condo is 10 steps from the beach and just a mile walk along the beach to lots of great restaurants and bars. We had an amazing time! We laid on the beach, ate on the beach and I soaked up the the warm summery sun. I can't wait to go back as soon as possible. Mags is currently commuting to several locations around the country to shoot weddings. She has 2 weddings this summer in KC so if you know someone that needs a wedding photographer contact Maggie Stolzberg. We share a love of photography and a love for the beach!!!!!]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Newborn TWINS!</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/55</link>
		<pubDate>Sun, 01 Feb 2009 20:40:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/55</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SYZzRAvsVYI/AAAAAAAAAmM/whCbFIwsgr4/s1600-h/t5.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SYZzRAvsVYI/AAAAAAAAAmM/whCbFIwsgr4/s320/t5.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5298048747742975362" /></a><br /><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SYYI7OJPSTI/AAAAAAAAAl8/ffu5U58Z0oo/s1600-h/t4.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SYYI7OJPSTI/AAAAAAAAAl8/ffu5U58Z0oo/s320/t4.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5297931825150118194" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SYYI6gvzvLI/AAAAAAAAAl0/_S4-J3ypQCU/s1600-h/t3.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SYYI6gvzvLI/AAAAAAAAAl0/_S4-J3ypQCU/s320/t3.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5297931812963859634" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SYYI6BnSKuI/AAAAAAAAAls/pSAd9nzbwUI/s1600-h/t2.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SYYI6BnSKuI/AAAAAAAAAls/pSAd9nzbwUI/s320/t2.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5297931804606606050" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SYYI5ud-UoI/AAAAAAAAAlk/h297X1RxDmY/s1600-h/t1.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SYYI5ud-UoI/AAAAAAAAAlk/h297X1RxDmY/s320/t1.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5297931799467283074" /></a>This weekend I got to take pictures of two beautiful baby twin girls! These little darlings are fraternal twins and they not only looked different, but couldn't be more different in personality as well. It was a lot of fun taking their pictures, holding them, and watching them cuddle with each other. I have to admit that one newborn is a challenge, two is ...well don't know if there's a word to describe it comical maybe. As soon as we would get one peaceful the other would get fussy and vice versa, well you get the picture. Even with the challenge they were so much fun, I look forward to watching these two grow up. I've often wondered what it would be like to be a twin, I think having a built in best friend would have been a lot of fun. I've known a lot of twins and they always seem to be more confident, cool with who they are, and always close.]]></content:encoded>

margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 213px;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SY9PXI1brsI/AAAAAAAAAms/s3QudfOSWIQ/s320/k4.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5300542545365544642" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SY9PXNjnFtI/AAAAAAAAAmk/EglpD9dM6ew/s1600-h/k3.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SY9PXNjnFtI/AAAAAAAAAmk/EglpD9dM6ew/s320/k3.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5300542546632971986" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SY9PW3xKm0I/AAAAAAAAAmc/RKCGYqst7i0/s1600-h/k2.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 213px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SY9PW3xKm0I/AAAAAAAAAmc/RKCGYqst7i0/s320/k2.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5300542540784245570" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SY9PWuYGQUI/AAAAAAAAAmU/3RzUJdEmpDk/s1600-h/k1.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SY9PWuYGQUI/AAAAAAAAAmU/3RzUJdEmpDk/s320/k1.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5300542538263183682" /></a>This weekend I had the awesome opportunity to take pictures for a martial arts group. Axe Capoeira is a Brazilian martial art that was developed 400 years ago. With strong African roots and Brazilian influence, Capoeira is an art form that has incorporated elements of Afro-Brazilian dance, music, song, self-defense, acrobatics, language, culture and philosophy into one exciting body of movement and expression. Taking pictures with the music and movement was an experience that I won't forget anytime soon. I've always wanted to study a martial art and if I had time to add something more to my plate this would be the martial art for me. If you're interested in learning more check out their website at <a href="http://www.capoeirakc.com/">www.capoeirakc.com</a> Jon and I had a great time and look forward to working with Kansas City's own Capoeira group again soon.]]></content:encoded>

margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SZzIB2xYW_I/AAAAAAAAAn8/Ql7OJNQMFv4/s320/bs4.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5304334395343657970" /></a>I've been horrible about keeping up with my blog. This week I'm going to do a better job. These are pics of baby Judson's baptism. He was baptized 2 weeks ago and the whole ceremony was quick and easy. Despite the speed Judson wanted nothing to do with it, he would barely make eye contact with the minister, and he had to have his "pappy" and "blankie". It was pretty adorable, and I couldn't help wondering what he was thinking. "Hey why is this guy putting water on my head" or maybe he was wondering why everyone was staring at him. At any rate he was asalways the entertainment!]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Weird Valentine&#039;s Day</title>

		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>

		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SZ4KtUq0IJI/AAAAAAAAAo0/JNmjt7McFb0/s1600-h/w4.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SZ4KtUq0IJI/AAAAAAAAAo0/JNmjt7McFb0/s320/w4.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5304689184847700114" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SZ4KtWkR1MI/AAAAAAAAAos/4aMirTSME2I/s1600-h/w2.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SZ4KtWkR1MI/AAAAAAAAAos/4aMirTSME2I/s320/w2.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5304689185357157570" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SZ4KtNuszdI/AAAAAAAAAok/c9ZE54TFJuU/s1600-h/w1.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SZ4KtNuszdI/AAAAAAAAAok/c9ZE54TFJuU/s320/w1.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5304689182984949202" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SZ4KtOQJEuI/AAAAAAAAAoc/2duTXGoOJQQ/s1600-h/w3.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SZ4KtOQJEuI/AAAAAAAAAoc/2duTXGoOJQQ/s320/w3.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5304689183125213922" /></a>Jon and I can be rather random, and this Valentine's day was definitely random. We decided to go down to the river market and <span class="blsp-spelling-corrected" id="SPELLING_ERROR_0">reminisce</span>about our fun times living down there. Well that's somewhat true we also wanted to check out the free weddings. Yup! The river market was hosting FREE weddings. I just couldn't resist and it was totally worth it. In just one short hour we watched 3 weddings. The ceremonies lasted about 5 minutes everything else was comings and goings and that was the best part. The diversity was amazing, and entertaining. ]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Perfect Puppies</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/59</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 23 Feb 2009 01:54:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/59</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SaICJ28voTI/AAAAAAAAApE/bODR2NswgJQ/s1600-h/d2.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 213px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SaICJ28voTI/AAAAAAAAApE/bODR2NswgJQ/s320/d2.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5305805679388238130" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SaICJsJ98CI/AAAAAAAAAo8/-ST29re7YRQ/s1600-h/d1.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 214px; height: 320px;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SaICJsJ98CI/AAAAAAAAAo8/-ST29re7YRQ/s320/d1.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5305805676490911778" /></a>Recently I read the book Marley and Me. I know everyone has heard of it, and most people have either read the book, or seen the movie. I avoided this book for months I thought it would be another predictable <span class="blsp-spelling-error" id="SPELLING_ERROR_0">doggie</span> book like Old <span class="blsp-spelling-error" id="SPELLING_ERROR_1">Yeller</span>, or Where the Red Fern Grows. I was wrong, this book wasn't about the perfect dog like those books of the past. This was about a typical dog that was naughty to the core. The cool thing is that the owners loved the dog despite it's <span class="blsp-spelling-error" id="SPELLING_ERROR_2">psycho</span> nature. I found that weeks after I was done it was still with me. Sometimes a great book comes along that sticks, and this was one of them. I appreciate my little ratties a lot more now. My doggies are perfect and affectionate, and just like Marley in the book, they give unconditional love! If you haven't read the book I recommend it to any dog owner.]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Green</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/60</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 27 Feb 2009 02:37:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/60</guid>
		<description></description>

		<title>Downtown Blue Springs</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/61</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 02 Mar 2009 01:05:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/61</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SasxQBITYQI/AAAAAAAAAsg/nHcBGjYTQt8/s1600-h/downtown1.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 213px;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SasxMALCxZI/AAAAAAAAAsY/jYrxC_01pVw/s320/downtown2.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5308390668060771730" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SasxMBHkPMI/AAAAAAAAAsQ/58npPfA5Hr0/s1600-h/downtown3.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 213px;" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SasxMBHkPMI/AAAAAAAAAsQ/58npPfA5Hr0/s320/downtown3.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5308390668314623170" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SasxL96HIlI/AAAAAAAAAsI/B2nHxbpllRg/s1600-h/downtown4.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SasxL96HIlI/AAAAAAAAAsI/B2nHxbpllRg/s320/downtown4.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5308390667452883538" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SasxLlqJXDI/AAAAAAAAAsA/m4xGX_qaTLs/s1600-h/downtown5.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 213px;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SasxLlqJXDI/AAAAAAAAAsA/m4xGX_qaTLs/s320/downtown5.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5308390660943469618" /></a>I did go in this little shop Accessorize Yourself. Really cute and unique jewelry. I think it will be a new favorite place to stop in for me. Very unique and fun little store!<br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SasxLJvOAjI/AAAAAAAAAr4/wSUtQ2IMtnY/s1600-h/downtown6.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 214px; height: 320px;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SasxLJvOAjI/AAAAAAAAAr4/wSUtQ2IMtnY/s320/downtown6.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5308390653448553010" /></a>Unfortunately with our current economy, for rent and for sale signs are all to common. <br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sasw_o3nGlI/AAAAAAAAArw/MF7EeUllVkE/s1600-h/downtown7.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 213px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sasw_o3nGlI/AAAAAAAAArw/MF7EeUllVkE/s320/downtown7.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5308390455646820946" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sasw_c9xZyI/AAAAAAAAAro/jUIMRLPqFoA/s1600-h/downtown8.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 213px; height: 320px;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sasw_c9xZyI/AAAAAAAAAro/jUIMRLPqFoA/s320/downtown8.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5308390452451436322" /></a>Do you see the dust?<br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sasw_bfXqwI/AAAAAAAAArg/PT18s5qX7hM/s1600-h/downtown9.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 213px;" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sasw_bfXqwI/AAAAAAAAArg/PT18s5qX7hM/s320/downtown9.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5308390452055485186" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sasw-5mqKmI/AAAAAAAAArY/wTONP9Vm8_Q/s1600-h/downtown10.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 214px; height: 320px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sasw-5mqKmI/AAAAAAAAArY/wTONP9Vm8_Q/s320/downtown10.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5308390442959252066" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sasw-fR09BI/AAAAAAAAArQ/vR_EZOloCtw/s1600-h/downtown11.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 213px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sasw-fR09BI/AAAAAAAAArQ/vR_EZOloCtw/s320/downtown11.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5308390435892556818" /></a>Where have the times of a lively downtown gone? These pics were taken on a Sunday so the shops were closed I'll give you that, but for the most part downtown Blue Springs is a ghost town. It's so depressing because I think there is so much more charm in these little buildings than a mall. Why do we Americans insist that everything has to be new to be good. I love Europe because they don't tear everything down and rebuild every few years, they use what they have to recreate. First of all it makes for a much more unique look, but also it's green.  I would love to see more shops, restaurants, and nightlife in our little downtown areas in KC especially Blue Springs. We need to stop building strip malls, and start using the structures we already have built. Tomorrow as you drive around take notice of all the empty strip malls, K-marts, and chain restaurants.]]></content:encoded>

		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SbG7W_TZ9UI/AAAAAAAAAss/XWihRx6frrs/s1600-h/light.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 214px; height: 320px;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SbG7W_TZ9UI/AAAAAAAAAss/XWihRx6frrs/s320/light.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5310231439270868290" /></a><br />I love spring, the rebirth of the Earth as I like to think of it. 		<title>Hawaii!</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/63</link>
		<pubDate>Sun, 15 Mar 2009 20:40:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/63</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div><br /></div><div><br /></div><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sb1n1d73_gI/AAAAAAAAAs0/Yj9X5lzWBvs/s1600-h/h1.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 213px;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sb1n1d73_gI/AAAAAAAAAs0/Yj9X5lzWBvs/s320/h1.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5313517303633542658" /></a>After a week in paradise I'm home. We had an amazing time and I have some interesting pics to share. I'm currently in the process of picking from over 500 images. Not so sure how I'll do this, but I'll probably share pics in different blogs. I'm really happy to be home, but looking out my window I'm really missing the lush green everything, the big volcanic rock formations, and of course the ocean. Hopefully our spring is just around the corner. Mahalo ]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Kauai...the little garden island</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/64</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 16 Mar 2009 00:23:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/64</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div><br /></div><div>After a week of Kauai I am in total relaxation mode. In fact I'm so relaxed I'm having trouble doing anything. Here are some of the first pics of Kauai. It's an interesting and fun little island.</div><div>This is a picture of the pool at the house where we stayed. It was really cold in the water so I didn't get in, but the boys really enjoyed it.</div><div><br /></div><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sb2chX-0pvI/AAAAAAAAAt8/QxzA33OiH9A/s1600-h/h8.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sb2chX-0pvI/AAAAAAAAAt8/QxzA33OiH9A/s320/h8.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5313575232554182386" /></a>On my horseback ride I heard there are 800 different types of palm trees. That's a lot considering they aren't even native to Hawaii.<div><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sb2chHSylBI/AAAAAAAAAt0/wtkdRjuOSbQ/s1600-h/h7.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 213px;" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sb2chHSylBI/AAAAAAAAAt0/wtkdRjuOSbQ/s320/h7.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5313575228074529810" /></a>There are a lot of palm trees, but even more roosters. In fact the first morning this little rooster was our wake up call at 6:30. I did get use to their loud chatter, but not the fact that they were everywhere. Apparently not so long ago cock fighting was a big sport on the island until a nasty hurricane that knocked them all lose. Now they just let them roam free. A permanent fixture on the island, seriously they're like squirrels over there. In case you're wondering they don't taste good, that's what they said anyway. I'm not much for catching and killing chickens. I stuck to the sea food on this trip.<br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sb2cZ4q-epI/AAAAAAAAAts/h52PQsX1N6s/s1600-h/h6.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 214px; height: 320px;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sb2cZ4q-epI/AAAAAAAAAts/h52PQsX1N6s/s320/h6.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5313575103890356882" /></a>The monk seal is also a common site. These guys swim up on the beach after a big meal and lay in the sun for hours. There's a whole slew of people that volunteer to drive around and put up little ropes around them so no one will mess with them. One busy day on the beach a monk seal was looking for a good spot on the beach by swimming up and down the beach. He would just poke his head out and look around. Swimming just feet from snorkelers it was really fun to watch. <br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sb2cZuF5_BI/AAAAAAAAAtk/S6SlHx5DG-g/s1600-h/h5.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 214px; height: 320px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sb2cZuF5_BI/AAAAAAAAAtk/S6SlHx5DG-g/s320/h5.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5313575101050518546" /></a>Yup the state flower. <span class="blsp-spelling-corrected" id="SPELLING_ERROR_0">Hibiscus</span>. You know I had to take a picture, although its so so hard to capture red digitally. I put it up here anyway.<br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sb2cZjTCXfI/AAAAAAAAAtc/-O9guQ7DhSo/s1600-h/h4.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sb2cZjTCXfI/AAAAAAAAAtc/-O9guQ7DhSo/s320/h4.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5313575098152803826" /></a>This is an old sugar mill, there were over a dozen of these on the island at one time. Now there is just one active sugar mill left. They take a lot of water and a lot of labor to run so of course we have other countries that can do it for less.<br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sb2cZlOkh7I/AAAAAAAAAtU/WbnxWK8bUM0/s1600-h/h3.jpg"><br /><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 213px;" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sb2cZlOkh7I/AAAAAAAAAtU/WbnxWK8bUM0/s320/h3.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5313575098670942130" /></a>Finally you might find it surprising to know that the island has a lot of cacti. I was surprised considering the high point of the island (an inactive volcano) gets 32 feet of rain a year. They say it's the wettest place on Earth.<br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sb2cYmVi9ZI/AAAAAAAAAtM/UWT2Mu6b0H4/s1600-h/h2.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 213px;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sb2cYmVi9ZI/AAAAAAAAAtM/UWT2Mu6b0H4/s320/h2.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5313575081788765586" /></a><span class="blsp-spelling-error" id="SPELLING_ERROR_1">Ok,</span> that's it for the tour of Kauai, I think next time I'll just post pictures. Look for more to come. </div>]]></content:encoded>

The water basically comes crashing in all these underwater caves. In some places there are holes for the water to shoot out. The water would shoot 50 feet up.<br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/ScL573DjGQI/AAAAAAAAAws/gsf9Ei5WxdM/s1600-h/hi17.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 213px; height: 320px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/ScL573DjGQI/AAAAAAAAAws/gsf9Ei5WxdM/s320/hi17.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5315085317037037826" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/ScL57sg1a2I/AAAAAAAAAwk/xn8esaA59fU/s1600-h/hi16.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 213px;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/ScL57sg1a2I/AAAAAAAAAwk/xn8esaA59fU/s320/hi16.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5315085314207083362" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/ScL5dvyA0PI/AAAAAAAAAwc/Tk6adIHN3Ac/s1600-h/hi15.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 213px; height: 320px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/ScL5dvyA0PI/AAAAAAAAAwc/Tk6adIHN3Ac/s320/hi15.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5315084799688364274" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/ScL5dQm0gkI/AAAAAAAAAwU/3zHecUeDh-o/s1600-h/hi14.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/ScL5dQm0gkI/AAAAAAAAAwU/3zHecUeDh-o/s320/hi14.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5315084791319921218" /></a>Jon and I took a sailboat ride. Well it was really a catamaran. It was fun, but we didn't make it up the Nepali coast because there were 30-40 mile an hour winds on the west side of the island. This is a picture of a spinner dolphin. It's the most beautiful dolphin I've ever seen. They actually don't survive in captivity that's why I've never seen one. They either drown themselves or starve to death days after being caught. There were times our boat was surrounded by groups of 20 or more of these at a time.<br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/ScL5c2E0AJI/AAAAAAAAAwM/moxe3aFLdWw/s1600-h/hi13.jpg"><img style="display:block; 	<item>
		<title>Just Play</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/68</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 30 Mar 2009 01:25:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/68</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SdAf9aVphvI/AAAAAAAAA0w/i3JLOBSUG_4/s1600-h/avery5.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 214px; height: 320px;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SdAf9aVphvI/AAAAAAAAA0w/i3JLOBSUG_4/s320/avery5.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5318786299827160818" /></a><br /><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SdAf9M6jRZI/AAAAAAAAA0g/mrq9lfLsmwg/s1600-h/avery3.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 213px; height: 320px;" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SdAf9M6jRZI/AAAAAAAAA0g/mrq9lfLsmwg/s320/avery3.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5318786296223843730" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SdAf84IBmvI/AAAAAAAAA0Y/htEPvuSy_vI/s1600-h/avery2.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 214px; height: 320px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SdAf84IBmvI/AAAAAAAAA0Y/htEPvuSy_vI/s320/avery2.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5318786290643213042" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SdAf8sz5kdI/AAAAAAAAA0Q/GLf4_vRzMbQ/s1600-h/avery1.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 214px; height: 320px;" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SdAf8sz5kdI/AAAAAAAAA0Q/GLf4_vRzMbQ/s320/avery1.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5318786287606010322" /></a>I was recently at a studio lighting workshop, and had an interesting conversation with the instructor about the most challenging age to shoot. The instructor was saying that 5 year old boys are the toughest, I think 2 year olds...period. I actually love shooting 2 year olds, but they are by far the most challenging to capture, but when I do it's always an image full of personality. These pics are of little Avery. Avery is a little person with a big personality. She was all over the studio. I just set my lights up and let her play. At one point she even stood up on the bench and tried to get mommy an daddy to smile. It was hilarious. <div>These are some of my favorite images, not only because she's adorable, but also for the artistic edge. Lately I've been experimenting with the rule of 255. Basically anything over 255 is going to be lost data in the digital world. In other words it's blown out, or really white. So white that there is actually no digital information there. Technically speaking, I'm suppose to to stay under 255, but I wouldn't be an artist if I didn't try to break the rules. This work reminds me of the paintings where the artist filled large parts of the portrait with black. I haven't printed a lot of these pics, so that might be where I run into problems, but I'm curious to see what people think of the images.</div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Beautiful Eden</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/70</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 14 Apr 2009 01:35:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/70</guid>
		<description></description>

margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 213px;" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SePojSd771I/AAAAAAAAA2w/y_XJWyjnRts/s320/eden5.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5324354877432524626" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SePojHhF0wI/AAAAAAAAA2o/FtTUt2WyzAU/s1600-h/eden6.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 213px; height: 320px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SePojHhF0wI/AAAAAAAAA2o/FtTUt2WyzAU/s320/eden6.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5324354874492965634" /></a>I'd always heard that women glow when they're pregnant, but I didn't truly understand it until I started taking pictures of them. I haven't quite pinpointed what it is that makes them look so different, it might be the hormones, maybe just the excitement and anticipation, but after working with many future mother's I've come to think that the glow is really the reality that our bodies are capable of creating new life. Two souls sharing the same body. All that energy and love bundled in one big belly. What a powerful and amazing experience. <div>These pictures are of beautiful Eden, a mommy to be that exudes happiness and love.It was such a wonderful experience working with Eden.Every moment of her pregnancy has been a thrilling experience, and she's bubbling over with the anticipation of starting a new life with her little one. She's going to make an amazing mother, and I can't wait to meet her little one really soon!</div>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Easter is the best!</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/71</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 21 Apr 2009 01:29:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/71</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Se0h0MypLJI/AAAAAAAAA4A/BSJqZVi7xIs/s1600-h/j1.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 213px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Se0hzwMcDfI/AAAAAAAAA34/VMNFXrXsha4/s320/j3.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5326951107243281906" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Se0hz3nDrcI/AAAAAAAAA3w/7UIzifeW_zM/s1600-h/j4.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Se0hz3nDrcI/AAAAAAAAA3w/7UIzifeW_zM/s320/j4.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5326951109233978818" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Se0hzpV4nlI/AAAAAAAAA3o/nRw2dFoYsxM/s1600-h/j5.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 214px; height: 320px;" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Se0hzpV4nlI/AAAAAAAAA3o/nRw2dFoYsxM/s320/j5.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5326951105403854418" /></a><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Se0hzsCTqZI/AAAAAAAAA3g/fFWy-wVq8QU/s1600-h/j6.jpg"><br /><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 214px; height: 320px;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Se0hzsCTqZI/AAAAAAAAA3g/fFWy-wVq8QU/s320/j6.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5326951106127047058" /></a>Easter was always my most favorite holiday as a kid, but it took me quite a few years to get the hang of the whole egg hunt thing. We totally did it old school with real eggs that we had painted earlier that week. I loved eggs so I didn't mind, but the plastic eggs they have now with candy and money inside are awesome! We also hid the eggs in the house which is different than the traditional egg hunt outside. I didn't mind, I didn't know the difference. There was this one year that we must have miss counted the eggs because we found one months later in a blue earn my mom kept on a glass table. It must have been a well sealed earn because we didn't smell it at all. <div>The pictures above are of two adorable little darlings. They are always so happy to have their pictures taken which makes my job way too easy. The bottom one is my favorite because yes it does say caution teething, and yes that is a long string of drool seeping out of his mouth. I love it, babies are the best! Just look at those big brown eyes. </div>]]></content:encoded>

She was cracking Jon and I up, singing "That's not my name" dancing and galloping around the studio. I always get done with a shoot feeling full of life and more appreciative of the moments we have together. Kids are such good medicine for the soul! Thanks for sharing your family and fun with me. I feel so honored to have been given the opportunity to capture these ever changing moments in time. ]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Mother&#039;s Day Special</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/74</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 05 May 2009 04:27:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/74</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: arial; font-size: 13px; "><p style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0in; "><b><span style="font-size:100%;"><span style="font-family:Times New Roman;">Make This the Most Memorable Mothers Day Yet!</span></span></b></p><p style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0in; "><span style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:100%;"></span></p><p style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0in; "><span style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:100%;">Mothers day is just around the corner!<span></span>This year, we have an easy way to give mom something from the heart!<span></span>Caring Touch Massage and Allison Carenza Photography (</span><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(42, 93, 176); 		<title>3 year old twins!</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/75</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 21 May 2009 02:34:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/75</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/ShS-ENT_v6I/AAAAAAAAA6A/dgWitwtmUhc/s1600-h/twins4.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/ShS-ENT_v6I/AAAAAAAAA6A/dgWitwtmUhc/s320/twins4.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5338100437843165090" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/ShS-DyswRfI/AAAAAAAAA54/gfwChE8R980/s1600-h/twins3.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 214px; height: 320px;" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/ShS-DyswRfI/AAAAAAAAA54/gfwChE8R980/s320/twins3.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5338100430699251186" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/ShS-DgWU3cI/AAAAAAAAA5w/sBi8yCNwTx8/s1600-h/twins2.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 214px; height: 320px;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/ShS-DgWU3cI/AAAAAAAAA5w/sBi8yCNwTx8/s320/twins2.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5338100425773342146" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/ShS-Dfn7UFI/AAAAAAAAA5o/-XY3fzsQiSU/s1600-h/twins1.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 213px; height: 320px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/ShS-Dfn7UFI/AAAAAAAAA5o/-XY3fzsQiSU/s320/twins1.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5338100425578729554" /></a>It might be hard to believe, but these two little darlings were shy for the first 20 minutes of our shoot. They were pretty convinced that they did not need their pictures taken. When kids are shy in the studio the best way to handle it is to just hang out and let them feel comfortable. I don't blame them for feeling insecure with the big camera, big paper, big lights, and big guy (aka Jon)! It doesn't take long for them to feel comfortable, and my goal is to make the experience fun so they will want to come back and see us again with no hesitation. These two kids were little balls of energy and personality, and I look forward to watching them grow up.]]></content:encoded>

		<title>The wonderful woods!</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/76</link>

		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[There is nothing better than a day taking pictures in the woods, especially after a day of rain. Rain is a common theme for Memorial day. In fact I can't remember a Memorial weekend when it didn't rain. This year between downpours I was able to snap a few pics on my random walks. Skiing was out of the question so Carter, my mom, and I had a good times going on turtle hunts. We never actually found turtles, but we did catch up with quite a few roly-polies which were equally exciting for Carter. One of our other favorite activities was fishing. It might look like the boys are having a great time fishing in these pics, but don't be deceived, they are fishing off the deck into the woods. <a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/ShtDcRd_10I/AAAAAAAAA8g/6macVD0Emg0/s1600-h/w20.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 213px; height: 320px;" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/ShtDcRd_10I/AAAAAAAAA8g/6macVD0Emg0/s320/w20.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5339935936182474562" /></a>Look closely in this pic you can tell what Jud had for lunch!<br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/ShtDcEnFSyI/AAAAAAAAA8Y/5YLMIsTvbjc/s1600-h/w19.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/ShtDcEnFSyI/AAAAAAAAA8Y/5YLMIsTvbjc/s320/w19.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5339935932730919714" /></a>After throwing his fishing pole over the deck he had to go retrieve it. <br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/ShtDb_JU6iI/AAAAAAAAA8Q/jWAmzaiernY/s1600-h/w18.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/ShtDb_JU6iI/AAAAAAAAA8Q/jWAmzaiernY/s320/w18.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5339935931263937058" /></a>This was one of my favorite quiet places to go when I was a kid. 	<item>
		<title>GO...Go...Go...</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/78</link>
		<pubDate>Sun, 31 May 2009 00:45:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/78</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[I pride myself on being a busy body, able to multi-task without much effort, it's the one good thing ADD gave me. But this time I really overdid it! Let me tell you about my crazy life and then you can serve me some cheese with my whine. <div><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Most of you know that I have been asked to teach 5<span class="blsp-spelling-error" id="SPELLING_ERROR_0">th</span> grade next year. I am excited about the change and look forward to doing reading and writing all day, however moving rooms was not first on my list of favorite things. This last week I managed to pack my classroom, move it, unpack it, and repack it for summer school. Forget the gym I got my workout at school. All is good my new room has a window and I love it. <span class="blsp-spelling-error" id="SPELLING_ERROR_1">Ok</span> back to this crazy weekend. Thursday morning I woke up at 5 something AM. YUCK! I decided since my body thought my TO DO list was more important than my sleep I might as well use the time wisely so I got to school really early, more of that unpacking stuff. After school I cleaned the house, played my first outdoor soccer game (I'm still sore) and met with a guy about selling the BMW. Oh wait and then Jon and I cleaned out the basement for garage sale stuff, put it all in the office, to bed sometime around 12. </div><div><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Friday rolls around it's time for some reflection with my little darlings. Good times, I miss them already. Then I'm checked out of school and hurry home in time for a 4pm shoot. The shoot went really well too many pics to choose. Then J wants to eat, so off to sushi, he's really going all raw. Back home we have to take the stuff out of the office and put it upstairs, but I get distracted by my photos, oh no, now it's 12 and still no movement. We finally get all the stuff upstairs at 1am. I'm asleep sometime around 2am. </div><div><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Saturday 6am the alarm sounds, well not really the alarm just NPR. I love NPR, keeps my up to speed! I start setting up in the garage which requires some shuffling of the 4 cars. Then sweeping, then moving of the beer pong tables. Yup, we have those in our garage and they do make great tables for garage sales. Sometime around 7:18 I yell to Jon to get up and help because I'm running out of time, I know only the best garage sale shoppers come out between 7 and 9. He comes out and moves some stuff around, it's done enough that I can go put signs up around 7:30. Still nothing is labeled, I told Jon to work on that. They make these little round stickers with garage sale prices already on them, it's awesome so it was really fast for him. I start driving around putting these little green signs up around, and on I-70. Sounds scary, was scary. There weren't too many people out so I didn't get hit. I decide J needs food, so stop off at <span class="blsp-spelling-error" id="SPELLING_ERROR_2">McDonalds</span>, which never happens. He likes the <span class="blsp-spelling-error" id="SPELLING_ERROR_3">McGriddles</span>, I think those are weird... syrup in the bread...how do they keep them from getting soggy?  I go for the egg <span class="blsp-spelling-error" id="SPELLING_ERROR_4">mcmuffin</span>, healthy and tasty. When I get back home Jon is surrounded by serious garage sale shoppers, they know where the good deals are. He's already sold a ton of stuff, but seems to be handling it well so I sat down and enjoyed my egg <span class="blsp-spelling-error" id="SPELLING_ERROR_5">mcmuffin</span>. It was another hour before J ate. He likes milk with his breakfast, I can eat dry! We sold everything, we were doing so well I looked at J and said hey lets sell our TV. So he went downstairs and got it, and we sold it! In fact everything we talked about wanting to sell we sold within a few minutes. Karma loved us today. We didn't end up making much money just a couple hundred bucks, but it was fun. We gave all the other stuff to a neighbor going through hard times. She's going to sell it in the neighborhood garage sale next weekend, and keep the money. I hope she sells a lot. After getting all that stuff packed away we ate and went to Nebraska furniture mart. I love <span class="blsp-spelling-error" id="SPELLING_ERROR_6">NFM</span>! It's like Disney world for adults. I got a new couch for the studio, because I sold the it in the GS. And a $300 rug for $80. It was a floor model so we have to get it cleaned, but I love it! <br /></div><div><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>After <span class="blsp-spelling-error" id="SPELLING_ERROR_7">NFM</span>, we headed to the plaza for another photo shoot. One of my favorite clients, the <span class="blsp-spelling-error" id="SPELLING_ERROR_8">Habiger family</span>, cute kids and wonderful family. We've become real friends. Despite the heat we got some excellent pics. I love shooting there, great energy. I can't wait to work on those photos. Tonight I am writing, and laying in bed, so buzzed with life I can't settle down even though Jon and I went to El <span class="blsp-spelling-error" id="SPELLING_ERROR_9">Maguey</span> and had some <span class="blsp-spelling-corrected" id="SPELLING_ERROR_10">Margarita's. I think this is what it's like to have kids, you're always thinking about what's next. The never ending to do's! I like it though, I'm so productive when I get in this crazy "keep up" mode. At some point I need to relax, hopefully next week. Not tomorrow, 2 more shoots, and we need to sell the car someone is coming to look from AR. Oh yah, and my family is coming over for dinner Sun. night. If you made it this far, you must relate. I love my life, and everyone in it, I am so lucky to be busy! </span><br /></div>]]></content:encoded>

Is that the first sign that we work too hard??  But you gotta work while you can!  Keep it up while you can...]]></wp:comment_content>

		<title>Beautiful Family in Beautiful light</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/80</link>
		<pubDate>Sun, 07 Jun 2009 22:36:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/80</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SixBMh325_I/AAAAAAAAA-0/7xxQL76ymJs/s1600-h/h5.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SixBMh325_I/AAAAAAAAA-0/7xxQL76ymJs/s320/h5.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5344718541288826866" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SixBMcTaV-I/AAAAAAAAA-s/7SFZaB1TYZ4/s1600-h/h4.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SixBMcTaV-I/AAAAAAAAA-s/7SFZaB1TYZ4/s320/h4.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5344718539793782754" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SixBMcXM0PI/AAAAAAAAA-k/rCSnwDqZNX4/s1600-h/h3.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 214px; height: 320px;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SixBMcXM0PI/AAAAAAAAA-k/rCSnwDqZNX4/s320/h3.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5344718539809673458" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SixBLz4y8-I/AAAAAAAAA-c/a1z3KmM2wAU/s1600-h/h2.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 213px;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SixBLz4y8-I/AAAAAAAAA-c/a1z3KmM2wAU/s320/h2.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5344718528944731106" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SixBLmulZTI/AAAAAAAAA-U/DMgrkqwdJwY/s1600-h/h1.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SixBLmulZTI/AAAAAAAAA-U/DMgrkqwdJwY/s320/h1.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5344718525412238642" /></a>Most people don't know that I do on location shoots. The Nelson is one of my favorite locations. I love getting out of the studio and experimenting with interesting locations. However, it can be challenging. In my studio I control the light, background, and weather. When we're out and about I have to work with mother nature. On this particular shoot we had beautiful summer sun, but were also dealing with early summer weather. It was hot! I love heat and rarely sweat, but most people do not like to get their pictures taken when it's hot. This family is always upbeat and amazing to work with, so they didn't let it get them down, but as a photographer I know I have to work fast in the heat. If you're considering scheduling an on location shoot there are many advantages and disadvantage. One of the big advantages is that I can literally follow the kids around as they play and have fun, but prepare yourself for the uncontrollable weather! <div><br /></div>]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>
		<wp:post_id>80</wp:post_id>
		<wp:post_date>2009-06-07 16:36:00</wp:post_date>
		<wp:post_date_gmt>2009-06-07 22:36:00</wp:post_date_gmt>

		<title>New Parents, New Baby</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/82</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 15 Jun 2009 01:41:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/82</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjWnWC-A29I/AAAAAAAABAE/y5yGUpDT3po/s1600-h/z5.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 213px;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjWnWC-A29I/AAAAAAAABAE/y5yGUpDT3po/s320/z5.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5347364129768266706" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjWnV5dy0fI/AAAAAAAAA_8/oMH1uVkDk0o/s1600-h/z4.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 214px; height: 320px;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjWnV5dy0fI/AAAAAAAAA_8/oMH1uVkDk0o/s320/z4.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5347364127217209842" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjWnVjESXjI/AAAAAAAAA_0/NwzedQw7Agw/s1600-h/z3.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 214px; height: 320px;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjWnVjESXjI/AAAAAAAAA_0/NwzedQw7Agw/s320/z3.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5347364121204645426" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjWnVv8mNbI/AAAAAAAAA_s/tIEM_DuAe10/s1600-h/z2.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 213px;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjWnVv8mNbI/AAAAAAAAA_s/tIEM_DuAe10/s320/z2.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5347364124662052274" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjWnVZVvAzI/AAAAAAAAA_k/Ii4CbsCuBnI/s1600-h/z1.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjWnVZVvAzI/AAAAAAAAA_k/Ii4CbsCuBnI/s320/z1.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5347364118593471282" /></a>Recently I had the honor of shooting this beautiful baby boy. His parents are brand new parents but so relaxed you would never know it. They were really enjoying the whole experience, even taking pictures of me taking pictures. They have a blog that they post pictures on regularly. I'll post a link when I get it. When they first got to my studio the little one was fussy so we just let him eat, after getting full to the gills he was ready to go. And go he did, right on dad. I warned them that they always go on the dads, but the parents were great sports and took the accident in stride. It was fun getting to know the family, working with them, and watching them love their boy. They will be very dedicated parents, committed to capturing all the big moments. I can't wait to watch this little one grow up!]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>They are all so cute!</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/84</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 16 Jun 2009 03:44:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/84</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjcVagsYarI/AAAAAAAABA8/mRbPqnEkH94/s1600-h/p5.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 213px;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjcVagsYarI/AAAAAAAABA8/mRbPqnEkH94/s320/p5.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5347766627722619570" /></a>I have dead straight hair and would love for my hair to have any of this body even if it was for just an hour. <br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjcVahE3jjI/AAAAAAAABA0/i9SdxJi79og/s1600-h/p4.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 214px; height: 320px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjcVahE3jjI/AAAAAAAABA0/i9SdxJi79og/s320/p4.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5347766627825323570" /></a>This next picture isn't actually "that moment" but it totally looks like it. I just love the expression on his face. It's like he's saying, momma look at me, I'm doing it, and I'm coming for you.<br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjcVaREUFcI/AAAAAAAABAs/sTqNwl5cL8k/s1600-h/p3.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 214px; height: 320px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjcVaREUFcI/AAAAAAAABAs/sTqNwl5cL8k/s320/p3.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5347766623528031682" /></a>This picture is of the birthday boy right after he enjoyed destroying his birthday cake. He didn't actually eat much, he just got really really messy and didn't like it much. I guess not all of us have a sweet tooth.<br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjcVaDFE2ZI/AAAAAAAABAk/k_LGol7kyQI/s1600-h/p2.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjcVaDFE2ZI/AAAAAAAABAk/k_LGol7kyQI/s320/p2.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5347766619773131154" /></a>I love this picture it reminds me of the little <span class="blsp-spelling-corrected" id="SPELLING_ERROR_0">ballerinas</span> in the music boxes that every little girl had growing up.<br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjcVZ5UNj5I/AAAAAAAABAc/GKax--Evh80/s1600-h/p1.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 214px; height: 320px;" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjcVZ5UNj5I/AAAAAAAABAc/GKax--Evh80/s320/p1.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5347766617152262034" /></a>I know I always say that I have so much fun taking pictures of these kids, and I have so much fun getting to know the families, and they are all so perfect and beautiful...but I truly think that. I'm sure it gets old hearing me rattle on and on about these darlings, but they are all so fun and unique. I think I'll start trying to tell you a funny story about our shoot. I always laugh, it never fails. With the exception of newborns all kids are hilarious. Newborns are floppy and adorable, but they don't do many funnies except when they tinkle on their dads. Ok funny kids, for example, the little beauty in the above pic was convinced she was Taylor Swift or Hannah Montana in fact she tromped right into the house without her parents, right into my studio ready to strike a pose. With that confidence I have no doubt she will do something amazing in her life. The little guy in the pics had the most gentle soul, and he just adored his sister. I know she'll be dressing him up before the year ends. They really were fun, and I couldn't stop laughing at their reactions to the adults dancing around the room trying to get their smile just right. Classic.]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Horse lovers</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/85</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 17 Jun 2009 03:24:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/85</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[I'm convinced that being a horse lover is a genetic trait. Some might call it a genetic flaw, but either way I believe you are born with a love for horses. I have loved horses for as long as I can remember. Definitely way before I ever had a horse. My point, well horses become the subject of a lot of my photography. I've been so busy with shoots that I haven't had time to take some fun photos. So today after editing photos for 4 hours and placing 4 orders I decided I wanted off the dang computer. So I grabbed my camera and went to the barn. I've been noticing some awesome light out there around 5. Today the sky was perfect, electric blue with puffy white clouds, the light was hitting the horses in a golden hue. I was in horse photo heaven. Until I realized that the horses in the pasture were all the way on the other side. No problem I wore my grubby tennis shoes to get grubby. So I took off through the weeds and grass up to my knees. Hoping the whole time that the chiggers weren't out yet. What I didn't think about was the<span class="blsp-spelling-corrected" id="SPELLING_ERROR_0">torrential</span> rain we've had these last few days. There was literally a river running through the pasture. I might be exaggerating that a little, but I definitely had to pause and ponder how I would get across. I even contemplated turning around, but then gingerly took my first step forward when it immediately sunk all the way into the water. I lifted it out expecting it to be covered in mud, but lucky for me just water. They needed a good cleaning so I trudged on. When I arrived at the horses I faced a new problem...flies. YUCK! You'll see in the pics. Now that I've rambled way too long I'll share some photos.<div></div>]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>
		<wp:post_id>85</wp:post_id>
		<wp:post_date>2009-06-16 21:24:00</wp:post_date>
		<wp:post_date_gmt>2009-06-17 03:24:00</wp:post_date_gmt>
		<wp:comment_status>open</wp:comment_status>
		<wp:ping_status>open</wp:ping_status>
		<wp:post_name>horse-lovers</wp:post_name>
		<wp:status>publish</wp:status>
		<wp:post_parent>0</wp:post_parent>
		<wp:menu_order>0</wp:menu_order>
		<wp:post_type>post</wp:post_type>
		<wp:post_password></wp:post_password>
		<wp:is_sticky>0</wp:is_sticky>
		<category domain="category" nicename="uncategorized"><![CDATA[Uncategorized]]></category>

	<item>
		<title></title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/86</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 17 Jun 2009 03:47:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/86</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjhqM2Nkn8I/AAAAAAAABEE/EsP-Jw3_SXU/s1600-h/ho10.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjhqM2Nkn8I/AAAAAAAABEE/EsP-Jw3_SXU/s320/ho10.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5348141326445879234" /></a>Look closely at the foot prints on the left. Yup those are mine. Soaked all the way through. Read the next blog for details. Then come back and look at the pics.<br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjhoDCYnr2I/AAAAAAAABD8/U19VhQ5isPE/s1600-h/ho9.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 213px;" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjhoDCYnr2I/AAAAAAAABD8/U19VhQ5isPE/s320/ho9.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5348138958891495266" /></a>In the above pic you can see the flies, a small price to pay for a pasture horse. In exchange they get lush grass to munch on all day. Look closely at this next pic and you see a fly in flight next to his right eye. As you can see I was greeted with a lot of love. While I was out there I couldn't help but think that the only subject harder to shoot than babies must be animals.<br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjhoC1RLHdI/AAAAAAAABD0/sWFijVq6Owc/s1600-h/ho8.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 213px; height: 320px;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjhoC1RLHdI/AAAAAAAABD0/sWFijVq6Owc/s320/ho8.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5348138955370601938" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjhoCp2G82I/AAAAAAAABDs/yi9uH8HiLxs/s1600-h/ho7.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 213px; height: 320px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjhoCp2G82I/AAAAAAAABDs/yi9uH8HiLxs/s320/ho7.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5348138952304292706" /></a>This big boy needs to keep up the running, he's a little on the chunky side.<br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjhoCrWRxoI/AAAAAAAABDk/9YsJwiewCQ4/s1600-h/h1.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjhoCrWRxoI/AAAAAAAABDk/9YsJwiewCQ4/s320/h1.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5348138952707655298" /></a>This little girl went down for a nice roll in the fresh mud. Not sure what her buddy was doing in the background. Most non horse people don't know that horses actually behave a lot like us, they have friends in the pasture and people they don't much like. They even have little gossip groups.<br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjhoCenrkII/AAAAAAAABDc/6qazaXkAwm0/s1600-h/h2.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjhoCenrkII/AAAAAAAABDc/6qazaXkAwm0/s320/h2.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5348138949290987650" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjhnxlesRPI/AAAAAAAABDU/IHwF0FHwNek/s1600-h/h3.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjhnxlesRPI/AAAAAAAABDU/IHwF0FHwNek/s320/h3.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5348138659074557170" /></a>The guy in the back ground is like dude.<br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjhnxTSLZaI/AAAAAAAABDM/OzsEJNalCgo/s1600-h/h04.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjhnxTSLZaI/AAAAAAAABDM/OzsEJNalCgo/s320/h04.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5348138654190232994" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjhnxZ1v69I/AAAAAAAABDE/h3k2o8Zv-so/s1600-h/ho4.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 213px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjhnxZ1v69I/AAAAAAAABDE/h3k2o8Zv-so/s320/ho4.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5348138655950040018" /></a>I took this one from my car. This donkey is hilarious.<br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjhnbX_BN3I/AAAAAAAABC8/_F1WFJet_AE/s1600-h/ho11.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjhnbX_BN3I/AAAAAAAABC8/_F1WFJet_AE/s320/ho11.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5348138277494929266" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjhnbGORr2I/AAAAAAAABC0/Bkcca2E8cNg/s1600-h/ho12.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 320px; height: 214px;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SjhnbGORr2I/AAAAAAAABC0/Bkcca2E8cNg/s320/ho12.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5348138272727084898" /></a>Diamond lives in a prison much like this one, however she gets hay and grain twice a day, has a fan, fresh water, gets turned out for 4 hours a day, and best of all a fly system. No flies in these eyes.<br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sjhna1L7-xI/AAAAAAAABCs/vC5ZtyNZfVE/s1600-h/ho13.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 214px; height: 320px;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sjhna1L7-xI/AAAAAAAABCs/vC5ZtyNZfVE/s320/ho13.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5348138268153871122" /></a>I'm going to continue taking pics of the barn, after 45 minutes 52 pictures and a pair of soggy shoes I had to cut my shoot short. Better luck next time.]]></content:encoded>

		<title>New Baby</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/87</link>
		<pubDate>Sun, 21 Jun 2009 15:26:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/87</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Friday Jon and I invested in another Mac. He was taking mine to work to work on his program. I needed it at home to do orders. It was time for two, and I'm so excited. However, the process of moving all my programs and photos over to the new computer is trying. If anyone checked my website yesterday you noticed it was down, part of the moving process. I wanted to let everyone know it's back up and running, along with all the proof pages. Thanks for your patience. Look for a new blog post later today from my new baby.]]></content:encoded>
