	<item>
		<title>Summer Solstice</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/88</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 22 Jun 2009 02:37:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/88</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sj7wMkIm4LI/AAAAAAAABEs/YlmIxDTvCYs/s1600-h/31.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 400px; height: 300px;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sj7wMkIm4LI/AAAAAAAABEs/YlmIxDTvCYs/s400/31.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5349977506011603122" /></a><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sj7upJczhYI/AAAAAAAABEk/gc9KJ3NyEBU/s1600-h/portfolio3.jpg"><br /><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 233px; height: 350px;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sj7upJczhYI/AAAAAAAABEk/gc9KJ3NyEBU/s400/portfolio3.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5349975798041511298" /></a>Today is one of my favorite and least favorite days of the year. It's the summer solstice, which means it's the longest day of the year. The sun didn't go down until 9:00 today, I know because I was out shooting until the last slivers of light slipped away.  It's also my least favorite because from here the days only get shorter while winter slowly creeps up on us.  I like winter don't get me wrong, but I love summer.<div> I also love this day because it's my parent's wedding anniversary.  They deserve a huge hurray because today is their 40th!!!!!!!!!  Their relationship has acted as a wonderful  model for Jon and I, and I am so happy for them.  When I asked my mom if she wanted to do something special for this special occation her response was,  no let's go on a big trip at 50 years.  What a women!  Humble, Adventurous, and Real.</div><div>There's just one more bonus to today, it was father's day.  My whole family is at the lake this weekend, so I didn't get to hang out with my dad today, but we see each other a lot, he's very involved in my life and I'm so lucky to have him as my dad!</div><div>This blog is all about Yay's today!</div><div>Yay for the summer which has official started today.</div><div>Yay for my parents and their 40 years of successful marriage.</div><div>Yay for my dad, for being the best!</div>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Cops for Kids</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/89</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 24 Jun 2009 03:33:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/89</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SkGeyddrPpI/AAAAAAAABFU/ab3z8kxJl_Y/s1600-h/cfk3.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 400px; height: 267px;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SkGeyddrPpI/AAAAAAAABFU/ab3z8kxJl_Y/s400/cfk3.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5350732422032604818" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SkGeyKvhDyI/AAAAAAAABFI/NBkKN92nbr4/s1600-h/cfk2.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 400px; height: 266px;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SkGeyKvhDyI/AAAAAAAABFI/NBkKN92nbr4/s400/cfk2.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5350732417007161122" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SkGexnMBSGI/AAAAAAAABE8/_4_U43ipQl0/s1600-h/cfk1.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 267px; height: 400px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SkGexnMBSGI/AAAAAAAABE8/_4_U43ipQl0/s400/cfk1.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5350732407463037026" /></a>July 25th the Independence Police Department is hosting the first ever fundraiser to help protect the kids in our community.  I love kids so anyone willing to take time to help them is on my A list.  I have been doing some photographing for the event and I feel blessed to be a part of this process.  The officers in charge, Matt and John are honorable men and have put a lot of their own time into making this event amazing.  They still have tickets left and really need to have them all sold by July 1st.  What better way to show your support to our men and women in black then to come and buy some of the awesome action items.  Not only are you showing your support to the people that protect us every day, but you're also helping those kids in the community that often get forgotten or lost in the shuffle.  Please take the time to look at their website and sign up.  Sorry about all the guilting, but I promise you'll have a great time!<div><span class="Apple-style-span"   style="  color: rgb(43, 30, 43); line-height: 20px; font-family:'lucida grande', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif;font-size:11px;"><h3 class="UIIntentionalStory_Message" ft="{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;msg&quot;}" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.4em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); overflow-x: hidden; overflow-y: hidden; "><a href="http://WWW.COPS-4-KIDS.ORG/">WWW.COPS-4-KIDS.ORG</a></h3></span></div>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Golden light</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/90</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 25 Jun 2009 02:50:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/90</guid>
		<description></description>

		<title>Family Portraits</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/92</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 30 Jun 2009 04:12:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/92</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SkmYPOu0VEI/AAAAAAAABHQ/r-r6kQ9nzfU/s1600-h/white1.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 400px; height: 267px;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SkmYOyuKc6I/AAAAAAAABHI/u7ipzk2Firw/s400/white2.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5352977012007531426" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SkmYO_eBmbI/AAAAAAAABHA/Q9hjPJoDmyY/s1600-h/white3.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 267px; height: 400px;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SkmYO_eBmbI/AAAAAAAABHA/Q9hjPJoDmyY/s400/white3.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5352977015429503410" /></a><br /><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SkmQ2ucxnWI/AAAAAAAABGg/8s8G8qZLMu4/s1600-h/white4.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 267px; height: 400px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SkmQ2ucxnWI/AAAAAAAABGg/8s8G8qZLMu4/s400/white4.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5352968901962603874" /></a>These pics were taken at Stone Canyon the brand new golf course near my house.  We had a short amount of time so I knew I needed a beautiful and versatile location.  I was thrilled to find this rock.  I think the background looks so good it might even be artificial.  We spent 30 minutes and got some fantastic shots thanks to the wonderful family.  Everyone was patient and happy.  It's never easy to do the big family pictures, but this family was amazing.  Despite the time crunch, burning sun, and  little ones we had a lot of fun. I think pictures are evidence enough that this family is close.  They seem to really love each other.  Look for more pics of this family to come.  We spent some time in the studio as well.]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Home Sweet Home</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/95</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 21 Jul 2009 19:35:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/95</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SmYYqkWM9XI/AAAAAAAABIw/c9YiR4_HdQQ/s1600-h/IND_b1.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 400px; height: 266px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SmYYqkWM9XI/AAAAAAAABIw/c9YiR4_HdQQ/s400/IND_b1.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5360999526021526898" /></a>Jon and I are finally home from Indonesia after 2 and a half weeks of adventure.  We had an amazing time.  It's really hard to put into words the experience we had, it was life changing. Indonesia is the most beautiful place I've ever been, a hidden jewel.  I'm currently going through the hundreds of pictures I took and trying to decide what to share.  This picture was from our last night on Gilli Air, an island off the coast of Lombok.  We were sitting on the beach at a restaurant enjoying a cocktail and trying to absorb our last moments in Indonesia.  This week my goal is to post a blog every day about our trip.  I hope everyone is doing well, we really missed you all.  I can't wait to share this experience with you.]]></content:encoded>

It was such an experience that I can't even sum it up in pictures or words, but I tried.  I kept a journal while on our trip and it's 18 pages.  I hope you enjoy the pics, thanks for taking the time to look at them.]]></content:encoded>

Matt Fowler, John Howe and a bunch of other wonderful Independence police officers put together a benefit to raise money for abused children. 		<title>kinda cool...</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/101</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 07 Aug 2009 02:37:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/101</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SnuT_UA50sI/AAAAAAAABPM/N2B_zkcIOuQ/s1600-h/Picture+3.png"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 400px; height: 250px;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SnuT_UA50sI/AAAAAAAABPM/N2B_zkcIOuQ/s400/Picture+3.png" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5367046096855618242" /></a><br />Google is so awesome!  Through their analytics program I can see the states and countries that view my website.  Recently I noticed that people from other countries are viewing my website.  11 different countries to be exact.  Ok...I know people that live in  7 of those countries, but it's still pretty cool.  I'm also getting page views in 20 states, New York, California, Texas, and Illinois are in the top 5 next to Missouri and Kansas.  It's really crazy when you think about how technology makes you feel so close to someone on the other side of the world.  I love it!]]></content:encoded>

		<title>First Birthday!</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/103</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 13 Aug 2009 01:24:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>

Everywhere and in everything.  He was shy and resistant for the longest time, but eventually we got some beautiful smiles out of him.  I had a lot of fun getting to know these two lovable kids! 	<item>
		<title>Eyes are the window to the soul</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/105</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 15 Aug 2009 03:07:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/105</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SoYmsYIp6vI/AAAAAAAABRs/nWPmw7b-jCo/s1600-h/d4.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 267px; height: 400px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SoYmsYIp6vI/AAAAAAAABRs/nWPmw7b-jCo/s400/d4.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5370022149520747250" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SoYmry7gAKI/AAAAAAAABRk/1KjMEUpWI1s/s1600-h/d3.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 267px; height: 400px;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SoYmry7gAKI/AAAAAAAABRk/1KjMEUpWI1s/s400/d3.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5370022139533459618" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SoYmrsLFaeI/AAAAAAAABRc/Oyz5LCSPOxw/s1600-h/d2.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 267px; height: 400px;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SoYmrsLFaeI/AAAAAAAABRc/Oyz5LCSPOxw/s400/d2.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5370022137719777762" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SoYmrKxcHBI/AAAAAAAABRU/DfFP7n7g8LY/s1600-h/d1.jpg" style="text-decoration: none;"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 267px; height: 400px;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SoYmrKxcHBI/AAAAAAAABRU/DfFP7n7g8LY/s400/d1.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5370022128753843218" /></a><div>I agree with the bible verse in Matthew that says that the eyes are the window to the soul.  So much can been seen in some ones eyes.  The eyes of these darling children sing happiness.  However when I look into peoples eyes, it's not always happiness that I see.  Take today for example when I ran into my friend Kelley at school.  Kelley's eyes spoke a world of emotion none of which were happiness.  Over the summer her husband unexpectedly died.  After 22 years of marriage, Kelley is lost without her husband.  They started dating when she was 18 and he treated her like a princess from day one.  While we caught up Kelley shared with me her heartache.  It's impossible to fully understand, but I will never forget her words.  She is being so strong right now, she has to be for her kids.  Kelley, I will keep you in my thoughts, and I am so very sorry for your loss.</div>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Boudoir Photo!</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/107</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 18 Aug 2009 02:42:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/107</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SooWY1RKlWI/AAAAAAAABSk/5VQGRU6WJ8o/s1600-h/k2.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 400px; height: 267px;" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SooWY1RKlWI/AAAAAAAABSk/5VQGRU6WJ8o/s400/k2.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5371130121464485218" /></a>The new trend in the wedding world is boudoir photos.  These photos are given to the groom as a gift from the bride.  I love taking these pictures.  I get to be completely creative with light, and make beautiful women look even more beautiful.  <span class="blsp-spelling-error" id="SPELLING_ERROR_0">Kersha</span>, the bride in these pictures  was absolutely gorgeous during our shoot and we got some amazing pictures.  If you're interested in getting your own hot pics for your hubby or boyfriend don't hesitate to call.  Taking these pictures is a total collaborative effort.  I want to make it personalized.  <span class="blsp-spelling-error" id="SPELLING_ERROR_1">Kersha</span> brought <span class="blsp-spelling-corrected" id="SPELLING_ERROR_2">lingerie, a John Deere hat, MU clothes, and even a shotgun to her shoot.  We got some hot photos.  I can't wait for her future husband Brian to see these on his weeding day.  If you're interested in scheduling, email me and I'll send you some more examples.  Even though the pictures are tasteful, classy and elegant, these images are private for obvious reasons. Thanks so much for reading!!!  Also, don't forget about my wedding special.  A massage and a boudoir photo!</span><div><br /></div><div><span class="blsp-spelling-corrected" id="SPELLING_ERROR_2"></span><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 20px; "><div>Looking for an easy, fun gift idea for the bride to be in your life? Caring Touch Massage and Allison Carenza Photography (<a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(42, 93, 176); text-decoration: none; ">http://www.allisoncarenza.<wbr>com/</a>) have teamed up to offer a package that includes lasting memories and a pre-wedding stress buster for your bride-to-be!</div><div></div><div>For just $110.00 you can boost the bride's confidence with a sexy boudoir photo shoot and a free 8x10 photo with Allison! Then, you can whisk the future Mrs. away to decrease her pre-wedding stress with a 60-minute massage from Erin! Both services can be used on different days, or they can be scheduled back to back for a full day of relaxation.</div><div></div><div>The best part about this gift is you dont have to leave the house to get it! Just hop on your computer and go to<a href="http://www.caringtouchmassage.biz/" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(42, 93, 176); text-decoration: none; ">http://www.caringtouchmassage.<wbr>biz</a>. Click on the online gift certificates link, and choose the Pampered Bride Package. margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 400px; height: 267px;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/So9-4D92uKI/AAAAAAAABS8/oSr5Ui8LDWg/s400/a2.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5372652382078810274" /></a><br /><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/So9-3uU_wYI/AAAAAAAABS0/cKfJ8TDFuF8/s1600-h/a1.jpg"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 267px; height: 400px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/So9-3uU_wYI/AAAAAAAABS0/cKfJ8TDFuF8/s400/a1.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5372652376270291330" /></a>Adorable, beautiful Amelia.  There's not much else to say, these pictures say it all.  She's a lively, beautiful, crazy 2 year old.  I love taking pictures of 2 year olds.  It's the most challenging age, but the most fun because you never know what you're going to get.  One minute they're smiling for the camera the next second their running across the room for their mom.  5 minutes later they're screaming and having a fit.  All 2 year olds are the same in that they're unpredictable.  I'm pretty laid back about the 2 year olds so if you're a parent and your 2 year is old is acting their age, don't worry they're all the same.  Crazy, hilarious and unpredictable all balled up in a little body with too much energy.  I get the best expressions at this age, pure genuine emotion.  We get to see their true colors and that's what pictures are all about.  I love 2 year olds so much that in the month of September all 2 year old shoots are free!  If you're up for the challenge, so am I!  I hope everyone is enjoying the beautiful weather, and I hope to see you soon.]]></content:encoded>

		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>

	<item>
		<title>Quantity vs. Quality?</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/113</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 01 Sep 2009 02:52:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/113</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Recently I had a conversation with my good friend Maggie about quantity vs. quality in photography. &nbsp;In todays digital world 1000 pictures is the norm for a wedding. &nbsp;10 years ago 200 pics was a lot. &nbsp;And of those 200 pics you might have gotten 50 good ones. &nbsp;Now you get 1000 pics and 200 good ones. &nbsp;So my question is, which would you rather have? &nbsp;1000 pics to pick from, or 100 really good ones. &nbsp;It's tough, but I want your opinion. &nbsp;On the right you can vote! &nbsp;Give me your opinion and comments if you have any.]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>

		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Meet Greyson! &nbsp;This 2 year old is a happy little ball of energy! &nbsp;Jon and I meet Greyson and his cool parents at Briarcliff, a new shopping area just north of downtown. &nbsp;We had a great time and got some wonderful shots. &nbsp;Look at those dimples. &nbsp;He's already a heartbreaker.&nbsp;</div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"></div><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/august/greyson2" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/august/greyson2" /></a><br /><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">I'm just experimenting with this shot. &nbsp;You can see the city in the background, but it's not big enough. &nbsp;Hmmm... &nbsp;Also we started our shoot at 9, but it wasn't really early enough. &nbsp;That summer sun acts as a hot light. &nbsp;My favorite light is the golden hour around 6.</div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; 		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/august/fire.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/august/fire.jpg" /></a></div><br />Typically I'm not a huge fan of colorized pictures or props, but I love this fire helmet. &nbsp;Having baby Maguire in black and white allows the richness of the red helmet to come out. &nbsp;Also, Maguire has a grandpa and uncle that are firefighters so I think this picture is precious, and the helmet has a lot of value.]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Cute kids!</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/116</link>
		<pubDate>Sun, 06 Sep 2009 21:38:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/116</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Meet Hunter and Anna! &nbsp;Two of my favorite kids. &nbsp;Anna is so sassy, and Hunter is the laid back cool guy. &nbsp;During this particular shoot Hunter was all serious on us. &nbsp;As you can see he's still absolutely adorable. &nbsp;He's got the round chubby cheeks and gorgeous blue eyes. &nbsp;She's got the big brown eyes and to die for dark Italian skin. &nbsp;Hunter takes after his dad in all ways, and Anna looks just like her mom. &nbsp;It's pretty cute really. &nbsp;</div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http:/allisoncarenza.com/blog/august/h1" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http:/allisoncarenza.com/blog/august/h1" /></a></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">I love this pic because Anna looks all little girl here, what a cute smile with those tiny teeth.</div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://allisoncarenza.com/blog/august/h2" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://allisoncarenza.com/blog/august/h2" /></a></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">In an effort to get Hunter to smile Marg and I went to all extremes next to standing on our heads. &nbsp;I'm pretty sure this look is saying "what the heck are they doing that's not funny just weird".</div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://allisoncarenza.com/blog/august/h4" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://allisoncarenza.com/blog/august/h4" /></a></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Anna's serious face...</div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://allisoncarenza.com/blog/august/h3" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://allisoncarenza.com/blog/august/h3" /></a></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">and her sassy face...</div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://allisoncarenza.com/blog/august/h5" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://allisoncarenza.com/blog/august/h5" /></a></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">In this photo Hunter is just amused.</div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://allisoncarenza.com/blog/august/h6" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://allisoncarenza.com/blog/august/h6" /></a></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">I love this shot because it shows just how much Anna loves her baby brother. &nbsp;I also love it for the story. Take a look at her hand. &nbsp;Yes that is a Jesus action figure. &nbsp;She came into the studio with it and said "I found Jesus in the bar" &nbsp;I love my job, I never stop laughing!!!!</div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://allisoncarenza.com/blog/august/h7" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://allisoncarenza.com/blog/august/h7" /></a></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"></div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Senior Pics in Kansas City</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/117</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 08 Sep 2009 02:42:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/117</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SqXDtNC8ZwI/AAAAAAAABUc/kI0W5MF9EHY/s1600-h/flowers.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SqXDtNC8ZwI/AAAAAAAABUc/kI0W5MF9EHY/s400/flowers.jpg" /></a></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"></div><br /><span style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif;">I was driving around this weekend when I saw the most perfect spot for senior pictures. &nbsp;A huge field of tall Brown Eyed Susans, they were everywhere. &nbsp; The problem is I don't have much time and this spot isn't going to stay perfect for long. &nbsp;I need seniors for this month preferably girls since boys and flowers don't go together. &nbsp;If you know anyone that is looking to get senior pics please send them my info. &nbsp;If we can find a time to get the shoot scheduled in the next couple of weeks I'll give them a free proof book of the best shots. PS this picture isn't of the field, it's just one I had on my computer. &nbsp;I'm not very good with flower names, but I'm pretty sure these are daisies. I hope everyone had a wonderful Labor Day weekend!&nbsp;</span>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Macon Missouri&#039;s, Fork and Food Festival</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/119</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 14 Sep 2009 02:04:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/119</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="text-align: center;">This weekend Jon and I were suppose to go on a float trip with the llamas. &nbsp;With bad weather in the forecast we decided to cancel the float and find another adventure. &nbsp;Jackie searched the internet high and low for something fun and different, and came acros little Macon Missouri and their fork and food festival. &nbsp;We booked a b and b and were on our way. &nbsp;We had no idea what to expect, but ended up having an amazing time. &nbsp;Here's a little bit about our adventure.<br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Their downtown was surprisingly big, this building was an old bank and it was a beautiful. &nbsp; Most of the stores were filled with antiques and thrift store type stuff. &nbsp;I really love small downtowns it's always such a shame that they aren't as unique on the inside as they are on the outside.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">I took lots of pictures of the locals. &nbsp;So much fun. &nbsp;Everyone recognized us as outsiders, they were shocked people from Kansas City would come up to their little festival. &nbsp;It wasn't long though before we felt like a part of the small town.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/macon6" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/macon6" /></a><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">&nbsp;&nbsp;It was a great day for sitting outside drinking wine and enjoying music. &nbsp;After the festival closed down we headed to a local bar where we danced like crazy people. &nbsp;Jon was unstoppable. &nbsp;I'll have to get some pics of the dancing from Smitty and add them later.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Remember these things. &nbsp;Were people supposed to tie their horses to these? &nbsp;I have no idea, but I would love to have one someday.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/macon4" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/macon4" /></a><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"></div><div style="text-align: center;">This is my favorite picture. &nbsp;The drive in was up and running until about 3 years ago. &nbsp;This picture is just a blast from the past.<br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/acon1" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/acon1" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">That night we stayed at the Phillips House b and b, &nbsp;carriage house. <a href="http://www.phillipsplacebandb.com/">http://www.phillipsplacebandb.com/</a>&nbsp;This house has history to say the least. &nbsp;It is the oldest building in Macon, built in the 1800's. &nbsp;Apparently it's haunted, which really doesn't surprise me it totally looks haunted from the outside in. &nbsp;We didn't find out that it was haunted until breakfast the next morning. <br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/macon3" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/macon3" /></a><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Jon told me on the way home that he had something weird happen to him. &nbsp;I guess he was going to the bathroom with his shirt off when he felt something lightly brush against his shoulder. At the time he thought it was a string from a light switch. &nbsp;After looking around he found nothing that could of touched him. &nbsp; He thought it was really weird. &nbsp;Hmm... I'll leave you to think what you want.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">If you need evidence that this house in haunted just look at the door.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">The home owner told us that people often notice two men that walk up and down the stairs, and a women in the bedroom Jon was in. <br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">This is the real b and b and it's beautiful. &nbsp;We had an amazing breakfast in this house. &nbsp;I liked the little haunted house, but I think next time I come to Macon I'll stay here. <br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; 		<title>Rusty Stout</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/121</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 19 Sep 2009 02:38:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/121</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="text-align: center;">It's not often I get to take pictures of adults. &nbsp;I love occationally taking pictures of adults because they actually listen. &nbsp;I know exactly how the shots are going to go for the most part. &nbsp;The following pictures are of Rusty Stout, a wonderful adult and a close friend.<br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/r1" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/r1" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Rusty had to have his pictures taken for an award. &nbsp;He was chosen to be the alumni of the year for North Kansas City High School.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/r2a" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/r2a" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: auto;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">The picture Rusty had to use was a plain head shot, but I couldn't put that picture up here because it's just not unique enough. &nbsp;Rusty is way more unique than the picture showed. &nbsp;I love the following picture because I think it shows his class. <br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/r3" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/r3" /></a><br /></div><br /><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Rusty has had a successful career in optometry. &nbsp;You might have even seen him on the commercials for Discover O, he is one of the owners. &nbsp;I think Rusty really deserved to win the alumni of the year, BRAVO Rusty! &nbsp;It couldn't have gone to a more deserving person.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/r4" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/r4" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><br /><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Bar Mitzvah Pictures</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/122</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 22 Sep 2009 03:03:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/122</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">I was one lucky photographer to be picked to take Ian Roozrokh's Bar Mitzvah pictures. &nbsp;It was hands down the most fantastic party I've ever shot. &nbsp; In the morning Ian had his ceremony, but before it got started I got to take a couple quick shots. <br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b19" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b19" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Here's Ian and his beautiful family! &nbsp;When I got there in the morning they greeted me with big hugs and smiles. &nbsp;There was so much joy.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b18" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b18" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Ian wasn't nervous at all, &nbsp;he seemed cool, calm, collected, and confident. &nbsp;I don't know many 13 year olds, but I know they aren't usually as nice as Ian. &nbsp;In fact he even thanked me for taking his pictures. <br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b17" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b17" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b22" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b22" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">After his ceremony there was a brunch, with some of the most amazing food. &nbsp;This was just party number one.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b21" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b21" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Rachel, Ian's mom used pictures we took for the newspaper for table centerpieces. &nbsp;Ian is all personality so the pictures looked great with his many expressions.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b20" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b20" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">I LOVE COOKIES, and these were delicious. <br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b16" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b16" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Ian is a bit of a ladies man. &nbsp;All the girls wanted their picture with him. <br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b15" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b15" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b14" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b14" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">His guy friends didn't want to be left out so they got together for a group shot. &nbsp;Totally different feel here. &nbsp;All boy!<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b11" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b11" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">...and all boy.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b23" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b23" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">This is the reception site for the party. &nbsp;It's a beautiful and unique facility in Overland Park just off Mission Rd.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.leawood.org/parks/lodge.aspx">http://www.leawood.org/parks/lodge.aspx</a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b24" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b24" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b13" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b13" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b12" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b12" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b9" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; text-align: center;">Yup the tables were all decked out with glow in the dark stuff, popcorn and everything kid. &nbsp;The kids even had their own food... pizza and pasta. <br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b8" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b8" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">The DJ was great and had games for the kids, I was daring enough to get in the middle of this one. &nbsp;I only got knocked down a couple times.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b7" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b7" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Meet David, Ian's dad! &nbsp;He was the life of the party. &nbsp;I think he missed his calling, he should be a party starter as his full time job. &nbsp;He was so much fun. &nbsp;I don't think he sat down all night.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b6" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b6" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b5" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b3" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b2" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; text-align: center;">So much movement! &nbsp;To this day anytime I hear the new Blackeyed Peas song I can't help but smile. &nbsp;It was the theme song of the night.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b26" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b26" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Even the adults were having a ball. &nbsp;They were dancing just as much as the kids! &nbsp;I love this picture because there is so much going on, just look at those faces.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b27" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b27" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">This last picture is meaningful to me. &nbsp;It totally sums up the night. Kick your shoes off and get down!<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">There were random shoes all over the place, even flats.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b1" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/september/b1" /></a><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;">There were over 400 pictures that I couldn't choose from. &nbsp; So many memories, &nbsp;Jon and I had a wonderful time, thanks Roozrokh's for opening your arms to us.<br /></div>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Happy Birthday Presley</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/124</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 02 Oct 2009 00:54:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/124</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif;">Last weekend I had a brand new experience as a professional photographer. &nbsp;I got to take pictures of a little girls 5th birthday. &nbsp;Not just any little girl, but beautiful Presley. &nbsp;Everything about Presley glows from her eyes, to her hair, to her big personality!&nbsp;</span><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/pp1" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/pp1" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif;">Here are her birthday presents. &nbsp;I remember as a kid loving the presents. &nbsp;Who am I kidding, I still love the presents.</span><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/pp2" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/pp2" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif;">This is one of those cool cupcake cakes. &nbsp;</span><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/pp3" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/pp3" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/pp4" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/pp4" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif;">Opening the presents, that must be the best as a parent. &nbsp;I just loved her many faces. &nbsp;I couldn't even pick which ones to share there were so many big smiles and great expressions.</span><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/pp5" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/pp5" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif;">Yum...</span><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/pp6" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/pp6" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif;">Seriously does it get much better than this?</span><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/pp7" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif;">Presley's friends were absolutely adorable too.</span><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/pp8" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/pp8" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/pp9" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif;">I love this picture because you can see the smile in her eyes. &nbsp;What is it?</span><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/pp10" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/pp10" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif;">Must be good!</span><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/pp11" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/pp11" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif;"><br /></span><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif;">Ok this is my favorite picture, however I'm still trying to figure out why. &nbsp;Maybe it's what she's doing. &nbsp;See she's running across the little bridge and it was an all kid moment.</span><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/pp12" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/pp12" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif;">Ok wait... maybe this is my favorite. &nbsp;Her idol is Taylor Swift and I think she could be her little sister.</span><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/pp13" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/pp13" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif;">This is Madi another one of my clients that I adore. &nbsp;When I got there she goes "there's Allison our favorite photographer lady." &nbsp;She smiled for me the whole time. Fantastic!</span><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/pp14" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/pp14" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif;">Oh the joy of a slide.</span><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/pp15" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/pp15" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/pp16" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; 		<title>Senior Pictures in KC</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/126</link>
		<pubDate>Sun, 11 Oct 2009 15:10:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/126</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: x-large;">&nbsp;Meet beautiful Loni. </span><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/l1" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/l1" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Loni is from Mound City, MO and not only is she beautiful, but she is also sincere and kind. &nbsp;I had the honor of taking her senior pictures and I had so much fun. The picture below is one of my favorites. &nbsp;It's so hard to look good serious, but Loni was a real natural.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/l2" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; text-align: center;">As you can see she was really relaxed which makes for great pictures. <br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/l3" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/l3" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">The first thing I noticed about Loni was her eyes. &nbsp;She's got huge brown eyes that quite literally steal the picture.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/l4" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/l4" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/l5" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/l5" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/l7" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/l7" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">While waiting for the train to go by we snapped off a few next to a moving train. &nbsp;It was intimidating to say the least. &nbsp;I don't even think the train was going that fast. &nbsp;This picture doesn't do the movement of the train justice, but I love the graffiti. <br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; 	<item>
		<title>MY BRAND NEW NEPHEW!!!!!</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/127</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 15 Oct 2009 01:40:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/127</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="text-align: center;">I am one proud aunt! Meet my new nephew Hayes Christopher!</div>
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/ha1"><img src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/ha1" border="0" alt="" /></a></div>
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">These pictures were taken only hours after little Hayes was born. I love baby feet. Hayes happened to have awesome nails. We were in need of baby nail clippers, the hospital gave us a baby file. Have you ever tried to file a newborns nails. Yikes!!!</div>
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Carter was absolutely infatuated with Hayes. he wanted to be around him at all times. He has already given him a new name "Peanut". In the picture below he was trying to tickle him. It was adorable because he was being so gentle.</div>
<div style="text-align: center;"><a style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/ha2"><img src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/ha2" border="0" alt="" /></a></div>
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">My mom is so obsessed with babies even though she works with them all day every day. She spent most of her time staring at him and saying ah I want to take him home.</div>
<div style="text-align: center;"><a style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/ha3"><img src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/ha3" border="0" alt="" /></a></div>
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Again, Carter was so obsessed!</div>
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Ilovethewayhislittlehandsarecuppinghishead.He'salittlenatural.</div>
<div style="text-align: center;"><a style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/ha4"><img src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/ha4" border="0" alt="" /></a></div>
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Juddy on the other hand was more interested in...well everything else. The gloves were very entertaining.</div>
<div style="text-align: center;"><a style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/ha5"><img src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/ha5" border="0" alt="" /></a></div>
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Carter back with the baby, my mom thinks he's the next Pediatrician. Maybe he'll take over the family practice. You might also want to notice the shirt. Too cute!</div>
<div style="text-align: center;"><a style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/ha6"><img src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/ha6" border="0" alt="" /></a></div>
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Shannon got the boys gifts on Hayes's b-day. Juddy got boots and he was so excited. You can't tell but they were green with a dragon on the side. He imediately threw his shoes off and put the boots on.</div>
<div style="text-align: center;"><a style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/ha7"><img src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/ha7" border="0" alt="" /></a></div>
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Even next to a 5 year old Hayes has tiny hands.</div>
<div style="text-align: center;"><a style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/ha8"><img src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/ha8" border="0" alt="" /></a></div>
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Carter may be the oldestofthe3,butheistotallymomma'sboy!</div>
<div style="text-align: center;"><a style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/ha9"><img src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/ha9" border="0" alt="" /></a></div>
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Oh my gosh, it doesn't get much better than this.</div>
<div style="text-align: center;"><a style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/ha10"><img src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/ha10" border="0" alt="" /></a></div>
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Little Peanut opened his eyes just long enough for a few pics.</div>
<div style="text-align: center;"><a style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/ha11"><img src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/ha11" border="0" alt="" /></a></div>
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Juddy, my dad and I roamed the halls so Shannon and the baby could eat. Otherwise he was wreaking havoc by jumping off the bed repeatedly. While walking the halls Juddy had to stop and talk to all the nurses (ladies man). He told them all about his new boots, and when they asked what they had on them, he told them humpty dumpty.</div>
<div style="text-align: center;"><a style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/ha13"><img src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/ha13" border="0" alt="" /></a></div>
<div style="text-align: center;"><a style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/ha14"><img src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/ha14" border="0" alt="" /></a></div>
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Shannon I don't know how you do it...amazing! You are and always will be the queen of the house.</div>
<div style="text-align: center;"><a style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/ha12"><img src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/ha12" border="0" alt="" /></a></div>
<div style="text-align: center;">I can't wait to get to know little Hayes. I am one lucky aunt.</div>]]></content:encoded>
