		<title>Blonde hair, blue eyes!</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/128</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 16 Oct 2009 03:06:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/128</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif;">This is Sumerlyn, and she is just as beautiful in person as she is in these pictures.&nbsp;</span><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/009" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/009" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif;"><br /></span><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif;">Being an only child she is very loved by her parents and also very grown up. &nbsp;I had a blast working with her. &nbsp; I will say she had a lot more fun playing with Lucy and Layla than &nbsp;taking pictues, but she was a great listener. Layla is actually our best prop. &nbsp;Go figure.</span><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/v1" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/v1" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif;">She was not afraid to be herself, it was awesome!</span><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/v2" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/v2" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif;"><br /></span><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/v4" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/v4" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif;">I love that they look so much alike! &nbsp;Blonde hair, and blue eyes... Todd you better watch out the boys are going to be knocking anytime now. &nbsp;One of which might be my nephew Carter. &nbsp;Sumerlyn and Carter will be starting school together next year at Chapel Lakes.</span><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/v5" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/v5" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/v3" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/v3" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif;">I can't wait to hang out with Sumerlyn more, she is such a sweet girl. &nbsp;Julie, and Todd, thanks for letting me take your pictures. &nbsp;</span><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Children Photography</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/129</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 20 Oct 2009 02:38:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/129</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;">This blog has a funny story. &nbsp;A couple of weeks ago I took pictures of a birthday party, and met some great people. &nbsp;One of those people passed my card on to another person. &nbsp;That person (Emily) &nbsp;looked at the card and said I know this person, they live up the street from me. &nbsp;Needless to say Emily stopped by and booked a session. &nbsp;We had a great time, and it's just proof that everything happens for a reason. &nbsp;Here are just a few pictures of her beautiful family.<br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/e1" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/e1" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Meet Shelby and Landon...adorable and spunky. &nbsp;They were all smiles during out shoot. &nbsp;It was awesome!<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/e2" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="640" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/october/e2" width="426" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">I had a ton of cute pictures of these two. &nbsp;I just couldn't pick. <br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/St0bf9Dq30I/AAAAAAAABVg/oCQLNlz_eL4/s1600-h/e3.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/St0bf9Dq30I/AAAAAAAABVg/oCQLNlz_eL4/s640/e3.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">You can tell they are very close,&nbsp;they were both full&nbsp;of&nbsp;smiles. <br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/St0bnqb4hjI/AAAAAAAABVw/xYbE7UoLZ3Q/s1600-h/e5.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/St0bnqb4hjI/AAAAAAAABVw/xYbE7UoLZ3Q/s640/e5.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">I love getting close enough to see the teeth. &nbsp;It's all about the little teeth. &nbsp;Someday those little teeth will be big teeth. <br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/St0blZvkXnI/AAAAAAAABVo/Wpehn2MWux0/s1600-h/e4.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/St0blZvkXnI/AAAAAAAABVo/Wpehn2MWux0/s640/e4.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; 	<item>
		<title>baby collages and more...</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/130</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 22 Oct 2009 00:12:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/130</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Lately I've been really reflecting on myself as a professional photographer. &nbsp;Trying to figure out what makes my work stand apart from the rest. &nbsp;There are so many amazing photographers out there so why should someone come to me? &nbsp;Well I've learned a lot about myself this past year. &nbsp;I learned that I love people and their faces in particular. &nbsp;I love to get up close so you can see the details in their eyes, their teeth and and even the little bit of drool that slips out at all the wrong times. &nbsp;I think the eyes show so much emotion and really when you look at someone you can tell so much about what their thinking, and feeling through their eyes. &nbsp;The collage below is exactly what I'm talking about. &nbsp;Just look at those faces!<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/St-fSDCM-aI/AAAAAAAABWA/1FVg3PtghBI/s1600-h/judson.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/St-fSDCM-aI/AAAAAAAABWA/1FVg3PtghBI/s640/judson.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">I don't do a good job of advertising my collages and design work, because quite frankly there's so much out there on the internet it's really hard to compete. &nbsp;I can, and do, design pretty much anything from collages, to canvas prints, to birthday thank you cards. &nbsp;If you can't find the perfect design on the internet just ask, I might be able to help. <br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/St-fWpFcKaI/AAAAAAAABWI/pDXYJKKYsoI/s1600-h/Evancollage.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/St-fWpFcKaI/AAAAAAAABWI/pDXYJKKYsoI/s640/Evancollage.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">The following 2 pictures were printed on canvas. &nbsp;Talk about art. &nbsp;I love it!!!<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/St-iqdS53kI/AAAAAAAABWY/O1IdallWaEY/s640/rudycanvas.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; 		<title>Family Portraits</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/131</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 23 Oct 2009 02:34:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/131</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;">Ok I think these might be some of the most amazing pictures I've ever taken! &nbsp;I know these are some of the most amazing people I've ever met. &nbsp;This is Rose and her boys Dalton and Garrett, and we had a blast taking pictures last week!<br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SuESae5AclI/AAAAAAAABWo/y5-m1DdbbHo/s1600-h/r2.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SuESae5AclI/AAAAAAAABWo/y5-m1DdbbHo/s640/r2.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Dalton has the best smile and he was totally willing to ham it up for me. <br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SuESYzZ7mAI/AAAAAAAABWg/pE04mOnfaE8/s1600-h/r1.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SuESYzZ7mAI/AAAAAAAABWg/pE04mOnfaE8/s640/r1.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Some people are so natural together and I would say this is definitely the case for Rose and her boys. &nbsp;They absolutely adore her, and treat her like a queen.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SuESbhZX24I/AAAAAAAABWw/75ch8Sq7buw/s1600-h/r3.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SuESbhZX24I/AAAAAAAABWw/75ch8Sq7buw/s640/r3.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SuEScLpWcyI/AAAAAAAABW4/HJJK8RpyctQ/s1600-h/r4.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SuEScLpWcyI/AAAAAAAABW4/HJJK8RpyctQ/s640/r4.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SuESdQT7bMI/AAAAAAAABXA/5amRew6rAqs/s1600-h/r5.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SuESdQT7bMI/AAAAAAAABXA/5amRew6rAqs/s640/r5.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Most of the time I like to play music during my shoots, sometimes it's funky town, sometimes its relaxing baby music, and sometimes it's kids bop. &nbsp;This time it was pure funk, and Garrett became Mr. Giggles. &nbsp;Apparently Garrett is Mr. Giggles at school. &nbsp;He was dancing all over the studio cuttin' a rug and breakin' down. &nbsp;We were absolutely cracking up. &nbsp;I love this picture because it shows just how much fun this family has together.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SuESeYRVuUI/AAAAAAAABXI/tRQ7SdVg0CM/s1600-h/r6.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SuESeYRVuUI/AAAAAAAABXI/tRQ7SdVg0CM/s640/r6.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; 	<item>
		<title>Cute Cute!</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/132</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 27 Oct 2009 03:02:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/132</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="text-align: center;">These pics were taken at Loose park. A fantastic location, unfortunately it was really cold outside. The kids were real troopers, and the parents were even more patient, so we got some really special shots.</div>
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SuZfm65VMEI/AAAAAAAABXg/Jf5c4ScKZJY/s1600-h/hab1.jpg"><img src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SuZfm65VMEI/AAAAAAAABXg/Jf5c4ScKZJY/s640/hab1.jpg" border="0" alt="" /></a></div>
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">I love Ella's big blue eyes, they absolutely sparkle. She was in a great mood and her grin showed up in her eyes.</div>
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SuZfoMRAg7I/AAAAAAAABXo/PraeGQqsZhI/s1600-h/hab2.jpg"><img src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SuZfoMRAg7I/AAAAAAAABXo/PraeGQqsZhI/s640/hab2.jpg" border="0" alt="" /></a></div>
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">The coolest family ever!!!</div>
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SuZfp-98zEI/AAAAAAAABXw/jbfLl6e2D84/s1600-h/hab3.jpg"><img src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SuZfp-98zEI/AAAAAAAABXw/jbfLl6e2D84/s640/hab3.jpg" border="0" alt="" /></a></div>
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Check out Rudy's jacket...adorable!</div>
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SuZfqBLsbhI/AAAAAAAABX4/k0yIThldh_M/s1600-h/hab4.jpg"><img src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SuZfqBLsbhI/AAAAAAAABX4/k0yIThldh_M/s640/hab4.jpg" border="0" alt="" /></a></div>
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SuZfrHGQTqI/AAAAAAAABYA/sdhY8q1hB68/s1600-h/hab5.jpg"><img src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SuZfrHGQTqI/AAAAAAAABYA/sdhY8q1hB68/s640/hab5.jpg" border="0" alt="" /></a></div>
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SuZfuPX_KFI/AAAAAAAABYI/T_cr0WVfIcw/s1600-h/hab6.jpg"><img src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SuZfuPX_KFI/AAAAAAAABYI/T_cr0WVfIcw/s640/hab6.jpg" border="0" alt="" /></a></div>
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Oh boy I love this picture! I love that you can see the movement in little Rudy, and I love the huge grin Karri has on her face. True joy!</div>
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;" href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SuZfu_D7lPI/AAAAAAAABYQ/YxpD02Blm9E/s1600-h/hab7.jpg"><img src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SuZfu_D7lPI/AAAAAAAABYQ/YxpD02Blm9E/s640/hab7.jpg" border="0" alt="" /></a></div>
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Thanks again Karri and Chris for making me feel like a part of your family.  Jon and I always enjoy seeing you and the kids!</div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>family photos</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/133</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 30 Oct 2009 02:50:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/133</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="text-align: center;">Fall, Fall, Fall! &nbsp;What a beautiful time of year. &nbsp;I've done dozens of shoots this fall in the beautiful fall colors and I can't get enough of it. &nbsp;Not only am I in love with the colors, but I'm also equally in love with the families I'm getting work with. &nbsp;I can't believe how lucky I am to have so many amazing people to work with. &nbsp;It makes taking pictures an experience! &nbsp;The following pictures are of one of those families that oozes love.<br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SupQoE7odGI/AAAAAAAABYY/nMiKIYxTmSU/s1600-h/m1.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SupQoE7odGI/AAAAAAAABYY/nMiKIYxTmSU/s640/m1.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Lexi is a gorgeous young lady with a glow to her eyes. <br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SupQp8uCNOI/AAAAAAAABYg/hJd5mkSnSB8/s1600-h/m2.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SupQp8uCNOI/AAAAAAAABYg/hJd5mkSnSB8/s640/m2.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Misti and Steve you 2 very lucky people to have eachother and your cool kids.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SupQqk10T7I/AAAAAAAABYo/dOMzn1w0uu8/s1600-h/m3.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SupQqk10T7I/AAAAAAAABYo/dOMzn1w0uu8/s640/m3.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Carter wasn't feeling well on the day of our shoot, but he gave me his all. &nbsp; I love the emotion you can see in his eyes in this picture.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SupQrVKdwTI/AAAAAAAABYw/4iDpSP5F9ds/s1600-h/m4.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SupQrVKdwTI/AAAAAAAABYw/4iDpSP5F9ds/s640/m4.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">This kids are so close they really seem to like each other. &nbsp;That doesn't happen often with siblings.<br /><br /><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SupQr1ae1BI/AAAAAAAABY4/GfFBScsMmhI/s1600-h/m5.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SupQr1ae1BI/AAAAAAAABY4/GfFBScsMmhI/s640/m5.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Misti has a heart of gold. &nbsp;She's that person that everyone wants as a friend because she's genuine, giving, and full of love. &nbsp;I'm very lucky to get to call her my friend. <br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SupQtTJsFEI/AAAAAAAABZA/smbM-xyocjo/s1600-h/m6.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SupQtTJsFEI/AAAAAAAABZA/smbM-xyocjo/s640/m6.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Nathan has such positive energy. &nbsp;He was totally down for any of my crazy ideas, I really enjoyed working with him.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SupQwg_5m6I/AAAAAAAABZY/ave4pTPQkak/s1600-h/m9.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; 		<title>The Fowler Family</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/134</link>

		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="text-align: center;"><br />This is Faith! &nbsp;The daughter of one of my closest friends.<br />The story of the following pictures is bitter sweet for me...<br /><br /><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Su-koYmEnRI/AAAAAAAABZw/tcv2ueVUryI/s1600-h/f1.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Su-koYmEnRI/AAAAAAAABZw/tcv2ueVUryI/s640/f1.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">You see, Matt on the left has been chosen to be a part of the FBI which requires him to do 5 months of training in DC, and then he and his family will be relocated to somewhere in the US. &nbsp;Sally is such a supportive wife she is about to give up so much to help Matt reach his dream. &nbsp;Don't get me wrong Matt really deserves to have his dreams come true and I'm so excited for him. He's one of the most amazing people I know. &nbsp;As you can see he comes from a long line of honorable men.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; 		<title>Salsman family</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/135</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 07 Nov 2009 04:15:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/135</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">I love this series of photos. &nbsp;Especially this one! &nbsp;His little eyes are absolutely glowing. &nbsp;Not to mention I chopped his mouth off. &nbsp;Not sure why, I can't remember now, but I probably had a reason like his little hand was in his mouth. &nbsp;This one says it all in his eyes.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SvTvA86ccpI/AAAAAAAABao/1x2mvMcPkPc/s1600-h/s7.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">This is Kim and her beautiful mom. &nbsp;In this family the blue eye gene is definitely dominant.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SvTvIihIoXI/AAAAAAAABbQ/NaLXL95BCLI/s1600-h/s2.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SvTvIihIoXI/AAAAAAAABbQ/NaLXL95BCLI/s640/s2.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SvTvFuF4PiI/AAAAAAAABbA/9P5QyWicIus/s640/s4.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Kim's parents were celebrating their 30th wedding anniversary the weekend of our shoot, and you would have thought they were newlyweds. &nbsp;After 30 years they're still very much in love. <br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SvTvHJVCsqI/AAAAAAAABbI/t6z2j6NmuKI/s1600-h/s3.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; text-align: center;">Seriously why did I get these boring brown eyes I want these eyes! &nbsp;Gorgeous.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SvTvE7y1DwI/AAAAAAAABa4/7wgB0n4qv1g/s1600-h/s5.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SvTvCnq1pBI/AAAAAAAABaw/qlDvrS6rQIc/s1600-h/s6.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SvTvCnq1pBI/AAAAAAAABaw/qlDvrS6rQIc/s640/s6.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; 	<item>
		<title>Maternity Pictures</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/136</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 09 Nov 2009 01:40:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/136</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;">Last month I did so many colorful family shoots in the beautiful fall colors that it was a breath of fresh air to be back in the studio this week. &nbsp;I love being outside, but I have a lot less control of the light and in photography light is everything. &nbsp;These past few weeks &nbsp;I've been doing bellies, and beautiful babies! <br /></div><div style="text-align: center;">Speaking of bellies this is Willam and Jennifer, and they have one beautiful belly!<br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SvdurNePY7I/AAAAAAAABbg/aGwm6-25giM/s1600-h/j1.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SvdurNePY7I/AAAAAAAABbg/aGwm6-25giM/s640/j1.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">I had so much fun taking their pictures, and even more fun watching William watch Jennifer. &nbsp;William wasn't the key player in the shoot so a lot of the time he would just sit down somewhere off set and stare at Jenn. &nbsp;Granted she wasn't always fully clothed, but it was obvious he thought she was gorgeous.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SvdusFknNVI/AAAAAAAABbo/PYabbNefKbA/s1600-h/j2.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SvdusFknNVI/AAAAAAAABbo/PYabbNefKbA/s640/j2.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">William you might have to come back sometime for your shoot. &nbsp;Great camera face here!<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SvdutS1p5mI/AAAAAAAABb4/_ybOJXfTE8g/s1600-h/j4.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SvdutS1p5mI/AAAAAAAABb4/_ybOJXfTE8g/s640/j4.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SvduswcV-nI/AAAAAAAABbw/jGggy84mrq8/s1600-h/j3.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SvduswcV-nI/AAAAAAAABbw/jGggy84mrq8/s640/j3.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">They were up for anything, and had a great attitude the whole time. &nbsp;As a result we got some amazing pictures. &nbsp;A lot of which I didn't share on the blog because they are so intimate. &nbsp;I love love love doing maternity pics, some of my most artistic shots come from these shoots.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Svduuw0sp_I/AAAAAAAABcA/TO0epTcBA7g/s1600-h/j5.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Svduuw0sp_I/AAAAAAAABcA/TO0epTcBA7g/s640/j5.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;">Thank you Jennifer, and William for allowing me to be a part of such a substantial moment in your life together. &nbsp;Thank you Brandi for finding me and getting the gift certificate for Jennifer. <br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Dog Photography</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/137</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 10 Nov 2009 03:49:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/137</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;">Check out these beautiful puppies!!! &nbsp;This is Maverick, Icy, and Debbie. &nbsp;She's the beautiful person in the middle of these two gentle giants.<br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SvjfkABOI7I/AAAAAAAABcw/ExmUS9Aak_k/s1600-h/d6.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SvjfkABOI7I/AAAAAAAABcw/ExmUS9Aak_k/s640/d6.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">There is only one thing harder to photograph than 2 year olds...dogs. &nbsp;Big dogs! &nbsp;We had a great time chasing these big goofy babies around the studio. &nbsp;But they were sooo excited to have their picture taken, anytime we called their names they hopped up and ran over with their little stub tails wiggling back and forth like crazy. &nbsp;Debbie was on the floor wrestling most of the time, and laughing the whole time. &nbsp;By the time we were done she had her very own fur coat.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Below is momma Icy. &nbsp;Her favorite thing to do is sit in people's laps.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SvjfdqqZuaI/AAAAAAAABcI/DuJaHeehoZc/s1600-h/d1.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SvjfdqqZuaI/AAAAAAAABcI/DuJaHeehoZc/s640/d1.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">This is her big goofy son Maverick. &nbsp;His favorite thing to do is give big slobbery kisses. &nbsp;Just one lick and you need a towel. &nbsp;He was definitely the ham in the studio, and Icy was all about giving him the stage.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SvjfhAoUQzI/AAAAAAAABcY/xRxXz7cWF_Q/s1600-h/d3.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; 	<item>
		<title>More KIDS!</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/138</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 12 Nov 2009 03:43:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/138</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[I am so far behind on blogs! I want to start this blog with I'm sorry for those of you looking forward to seeing your pics up here, and I promise I'm working on it. For those of you getting tired of looking at kids, I'll work on that too. Maybe Friday I'll grab my carmera and go outside for a bit, and see what I can see.

Thank you all for continuing to come back to the blog. love your support, and really appreciate it. Below are some pics of some outstanding kids.

<img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SvuC2dyKaDI/AAAAAAAABdA/IdoX7D_F3qY/s640/de1.jpg" />

Look at the muscles.

<img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SvuC4bTKVcI/AAAAAAAABdI/fG9zt5TF1sg/s640/de2.jpg" />

This little lady has to be tough with 2 older brothers. Believe it or not, she's just a 3 year old, but acts like she's 13. What an old soul.

<img border="0" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SvuC5VZr0xI/AAAAAAAABdQ/MU5Bf2wHZUY/s640/de3.jpg" />

We had a great shoot and it was really hard to pick which pics to share. Thanks you guys for being awesome! I can't wait to take your pictures next time!

<img border="0" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SvuC6dU9QaI/AAAAAAAABdY/VwyKOsiVXzQ/s640/de4.jpg" />]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Cindy and Stuart</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/139</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 16 Nov 2009 02:43:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/139</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SwC2pkyAGXI/AAAAAAAABdg/Dp2A0-nr_-w/s1600/c1.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SwC2pkyAGXI/AAAAAAAABdg/Dp2A0-nr_-w/s640/c1.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Oh boy, picking pics to share was really tough with this couple. &nbsp;I had the best time taking their pictures, they were all about having fun, and those of you that know me, know that I'm always all about having fun. &nbsp;Let me tell you a little bit about Cindy and Stuart.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SwC2qkpAZXI/AAAAAAAABdo/KDL42xgwwm8/s1600/c2.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SwC2qkpAZXI/AAAAAAAABdo/KDL42xgwwm8/s640/c2.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Stuart and Cindy married for love, while planning their wedding they decided waiting wasn't worth it and threw the wedding plans out the window to get married in a courthouse. &nbsp; Their passion for each other is so big it filled the studio. &nbsp;They are about to have one lucky little baby.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SwC2vJcoaPI/AAAAAAAABeI/8X8O6OcMKws/s1600/c6.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SwC2vJcoaPI/AAAAAAAABeI/8X8O6OcMKws/s640/c6.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Cindy has a gorgeous soul, pure and sincere. &nbsp;I love this picture of her.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SwC2wOMF9tI/AAAAAAAABeQ/Naz5NCdQR9o/s1600/c7.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SwC2wOMF9tI/AAAAAAAABeQ/Naz5NCdQR9o/s640/c7.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Believe it or not she can still cross her legs, a feat not many women 9 months pregnant can accomplish. &nbsp;This picture is simple and elegant.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SwC2r2WvfSI/AAAAAAAABdw/Bm-OC3fKRqc/s1600/c3.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SwC2r2WvfSI/AAAAAAAABdw/Bm-OC3fKRqc/s640/c3.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">They are waiting to find out if they're having a little boy or a little girl. &nbsp;I think that's so cool. &nbsp;Jon and I always said we would be surprised when we have kids, but now I don't know. &nbsp;Yellow and green are not my favorite colors. &nbsp;Either way I'm so excited to find out!<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SwC5jRT53pI/AAAAAAAABeg/0IoepH0Xwwk/s1600/c9.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SwC5jRT53pI/AAAAAAAABeg/0IoepH0Xwwk/s640/c9.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SwC2s84kcpI/AAAAAAAABd4/lkBgGqwB88k/s1600/c4.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SwC2s84kcpI/AAAAAAAABd4/lkBgGqwB88k/s640/c4.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SwC3YmDSjXI/AAAAAAAABeY/Ao3Ll3kX5yE/s1600/c8.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SwC3YmDSjXI/AAAAAAAABeY/Ao3Ll3kX5yE/s640/c8.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Stuart and Cindy, thank you for the experience of taking your pictures! &nbsp;I had so much fun, and I can't wait to be there when little mystery baby is born! &nbsp;Your love for eachother is going to make parenting a breeze...you're going to be amazing.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SwC2uIY8g7I/AAAAAAAABeA/IuUXGnlNWG0/s1600/c5.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SwC2uIY8g7I/AAAAAAAABeA/IuUXGnlNWG0/s640/c5.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;">PS &nbsp;I think it's a girl!<br /></div>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>My beautiful family!</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/140</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 20 Nov 2009 02:44:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/140</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SwYANskFJhI/AAAAAAAABfg/ekd987iOqP4/s1600/m8.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Remember my new nephew that was born just over a month ago. &nbsp;Well here he is, all cleaned up this time. &nbsp;He is one beautiful boy and I am proud to share some of his pictures with you! &nbsp;Meet Hayes!<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SwYARkhaGWI/AAAAAAAABf4/GK_n_puDtz8/s1600/m11.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SwYARkhaGWI/AAAAAAAABf4/GK_n_puDtz8/s640/m11.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Carter was and still is very much in love with his little baby brother. &nbsp;He is so affectionate it warms my heart just thinking about it.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SwYAOtQ_P7I/AAAAAAAABfo/Vlor6Zu1FxA/s1600/m9.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SwYAKzVnrhI/AAAAAAAABfQ/WeKxDktpQJg/s640/m6.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">This picture reminds me of the babies we had when we were kids. &nbsp;They were so realistic looking.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SwYAJ8H_61I/AAAAAAAABfI/_SpxHgtpeeU/s1600/m5.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; 		<title>The Best Christmas Present EVER!</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/141</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 24 Nov 2009 23:24:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/141</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[This year give the gift that keeps on giving! &nbsp;Haha, just kidding, but really you can get gift certificates from me of any amount. &nbsp;Just drop me an email with the amount and the name of the lucky person and I'll drop it in the mail for you. &nbsp; Remember stuff is just stuff, but pictures last forever! &nbsp;I hope everyone has a wonderful Thanksgiving. &nbsp;I absolutely love this holiday and can't wait to spend it with my family. &nbsp;I also plan on catching up on blogs so check back regularly. &nbsp;Happy Holidays!<br /><br /><br />Here is the front...<br /><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Swxq1tCwJbI/AAAAAAAABgA/xYDjK7csBe8/s1600/giftcard_front.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Swxq1tCwJbI/AAAAAAAABgA/xYDjK7csBe8/s640/giftcard_front.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: left;">and the back...<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Swxq3F1fNhI/AAAAAAAABgI/SCIsa54m_LA/s1600/giftcard_back.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Swxq3F1fNhI/AAAAAAAABgI/SCIsa54m_LA/s640/giftcard_back.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Forget black Friday this is way easier!<br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>The Smead Family</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/142</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 30 Nov 2009 02:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/142</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">The following pictures are of the beautiful Smead family. &nbsp;With 8 adults and 6 kids Jon and I had our hads full capturing this very important family shot. &nbsp;I told Mary (Mama Smead) &nbsp;that she needed to throw a couple dogs in there just to make it exciting. Speaking of excited, we were really excited when we got everyone looking at the camera for this shot, but I will tell you we had to bring out our secret weapon. &nbsp;Little Layla! (our little 7 pound rat terrier) She was busy dancing on my head, while I snapped away. <br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxMje78SbnI/AAAAAAAABiQ/YiKkV_vpg88/s1600/sm9.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxMje78SbnI/AAAAAAAABiQ/YiKkV_vpg88/s640/sm9.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">A lot of people want pictures of their kids smiling, but I love it when the kids just look like themselves. &nbsp;I'm sure the parents are pretty familiar with these looks. &nbsp;Pretty priceless if you ask me. &nbsp;What beautiful girls.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxMiqKhaGXI/AAAAAAAABgQ/HH9zLThoO_g/s1600/sm1.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxMiqKhaGXI/AAAAAAAABgQ/HH9zLThoO_g/s640/sm1.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">I couldn't resist posting this picture, I love it when mother and daughter look so much alike.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxMirHSt2TI/AAAAAAAABgY/eY_bqVhA_to/s1600/sm2.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxMirHSt2TI/AAAAAAAABgY/eY_bqVhA_to/s640/sm2.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Mary and I were talking about her awesome family after the shoot and she said "you know sometimes I stop and think this all started with the two of us". &nbsp;Mary you are so lucky to get to live with the joy of knowing you were responsible for bringing so much joy into the world!<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxMisb8E1nI/AAAAAAAABgg/LAPxjkmeUsY/s1600/sm3.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxMisb8E1nI/AAAAAAAABgg/LAPxjkmeUsY/s640/sm3.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Oh boy I'm a sucker for big brown eyes! &nbsp;This picture is stunning and we were really lucky to capture this little guy in his element. &nbsp;My light is actually turned away from my paper backdrop toward the couch in my studio. &nbsp;He was being shy and I was being flexible, and man I'm so glad we did, this picture is timeless! &nbsp;Pure perfection!<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxMivmrsIcI/AAAAAAAABg4/8Szemuncbw8/s1600/sm6.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxMivmrsIcI/AAAAAAAABg4/8Szemuncbw8/s640/sm6.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxMjbNWjJ3I/AAAAAAAABh4/t0WUlOUI-FM/s1600/sm4.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxMjbNWjJ3I/AAAAAAAABh4/t0WUlOUI-FM/s640/sm4.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">I'm experimenting with some photoshop in my spare time...haha! &nbsp;Any and all feedback would be much appreciated! &nbsp;I thought I couldn't go wrong with such a handsome couple.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxMjcdX0DVI/AAAAAAAABiA/cmaRYLznSfs/s1600/sm7.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxMjcdX0DVI/AAAAAAAABiA/cmaRYLznSfs/s640/sm7.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxMjfkCu0vI/AAAAAAAABiY/jm1fPfFMhGs/s1600/sm10.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxMjfkCu0vI/AAAAAAAABiY/jm1fPfFMhGs/s640/sm10.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxMjgRmzLSI/AAAAAAAABig/H8eUO93W1BY/s1600/sm11.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxMjgRmzLSI/AAAAAAAABig/H8eUO93W1BY/s640/sm11.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxMjeEMBA4I/AAAAAAAABiI/ga-poPCiZzY/s1600/sm8.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxMjeEMBA4I/AAAAAAAABiI/ga-poPCiZzY/s640/sm8.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">More photoshop, however the web doesn't do it justice, her eyes are tack sharp, everything else is a gooey mess of blurred pixels! &nbsp;Yum Yum!<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxMjZLy3S2I/AAAAAAAABho/iEZVDZgoEvw/s1600/sm5.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxMjZLy3S2I/AAAAAAAABho/iEZVDZgoEvw/s640/sm5.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Thank you Smead's for your patience. &nbsp;I had a lot of fun taking your pictures. &nbsp;I hope I can work with your kids again in the future, &nbsp;maybe one on one next time. <br /></div><br /><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Amber and Sean</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/144</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 04 Dec 2009 02:23:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/144</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;">Wow! &nbsp;Words can't describe how much I love these pics and how much I loved taking them. &nbsp;This is Amber and Sean and they are getting married!!!!!! &nbsp;Before I tell you all about this awesome couple let me tell you about my wedding photography. &nbsp;I&nbsp;love&nbsp;love&nbsp;love&nbsp;taking&nbsp;pictures&nbsp;of&nbsp;weddings,&nbsp;it's&nbsp;when&nbsp;I'm&nbsp;most&nbsp;creative,&nbsp;not&nbsp;to&nbsp;mention&nbsp;I&nbsp;love&nbsp;seeing&nbsp;people&nbsp;happy. &nbsp;I&nbsp;only&nbsp;like&nbsp;to&nbsp;take&nbsp;on&nbsp;about&nbsp;9&nbsp;weddings&nbsp;a&nbsp;year&nbsp;which&nbsp;allows&nbsp;me&nbsp;to&nbsp;work&nbsp;with&nbsp;the&nbsp;best&nbsp;couples&nbsp;like&nbsp;this&nbsp;couple&nbsp;below.<br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">For the following pictures we went to Swope park golf course, there is this interesting monument called the Swope Memorial. &nbsp;Hmmm didn't even know it existed until Amber told me about it. &nbsp;As it turns out it's a great spot for engagment pictures.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Amber is super ticklish on her neck, Sean wasn't afraid to take advantage any chance he got.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxhqgY4lG8I/AAAAAAAABmM/GGtpVu3PZRE/s1600-h/a2.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; text-align: center;">I love this picture because it is so them. &nbsp;Sean is doing his reflection pose and Amber is thinking he is a total goober. <br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxhqeLxAurI/AAAAAAAABl8/r3pSBFWA6u4/s1600-h/a4.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxhqeLxAurI/AAAAAAAABl8/r3pSBFWA6u4/s640/a4.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxhqcggWIdI/AAAAAAAABl0/y_p2bWf3D6g/s1600-h/a5.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxhqcggWIdI/AAAAAAAABl0/y_p2bWf3D6g/s640/a5.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;">Sean and Amber I had so much fun taking your pictures, I can hardly wait for June. &nbsp;I feel so lucky to be a part of your big day. &nbsp;We are going to get some gorgeous pictures and not because of the setting, the weather, the church, flowers or even lighting. &nbsp;We're going to get great pictures because of you! &nbsp;Your love will fill the frame! &nbsp;Ok someone give me some wine to go with my cheese. &nbsp;:)<br /></div>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Amanda</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/145</link>
		<pubDate>Sun, 06 Dec 2009 20:58:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/145</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;">I want to take a second to thank the person responsible for the maternity picture trend. &nbsp;I love love love taking pictures of beautiful pregnant women. &nbsp;There is something about their energy that makes for amazing pictures. &nbsp;The following pictures are of Amanda, a 3rd time mom, and the owner of one beautiful belly. &nbsp;The picture below surprised me with delight. &nbsp;I think it looks like old art. &nbsp;Jon and I were trying to figure out which artist, but it's been awhile since we've had art history. &nbsp;If you have an opinion please help me.<br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxwXWa5ncBI/AAAAAAAABmc/cHqiRmbGiXo/s1600-h/dm9.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxwXWa5ncBI/AAAAAAAABmc/cHqiRmbGiXo/s640/dm9.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Barely enough room for all those hands big and small.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxwXcFQrgGI/AAAAAAAABnE/baSCQ98_lZY/s1600-h/dm4.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxwXcFQrgGI/AAAAAAAABnE/baSCQ98_lZY/s640/dm4.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">This is Zander and Tatum. &nbsp;As you can see they both take after their daddy. &nbsp;Aren't they adorable. &nbsp;I have about 20 similar pics they didn't mind having their picture taken at all. &nbsp;I had a hard time picking.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxwXbP3uNGI/AAAAAAAABm8/XNZEp5Mpai8/s1600-h/dm5.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxwXbP3uNGI/AAAAAAAABm8/XNZEp5Mpai8/s640/dm5.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">After taking this picture little Zander walked over and tried to take Damon's place. &nbsp;He said, "mommy I want to make a heart on your belly". &nbsp;So cute.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxwXdKr91-I/AAAAAAAABnM/hwPIBG_-3cE/s1600-h/dm3.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxwXdKr91-I/AAAAAAAABnM/hwPIBG_-3cE/s640/dm3.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">I've known Damon since high school, and I'm so happy to see him happy. &nbsp;He and Amanda make a great team, and their kids really reflect that. &nbsp;I can't wait to meet this new little guy.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxwXZLjZt4I/AAAAAAAABm0/phhr3W31_Xw/s1600-h/dm6.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxwXZLjZt4I/AAAAAAAABm0/phhr3W31_Xw/s640/dm6.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxwXZLjZt4I/AAAAAAAABm0/phhr3W31_Xw/s1600-h/dm6.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"></a><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SxwXfQ7WjCI/AAAAAAAABnc/YcdPlB_ZeiQ/s1600-h/dm1.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; 		<title>Natalie and Emily</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/146</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 08 Dec 2009 03:34:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/146</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Perfection!<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sx2-CmovCTI/AAAAAAAABn0/wJ_fTtLX_RI/s1600-h/co3.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">These two are regulars on the blog. &nbsp;They are adorable, animated, and always a lot of fun. &nbsp;Meet Emily and Natalie. &nbsp;The picture below is Natalie and she was perfect for the whole shoot. &nbsp;It's amazing how fast these little ones grow up. &nbsp;Just a year ago she was running around the studio doing everything we said not to do, but not this time. &nbsp;There were way to many pics to choose from. &nbsp;This one pulled me. &nbsp;It looks like one of those sad portraits from the 1800's.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sx2-Ap14YVI/AAAAAAAABnk/14KDvxWYGH4/s1600-h/co5.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sx2-Ap14YVI/AAAAAAAABnk/14KDvxWYGH4/s640/co5.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">And then Emily... she's happy and ready for anything and everything. <br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sx2-EjtI17I/AAAAAAAABoE/yMgYi46wCu0/s1600-h/co1.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sx2-EjtI17I/AAAAAAAABoE/yMgYi46wCu0/s640/co1.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Both girls seem to love eachother. &nbsp;I stole this one from a magazine, I love the expression on Natalie's face. &nbsp;Beautiful.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sx2-BuOGvFI/AAAAAAAABns/rwwet-U-tu0/s1600-h/co4.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sx2-BuOGvFI/AAAAAAAABns/rwwet-U-tu0/s640/co4.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">This picture was taken while we were trying to corral Emily. &nbsp;She's entering the all over phase. &nbsp;Natalie was a big help and very patient with her 1 year old sister. &nbsp;I've loved watching these girls grow up, and can't wait to see what the future holds. <br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sx2-Dvn2IxI/AAAAAAAABn8/DktB6RfQozY/s1600-h/co2.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/Sx2-Dvn2IxI/AAAAAAAABn8/DktB6RfQozY/s640/co2.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; 		<title>Baby Izzie!</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/147</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 14 Dec 2009 02:30:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/147</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SyWhmDLj4_I/AAAAAAAABog/xt6VqhxMB-c/s1600-h/iz1.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; text-align: center;">This is baby Izzie! &nbsp;A Thanksgiving baby, well close enough just after. &nbsp;She is one of the most perfect new newborns I have ever seen. &nbsp;Flawless skin, loads of hair, and a beuatiful round face. &nbsp;She also had some of the longest toes and fingers I've ever seen. &nbsp;She got those from her daddy Brad.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">When I first saw Izzie I couldn't help thinking that she looks just like her momma. &nbsp;I can't wait to watch her grow and change.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SyWhne-tIoI/AAAAAAAABoo/Kw7eUz57tI0/s1600-h/iz2.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SyWhne-tIoI/AAAAAAAABoo/Kw7eUz57tI0/s640/iz2.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; 		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">This blog post makes me smile because these pictures showcase some of the most beautiful eyes I have ever taken. &nbsp;My photography is constantly evolving and in this set of photos you can see the evolution in the eyes. &nbsp;First let me tell you about this wonderful family. <br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Below is Hudson and he was a very easy 2 year old to photograph. &nbsp;His mom Meghan found me on the internet and scheduled a shoot. &nbsp;When she told me her last name was Duff I immediately thought of Justin Duff an old friend from junior high. &nbsp;I kept forgetting to ask her until she was on her way to my house. &nbsp;As it turns out she is married to Justin. &nbsp;It was so much fun catching up with Justin and telling Meghan old Justin stories. &nbsp;I'm so happy they found me.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both;
