	<item>
		<title>Kalea and Lincoln</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/150</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 22 Dec 2009 02:39:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/150</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;">When I started taking pictures of bellies, babies, and families I didn't realize how close to families I would get. &nbsp;I started taking pictures of these babies when little Lincoln was a newborn, and his big brother was barely walking, now a few years later the boys have a baby sister who is growing up way too fast! &nbsp;I don't really realize how much time has gone by until I watch my clients grow up. &nbsp;It's actually one of the best parts of my job.<br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;">Below is Kalea. &nbsp;I LOVE this picture for the teeth!<br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SzAtrYxf1oI/AAAAAAAABsg/luKCJ1eNCME/s1600-h/herring5.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SzAtrYxf1oI/AAAAAAAABsg/luKCJ1eNCME/s640/herring5.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">With 3 kids under the age of 4 Michelle has her hands full, but somehow she always arrives at my studio with a big smile on her face. &nbsp;She also is very realistic about the shoot knowing we're going to get what we're going to get so, on this particular day she didn't even want to attempt a picture of all 3. &nbsp;So we sat them down one at a time and had SUCH good luck. &nbsp; Kalea was a perma-grin. &nbsp;LOVE IT!<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SzAtsS9jjLI/AAAAAAAABso/-qVwVIrJ1Zo/s1600-h/herring7.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SzAtsS9jjLI/AAAAAAAABso/-qVwVIrJ1Zo/s640/herring7.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">This is Lincoln and he too was a happy little camper, but all of these smiles belong to his much loved Grandama! &nbsp;She was behind me holding Kalea and saying BAM BAM BAM! &nbsp;It was awesome and he loved it. &nbsp;I'm really considering hiring her full time.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SzAtpGG-5eI/AAAAAAAABsQ/6I0uBwehaAI/s1600-h/herring3.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SzAtpGG-5eI/AAAAAAAABsQ/6I0uBwehaAI/s640/herring3.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">I love the faces that aren't smiles. &nbsp;This is what Lincoln looks like.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Awww, I can't believe he's this big.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SzAtqU2a93I/AAAAAAAABsY/SOWSWsVEFio/s1600-h/herring4.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SzAtqU2a93I/AAAAAAAABsY/SOWSWsVEFio/s640/herring4.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">After having such success with the other two we were pumped and ready to finish up with the easiest, or so we thought. &nbsp;Vance is a happy kid and old enough to pretty much do what we want, or so we thought. &nbsp;Haha he did not want to smile for us. &nbsp;The picture below says it all. &nbsp;Finally Grandma pulled through yet again, and I was quick to capture this one gift.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SzAtoAmFvuI/AAAAAAAABsI/zz71XDLsvz8/s1600-h/herring2.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SzAtoAmFvuI/AAAAAAAABsI/zz71XDLsvz8/s640/herring2.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">We were trying everything at this point, laughing,&nbsp;bribing,&nbsp;he&nbsp;wasn't&nbsp;having&nbsp;it,&nbsp;but&nbsp;I&nbsp;love&nbsp;this&nbsp;picture.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SzAtnPcSK4I/AAAAAAAABsA/D0bTcfZKNiE/s1600-h/herring1.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/SzAtnPcSK4I/AAAAAAAABsA/D0bTcfZKNiE/s640/herring1.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;">Michelle I have really enjoyed working with your kids, and watching them grow. <br /></div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>My Goals for 2010!</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/152</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 04 Jan 2010 01:22:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/152</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[I can't believe yet another year has flown by, and when I look back I was really busy and some amazing things happened, but I didn't really do what I want to do.   You see I always start a new year with fresh ideas, a big plate of ambition and the goal of being more organized in my bookwork.  Haha, the bookwork never happens.  Usually about mid February I realize I haven't worked on any of my goals, life or what we call life, gets in the way.  This year to make sure my goals become achievements I want to say my goals out loud, not an easy feat because failure is always lming in the corner glaring at me.  Well not anymore I'm kicking those thoughts to the curb, and I'm going to feel the fear and do it anyway!

Deep Breath...here goes...

1. Grow my business, I mean really grow my business.  That means following up with clients, asking them for referrals, and being brave enough to put myself out there. Part of this will come from being a part of a business networking group.

2. Have my first gallery opening!  There are really 2 sets of photos I want to have gallery openings for.  The first Indonesia, and the second women, beautiful women, normal women.  You get the idea.  Photography is my passion, my art and I need to make that form of my expression a priority.

3. Have over 150 shoots.

4. Run a photography workshop, I want to share what I know with others, and hopefully learn something too.

5. Some small stuff, shopping cart for proof page, new blog, new pics on website (almost done with that one YES), you get the idea, for most of this stuff I need Jon's help.

6. Get 1,000 fans on my facebook page.  I'm not sure if this directly results in new clients, but it can't hurt.  Just 500 to go.  Yikes that's a lot!  Please suggest my page to friends, that would be awesome, and help a lot!

7. I have 2 photography book ideas, but I have no idea where to start.  This year I'm going to start and see what happens.

8. Finally I want to start a charity organization that takes pictures of kids in poverty.  I've seen those kids, I've worked with those families and those kids deserve good pictures too!

Ok that's a lot, and it might have to be a 5 year plan, but I've always had these goals in my head. It's time I put them into action.  It's just when I say them to the world, it's different, it's real, it's scary. I hope the universe rewards my bravery.  If you've made it this far, you've just learned a little bit about me that I don't often share.  This year I'm going to buck up and be who I want to be!!!! Get ready world, here I come.]]></content:encoded>

		<wp:post_name>my-scary-2010-goals</wp:post_name>

		<wp:comment>
			<wp:comment_id>86</wp:comment_id>
			<wp:comment_author><![CDATA[Smitty]]></wp:comment_author>
			<wp:comment_author_email></wp:comment_author_email>
			<wp:comment_author_url></wp:comment_author_url>
			<wp:comment_author_IP></wp:comment_author_IP>
			<wp:comment_date>2010-01-04 15:03:16</wp:comment_date>
			<wp:comment_date_gmt>2010-01-04 21:03:16</wp:comment_date_gmt>
			<wp:comment_content><![CDATA[Baby steps Al!!!  You have wonderful goals and they all do not have to be done by next month.  Take a little bit time each week to work on the one you are most enthusiastic about.  Then next week (or couple of weeks) work on another.  Whatever time period works for you.  Also, Luis Garcia (my sister&#39;s boyfriend) has a small gallery he uses at first Friday&#39;s, he would be a wonderful network contact if you&#39;d like introductions.]]></wp:comment_content>

	<item>
		<title>Homeless Hero</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/153</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 07 Jan 2010 04:52:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/153</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="text-align: center;">The snow continues to fall, the windchill is dropping and the air is dangerously cold. &nbsp;The good news, I'm sitting in my warm house on my warm couch under a big comfy down blanket, with sweats, fuzzy socks and a dog snuggled up near my legs. &nbsp;I'm happy and comfortable, but there are many many people out there tonight suffering. &nbsp;One of those many people is someone I admire. &nbsp;He's a homeless hero.<br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S0Vkjqx466I/AAAAAAAABuA/a_SO8VyCq1o/s1600-h/h3.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S0Vkjqx466I/AAAAAAAABuA/a_SO8VyCq1o/s640/h3.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">There's not much to tell because his life is pretty simple. &nbsp;He loves to read books that he gets at the library, cheezy novels if I remember. &nbsp;He has a small bag of items that keep him comfortable. &nbsp;He told me that he didn't keep much in his bag so when it got stollen it wouldn't matter. &nbsp;Even his most precious belonging, his purple heart.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S0VkidfN3LI/AAAAAAAABt4/mW9HY4edvBk/s1600-h/h2.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S0VkidfN3LI/AAAAAAAABt4/mW9HY4edvBk/s640/h2.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;">While fighting in the Vietnam war he was shot in the arm. &nbsp;One of his fellow soldiers was badly injured in the same combat so he carried him over his shoulder for miles to the nearest camp.<br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S0VkhSvL1GI/AAAAAAAABtw/47tsN94A8nk/s1600-h/h1.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S0VkhSvL1GI/AAAAAAAABtw/47tsN94A8nk/s640/h1.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Now he's homeless, not because he has to be. &nbsp;He has a sister that keeps his purple heart safe at her house. &nbsp;He lives on the streets because he wants to or so he says. &nbsp;He said he still wakes up in the night with bad dreams and he doesn't trust himself around others even in the homeless shelter.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">I have two questions first what has our country done to this man that had such strength, and what can I do to make it better? <br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div>]]></content:encoded>

		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Today I have two things to talk about first of all my NEW portfolio is up and running! &nbsp;There are sooo many pictures, but I just couldn't resist. &nbsp;Check it out. &nbsp;<a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/">www.allisoncarenza.com</a><br /><br />Also I am running a Valentine's day special that I think everyone should get in on. &nbsp;Husbands you can get this for your wives, it's really a gift for yourself. &nbsp;Ladies you can get this for your husbands or boyfriends, it's really a gift for you too because we will have so much fun. &nbsp;From now until February 14th I'm offering my bloggers half off my sitting fee for boudoir photos. &nbsp;Basically for $25 you get an hour of photos taken, a 4x6 to give to hubby or boyfriend, and gorgeous airbrushed magazine quality photos. &nbsp;When else in your life are you going to get airbrushed? &nbsp;Don't get to worried, I love taking these pictures and making women look and feel beautiful. &nbsp;So if you are unsure just call or email and I can help you with any questions you might have. &nbsp;I can't wait to make you or your wife look sexy sexy sexy! &nbsp;For obvious reasons I can't share a lot of pics, but here is one of my favorite ones. &nbsp;It's all in the eyes!<br /><br />Call- 816 830 2127 or email acarenza@gmail.com<br /><br /><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S0dSH4MJ1MI/AAAAAAAABuI/SNLP4m293I0/s1600-h/032.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S0dSH4MJ1MI/AAAAAAAABuI/SNLP4m293I0/s640/032.jpg" /></a><br /></div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Winter Photos</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/155</link>
		<pubDate>Sun, 10 Jan 2010 17:56:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/155</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S0oSGdqs8nI/AAAAAAAABug/HD8_BKdV3mo/s1600-h/winter2.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S0oSGdqs8nI/AAAAAAAABug/HD8_BKdV3mo/s640/winter2.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">I'm excited to share with you some photos I took during this crazy winter. &nbsp;Above is a photo taken at sunset. &nbsp;I love the lines of clouds, I think they are cold too. <br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S0oSKcMr7_I/AAAAAAAABvA/XPPcrv54zJg/s1600-h/winter6.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S0oSKcMr7_I/AAAAAAAABvA/XPPcrv54zJg/s640/winter6.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Beautiful and deep Lucy. &nbsp;She and Layla have been locked up in the house and are going pretty stir crazy. &nbsp;She's looking out at the yard mournfully. &nbsp;They have little paths in our yard where they go to the bathroom. &nbsp;I think they spend all of 3 minutes outside a day.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S0oSHYB6HJI/AAAAAAAABuo/nwTySq9kX9s/s1600-h/winter3.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S0oSHYB6HJI/AAAAAAAABuo/nwTySq9kX9s/s640/winter3.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S0oSJvTrp6I/AAAAAAAABu4/2WUyS8h2zIY/s1600-h/winter5.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S0oSJvTrp6I/AAAAAAAABu4/2WUyS8h2zIY/s640/winter5.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">And then there's Layla. &nbsp;The crazy and loving one. &nbsp;She is much more willing to look into the camera than her sister, but she always has a confused look on her face. &nbsp;She has to wear a winter blanket or she shivers. &nbsp;She spends her days laying in patches of sunlight when she's not chewing on a bone or pestering her sister. &nbsp; Funny fact, she never sits on the ground, she always sits on Lucy. &nbsp;Even in this picture she is straddling Lucy. <br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S0oSMbKt3CI/AAAAAAAABvI/ikN9Ao_utr8/s1600-h/winter7.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S0oSMbKt3CI/AAAAAAAABvI/ikN9Ao_utr8/s640/winter7.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">The above pic was taken at night. &nbsp;It was a bitter night when the clouds lifted and left the full moon to light up the snow. &nbsp;Jon and I had just gotten done watching a movie when I saw this shadow on the snow, I couldn't resist. <br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S0oSEhwgXoI/AAAAAAAABuY/yt14MeT_mp4/s1600-h/winter1.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S0oSEhwgXoI/AAAAAAAABuY/yt14MeT_mp4/s640/winter1.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">I honked my horn in my car to get the geese to fly off. &nbsp;I love love this picture. &nbsp;Even though it's a sunset it reminds me of mornings duck hunting with my dad. &nbsp;You should know I never shot the geese with a gun, then or now.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S0oSITyxHKI/AAAAAAAABuw/v-l0nLyGizU/s1600-h/winter4.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S0oSITyxHKI/AAAAAAAABuw/v-l0nLyGizU/s640/winter4.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;">I hope everyone is enjoying this winter, because it's really going to make us appreciate spring. <br /></div>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Family Portraits</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/158</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 15 Jan 2010 03:29:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/blog/archives/158</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;">Check one on part of goal 5! &nbsp; Jon and I updated my blog design. &nbsp;I'm so excited, I love it. &nbsp;Thank you Jon I love you so much. &nbsp;Now for some pictures of an adorable family. &nbsp;This is Gina and her blonde beauties Katie and Maggie. &nbsp;They were all so very photogenic!<br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S0_eIe4ctKI/AAAAAAAABxg/Y2yEpugG_HU/s1600-h/sch1.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S0_eIe4ctKI/AAAAAAAABxg/Y2yEpugG_HU/s640/sch1.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S0_eKBZekjI/AAAAAAAABxo/X-zGdc63eqI/s640/sch2.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">I have about a dozen pictures of this cutie all with different faces.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S0_eLWMqT1I/AAAAAAAABxw/YIZQVXFu1tA/s1600-h/sch3.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S0_eLWMqT1I/AAAAAAAABxw/YIZQVXFu1tA/s640/sch3.jpg" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">This isn't your typical family picture, but I like it because it's in close, and everyone is looking at someone else. &nbsp;Not to mention Gina and Brian and so relaxed with the girls. &nbsp;Getting your picture taken can be such a stress, but they just let it happen and we got some great pictures!<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; 	<item>
		<title>Chase</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/321</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 27 Jan 2010 01:35:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/321</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;">This is Chase Okerstrom. &nbsp;Believe it or not this is his natural camera face. &nbsp;Perfect!<br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S1-U8U7y58I/AAAAAAAAB0s/_SCINY2PoAY/s1600-h/ok5.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="640" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S1-U8U7y58I/AAAAAAAAB0s/_SCINY2PoAY/s640/ok5.jpg" width="428" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Chase is one of the most polite 5 year olds I've ever met. &nbsp;He did everything and anything I asked of him with an ok. &nbsp;And then when I showed him the pictures he followed up with thank you. &nbsp;WOW!<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S1-U5ilTfCI/AAAAAAAAB0U/lO7zHUtnV2A/s1600-h/ok2.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="428" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S1-U5ilTfCI/AAAAAAAAB0U/lO7zHUtnV2A/s640/ok2.jpg" width="640" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S1-U6XBf1gI/AAAAAAAAB0c/o_nE37bYcEo/s1600-h/ok3.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="640" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S1-U6XBf1gI/AAAAAAAAB0c/o_nE37bYcEo/s640/ok3.jpg" width="428" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">This is Chase with his dad Haakon. &nbsp;I've know Haakon since he was itty bitty, or should I say Haakon has known me since I was itty bitty. &nbsp;You see he was my brother's best friend! &nbsp;I remember many trips to the lake when Haakon and my brother James would allow me to tag along while they wreaked havoc on the woods that surrounded our house. &nbsp;Hours of shooting BB guns off the deck, building forts in the trees and sloshing around in the creek. &nbsp;Good times! &nbsp; It was an honor taking his pictures, Chase is just a mini Haakon with a splash of Jennifer's sass.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S1-U-vRqUXI/AAAAAAAAB08/QT1lkItO5kk/s1600-h/ok7.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="640" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S1-U-vRqUXI/AAAAAAAAB08/QT1lkItO5kk/s640/ok7.jpg" width="428" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S1-U4j4pGRI/AAAAAAAAB0M/qyTUglfgtSo/s1600-h/ok1.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="640" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S1-U4j4pGRI/AAAAAAAAB0M/qyTUglfgtSo/s640/ok1.jpg" width="428" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Jennifer and I went to high school together and she was and still is one of the most lively, fun loving people I know. &nbsp;She has the most beautiful blue eyes, and lucky little Chase got them too.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S1-U9ZsRBRI/AAAAAAAAB00/TRAfKFkYF0k/s1600-h/ok6.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="640" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S1-U9ZsRBRI/AAAAAAAAB00/TRAfKFkYF0k/s640/ok6.jpg" width="428" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">I love this pic! It was not as easy to get as it looks. &nbsp;This little girl was shy shy shy!<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S1-U7WglJPI/AAAAAAAAB0k/n5SVTva_s10/s1600-h/ok4.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="640" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S1-U7WglJPI/AAAAAAAAB0k/n5SVTva_s10/s640/ok4.jpg" width="428" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S1-U__UsqrI/AAAAAAAAB1E/ez9JulvV-G0/s1600-h/ok8.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="428" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S1-U__UsqrI/AAAAAAAAB1E/ez9JulvV-G0/s640/ok8.jpg" width="640" /></a><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;">Thank guys, I look forward to taking more pictures &nbsp;of your fam at your farm this fall!<br /></div>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Baby Hunter</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/322</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 28 Jan 2010 00:14:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/322</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;Get ready, because you are about to look at pictures of an adorable one year old. &nbsp;This series of pictures is all about Hunter experienceing his first of many birthday cakes! &nbsp;I'm going to do my best to describe the emotions/reactions I think were going through his head. &nbsp;I'll say this, Marg, Jon and I were laughing histarically the whole time, so add that as background noise. &nbsp;I hope you enjoy.<br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;">Look at me standing up like a big boy. &nbsp;What are we doing anyway?<br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S2DUDBQvOuI/AAAAAAAAB1U/eNd8ZCP6Rho/s1600-h/hunter1.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="640" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S2DUDBQvOuI/AAAAAAAAB1U/eNd8ZCP6Rho/s640/hunter1.jpg" width="428" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Wha Wha What?! &nbsp;That is colorful, what is it?<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S2DUER6CWII/AAAAAAAAB1c/o6pBAgNea9U/s1600-h/hunter2.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="640" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S2DUER6CWII/AAAAAAAAB1c/o6pBAgNea9U/s640/hunter2.jpg" width="428" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">When in doubt grab it.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S2DUFzE1DII/AAAAAAAAB1k/5DnQ0oyPj64/s1600-h/hunter3.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="640" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S2DUFzE1DII/AAAAAAAAB1k/5DnQ0oyPj64/s640/hunter3.jpg" width="426" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Mom is this ok, because that was gooey.<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S2DUIDetqHI/AAAAAAAAB10/PrN5_-w5tYo/s1600-h/hunter5.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="426" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S2DUIDetqHI/AAAAAAAAB10/PrN5_-w5tYo/s640/hunter5.jpg" width="640" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">You mean it's mine, all mine, ALL RIGHT! &nbsp;Time to make a mess!<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S2DUKbAlb9I/AAAAAAAAB18/AXijc2WN2sc/s1600-h/hunter4.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="640" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S2DUKbAlb9I/AAAAAAAAB18/AXijc2WN2sc/s640/hunter4.jpg" width="428" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Yum!<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S2DUMg3YVzI/AAAAAAAAB2M/_1jRHwIWH6o/s1600-h/hunter7.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="428" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S2DUMg3YVzI/AAAAAAAAB2M/_1jRHwIWH6o/s640/hunter7.jpg" width="640" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">I think I'll have some more of that, in fact I think I'll have a lot more. <br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S2DULadGKjI/AAAAAAAAB2E/FqvszwlfPFc/s1600-h/hunter6.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="640" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S2DULadGKjI/AAAAAAAAB2E/FqvszwlfPFc/s640/hunter6.jpg" width="426" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Look I can be cute with food on my face. &nbsp;Who wants to be my agent?<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S2DUN9mgIUI/AAAAAAAAB2U/5mKdm65wgRM/s1600-h/hunter8.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="426" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S2DUN9mgIUI/AAAAAAAAB2U/5mKdm65wgRM/s640/hunter8.jpg" width="640" /></a><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">What are you guys looking at anyway? &nbsp;Can't a baby enjoy his cake in peace?<br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S2DUO5DrzYI/AAAAAAAAB2c/XuMYv6kyGuY/s1600-h/hunter9.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="640" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S2DUO5DrzYI/AAAAAAAAB2c/XuMYv6kyGuY/s640/hunter9.jpg" width="428" /></a><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;">Hunter you are adorable. &nbsp;It's hard to believe you are such a big boy, it seems like just yesterday we were wrapping you in blankets for newborn pictures. &nbsp;My how time flies. <br /></div>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>A winter special!</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/323</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 03 Feb 2010 01:52:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/323</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S2jVRSy_x_I/AAAAAAAAB2k/M2viNL7q8oc/s1600-h/birthday.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="640" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S2jVRSy_x_I/AAAAAAAAB2k/M2viNL7q8oc/s640/birthday.jpg" width="640" /></a></div><br />I got the depressing news this morning when a little groundhog named<span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px;">&nbsp;Punxsutawney Phil saw his shadow and reported that we had 6 more weeks of winter to look forward to. &nbsp;But it gets worse, much worse as a matter of fact, I can deal with the cold dreary weather, the lack of sun, and the short days, it's the snow that I can't stand, and apparently Gary reported another huge snow storm in the works for later this month. &nbsp;15 more inches. &nbsp;YUCK!</span><br /><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px;">SO to cheer myself up I decided to offer a groundhog special. &nbsp;Come see me in the next 6 weeks and I'll give you a free 12x12 collage like the one above, and you can thank Phil for even though he does not deserve it. &nbsp;Taking pictures makes me happy, and so does this collage! &nbsp;Have a wonderful week everyone!</span></span><br /><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px;"><br /></span></span>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>My Nephews</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/324</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 04 Feb 2010 03:44:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/324</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="text-align: center;">It seems like just weeks ago I was at St. Lukes taking pictures of my adorable new nephew Hayes, but actually it was 3 months ago. &nbsp;It's time for an update of "the boys". &nbsp;Specifically Shannon's boys. &nbsp;Here are a few of my favorites from the shoot.</div><div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div></div><div><div style="text-align: center;">Juddy is the natural in front of the camera. &nbsp;He's been my #1 model since...well&nbsp;since&nbsp;his&nbsp;first&nbsp;breath,&nbsp;literally. &nbsp;On this particular shoot he walked into the studio pulled out his pappy and plopped down on the bench with&nbsp;the&nbsp;most&nbsp;perfect&nbsp;smile&nbsp;on&nbsp;his&nbsp;face.&nbsp;&nbsp;He'll&nbsp;smile&nbsp;all&nbsp;day&nbsp;long&nbsp;for&nbsp;me,&nbsp;it's just&nbsp;keeping&nbsp;his&nbsp;attention&nbsp;that's&nbsp;a&nbsp;challenge.</div><div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div></div><div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S2o_hD81mRI/AAAAAAAAB2s/0dun6PbOMoI/s1600-h/boys1.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="428" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S2o_hD81mRI/AAAAAAAAB2s/0dun6PbOMoI/s640/boys1.jpg" width="640" /></a></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Then there's C who is equally adorable, but tries to give me all the most cheezy smiles. &nbsp;I love him soooo much! &nbsp;Oh and if you can't tell, he's 5! &nbsp;Carter you are growing up way to fast, I just let out a moan thinking about the day when he won't have a collection of superhero costumes that he changes into any chance he gets.</div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S2o_ilitJNI/AAAAAAAAB20/CGp_PucI-mI/s1600-h/boys2.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="428" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S2o_ilitJNI/AAAAAAAAB20/CGp_PucI-mI/s640/boys2.jpg" width="640" /></a></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">Finally the little guy! &nbsp;Hayes is a perfect mix of the two boys. &nbsp;His rolls are growing, his smile is getting more frequent, and his kind and tolerant personality is emerging. &nbsp;I love everything about you!</div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S2o_pnmq2_I/AAAAAAAAB3c/ua3PF19u1a8/s1600-h/boys7.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; 		<title>Valentine&#039;s Day</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/325</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 13 Feb 2010 20:59:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>

		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[I hope everyone is enjoying their weekend. &nbsp;Tomorrow is Valentine's day and I happen to love V day. &nbsp;I know it's cheezy and overdone, but I like being reminded to slow down and look at the people in my life that I love. &nbsp;I have a lot of people in my life that I love. &nbsp;I hope all of you are have a great Valentine's day! &nbsp;I love you!<br /><br />Here are some pics to make you smile. &nbsp;This is Michelle and Maguire. &nbsp;She decided to come take a few quick pics for her husband for Valentine's day. &nbsp;I think pictures are the perfect gift, almost as perfect as little Maguire. &nbsp;Check it out!<br /><br /><div class="separator" style="clear: both; 		<title>Baby Kenley</title>

		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;&nbsp;You remember that beautiful belly with the big "?" we saw a few months ago, well that belly turned into a beautiful baby girl. &nbsp;Baby Kenley is a doll and doing so well! &nbsp;Here are a few pictures from her newborn photo session.</div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; 	<item>
		<title>Cousins</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/327</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 17 Feb 2010 04:13:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/327</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="text-align: center;">I was so fortunate to grow up with cousins. &nbsp;They were a huge part of my childhood, &nbsp;and I am still so close to them. &nbsp;There were 8 of us and we were all around the same age, it was great! &nbsp;We spent hours in Marnie and Papa's basement boxing, playing hide and go seek, and bumper pool. &nbsp; In the summer we spent our time in their pool or camping in the backyard. My cousins were like brothers and sisters and this is definitely the case in the following family. These kids love and adore eachother. &nbsp;I just know they will be close forever. &nbsp; I hope you enjoy!</div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S3trVDptFoI/AAAAAAAAB5U/6p4am6IdnMY/s1600-h/st1.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="428" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S3trVDptFoI/AAAAAAAAB5U/6p4am6IdnMY/s640/st1.jpg" width="640" /></a></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S3trYY9Xu-I/AAAAAAAAB5s/GGiCx4YJiig/s1600-h/st2.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; 		<title>Family Portraits</title>

		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;">This week is all about families! &nbsp;Earlier this week I showed you a family of close cousins, well today here is a family of close siblings. &nbsp;So close! &nbsp;I had a blast taking their pictures. &nbsp;I would have taken a whole lot more, but Jana is smart and didn't want too many to pick from. &nbsp;It was hard enough. &nbsp;Here a just a few of my favorites. &nbsp;Easton is the only other girl in the family and she and her mom have the most amazing red hair. &nbsp;LOVE IT!</div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; 		<title>Baby Photo Contest</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/329</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 20 Feb 2010 19:39:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/329</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="text-align: center;">I am having a baby photo contest on my facebook page! &nbsp;It's easy just post a picture of your favorite little person &nbsp;and get all of your friends to vote for it by leaving a comment or saying they like it. &nbsp;Then the person with the most votes wins a free sitting fee with me and an 11x14 wall art print. &nbsp;There will be other winners as well. &nbsp;I hope you have some cute pictures because I want to see some cute kids. &nbsp;Just click on the link on the right to enter. &nbsp;</div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><div style="text-align: center;">Here's a picture to get you thinking. &nbsp;This is Chloe, I took her pics last weekend. &nbsp;Look for more pics of her to come. &nbsp;I'm just having a very hard time picking. &nbsp;</div><br /><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S4A6EZr72tI/AAAAAAAAB6s/4fHG3BH9CMY/s1600-h/028.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="426" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_xPvpqP-jL3A/S4A6EZr72tI/AAAAAAAAB6s/4fHG3BH9CMY/s640/028.jpg" width="640" /></a></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>New and Improved Blog!</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/365</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 02 Mar 2010 04:41:57 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/?p=365</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">This is my first post on my brand new blog! I have to admit I don't really like learning yet another program, but it's like a new phone after awhile it feels like home. The following pictures are of two of the most beautiful babies ever! Below is Easton, and I know this is a severe crop, but I love it because it's all about the eyes. Please enjoy viewing the photos and feel free to leave a comment, I would love your feedback!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-374" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/365/el1-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-374" title="el1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/el11.jpg" alt="" width="868" height="579" /></a>

<a style="text-decoration: none;" rel="attachment wp-att-373" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/365/el2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-373" title="el2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/el2.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Just playing with his belly button!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-369" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/365/el6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-369" title="el6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/el6.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">He's like seriously guys, enough is enough!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-368" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/365/el7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-368" title="el7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/el7.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is a picture of Cole. Cole was such a great 5 year old. He was willing to do everything I asked and then some. I'm not really sure what he's doing here, but I'm really sure it's pretty cute. If you look closely at Cole's eyes he's got two different colors in there. I might have to post some more of him later so you can get a close up. What a great kid!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-371" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/365/el4">
<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-371" title="el4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/el4.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">And then there is Andrea with her boys. I love this pic, Cole is so perfect, and Easton is so whatever I'm a baby and cute what else do you want.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-372" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/365/el3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-372" title="el3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/el3.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Ok this picture is my favorite. Andrea and I put the boys in the chair and told them to look cute when I went to get my camera I realized Cole had his finger over his nose. When we asked what's up, he told us "he's stinky" with a big grin. LOVE IT!!! Of course we told him it was fine and got the shot before changing Easton. The others were more ideal, but I like this one more because it shows just how tolerant Easton is.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-370" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/365/el5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-370" title="el5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/el5.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">And then there is some momma love. Andrea is such a loving mommy. I can tell her boys are her life, and she loves everything about them, even whey they're stinky because my goodness most of the time they look like this. Who can resist this face?</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-367" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/365/el8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-367" title="el8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/el8.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Andrea thank you so much for picking me to capture your boys and all their faces. I had so much fun and I look forward many more shoots.</p>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Meet Oscar</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/405</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 04 Mar 2010 04:26:05 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/?p=405</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">This is Oscar and he is absolutely adorable.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-395" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/405/oscar1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-395" title="oscar1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/oscar1.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">With teeny tiny feet...</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-396" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/405/oscar10"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-396" title="oscar10" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/oscar10.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">and teeny tiny hands...</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-398" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/405/oscar8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-398" title="oscar8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/oscar8.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">and amazing parents that love him with their whole hearts.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-403" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/405/oscar3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-403" title="oscar3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/oscar3.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is Oscar and he is a wonderful baby!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-402" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/405/oscar4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-402" title="oscar4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/oscar4.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Kristin and Dave thank you so much for letting me capture Oscar at his very best. He is one beautiful boy!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>

	<item>
		<title>Chloe&#039;s First Birthday</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/421</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 08 Mar 2010 16:03:45 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/?p=421</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">Meet Chloe! She was the winner of my first baby photo contest on facebook. There were over 50 entries and 500 votes. Chloe was the adorable winner.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Attached is the picture that she won with. <a href="http://www.facebook.com/photo.php?pid=38674872&amp;o=all&amp;op=1&amp;view=all&amp;subj=88773417960&amp;aid=-1&amp;id=34304858" target="_blank">http://www.facebook.com/photo.php?pid=38674872&amp;o=all&amp;op=1&amp;view=all&amp;subj=88773417960&amp;aid=-1&amp;id=34304858</a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">She won a free sitting and 11x14 wall art print!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-422" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/421/chloe9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-422" title="chloe9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/chloe9.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Chloe has the biggest personality! She was all about taking pictures and for a one year old that's not usually the case. She was all smiles and good times. I think the following pictures show Chloe at her best.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-424" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/421/chloe7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-424" title="chloe7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/chloe7.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is her favorite little piano, and stuffed bunny. I'm not a big prop person but when the objects are meaningful I think it makes for a great picture. Don't ever hesitate to bring your childs favorite blanket, stuffed animal, or toy. Those objects that your child endears so mucy will soon be gone and all you'll have to remember is a picture.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-429" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/421/chloe2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-429" title="chloe2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/chloe2.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Have you noticed the adorable tutu and onsy outfit yet. Chloe's mom Kelly makes and sells these when she's not being an amazing teacher. She can make the bows too. She does wonderful work and for a lot more resonable price than the boutiques that made these so popular. Take a second to become a fan of her page on facebook. <a title="Lisa Jo's and Kelly's Bows" href="http://www.facebook.com/pages/Blue-Springs-MO/Lisa-Jos-and-Kellys-Bows/105150419051?ref=sgm" target="_blank">http://www.facebook.com/pages/Blue-Springs-MO/Lisa-Jos-and-Kellys-Bows/105150419051?ref=sgm</a> Lisa and Kelly do great work!</p>


<a rel="attachment wp-att-428" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/421/chloe3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-428" title="chloe3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/chloe3.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-427" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/421/chloe4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-427" title="chloe4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/chloe4.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-425" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/421/chloe6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-425" title="chloe6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/chloe6.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">She has the most amazing blue eyes! I just love photographing kids with bright eyes.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-423" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/421/chloe8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-423" title="chloe8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/chloe8.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a><a rel="attachment wp-att-426" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/421/chloe5"></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-426" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/421/chloe5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-426" title="chloe5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/chloe5.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Chloe is a girl after my own heart, she loves cake! She was all about the cake, some kids dive in, some kids don't want to have anything to do with the cake, but Chloe was all about eating it all. She was adorable. There were about 20 pictures I wanted to post of her cake eating, but this was Kelly's favorite and I have to admit it is pretty adorable. I especially like that you can see her two little teeth. Perfect!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-430" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/421/chloe1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-430" title="Chloe1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/Chloe1.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Chloe your 1 year pictures are perfect just like you! Thank you for letting me take them. I can't wait to watch you grow up, and be there to capture it with my camera.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Baby William</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/452</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 15 Mar 2010 02:42:10 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/?p=452</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a rel="attachment wp-att-456" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/452/william4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-456" title="William4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/William4.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="700" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is little William. He is one adorable little baby boy. William had his pictures taken on the coldest day in the history of KC. I'm pretty sure the high was 5 degrees. Brrrrr! William was a trooper and we managed to get some adorable pics of his cute face despite the cold.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-453" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/452/william1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-453" title="William1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/William1.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I couldn't resist posting just a few other pics of little William.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-455" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/452/william3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-455" title="WIlliam3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/WIlliam3.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Jennifer thanks for letting me take William's newborn pictures. He is awesome, and I hope he is enjoying his new life in Chicago. I hope I can continue to document his life when he comes to visit family.</p>


<a rel="attachment wp-att-454" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/452/william2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-454" title="William2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/William2.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Baby Jackson</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/459</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 16 Mar 2010 12:48:34 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/?p=459</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a rel="attachment wp-att-460" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/459/lager2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-460" title="Lager2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/Lager2.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Love, love, love this collection of photos. This is baby Jackson!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-465" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/459/lager7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-465" title="Lager7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/Lager7.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Jackson's parents Jessica and Rob were so happy to have their beautiful baby boys pics taken they were natural and ineractive. It was such a joy to photograph them.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-461" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/459/lager3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-461" title="Lager3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/Lager3.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I often look at other artists work for ideas and the babies are sleeping, I just don't have that experience in my studio. Most of the time my clients are bright eyed and bushy tailed just like the above photo. Jackson was alert and looking right at the camera which made for some great shots. The below shot just shows how tiny his little hands are compared to his dad's.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-466" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/459/lager1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-466" title="Lager1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/Lager1.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Again with the big blue eyes! He had so much depth to his eyes lots of color it was absolutely beautiful.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-463" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/459/lager5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-463" title="Lager5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/Lager5.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">While taking this shot we were all laughing, he looks like a little fish or seal or something. Still makes me giggle, but I like the shot.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-462" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/459/lager4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-462" title="Lager4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/Lager4.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-464" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/459/lager6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-464" title="Lager6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/Lager6.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Jessica and Rob thank you so much for allowing me to capture these precious moments in your family history. I look forward to seeing Jackson again soon!</p>]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>

		<title> Jenny and Steve</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/476</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 18 Mar 2010 02:08:43 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/?p=476</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="text-align: center;">I love taking pictures of bellies! I think women that are pregnant are magical. Below are pictures of Jenny and her man Steve!

</div>
<div><a rel="attachment wp-att-477" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/476/jenny1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-477" title="jenny1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/jenny1.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></div>
<div style="text-align: center;">Jenny is so excited to be a mom, but she was hesitant about having her maternity pictures taken. It was actually Steve that convinced her.</div>
<div style="text-align: center;">Steve called me to book the appointment, and made me feel like a million bucks. He went on and on about how artistic my photos are. It made me feel amazing. It's not often the hubbys and boyfriends notice the artistic photos. Thanks Steve, you made my day!</div>
<div><a rel="attachment wp-att-482" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/476/jenny6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-482" title="jenny6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/jenny6.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a></div>
<div style="text-align: center;">Jenny you are stunning!</div>
<div><a rel="attachment wp-att-481" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/476/jenny5">
<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-481" title="jenny5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/jenny5.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></div>
<div style="text-align: center;">Love the light on this one.</div>
<div style="text-align: center;"></div>
<div><a rel="attachment wp-att-479" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/476/jenny3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-479" title="jenny3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/jenny3.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a></div>
<div style="text-align: center;">There were so many of these I couldn't pick.</div>
<div style="text-align: center;"></div>
<div><a rel="attachment wp-att-478" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/476/jenny2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-478" title="jenny2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/jenny2.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></div>
<div style="text-align: center;">Love it!</div>
<div style="text-align: center;"></div>
<div><a rel="attachment wp-att-480" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/476/jenny4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-480" title="jenny4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/jenny4.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></div>

<p style="text-align: center;">This spring I'm offering a special special for all the moms and grandmas out there. Schedule a shoot between now and mothers day and get a free brag book complete with 10 of your favorite images from the shoot. This book is small enough to fit in your purse, but durable enough to last. The perfect gift for all those loving, hard-working, much deserving moms and grandmas. Give me a call or drop me an email and we'll find a time for your appointment. I hope everyone is ready for spring, because I know I am!<a rel="attachment wp-att-502" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/498/proofing_pressproofmag_closeup04">

	<item>
		<title>Aspen Colorado</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/506</link>
		<pubDate>Sun, 21 Mar 2010 18:46:12 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/?p=506</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a rel="attachment wp-att-507" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/506/aspen1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-507" title="Aspen1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/Aspen1.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Aspen Colorado might be one of the most beautiful places on Earth. Big blue skies, untouched mountains, and perfect snow. Jon and I were lucky enough to go ski this awesome mountain.</p>
<a style="text-decoration: none;" rel="attachment wp-att-514" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/506/aspen8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-514" title="Aspen8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/Aspen8.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Jon is such a cutie! He is addicted to skiing even more than me. Most of these pictures were taken on the same day because we only had one day of solid sunshine.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-508" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/506/aspen2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-508" title="Aspen2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/Aspen2.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Aspen is one of my new favorites for a couple reasons. First of all it's not busy at all, secondly it is dark, and I like a good challenge. Finally I love that the mountain literally runs right into the middle of the town of Aspen. The Gondala that takes you to the top is right in the middle of everything. I love that. I also love that the people were all about making our experience pefect. They helped us load our skis on the Gondala, gave us hot cider and granola bars, for free, and they always greeted us with a huge smile.</p>


<a rel="attachment wp-att-509" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/506/aspen3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-509" title="Aspen3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/Aspen3.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-522" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/506/aspen16"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-522" title="Aspen16" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/Aspen16.jpg" alt="" width="533" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">The above pictue was taken at Snowmass the big mountain a short shuttle ride away from Aspen. That's another great feature about Aspen, their public transportation is perfect. We didn't wait once! On this particular day the clouds were sitting low on the mountain, so Jon and I stayed on a run called campground. It was a long black, covered in powder, but not too many bumps so Jon was happy.  No one was around so we had a blast with this run to ourselves. We started the long run in a cloud, but ended it in the sun. There are several other shots of campground to come.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-511" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/506/aspen5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-511" title="Aspen5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/Aspen5.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-510" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/506/aspen4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-510" title="Aspen4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/Aspen4.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-512" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/506/aspen6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-512" title="Aspen6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/Aspen6.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">On our last day on the mountain we made a plan to meet at this lift. Well Jon hit a slick spot and missed the turn and ended up at the bottom. I didn't know and ended up at the lift. No worries until he didn't show up for 5 minutes. He's never 1 minute behind let alone 5. That's when the worrying started. All the worst images started popping up in my head. I sent our friend Ron to go on up so he could try to find him, hopefully not sprawled out on the ground somewhere. I've been in this position before when my dad got injured and I waited for 15 minutes before my family came and told me what happened. Luckily we have cell phones now! When I finally heard his voice after 3 missed calls it was all good. I was at the lift for about 30 minutes waiting for him to get down and back up and back down to me. I was the only person at this lift with these 2 hilarious lift managers. The above picture was the dancer. He had Lady Gaga blasting and he was dancing up a storm. Very entertaining!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-520" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/506/aspen14"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-520" title="Aspen14" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/Aspen14.jpg" alt="" width="533" height="400" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-521" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/506/aspen15"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-521" title="Aspen15" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/Aspen15.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">More of Campground.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-517" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/506/aspen11"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-517" title="Aspen11" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/Aspen11.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-519" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/506/aspen13"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-519" title="Aspen13" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/Aspen13.jpg" alt="" width="533" height="400" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-516" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/506/aspen10"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-516" title="Aspen10" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/Aspen10.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Jon and I spent most of our trip on Aspen we liked it so much. We would take the Gondola up and ski all the way down.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-518" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/506/aspen12"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-518" title="Aspen12" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/Aspen12.jpg" alt="" width="533" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Thanks for reading my blog, have you ever skied Aspen? What's your favorite mountain?</p>]]></content:encoded>
