	<item>
		<title>~ Elizabeth ~ </title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/551</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 24 Mar 2010 23:49:42 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/?p=551</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a rel="attachment wp-att-545" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/551/hu4-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-545" title="hu4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/hu41.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is Elizabeth! She is the most photogenic, patient, loving 5 year old I have seen in a long time. We captured so many beautiful pictures that I had a very hard time picking which ones to share. Here are a few of my favorites.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-543" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/551/hu2-3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-543" title="hu2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/hu22.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is Thomas her dad and Ashley her step-sister. Poor guy is out-numbered all the time.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-550" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/551/hu9-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-550" title="hu9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/hu91.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">We did a whole bunch of pictures with this hat and they came out adorable. If you're planning a shot with me soon the hat is a great idea for the older kids. Gotta love the side ponytail too.</p>


<a rel="attachment wp-att-547" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/551/hu6-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-547" title="hu6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/hu61.jpg" alt="" width="692" height="462" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-546" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/551/hu5-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-546" title="hu5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/hu51.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-549" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/551/hu8-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-549" title="hu8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/hu81.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">I'm really into capturing the kids in their true essensse. I think this one really reflects Elizabeth as the quiet and sweet little girl she really is.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-544" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/551/hu3-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-544" title="hu3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/hu31.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Gotta love pockets in the dress!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-542" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/551/hu1-3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-542" title="hu1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/hu12.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is her mom Marsha and she is just as beautiful as the girls.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-548" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/551/hu7-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-548" title="hu7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/hu71.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This shoot was really all about Elizabeth but as you can see the whole family is beautiful!</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Senior Pictures</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/557</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 31 Mar 2010 01:41:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/?p=557</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-558" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/557/ryan1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-558" title="ryan1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/ryan1.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is Ryan and he is not your typical teenager. What is a typical teenager anyway? Would it be the high school cheerleader type, the jock, the computer geek? I think the point I'm trying to make is that there is no such thing as a typical teenager. It's the nature of the beast. Teens are flooded with influences, and feelings of uncertainty. That's why I like them. They've got all the confidence to achieve everything and anything. Ryan is no different.</p>


<a rel="attachment wp-att-559" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/557/ryan2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-559" title="ryan2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/ryan2.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Ryan's mom found me on the internet and liked my style because she said it was different. I love that! She knew Ryan wasn't a big fan of having his pictures taken and knew it would take edgy photos to get him to cooperate. Edgy is just what we went for, and Ryan totally cooperated, minus the smiles. Despite my greatest efforts Ryan wouldn't give me more than a smirk. I even popped out from behind my camera and said boo. It's ok though I think portraits are at their greatest when they are real.</p>


<a rel="attachment wp-att-560" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/557/ryan3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-560" title="ryan3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/ryan3.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Here's the smirk!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-562" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/557/ryan5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-562" title="ryan5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/ryan5.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-561" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/557/ryan4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-561" title="ryan4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/ryan4.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-563" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/557/ryan6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-563" title="ryan6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/ryan6.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Ryan thanks for letting me capture you in this important phase of your life. I wish you the biggest and brightest future!</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Baby Nolan</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/566</link>
		<pubDate>Sun, 04 Apr 2010 22:54:27 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/?p=566</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-567" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/566/k1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-567" title="k1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/k1.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a> This is baby Nolan with his parents Carrie and Brian! He is one adorable little guy. He was so alert during our shoot he was all about having fun! Looking everywhere including the camera. We got so many great shots, but here are a few of my favorites. I love his big laugh. Brian was actually over my shoulder making a hilarious noise/face at him. He just couldn't stop laughing. This is one of many. It's pretty funny what we'll do to get a good smile.</p>


<a rel="attachment wp-att-569" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/566/k3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-569" title="k3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/k3.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Ahhhh....</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-571" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/566/k5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-571" title="k5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/k5.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Ahhhh...</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-570" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/566/k4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-570" title="k4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/k4.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">And there there are those blue eyes. Actually there are some cute little teeth in there too, but you can't see them in this picture. What a fun baby. I can't wait to capture some more of Nolan as he grows in his first year!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-568" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/566/k2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-568" title="k2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/k2.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Everglades ~ Photos of the natural reserve and some GATORS</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/576</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 06 Apr 2010 02:18:51 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/?p=576</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">I love traveling! I love taking pictures of my traveling. In fact travel photography is probably my big passion.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-578" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/576/everglades2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-578" title="everglades2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/everglades2.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Jon and I went to south Florida for a spring break this year! Everyone with me now ahhhhh..... Ah is right, we stayed with my best friend and little sis Maggie! Mags is a photographer as well. She does amazing work and I know those of you that have followed my blog for awhile have heard me talk about her alot. I encourage you to check out her work if you have the chance. She's the best wedding photographer in the world and was recently choosen as one of the top 10 wedding photographers in south Florida. She is a real inspiration to me. <a href="http://www.maggiestolzberg.com"> www.maggiestolzberg.com </a> Anyway enough talking about the amazing, loving, perfect mags, let me tell you about the pics.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Of course we picked the gloomiest day to go south, but the treat of continued rain the rest of the week pushed us to go when we did. As it turned out we had happy Florida sun almost every day.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-584" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/576/everglades8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-584" title="everglades8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/everglades8.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Jon and I took an airboat ride. It was awesome. <a href="http://http://travel.yahoo.com/p-travelguide-2819920-miccosukee_indian_village_airboat_rides_miami-i">http://travel.yahoo.com/p-travelguide-2819920-miccosukee_indian_village_airboat_rides_miami-i</a> For only 12 dollars we got a loud, fast and fun airboat ride. If you don't mind the cotton balls, and the fact that the guide can't speak english, it's the best. We saw a ton of gators. I got some crazy pics of a few. Just wait, it's kinda scary. Maybe I should put one of those warnings on here. Ok here it is!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-583" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/576/everglades7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-583" title="everglades7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/everglades7.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Yup that was a for real sign. They have to tell people not to touch them! I think those people might be me. Just wait.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">During our boat ride we made a stop off at this worn out old dock. They told us to roam around. I'm not going to lie, the thought that this was some sort of dirty trick did cross my mind. I thought maybe that's how the Native Americans kept the gators happy. Tourists as gator food. We walked around and saw some gators. smile! If you think it looks like it might fall apart you're not seeing things, I thought that too.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-585" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/576/everglades9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-585" title="everglades9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/everglades9.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Here she is, and yes I'm using a zoom, but still leaning out over the rickedy planks to get an unobstructed shot. NOW that I look at these pics I'm not thinking it was the smartest thing I've ever done. If my memory serves me right I think I remember in the crockodile hunter that they can be real fast and snappy. Maybe gators are more laid back, look at this next pic.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-581" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/576/everglades5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-581" title="everglades5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/everglades5.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">She was sleepy..</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-580" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/576/everglades4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-580" title="everglades4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/everglades4.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">I know close right. I didn't even crop this. ahhhh. Look at that skin. Makes you want to reach out and touch it right? Jon had to tell me to step away from the gator.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-579" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/576/everglades3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-579" title="everglades3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/everglades3.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This big girl was actually about 10 feeet long. I told Jon to put a hand out so we could get perspective, but he wouldn't. Silly boy.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-577" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/576/everglades1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-577" title="everglades1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/everglades1.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">And then this was at the backside of the dock. Maybe you have an answer?</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-582" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/576/everglades6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-582" title="everglades6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/everglades6.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Here's goober one and goober two. We always manage to look so cool in our pictures. I just don't know how we do it. haha!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-586" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/576/everglades10"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-586" title="everglades10" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/everglades10.jpg" alt="" width="533" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">If you made it this far thanks for reading or looking. I would love to hear your gator stories. YOU know you've got them!</p>]]></content:encoded>

I also like to bump the saturation usually, but in this case it was already a gritty green.  I got that look by playing with my white balance.  Thanks for commenting!]]></wp:comment_content>

	<item>
		<title>Kansas City Baby Portraits ~ Sophia</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/604</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 07 Apr 2010 01:43:10 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/?p=604</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">Sophia is the beautiful daughter of Bethany and Zachary! I had so much fun taking their pictures.  Get ready for cute, cute, cute!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-606" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/604/baby2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-606" title="baby2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/baby2.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Sophia had the most beautiful blue eyes. She was also bubbling over with smiles, which makes my job sooo easy. Sophia's smile is the reason I love my job so much. When you look into her eyes you see pure joy. Where else can you find that.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-605" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/604/baby1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-605" title="baby1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/baby1.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">ahhhh!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-609" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/604/baby5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-609" title="baby5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/baby5.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Cute Cute!<a style="text-decoration: none;" rel="attachment wp-att-607" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/604/baby3"><br style="text-decoration: underline;" /></a><span style="color: #000000;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-610" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/604/baby6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-610" title="baby6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/baby6.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a></span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Below is a new shot I'm experimenting with. I haven't quite perfected it, but I do like the effect. The light is just right on little girls face, but I haven't quite got the parents lit like I want. It's such a challenge to play with creative lighting when you're working with little ones. I guess I need to invest in a nice doll.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #000000;">
</span></p>
<span style="color: #000000;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-620" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/604/baby4-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-620" title="baby4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/baby41.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
</span>
<p style="text-align: center;">Now you see what I mean. Smiley, happy baby in all the pictures! What a doll! Thanks guys, I look forward to seeing you again soon!</p>
<span style="color: #000000;">
</span><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-607" style="text-decoration: underline;" title="baby3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/baby3.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" />]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>4 Generation Photos ~ Kansas City Photographer</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/627</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 09 Apr 2010 04:07:26 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/?p=627</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-630" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/627/ba3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-630" title="ba3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/ba3.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">And this is a four generation picture!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Meet Great Grandma Cora, Grandma Karen, Mama Cindy, and Baby Kenley! I know that first you noticed the beautiful women in the picture, then you probably noticed that they all have the same warm smile.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I noticed those things too and then I wondered. I wondered what a picture of my Memo, Marnie, Mom and I would have looked like. And then I wish. Wish I had that very picture. This picture is timeless just like the women in it. We all want to go out being remembered and I think this picture does just that, helps you remember, linking the past to the future.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Let me tell you about my wonderful experience with these ladies. Cindy came to me months ago for maternity pictures, then newborn, and then she told me she wanted a 4 generation picture. I was in awe, and excited, and nervous all at the same time. This was the first time I'd done anything like this and I totally understood the importance and value of what I was about to document. History.</p>


<a rel="attachment wp-att-633" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/627/ba6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-633" title="ba6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/ba6.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">From the moment they stepped into my studio we were bubbling over with laughter, tears, and amazing conversation. And of course there was lots of googooing and gagaing on Kenley's part. I'm sure she was entirely overwhelmed by the whole experience.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-632" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/627/ba5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-632" title="ba5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/ba5.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Now for the tears. I'm not the mushy emotional type. I get the uncomfortable lump in my throat in movies on occasion, but rarely do I cry. I think of life as a series of experiences that are just tha,t experiences. But this moment, the one you're seeing below, brought me to tears. Let me explain.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">You see I didn't realize that Karen had just finished her chemo treatments a few months before our shoot. While talking about her battle with cancer and eventual victory she told me that her motivation was baby Kenley. She wanted to see Kenley become a woman. So I asked her if she would be willing to throw the wig off for a bit. She was more than willing. I guess those things are itchy. While watching Karen interact with Kenley the room got quiet. All the joyful, bubbly laughter was gone in the wake of raw emotion. This will be one of those moments I get to store away for a rainy day.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-629" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/627/ba2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-629" title="ba2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/ba2.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-631" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/627/ba4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-631" title="ba4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/ba4.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">I wish I were a better writer so I could do Karen's story justice, but really the story isn't about one woman overcoming cancer it's about a group of women that love and support eachother with unconditionally. In the center of it all, baby Kenley!</p>


<a rel="attachment wp-att-628" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/627/ba1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-628" title="ba1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/ba1.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Maternity Photography~ Kansas City </title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/636</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 13 Apr 2010 00:58:38 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/?p=636</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-640" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/636/deanna5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-640" title="Deanna5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/Deanna5.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I have been taking so many pictures of bellies lately! I absolutely love it. Pregnant women are stunning and Deanna is no different. Here is the story of our wonderful time together.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-637" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/636/deanna1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-637" title="deanna1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/deanna1.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Deanna tried for years to get preganant with her now ex husband before they finally gave up. With severe Endometriosisand cancer in her past the doctors told her she was unable to conceive.  So she stopped trying, and stopped worrying about it all together. She has a huge family with tons of nephews and nieces that she was very close to. She had accepted the role as an aunt as her reality, and the closest she was ever going to get to being a mommy. After her divorce she started living her life again. No worries of babies or trying to make babies. She started dating a long time friend, and you can see where this is going. That's when she got the news!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-639" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/636/deanna4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-639" title="Deanna4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/Deanna4.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">She was surprised to say the least and her mom was so surprised that she didn't even believe her.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Deanna you are going to make an awesome mommy! Thanks for letting me take your maternity pictures, I had a blast! I can't wait to meet the little man.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-638" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/archives/636/deanna2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-638" title="Deanna2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/Deanna2.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>
		<wp:post_id>636</wp:post_id>
		<wp:post_date>2010-04-12 19:58:38</wp:post_date>

		<wp:comment_status>open</wp:comment_status>

	<item>
		<title>Bat Mitzvah pictures ~ Kansas City Photographer</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/644</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 19 Apr 2010 03:41:16 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=644</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">So I haven't even begun to download the hundreds of pictures I took at the Bat Mitzvah on Saturday. I did however have the red carpet pictures downloaded. Let me explain...</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">This Bat Mitzvah was for Melanie, the adorable brunette third from the right. She wanted her party to be movie star quality complete with a red carpet entrance, paparazzi, and Taylor Lautner. I'm pretty sure the following picture isn't that far from reality for poor Taylor.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-645" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/644/attachment/012"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-645" title="012" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/012.jpg" alt="" width="685" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Melanie was so much fun to work with and her party was happening to say the least.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-650" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/644/attachment/148"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-650" title="148" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/148.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>These pictures were taken by my best friend, husband, and business partner Jon. While I was off capturing more serious shots he was snapping away. He was amazing and surprisingly good at getting the girls to act normal, despite the fact that the real stud was behind the camera.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-654" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/644/attachment/189"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-654" title="189" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/189.jpg" alt="" width="521" height="350" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I love this shot. The girl on the right has got true sass! I'm lovin' it!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-652" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/644/attachment/154"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-652" title="154" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/154.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">We'll title this one obsession!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-651" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/644/attachment/151"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-651" title="151" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/151.jpg" alt="" width="521" height="350" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-653" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/644/attachment/176"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-653" title="176" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/176.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">You might recognize the guy on the right. That's Ian and I shot his Bar Mitzvah in the fall. He's already grown up soo much. In fact they all have. It was odd. The big dance of the night was "snowball" which is a slow dance when every few minutes the DJ says snowball and they have to swap partners. I think it was a nice way to relieve some of the awkward pressure of being 13 and "liking" people.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-649" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/644/attachment/140"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-649" title="140" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/140.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Ok if this picture isn't all 13 year old boy I don't know what is! Just look closely. Enough said.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-646" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/644/attachment/027"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-646" title="027" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/027.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Gotta love the candid.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-647" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/644/attachment/033"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-647" title="033" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/033.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Look for more pics of Melanie! I have tons! Can't wait to dig into them.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Baby Photography~ Kansas City Photographer</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/657</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 21 Apr 2010 01:35:35 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=657</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a rel="attachment wp-att-658" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/657/palmer1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-658" title="Palmer1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/Palmer1.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is Stephanie and Tyson! It really doesn't get much better! The following are pics of Stephanie and "her boys". Let me tell you about their special love.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Below is Nickolas and he really does have those great big blue eyes!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-660" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/657/palmer3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-660" title="Palmer3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/Palmer3.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Tyson is an amazing big brother he was so helpful during our shoot. Nickolas was starting to break teeth during our shoot and want's feeling top notch, but Tyson was right there to help out any way he could. He was one of the most helpful kids I've ever had the honor of working with. So pleasant and willing to contribute. Stephanie is one lucky momma to have these beautiful boys.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-667" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/657/palmer5-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-667" title="Palmer5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/Palmer51.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-666" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/657/palmer4-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-666" title="Palmer4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/Palmer41.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-665" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/657/palmer2-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-665" title="Palmer2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/Palmer21.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">It was Nickolas's first birthday so we of course had the traditional birthday picture celebration. Don't let this picture decieve you, he was not into it at all. Some kids just aren't. In fact he wasn't into the cake at all. That's when I called on Jon to help. He had just gotten home from work. He walked into the studio and Nickolas was captivated. All kids are when they see Jon. He's tall and funny, and has an energy that kids can't resist. He looked at Jon for a good minute and this was his expresstion the whole time. Like hey big guy are you going to play with me? Pure perfection for a photograph. Thanks hubby for being my guarenteed baby smile machine. LOVE YOU!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-664" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/657/palmer7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-664" title="Palmer7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/Palmer7.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Here are just a few more. I had so much fun working with these kids, I look forward to watching these boys grow into amazing men!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-663" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/657/palmer6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-663" title="Palmer6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/Palmer6.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Maternity Pictures~ Kansas City Photographer</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/672</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 22 Apr 2010 00:40:06 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=672</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">Are you ready? In not, you better sit down because here are some of the most gorgeous maternity shots ever taken! Really truly in the whole world. I love my future mammas and Mecia is no exception. She is so obviously stunning on the outside, but equally beautiful on the inside. Here are a few of my favorites. I had to pick! PS you have to read the whole thing because there's a surprise at the end!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-678" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/672/mecia6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-678" title="mecia6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/mecia6.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Mecia is one of the lucky few that just grows a belly. However, when she told me how much she gained I was shocked. She looks great! PS I think her shoulder tat is rad. You heard me right RAD!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-673" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/672/mecia1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-673" title="mecia1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/mecia1.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-679" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/672/mecia7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-679" title="mecia7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/mecia7.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-674" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/672/mecia2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-674" title="mecia2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/mecia2.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is her handsome hubby Ashley. Do you think they're going to have a cute baby? HECK YAH! Just look at those big eyes. I will say we had a few giggles when Ashley was making fun of his pastey skin tone. I told him everyone looks pastey next to Mecia. By the way I had to look the word pastey up for spelling. Turns out it's just in the urban dictionary. Hmm I thought it was a lagitamate word. Just in case you're wondering here's the definition.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">1.Someone thats so white they blind you.

2.Someone thats so white you can see them in the dark because they glow.

3. Someone who is whiter than Micheal jackson</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">There were some other pretty funny definitions. If you get the chance check it out. Will make you giggle!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://http://www.urbandictionary.com/define.php?term=pastey">http://www.urbandictionary.com/define.php?term=pastey</a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-675" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/672/mecia3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-675" title="mecia3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/mecia3.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Ashley you are far from pastey accourding to the urban dictionary. You looked almost as stunning as Mecia.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-676" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/672/mecia4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-676" title="mecia4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/mecia4.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Mecia and Ashley I had so much fun taking your pictures. You are a solid couple ready for parenthood, well, ready as you'll ever be. I've heard it's hard. haha! You're going to be amazing.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-677" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/672/mecia5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-677" title="mecia5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/mecia5.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Mecia and Ashley had their baby boy on Monday! He's a healthy 7ibs 6oz and 21 inches long!!!!! Mom and baby are doing well. I will be taking pics of little Jonah in just a few weeks. I can't wait!</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Portraits~ Kansas City Photographer</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/687</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 26 Apr 2010 02:11:33 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=687</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">Remember the Bat Mitzvah pics I mentioned? Well before the big event took place Melanie came in and had her pictures taken for her red carpet themed party. She has one of the most upbeat personalities and a smile that will light up a room! The pictures tell it all! Enjoy!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-688" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/687/mel1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-688" title="mel1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/mel1.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-689" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/687/mel2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-689" title="mel2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/mel2.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-690" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/687/mel3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-690" title="mel3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/mel3.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-691" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/687/mel4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-691" title="mel4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/mel4.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-692" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/687/mel5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-692" title="mel5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/mel5.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-693" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/687/mel6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-693" title="mel6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/mel6.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-694" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/687/mel7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-694" title="mel7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/mel7.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-695" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/687/mel8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-695" title="mel8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/mel8.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">I so enjoyed working with Melanie and her parents, Mary and George. I had a blast watching them have fun. I have so much more to show and share when I post the pics from the event. I just got done processing them today. Can't wait to share!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-696" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/687/mel10"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-696" title="mel10" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/mel10.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Children Photography~ Kansas City </title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/699</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 29 Apr 2010 02:50:48 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=699</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">Meet the Yoders! There are two things I love about this picture. First the obvious adorable family. Second the great wardrobe selection. I am a MU grad and will always have tiger pride good times, and bad. MIZ</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">
<a rel="attachment wp-att-700" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/699/y1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-700" title="y1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/y1.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is baby Claire, and she really is this adorable in person. She was crawling all over the place during our shoot in this particular shot she just happened to look up and give me the "What's up" look.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-701" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/699/y2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-701" title="y2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/y2.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Do you even need comments for this pic. She's adorable. Especially the big bow.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-711" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/699/y4-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-711" title="y4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/y41.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">What's that you say? Oh yah I know.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-714" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/699/y8-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-714" title="y8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/y81.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Look at me mom I'm standing up!  Just one and already independent. Watch out world.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-713" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/699/y7-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-713" title="y7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/y71.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">You would have thoughts she just stuck her hands in a bag of fun dip, but no somehow fingers always taste good when you're just one.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-712" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/699/y6-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-712" title="y6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/y61.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">And now you know where Claire gets it. Amy is an amazing mommy.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-715" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/699/y9-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-715" title="y9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/y91.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">What we didn't realize is that little Claire was actually getting sick. I had a hunkering because she was up and down the whole shoot and desperately hungry for those little foamy things. What are they called. They look and feel funny, but taste decent. I had to post this because, well it's just cute. Poor Claire. I promise we won't use this one in your graduation slideshow.  haha JK</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-710" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/699/y3-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-710" title="y3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/y31.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Amy, Colby and Claire I had so much fun taking your pictures even though you weren't feeling your best Claire. I can't wait to take some more when little baby two arrives. wink wink Thanks guys. Lots of love!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>

	<item>
		<title>5 fabs and 5 drabs</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/718</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 04 May 2010 01:12:37 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=718</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<strong>Every now and then I open my eyes and realize all kind of craziness is happening around me. I mean seriously fabulous things, and seriously drab things. So I decided every now and then I should document these monumental moments in my life. Ok mostly not monumental, but still important. Somewhat important anyway. Here are my 5 fabs for the week...</strong>

*Went to lunch at Gingers on the square in Liberty. Good food, and better company. Thanks Jamie.

*Played 4 hours of tennis!

*Went to the Designer showhouse. Favorite one in years!

*Discovered my new favorite snack. A flat wrap with Mozzarella and salami microwave for a few secs. Just a little party in my mouth.

And the fab of the week... drum roll xmas vacation style please...

*My dad washed my car for me! Inside and out!!! YAY!

<strong>And sadly enough my 5 drabs...</strong>

*Lost was a rerun.

*Layla woke up in the middle of the night and puked yellow stuff on the floor, what a treat.

*The people racing on I-70. Scary.

*Hitting myself in the eye with my tennis raquet. I'll only say this once if you ask or notice my bump I will tell you Jon threw his raquet and hit me.

*Got peed on in a shoot this weekend by a newborn. I will say this one is funny. The little guy peed 3 times during our shoot one of which was on me. I do love my job!

Looking over this list I realize most of this happened this weekend. I am a busy girl, but I had a lot of fun doing what I do! I hope everyone had a great weekend! Lots of love!!!!!

Al

PS If you're having Monday blues just think it could look like this outside! Just a few short months ago it did!

<a rel="attachment wp-att-725" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/718/w6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-725" title="w6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/w6.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-724" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/718/w5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-724" title="w5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/w5.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-723" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/718/w4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-723" title="w4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/w4.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-722" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/718/w3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-722" title="w3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/w3.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-721" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/718/w2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-721" title="w2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/w2.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a>

Ahhh... Looking at these pictures makes me so happy to be alive! Today is was sunny, 70 and flawless in KC. A perfect day for something outside.]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Maternity Pictures~ Kansas City Photographer</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/729</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 08 May 2010 02:40:09 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=729</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">These are pictures of Elizabeth and her perfect belly. Elizabeth came to me from Miami. Not Miami Florida, Miami MO. I am so happy she found me and let me capture the love she has for her baby and husband. Our time together was filled with lots of laughing and amazing conversation. Elizabeth is a horsey lover like myself. She actually trains Arabians and is very competitive.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-735" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/729/liz7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-735" title="liz7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/liz7.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is her husband Nick and he was so awesomly adorable during our shoot. I said it, it might not be a word, but it fits Nick. There were tons of amazing pics of the two of them. I just couldn't even pick so I decided to share this adorable one with you.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-733" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/729/liz4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-733" title="liz4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/liz4.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Elizabeth is stunning. I mean really who gets to look this great preggers! Amazing!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-732" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/729/liz3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-732" title="liz3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/liz3.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-734" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/729/liz6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-734" title="liz6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/liz6.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-736" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/729/liz9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-736" title="liz9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/liz9.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Tomorrow I get to take pictures of their new baby boy and I can't wait! Thank you guys for letting me be a part of your awesome experience!</p>

	<item>
		<title>Engagement Session~ Jamie and Tim</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/741</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 10 May 2010 23:54:15 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=741</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">Jamie and Tim are getting married this coming weekend and I'm so excited! Let me tell you why. Jamie and I have become such good friends this year with the wedding planning and the venting about our oh so busy lives!  So, I knew and loved Jamie way before I met Tim. When we were planning for their engagement session this spring I was eager to meet the man in Jamie's life. I knew he had to be great. And he was.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Jamie is all spunk and lively happy energy, while Tim is quiet and patient, and down for any and all of Jamie's cute antics. Sound familliar. It should to all of you out there that know Jon and I. They are a great match!
<a rel="attachment wp-att-755" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/741/jt15"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-755" title="jt15" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/jt15.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">When I take pictures of couples it's hard not to notice and feel the depth of the relationship. I think with this serious of photos we captured their love. I hope you agree.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-754" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/741/jt14"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-754" title="jt14" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/jt14.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">On this particular day we were lucky enough to have the greyest, most washed out, blah sky ever! BOOOO, but we managed to make it happen and the good news. No ugly shadows.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-753" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/741/jt13"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-753" title="jt13" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/jt13.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Besides who needs a pretty sky when you've got these hotties to brighten it up!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-752" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/741/jt12"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-752" title="jt12" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/jt12.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Jamie has the most brilliant eyes!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-751" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/741/jt11"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-751" title="jt11" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/jt11.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Yup it started raining. Adorable. I wonder what they're doing under there?</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-750" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/741/jt10"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-750" title="jt10" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/jt10.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Bling Bling!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-749" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/741/jt9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-749" title="jt9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/jt9.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-748" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/741/jt8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-748" title="jt8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/jt8.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-747" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/741/jt7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-747" title="jt7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/jt7.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is their little girl Ivy. She's hilarious and was very obidient but a little worried about her mamma and papa the whole time. She was always nearby, quietly watching and waiting.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-745" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/741/jt5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-745" title="jt5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/jt5.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Winston on the other hand was never nearby. In typical Jack Russell style he was always out doing whatever he wanted. We literally lost him several times, but he made it home muddy paws and all.  Totally opposite personalities here! Ivy and Winston really are their babies, but I have no doubt that in the near future real babies will take away from the attention theses four legged friends get.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-744" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/741/jt3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-744" title="jt3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/jt3.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-743" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/741/jt2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-743" title="jt2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/jt2.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Really Jamie and Tim are all about having fun! By this time it was really raining and time to go, but of course Jamie jumped on his back. Adorable, and fun!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-742" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/741/jt1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-742" title="jt1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/jt1.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I can't wait to shoot this weeding this weekend. This love story is to be continued...</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Baby Photography ~ Kansas City</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/775</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 14 May 2010 00:58:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=775</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-773" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/775/ma8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-773" title="ma8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/ma8.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I know you've seen this little model before. She's kinda hard to forget! Little Maven is literally growing up before our very eyes on the blog. She loves the camera and the camera loves her! Prepare for uncontrollable ahh's complete with squenchy eyebrows.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-772" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/775/ma7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-772" title="ma7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/ma7.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Cute smile complete with tongue and adorable monkey.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-768" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/775/ma3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-768" title="ma3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/ma3.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Maven gets her happy demeanor and big smile from her mom Lesle. I love working with Lesle and her husband Matt, always good times.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-774" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/775/ma9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-774" title="ma9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/ma9.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Her little hands will only be this adorable for a short amount of time.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-769" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/775/ma4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-769" title="ma4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/ma4.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">This picture says princess to me!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-770" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/775/ma5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-770" title="ma5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/ma5.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">She loves looking into the camera which is awesome. I am really good at getting kids to smile until I go back behind my camera then they give me this look. Hey where did that lady go?</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-771" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/775/ma6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-771" title="ma6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/ma6.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">There she is. Haha I love it!  There are 90+ pics of beautiful Maven equally as cute. If you want to see more, just drop me a message. Lesle and Matt thanks again for letting me take your pictures! I can't wait to see Maven again in a few months. She's just changing so much, I love being the one to capture it.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-766" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/775/ma1">
<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-766" title="ma1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/ma1.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Boca Raton Wedding</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/791</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 15 May 2010 03:11:29 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=791</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[There's no doubt I love taking pictures of bellies, and babies but every now and then I like to step out of the studio to take pics of a beautiful wedding.  It keeps me on my toes, challenges me in ways my studio never can, and gives me a chance to take pictures of one of my most favorite things...weddings!  I love love love weddings!  The bride, the groom, the guests, the music, dancing, the food and of course the cake.  It's all amazing and watching it all go down through the lens of my camera capturing all the coolest moments is an adreniline rushing experience that leaves me exhausted with a perma grin.  Tomorrow I have a wedding and I'm so excited.  I always like to go back and review my old wedding photos basically tearing them apart.  I'm hard on myself, sometimes too hard, but it's how I learn.  While reviewing tonight I came across some photos I took with Mags in Boca this March.  I wanted to share a few.  I can't wait to pack my gear and get going tomorrow.  I'm feeling the creative juices a flowing.

These pics are of Waylan and Susan.  Two St. Lous studs.  They've been together a long time and are still madly in love.  I really enjoyed working with them on their big day.

<a rel="attachment wp-att-801" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/791/wed11"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-801" title="wed11" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/wed11.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-802" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/791/wed12"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-802" title="wed12" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/wed12.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-807" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/791/wed17"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-807" title="wed17" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/wed17.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">The wedding was supoosed to be at a beautiful outdoor venue, but unfortunately it was raining hard that day. Blah. I think the inside alternative was beautiful, but it definitely made it hard on Mags and I.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-792" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/791/wed1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-792" title="wed1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/wed1.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-806" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/791/wed16"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-806" title="wed16" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/wed16.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-793" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/791/wed2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-793" title="wed2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/wed2.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-804" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/791/wed14"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-804" title="wed14" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/wed14.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">This picture below makes me smile because Susan is totally smiling while she's kissing Waylan. These are the moments our lives are made of.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-800" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/791/wed10"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-800" title="wed10" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/wed10.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-794" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/791/wed3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-794" title="wed3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/wed3.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-795" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/791/wed4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-795" title="wed4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/wed4.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-797" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/791/wed7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-797" title="wed7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/wed7.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-796" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/791/wed6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-796" title="wed6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/wed6.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-799" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/791/wed9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-799" title="wed9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/wed9.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-798" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/791/wed8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-798" title="wed8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/wed8.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-803" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/791/wed13"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-803" title="wed13" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/wed13.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-805" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/791/wed15"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-805" title="wed15" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/wed15.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Please send me all your creative juice for my wedding tomorrow. Oh and if you could send the sunshine that would be great too!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>

	<item>
		<title>Soccer pictures~ Kansas City Photography</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/815</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 18 May 2010 03:27:23 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=815</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-822" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/815/soccer10"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-822" title="soccer10" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/soccer10.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Those of you that know me well know I love soccer. I love playing it, and watching it. Unfortunately my knees have said enough. No more soccer for me, but you can imagine the joy I get out of watching my nephew Carter play. And even better watching my brother James coach.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Pretty awesome stuff. I probably don't need to point out my nephew. He's kinda big think on the blog.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I will say all these boys are adorable.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-817" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/815/soccer2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-817" title="soccer2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/soccer2.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I mean look at that mug. Adorable! PS you should know Jon totally posed them. It was the cutest thing ever. Jon played soccer in college so he had some real experience with soccer pics.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-823" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/815/soceer9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-823" title="soceer9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/soceer9.jpg" alt="" width="531" height="354" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-821" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/815/soccer8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-821" title="soccer8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/soccer8.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">The light was slipping through the trees just right. I loved it.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-820" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/815/soccer7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-820" title="soccer7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/soccer7.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Not only did Jon pose the boys, but he also got to be the celeb guest. He was really unsure at first, but I think he was a natural.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-818" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/815/soccer3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-818" title="soccer3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/soccer3.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Just running drills. Look at Carter. Give me some space please. HAHA that's my boy.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-816" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/815/soccer1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-816" title="soccer1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/soccer1.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">No comment necessary.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-819" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/815/soccer5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-819" title="soccer5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/soccer5.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>]]></content:encoded>
