	<item>
		<title>Children&#039;s Photography~ Kansas City</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/826</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 19 May 2010 02:01:34 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=826</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a rel="attachment wp-att-827" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/826/eva1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-827" title="eva1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/eva1.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is Eva and yes she is this perfect! Eva lives in Arkansas and she's been coming to me for pics since she was itty bitty! Now she's a big girl, with a big smile, and a big personality. I always love my time with Eva she always makes me smile.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">The picture below is just Eva hiding a smile. I love it!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-828" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/826/eva2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-828" title="eva2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/eva2.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">And here's Eva hiding eggs under her dress. This only lasted a few seconds so I'm really excited we were able to capture it. Asking a 2 year old to do something again is not a good idea.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-829" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/826/eva3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-829" title="eva3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/eva3.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a> "Mommy what are you doing?"</p>


<a rel="attachment wp-att-830" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/826/eva4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-830" title="eva4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/eva4.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Big blue eyes, natural soft curls, she's already a hear breaker.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-833" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/826/eva7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-833" title="eva7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/eva7.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is Eva's bunny. I love taking pictures of kids with their beloved stuffed animal. Those stuffed animals will wear and fade, but the memory will always be stong, because we've now captured it forever.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-832" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/826/eva6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-832" title="eva6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/eva6.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="601" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-831" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/826/eva5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-831" title="eva5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/eva5.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Lastly, I've got to share some pics of Eva dancing around the studio in pure 2 year old style!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-834" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/826/eva8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-834" title="Eva8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/Eva8.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="600" /></a>My hope is that Eva was able to put a smile on your face too. The good news...Eva is going to have a sibling soon! More to come!</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Newborn Pictures~Kansas City Photography</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/837</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 21 May 2010 00:59:22 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=837</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">Remember beautiful Mecia with the prefect belly. Well this is her baby Jonah. He is big and beautiful. We had a great time taking his pictures even though he wanted to eat the ENTIRE time. That's what makes newborns a challenge. Being that these little guys have only been on Earth a few days or weeks it's hard to predict their mood. Jonah's mood was easy... hungry. Despite the hunger we managed to get him to go to sleep for a bit and caputre some perfect pictures. Here are just a few.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-839" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/837/jon2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-839" title="jon2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/jon2.jpg" alt="" width="800" height="600" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-838" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/837/jon1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-838" title="jon1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/jon1.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Jonah's daddy Ashely is a war hero. He was a marine and was in Iraq when we declared war. He was literally the first on duty. Ashley is still recovering physically and emotionally but you can't tell. He is a super loving father who has embraced fatherhood with an open heart and tolerance. Every new parent needs that. When I met Ashley during maternity pics I had no idea he was a hero. Now that I know I'm a little star struck. Seeing celebrities doesn't do much for me, but meeting someone like Ashely that fights for our country, puts his life on the line for us, now thats cool! Thank you Ashley. I hope you know you are appreciated, and even better, Jonah is going to grow up to be so proud!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-842" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/837/jon7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-842" title="jon7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/jon7.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Teeny Tiny hands!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-843" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/837/jon8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-843" title="jon8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/jon8.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Ok I said he was hungry, but he was also tired.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-841" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/837/jon5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-841" title="jon5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/jon5.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-845" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/837/jon10"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-845" title="jon10" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/jon10.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-844" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/837/jon9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-844" title="jon9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/jon9.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Again look at that itty bitty hand! He's got some long fingers though!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-840" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/837/jon3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-840" title="jon3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/jon3.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Mecia, Jonah, and Ashley thank you for letting me spend a few hours with you hanging out, and taking a few picutres too.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">xoxo</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Maternity Pictures~Kansas City</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/848</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 02 Jun 2010 03:58:08 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=848</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a rel="attachment wp-att-852" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/848/dan4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-852" title="dan4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/dan4.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Danielle is such a stunning pregnant woman. Being that she's a dancer her body moved and molded right into pregnancy with ease. She was so much fun to work with. It's always so inspiring to be around pregnant women. They are so full of life and hope, and love. I really can't find the words to describe the feel I get when I take maternity pics. I love it!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-849" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/848/dan1">
<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-849" title="dan1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/dan1.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">The lines of pregnant women are perfect for art.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-850" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/848/dan2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-850" title="dan2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/dan2.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This was one of my favorite pics from the shoot. I think it's so vogue. Most the time I'm really really really hard on my photos. But, every now and then I fall in love with a photo and this is one of them. I really wanted to use this for my Little Blue Art Fest booth, but just couldn't crop it to work. Danielle thanks for being beautiful!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">My favorite part of maternity blogs is announcing the arrival of a healthy baby! Baby Bob is here and he came 2 weeks early! I guess he was in a hurry to get started. I'l be taking Bob's pic next Monday and I can't wait!!!! If he looks anything like his parents I'm sure he's perfect!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-851" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/848/dan3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-851" title="dan3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/dan3.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>A new chapter</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/855</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 03 Jun 2010 01:38:08 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=855</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[It's odd. Usually on the last day of school I'm bubbling over with excitement and anticipation of the coming summer. I count the hours, minutes, seconds. I have a perma grin for weeks before. I can't wait to sit on my deck and read <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">a </span><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">book </span> books. Not so much this year. This year it's more than a break. This year it's more than a few months. You see I started my morning today teary eyed and I ended my day confused. I'm really trying to show myself here, but it's so hard. How do I put into words the feelings I'm having. Is it sad, happy, anxious, scared or a combo? Is it the change, the possibilities, or the end I feel most. These things I'm very unsure of, what I'm sure of is what I'm giving up. I'm giving up an 8 year career doing something I love, something that felt great. I'm leaving behind a place where I contributed to the world. I molded my little loves into confident happy little people ready to conquer the world. The feeling of watching them grow is something that I won't be able to replace, I will always miss it. As the tears roll down my cheeks I realize that that's really what it is. Nothing is gained without sacrifice and I'm giving up that joy for my passion. Being a teacher I was always sure of one thing...I could make a difference. So now I say goodbye to that chapter, to those kids, those faces I will never forget, and I look to the future unsure of everything but the hope in my heart, and the dream of making it, whatever it may be. Today is for mourning, tomorrow is for dreaming. I hope when you read this you see a little piece of me in all my craziness. I feel exposed, but loved. Thank you to all the amazing people in my life for cheering me on. I wouldn't be making this sacrifice without you.]]></content:encoded>

It will not be as obvious as with students, but you will continue to make people shine and feel important. I know you have made a difference in my life. I am so proud of you and am here for anything you need. Be sad for today, but think of all the possibilities the future holds.]]></wp:comment_content>

	<item>
		<title>Family Pictures~ Kansas City Photographer</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/869</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 08 Jun 2010 12:52:46 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=869</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a rel="attachment wp-att-861" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/869/mon1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-861" title="mon1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/mon1.jpg" alt="" width="657" height="438" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">These are the feet of one lucky and adorable little girl! She has a mom that is absolutely perfect and a grandma that gives her endless love. Meet Erika and the very important ladies in her life!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">The below picture pretty much sums up Jenny's all around demeanor, she is always upbeat and positive. I love being around her because she oozes love.  So let me tell you a little story. A few months ago, I have no idea when I just know it was winter, Jenny contacted me to do a head shot for her new job and business card. The day before the shoot it snowed a couple feet, that might have been an exaggeration, but Jenny was determined to make it in her little car anyway.  About 15 minutes before the shoot she called and told me she was stuck. I told her no worries I have a big black truck that loves snow. She wasn't real familiar with the area so I just drove around with no luck. Jenny called shortly after I stared looking and told me a bunch of men had come and literally pulled her car out of the snow. After meeting Jenny I could see why getting help was no problem for her. She's absolutely stunning inside and out. The following pictures are from our spring shoot. Jenny's mom was in town from South America and she wanted a generation pic. I love these pics, her are a few of my favorites!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-868" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/869/mon9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-868" title="mon9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/mon9.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a><a rel="attachment wp-att-864" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/869/mon5"></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-867" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/869/mon8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-867" title="mon8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/mon8.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">This one is hilarious! Erika has a huge personality so it totally fits her.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-864" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/869/mon5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-864" title="mon5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/mon5.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-866" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/869/mon7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-866" title="mon7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/mon7.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-865" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/869/mon6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-865" title="mon6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/mon6.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">You might have noticed Erika is missing a few teeth. Pretty cute!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-863" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/869/mon4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-863" title="mon4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/mon4.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">This pic touches my heart. It totally sums this relationship up.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-862" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/869/mon2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-862" title="mon2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/mon2.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">What I failed to tell you is that Jenny works for Liberty Mutual and she saved Jon and I a ton of money on our insurance. I am so lucky to now have her in my life. We will be life time friends! Jenny and Erika it is always a pleasure photographing you!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Little Blue River Art Fest ~ Blue Springs, MO</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/872</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 09 Jun 2010 15:23:18 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=872</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Walls- check

Art work- check

Lighting- check

Marketing materials- check

People- ???? I hope :)

The Little Blue Art Fest is only 3 days away and I'm beside myself with excitement. I remember years ago walking down the many rows of the Plaza Art Fair and thinking to myself I wanna do this. Never in a million years did I think I was actually gonna do this. Obviously this isn't the Plaza Art Fair, but it's a start. I was actually thinking just yesterday that following your dreams is a lot like walking the plank. I'm consumed with fear, but if I don't look down I won't fall down. That pretty much describes the events leading up to this. I just kept looking up, moving forward, and hoping for the best. Last night Jon and I sat on the couch and admired our booth. Both just staring, a little bit in awe. I spend a lot of time dreaming of making my dreams come true, but now that one has, it's pretty euphoric.

Now that the work is done I can relax and have fun. The festival is this Saturday on the corner of 7hwy and 40hwy (White Oak Plaza) from 10-6. There will be kids activities, music, food, and of course art. If you're a client of mine I also have a little surprise for you when you stop by and say hi. Who knows your picture might be on display.

Well, back to work. I hope to see you Saturday!

xoxo

Allison

<a rel="attachment wp-att-873" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/872/little-blue-river-art-fest_invitation"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-873" title="Little Blue River Art Fest_Invitation" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/Little-Blue-River-Art-Fest_Invitation.jpg" alt="" width="563" height="250" /></a>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Boys and their dogs~Kansas City Photographer</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/879</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 09 Jun 2010 21:28:37 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=879</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[I've been excited about doing this blog post for awhile. If you just looked at the pics you're probably wondering why. Well this post is all about Anthony, a handsome, 17 year old guy who happens to have Autism. When Liza his aunt, one of my beloved clients, contacted me and told me she wanted pics taken of her autistic nephew I was excited and nervous. She told me she couldn't remember the last time he'd had his pics taken and she wanted to surprise her sister Angel who has devoted her life to Anthony and helping other kids with Autism. Wow! Liza was preparing me for anything and everything that Anthony might do and then she asked if he could bring his dog. A one year old boxer pup. I'm pretty sure my eyes got big at that point but I agreed to take on the challenge and actually thought it would be fun if not funny to watch. Shooting dogs is always funny to watch.

<a rel="attachment wp-att-882" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/879/antho3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-882" title="antho3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/antho3.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>

The day of the photo shoot Liza told me she had talked it over with Anthony and he was excited. I will just say he was perfect, hilarious and all around good fun! He did everything and anything I asked. I tend to make lots of weird faces and say ridiculous things during shoots to get people to relax. At one point Anthony was giving me a look. So I asked, "Anthony you must think I'm totally weird"? His response, "No actually I think you're pretty cool". Well at that point he had totally won me over, so I gave him my complete A game. We had a blast. We talked about his favorite band Green Day. His favorite things to do, x box. We chatted this way and that. Then I told him to say something funny so he said, "Zombie Apocalypse" and started laughing. I mean really laughing the kind that makes wrinkles in the corners of your eyes. Here's him thinking about something funny.
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-880" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/879/antho1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-880" title="antho1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/antho1.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Here's him laughing after saying it.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-883" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/879/antho4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-883" title="antho4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/antho4.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Then there's Daisy the dog. One of the best behaved boxer pups ever. She loves Anthony and Anthony loves her. Look and see for yourself.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-884" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/879/antho5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-884" title="antho5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/antho5.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-881" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/879/antho2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-881" title="antho2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/antho2.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">When we got done I asked Anthony if it was so bad? His response..."Actually this was more fun than x box". Tear</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Anthony you are such a stud, what a great face! Thanks for being a great model. I'll take your pics any chance you give me.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-885" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/879/antho6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-885" title="antho6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/antho6.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Side note/Funny story: Despite my efforts some of the Daisy hair remained on the floor the next day at my shoot. I turned to the client and said sorry if there is some hair on the floor we shot a dog in here yesterday. Man you should have seen their faces. Priceless! I quickly explained. I love my job.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Dillon~ Senior Pictures, Kansas City</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/896</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 11 Jun 2010 13:00:06 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=896</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a rel="attachment wp-att-908" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/896/dil12"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-908" title="dil12" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/dil12.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">I think you know what I mean when I say senior girls are easier to photograph than senior boys. There's more pose options, more clothes options, and the girls just get into it more. Having said that I had so much fun on this shoot with Dillon. He is an outgoing, fun-loving, gorgeous guy, with the world in his fingertips. Meet Dillon.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-909" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/896/dil13"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-909" title="dil13" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/dil13.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">I photographed Dillon's brother Jake a few years back. His brother is equally good looking so you know the boys got some good genes. But, it's really not his good looks that make him attractive. Dillon loves to smile and have fun. He had me cracking up during our whole shoot together.  Some people just know how to make others feel comfortable and Dillon is one of "those people".  He's also a natural in front of the camera just look.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-904" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/896/dil8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-904" title="dil8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/dil8.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-907" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/896/dil11"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-907" title="dil11" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/dil11.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-897" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/896/dil1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-897" title="dil1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/dil1.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-903" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/896/dil7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-903" title="dil7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/dil7.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-906" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/896/dil10"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-906" title="dil10" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/dil10.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">His girlfriend popped in for a few quick shots. She's pretty adorable.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-899" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/896/dil3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-899" title="dil3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/dil3.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-901" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/896/dil5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-901" title="dil5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/dil5.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-900" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/896/dil4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-900" title="dil4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/dil4.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-898" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/896/dil2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-898" title="dil2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/dil2.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I love this last shot for two reasons. First, I technically pulled off what I was going for which doesn't always happen for me when it comes to speedlights. I wanted the wrap around rim light you see giving him a glow, and I wanted his shadow at the bottom, but I didn't want him undexposed. That's where the flash comes in. I had Jon stand camera left with a speedlight and umbrella to shoot through. Yay! Second I think this shot is symbolic of Dillon as he moves on down the road. Anything is possible for Dillon but I have no doubt he is going to be amazing!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-905" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/896/dil9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-905" title="dil9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/dil9.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Belly pics ~ Kansas City Photographer</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/915</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 15 Jun 2010 19:19:27 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=915</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">This is Keira and she just became a big sister.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-916" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/915/willis1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-916" title="willis1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/willis1.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">But before that big day we had to take some pics of her with her momma Devin. They were comparing bellies. Keira was totally confused as to why her belly doesn't look like Devin's.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-917" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/915/willis2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-917" title="willis2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/willis2.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">She has the most beautiful hair that does a good job of framing her face and sometimes hiding it. I didn't mind, in fact I loved it even when she was teeny tiny. I've know Keira since she was a week old when she came to me for newborn pics. She was absolutely adorable and her head was covered in thick hair just like now. Below is her announcement that I was able to dig out of the archives.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-922" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/915/devin-announcement"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-922" title="Devin-announcement" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/Devin-announcement.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-919" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/915/willis4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-919" title="willis4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/willis4.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Jason and Devin you look the same, but my little Keira you have definitely changed. What a gorgeous little girl! Thanks for letting me take your pics. You were awesome to work with!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-920" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/915/willis5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-920" title="willis5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/willis5.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">This one just leaves me staring. I can't even find the words, they're stuck.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-921" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/915/willis6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-921" title="willis6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/willis6.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Congrats on your new little addition!</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Belly Pictures, and a little bit about lighting~ Kansas City Photographer</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/926</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 17 Jun 2010 14:03:25 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=926</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">This is Tyra and Nathan. They were pregnant, but now their life's are changed forever. It started with a belly.</p>


<a rel="attachment wp-att-931" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/926/tyra5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-931" title="tyra5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/tyra5.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a><a rel="attachment wp-att-929" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/926/tyra3"></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">When Tyra originally contacted me she was interested in newborn pics. The belly thing was not something she thought was for her. I always gently encourage women to do the maternity pictures because I know in the end they are going to love them, but I also understand it's not for everyone. After I showed the pics to Tyra she decided to give it a go and I'm so happy she did because she's a beautiful pregnant woman!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">And yes she always has her fingers painted a rockin color for photos!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-929" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/926/tyra3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-929" title="tyra3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/tyra3.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">How to light this shot?</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Easy, have the subject stand relatively close to the background. Aim two strobes with softboxes on each side of her at the background. In my case it was seamless white paper. The light will magically wrap around the subject giving this awesome effect.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-930" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/926/tyra4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-930" title="tyra4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/tyra4.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Below is a picture of baby Jackson just before he was born. He has the prettiest eyes, can't you tell? Haha he really does, keep reading.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-928" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/926/tyra2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-928" title="tyra2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/tyra2.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I heart this picture! The lighting is very similar to that above. Just get the light to hug the subject!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-927" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/926/tyra1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-927" title="tyra1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/tyra1.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Tyra and Nathan are a very happy couple. They are both teachers so they get to enjoy lots of time off together. I know for some couples that would be a bad thing, but I can tell they really like being around eachother. They are going to make amazing parents, I've already gotten to witness their gentle parenting techniques because just last week we had Jackson's shoot. Here is just a few pics of the little guy from our shoot last week.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-932" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/926/tyra6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-932" title="tyra6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/tyra6.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I told you he had nice eyes. Even looking the same direction. Pefection!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-938" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/926/tyra12"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-938" title="tyra12" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/tyra12.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">And it's not easy for new mommas to bring their week old babies in to have their pictures taken. Sometiems they're exhausted, sometimes they're worried, sometimes they're overwhelmed, and sometimes they're all those things. Tyra was relaxed, and made the very difficult job of being a new mom look easy.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-934" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/926/tyra8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-934" title="tyra8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/tyra8.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Nathan was also obsessed!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-933" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/926/tyra7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-933" title="tyra7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/tyra7.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Two big long legs coming your way! Just look at those feet!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-935" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/926/tyra9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-935" title="tyra9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/tyra9.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Get ready for some cuteness that hurts.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-937" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/926/tyra11"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-937" title="tyra11" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/tyra11.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Jackson you are so perfect, but you did not want to go to sleep during your shoot. I'm so happy you finally did!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-936" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/926/tyra10"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-936" title="tyra10" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/tyra10.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Want to know how I did something or lit something just ask, I'd love to help all my photog followers out there.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Senior Pictures~ Kansas City Photographer</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/942</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 22 Jun 2010 17:48:55 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=942</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-945" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/942/tyler4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-945" title="tyler4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/tyler4.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is Tyler and he's a graduated senior from Blue Hills High School. I got to spend some time with Tyler taking his senior pics and he is a an outstanding person.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-947" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/942/tyler6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-947" title="tyler6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/tyler6.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">He's very driven and determined. One of those kids that you know is going to do great things because of the fierce passion in their eyes. Tyler definitely is passionate in fact I think it's fair to say he has one love, and that's hockey!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">He's played forever and traveled the country on teams. He is currently trying to get on a professional team. I love when people go for their passion. Go Tyler Go!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-943" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/942/tyler1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-943" title="tyler1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/tyler1.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Hockey always seems like a scary sport to me. I expect all hockey players to be a little rough around the edges. Ya know missing a few teeth and stuff. Not Tyler he's got style and class. Check it out!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-948" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/942/tyler7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-948" title="tyler7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/tyler7.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-944" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/942/tyler2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-944" title="tyler2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/tyler2.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-949" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/942/tyler8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-949" title="tyler8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/tyler8.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">And big hands! I guess you gotta have big hands to hold the hockey stick. Wait is that what it's called? Tyler also told me he likes the fights. I told him I do too, but only because they have lots of stuff on. So it's kinda like fighting in the sumo suits. And they always break 'em up pretty fast.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-946" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/942/tyler5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-946" title="tyler5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/tyler5.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Tyler good luck in all you do! I say go for it! Keep me posted on your progress, and next time we do picks don't forget your hockey stick. :)</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Kid Photography~Kansas City</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/952</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 24 Jun 2010 15:48:02 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=952</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a rel="attachment wp-att-954" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/952/b2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-954" title="b2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/b2.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Sometimes kids come into the studio timid, fearful, and downright scared. Ok I take that back, most of the time kids, that are new, come in that way.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I mean really I'd be scared too. Imagine from their point of view, a big dark room, a big scary box things that shoots light, sitting in the middle of a room while a crazy lady aims a big black thing at you.  All the while your parents are in the background acting crazy and telling you to smile. I'd be intimidated too.  Baby girl Brooksley was no different. She was attached to her mom Beth like a leech. So we just played. And after a few minutes here are the shots we started getting.<a rel="attachment wp-att-956" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/952/b4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-956" title="b4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/b4.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="600" /></a></p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-957" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/952/b5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-957" title="b5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/b5.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Brooksley has beautiful red hair and big brown eyes as you can see. The camera loves her! And after a short time, she was starting to love the camera. Just look.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-958" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/952/b6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-958" title="b6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/b6.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">She even stuck her tongue out. I think we told her to make a funny face. Job well done Brooksley!<a rel="attachment wp-att-955" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/952/b3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-955" title="b3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/b3.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">The picture below is something powerful to me. I look at it as a baby no longer a baby. Ready to get rid of the Bumbo and stand on her own. Makes me take a deep breath and give thanks that I captured this awesome moment.<a rel="attachment wp-att-959" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/952/b7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-959" title="b7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/b7.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Brooksley you are beautiful! Thanks for making your pictures so easy to take!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-953" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/952/b1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-953" title="b1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/b1.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="600" /></a></p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-960" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/952/b8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-960" title="b8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/b8.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Happy 5th Anniversay!</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/965</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 25 Jun 2010 20:42:22 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=965</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Five years ago today I was driving around in my Volvo with my girls getting our hair and makeup done, taking pictures, and having an all around blast. I remember being so relaxed on my wedding day. I think because for the first time and maybe the last time in my life, I was sure, sure that I was doing the right thing, sure that I was marrying the perfect man, sure that everything would work out even if it wasn't perfect. Now on my 5th anniversary, a baby milestone, I'm feeling reflective. We've had some awesome times together traveling, making friends, throwing parties, and turning our house into a home. But at this time in my life, this very moment, what I'm really thinking about is how lucky I am. Lucky to have a man that not only allows me to do what I love, but encourages it. Not only supports my passion, but helps me find my way. Spends his evenings and Saturdays holding lights, posing babies, setting up art booths, and chatting with strangers that become freinds. Jon doesn't always <em>want</em> to be my "light boy", but he always wants to help me and always with a quiet smile. How do you thank your husband when he gives so much more than expected. He is my best friend, my inspiration, and partner in crime. He is helping me become the person I dream of being, and I love him sooo much for it. Even better I really like him too. Thank you bubby for picking me to love. I am the lucky one...

<a rel="attachment wp-att-966" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/965/ann1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-966" title="ann1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ann1.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-970" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/965/ann5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-970" title="ann5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ann5.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-968" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/965/ann3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-968" title="ann3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ann3.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-967" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/965/ann2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-967" title="ann2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ann2.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-969" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/965/ann4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-969" title="ann4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ann4.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-971" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/965/ann6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-971" title="ann6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ann6.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>

In honor of our fabulous 5 years together I am giving away 10 free sitting fees to 10 happy couples!

Here's the catch... there are requirements

~ you're a happily married couple with love that shows

~ you've been married 5 or more years

~ you love pictures and haven't had any taken of just the two of you in years, maybe since you were married

~ you have to schedule your shoot in the months of July and August

I can't wait to start shooting these pics! I've already found some fabulous spots around the city perfect for "just because" photos!

Oh and one more thing... drinks on me after the shoot!]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Cute Kids! ~ Kansas City Photographer</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/974</link>
		<pubDate>Sun, 27 Jun 2010 20:17:07 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=974</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Owen is now 1! It's crazy how time flies.  I've been takin' this little cowboys pics since he was itty bitty. Usually he is very timid and quiet, but not during this shoot. He was crazy, fun, and all over the place. It's funny how comfortable the kids that grow up in my studio get. I love it.

<a rel="attachment wp-att-975" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/974/sals1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-975" title="sals1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/sals1.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Howdy partner!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-976" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/974/sals2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-976" title="sals2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/sals2.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Yes! I would define Owen't eyes as electric blue. And he's got the best serious face ever!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-977" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/974/sals3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-977" title="sals3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/sals3.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">And silly face!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-978" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/974/sals4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-978" title="sals4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/sals4.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Everybody needs a picture like this of their kids. We'll call this one saggy diaper.</p>


<a rel="attachment wp-att-979" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/974/sals5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-979" title="sals5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/sals5.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">His shoes were pretty awesome. His momma Kim and I were cracking up! How does he even walk on those little stubs.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-980" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/974/sals6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-980" title="sals6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/sals6.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is his big sister Izzie. And big she is. She's growing up sooo fast. I remember being able to hold her in one arm. She's got so much personality, just look. Oh and these these pics were taken at a different shoot. I highly recommend this method. Kim is so smart, she knows to get good pics they need no distractions like crazy brother running around. It gives me a chance to give the little ones my undivided or distracted attention.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-981" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/974/sals7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-981" title="sals7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/sals7.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Gotta love the little leg sticking out.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-982" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/974/sals8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-982" title="sals8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/sals8.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Sometimes my favorite shots are the ones where kids aren't looking. You have to wonder what she's thinking right here. She does this a lot with her fingers. Adorable.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-983" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/974/sals9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-983" title="sals9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/sals9.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">We'll call this one cotton candy. She a puff of cuteness. Notice the little green jelly belly in her hand. Nothing makes kids happier than candy.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-984" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/974/sals10"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-984" title="sals10" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/sals10.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is no wall print, but it is soooo Izzie. She makes THE BEST faces.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-985" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/974/sals11"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-985" title="sals11" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/sals11.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-986" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/974/sals12"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-986" title="sals12" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/sals12.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="601" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-987" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/974/sals13"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-987" title="sals13" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/sals13.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-988" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/974/sals14"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-988" title="sals14" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/sals14.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-989" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/974/sals15"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-989" title="sals15" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/sals15.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Does the picture below remind you of a magazine ad. Only the model was 25 and in her wedding gown. Haha</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-990" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/974/sals17"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-990" title="sals17" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/sals17.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-991" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/974/sals18"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-991" title="sals18" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/sals18.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="1000" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Kim I always look forward to our sessions together. I'm lucky to call you a client and a friend.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Wedding Photography~ Kansas City</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 30 Jun 2010 15:04:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=994</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">The style of wedding photography that is "in" right now is the details. The Martha Stewart wedding magazine kinda pics. And while those details make pretty pretty pictures, they don't tell the story the way I want to tell this story. This is indeed a story of Jamie and Tim and the love they shared on their wedding day, and a little about being a wedding photographer too.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-995" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja1a"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-995" title="ja1a" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja1a.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">It started for me, on a rainy day. Drizzly really, but the deepest thickest grayest clouds ever. I was hopeful though. I woke up telling Jon that it would all blow over by 6. Haha</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1036" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1036" title="ja1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja1.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">When I got to the church around 2, Jon and I scowered it looking for some northern light, a pretty room, or ever a window with some decent curtains. No such luck. I was still hopeful the rain was going to go away, so we got started. A lot of wedding photography is flying by the seat of your pants. Lucky for me, that's how I roll. But don't let me fool you, I still get the sweaty palms, lightheaded pucky feeling when things don't go right like the light, people, weather, and well I could go on and on. Ahhh the challenges of wedding photography.  This is Jamie with "her girls".</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1030" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja2-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1030" title="ja2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja21.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Jamie's dress was stunning and it fit her perfectly!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-997" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-997" title="ja3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja3.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="601" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">She wore 2 garters, one KU one MU! Let's just say Tim later picked the MU garter. Smart man!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-998" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-998" title="ja4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja4.jpg" alt="" width="650" height="350" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-999" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-999" title="ja5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja5.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1000" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1000" title="ja7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja7.jpg" alt="" width="650" height="800" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Jamie was so chilled out. She was carefree and relaxed the entire day. It was so much fun to take her pictrues. And this couch was fabulous.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1001" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1001" title="ja8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja8.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1002" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1002" title="ja9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja9.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Did I mention I loved this couch. The room was tiny, but the couch was rockin so I used it in lots of shots. This one is Jamie being Jamie. She's always laughing or making someone feel good.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1003" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja10"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1003" title="ja10" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja10.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I love this picture. We were just walking down to take pics by the stone wall. I grabbed my camera just in the knick of time.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1004" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja11"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1004" title="ja11" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja11.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Is anyone else thinking gorgeous? Hot even!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1005" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja12"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1005" title="ja12" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja12.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">And true to Jamie she laughs just after I tell her that.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1006" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja13"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1006" title="ja13" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja13.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1007" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja14"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1007" title="ja14" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja14.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">These are the moments leading up to their first encounter on their wedding day. Tim is looking at her boudoir pictures (HOT)! Jamie is so excited to see him, and that kiss was so perfect. Then Jamie cried. Just look at Tim's face.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1008" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja15"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1008" title="ja15" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja15.jpg" alt="" width="800" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">The audience hiding out finally couldn't resist an audible ahhhhh.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1009" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja16"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1009" title="ja16" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja16.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">With the rain we were forced to stay inside even though Jamie and I had made a plan earlier that week to take pics at the adorable stone house just behind the church with the hugemongous yard surrounding it. These are the moments for sweaty palms. But Jon and I made it happen. Sometimes I just have to say Al chill. And I usually do.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">They would kiss A LOT!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1010" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja17"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1010" title="ja17" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja17.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">And laugh A LOT!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1011" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja18"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1011" title="ja18" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja18.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Love this pic, Jamie is so close to her momma!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1012" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja19"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1012" title="ja19" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja19.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">The bridesmaid dresses and shoes were AHHH dorable!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1013" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja20"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1013" title="ja20" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja20.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Just after doing all the fam pics the rain stopped. It was still soaking wet, but I told Jamie and Tim we could make this happen. So for 20 minutes we got to go outside where the light was literally perfect, and the trees were all glisening and reflective from all the rain. Ahhh love these moments.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1014" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja23"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1014" title="ja23" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja23.jpg" alt="" width="466" height="700" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1015" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja24"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1015" title="ja24" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja24.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Did I mention they're cute and funny?</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1016" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja25"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1016" title="ja25" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja25.jpg" alt="" width="650" height="650" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">The green of the trees and grass was blowin' up Jamie's eyes. GORGEOUS!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1017" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja26"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1017" title="ja26" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja26.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Hello magazine cover!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1018" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja27"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1018" title="ja27" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja27.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1019" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja28"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1019" title="ja28" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja28.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">And then mother nature said enough. 20 minutes was just not enough time, but it was perfect while it lasted.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1020" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja29"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1020" title="ja29" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja29.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">You might be wandering what Jamie is doing here?</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1021" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja30"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1021" title="ja30" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja30.jpg" alt="" width="800" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">She and her best friend Cassie were throwing wrappers down eachothers dresses. Yup! Funny stuff. This is just before she walks down the isle.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1031" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja32"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1031" title="ja32" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja32.jpg" alt="" width="800" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Jamie with her Dad.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1022" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja31"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1022" title="ja31" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja31.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">The wedding was beautiful</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1033" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja43"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1033" title="ja43" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja43.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">But the kiss was my favorite. No flashes during the ceremony, but the dramatic lighting is so perfect for this moment. Look how Jamie's face is lit up during their first kiss as husband and wife. And then the moment just after when you're trying to hold on to that feeling forever.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1023" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja35"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1023" title="ja35" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja35.jpg" alt="" width="850" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Just after the ceremony we made a quick dash to the bowling alley down the street from the reception. This is where Jamie and Tim had their first date so it was a perfect spot to take some pics.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a style="text-decoration: none;" rel="attachment wp-att-1024" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja36"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1024" title="ja36" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja36.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1025" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja37"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1025" title="ja37" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja37.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">We had a bunch more of the two of them bowling but I had to cute myself off somewhere.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1026" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja38"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1026" title="ja38" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja38.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">This reception hall is downtown North Kansas City. What a fun venue. Perfect for the couples personality.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1027" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja39"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1027" title="ja39" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja39.jpg" alt="" width="1000" height="1000" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">There was dancing, there was drinking, there was eating. It was a fun night! Jamie danced her feet off!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1032" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja42"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1032" title="ja42" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja42.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">But at the end of the day it's really all about this...</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1029" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/994/ja41"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1029" title="ja41" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/ja41.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Kids~ Children Photography Kansas City</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1039</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 02 Jul 2010 14:19:06 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1039</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a rel="attachment wp-att-1040" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1039/zimm1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1040" title="zimm1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/zimm1.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is Elijah and he is adorable. I've been taking his pictures since he was itty bitty. So when his family moved to Chicago I was so sad. But then Katy his momma called me and told me they were coming into town for his first birthday. Perfect for pictures.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1041" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1039/zimm2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1041" title="zimm2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/zimm2.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This picture cracks me up. He looks like he's in timeout. What you don't see it the 3 silly adults behind the camera juming around trying to get his attention. I swear kids can be so smart.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1043" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1039/zimm4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1043" title="zimm4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/zimm4.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">But eventually we won, and Elijah gave in. Check out those awesome eyes and little tiny teeth. Fabulous!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1044" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1039/zimm5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1044" title="zimm5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/zimm5.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Aaron, Katy, and Elijah thanks for coming and seeing me during your valuable family time. I just love taking your pictures!</p>]]></content:encoded>
