	<item>
		<title>6 months gone!</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1047</link>
		<pubDate>Sun, 11 Jul 2010 23:55:03 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1047</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[What! I can't even believe 6 months of 2010 are gone. It seems like just a few short months ago I was making my goals. I figured since time seems to be flying by I should probably revisit my goals. Kinda fun, kinda not. I think about these goals a lot, but I haven't looked at them since I hit publish when I wrote the post. So here goes. I've definitely been working hard, but have I actually achieved anything? Hmmm...

1. <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">Grow my business, I mean really grow my business. That means following up with clients, asking them for referrals, and being brave enough to put myself out there. Part of this will come from being a part of a business networking group. </span> <em>Umm yah I'm gonna cross that one off. I still need to do a better job of the follow up thing. I love my clients and I think about them often, but do I tell them. Not so much. I just gotta get this juggling thing down. I've gotten sooo much better about putting myself out there. That credit goes to you. I've been so supported and encouraged, so thank you. xoxo</em>

2. Have my first gallery opening! There are really 2 sets of photos I want to have gallery openings for. The first Indonesia, and the second women, beautiful women, normal women. You get the idea. Photography is my passion, my art and I need to make that form of my expression a priority. <em>It's on the calendar. The pics are printed and with the framer. This is a dream come true. Gives me the shakey hands to think about it. Details to come.</em>

3. Have over 150 shoots. <em>I'm more than half way there! Can't cross it off yet.</em>

4. Run a photography workshop, I want to share what I know with others, and hopefully learn something too. <em>It's on the calendar! Look for September workshops. Right now I have 2 dates and a kickass workshop planned. It's the Fabulous Photography Workshop series!</em>

5. Some small stuff, shopping cart for proof page, <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">new blog, new pics on website</span> (almost done with that one YES), you get the idea, for most of this stuff I need Jon's help. <em>Shopping cart is on the verge of being done! Can't wait!</em>

6. <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">Get 1,000 fans on my facebook page. I'm not sure if this directly results in new clients, but it can't hurt. Just 500 to go. Yikes that's a lot! Please suggest my page to friends, that would be awesome, and help a lot! </span> <em>Done! Thank you Thank you!</em>

7. I have 2 photography book ideas, but I have no idea where to start. This year I'm going to start and see what happens.

8. Finally I want to start a charity organization that takes pictures of kids in poverty. I've seen those kids, I've worked with those families and those kids deserve good pictures too! <em> While I haven't started an organization I am now trying to get active in 2 photography charities, and I've made donations to almost a dozen organizations.</em>

<em><span style="font-style: normal;">OK, so not bad! In fact I'm liking where this is going. Thank you all for you super awesome fab support and words of encouragement. I do have the most fabulous people in my life.  I just hope I can repay you someday in some way!</span></em>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Newborn Photography~ Kansas City Photographer</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1051</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 12 Jul 2010 22:19:10 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1051</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a rel="attachment wp-att-1052" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1051/eliz1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1052" title="eliz1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/eliz1.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">So sometimes babies do cute things. Wait I take that back, babies are always doing cute things. Even their little cries are cute. I think it's the only way we are still in existence. God said ok I know I am about to give you a huge burden, one that most days you'll wake up wondering how you'll survive. But, I'm gonna make it real cute. And so we have babies. Because they're cute. After looking at this little baby you might decide you need one for yourself, or need another one.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Being a baby is awesome, it's the only time a double chin looks good!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1056" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1051/eliz5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1056" title="eliz5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/eliz5.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1054" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1051/eliz3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1054" title="eliz3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/eliz3.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">If you're thinking this baby looks fat, you're right at just a few days old this little porker barely fit into my newborn props. I love a fat baby. And Axel is no exception. You remember his mommy Elizabeth when she had the beautiful belly. Well look what she was hiding inside. Axel was an awseome model. We was awake, he was alert and then he went to sleep. A perfect shoot for a perfect baby.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1053" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1051/eliz2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1053" title="eliz2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/eliz2.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Who can resist really?</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1055" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1051/eliz4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1055" title="eliz4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/eliz4.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a><a rel="attachment wp-att-1057" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1051/eliz6"></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Nick, Elizabeth, and Axel I am so lucky to know you. I look forward to capturing your family for years to come.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1057" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1051/eliz6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1057" title="eliz6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/eliz6.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a>]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Newborn Photography~ Kansas City</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1060</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 14 Jul 2010 02:19:13 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1060</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a rel="attachment wp-att-1066" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1060/ja1-3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1066" title="ja1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/ja11.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Meet Riley! Looking at this adorable pic you might find it hard to believe she's just a newborn. The seriousness of this expression belongs on the cover of a magazine, or CD. But I find it perfect. It's like she's saying, please give me a bottle... or hold me... or wrap me in a warm blanket so I can sleep the afternoon away.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1069" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1060/ja4-3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1069" title="ja4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/ja41.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Riley was so perfect the whole shoot. She was a model model, minus the fact that she refused to go to sleep. Most my babies do. I think I have too much energy to make them fall asleep. As long as the little ones stay happy I'm happy.</p>


<a rel="attachment wp-att-1067" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1060/ja2-4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1067" title="ja2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/ja21.jpg" alt="" width="467" height="700" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is Riley with her daddy Jody. It is already so obvious she is going to be daddy's little girl! Jody absolutely adores her, from her perfect tiny toes, to her perfect little eyelashes.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1070" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1060/ja5-3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1070" title="ja5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/ja51.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Janee is equally obsessed. She seemed to have so much intuition about Riley's needs.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1071" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1060/ja6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1071" title="ja6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/ja6.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1068" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1060/ja3-3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1068" title="ja3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/ja31.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Janee and Jody thanks so much for giving me the chance to take these pics. I hope you cherish them forever. I'm excited to watch Riley grow.</p>]]></content:encoded>

		<content:encoded><![CDATA[This is the Parker family and I had the most difficult time deciding which pics to put on the blog. I've been dabbling in slideshows for awhile trying to find a program that best suits me. So I decided to share their awesome session via slideshow. You should know little Parker truly is the diva she seems to be in the pics, and little Braxton truly is the little sweet heart he seems to be. They were both a blast to work with and I always enjoy taking their pictures. Thank you Rachel and Olin for letting Jon and I hang out with your awesome fam for awhile. It was the most perfect evening!

	<item>
		<title>Baby Pictures~ Kansas City Photographer</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1078</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 19 Jul 2010 22:41:56 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1078</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a rel="attachment wp-att-1085" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1078/claire7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1085" title="claire7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/claire7.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1087" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1078/claire9"></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is Claire! And she had her pictures taken for her first birthday!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1082" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1078/claire4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1082" title="claire4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/claire4.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Claire has a viabrant personality.  She is curious, excited, and overall happy. Did I mention she loves to crawl. SHE LOVES TO CRAWL and laugh at the same time.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1081" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1078/claire3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1081" title="claire3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/claire3.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a>She loves to crawl so much she spent most of her time crawling right off the set.  Lucky for me I had to fabulous parents on hand to pick her up and start her over...on the other side of the studio. LOL</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1086" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1078/claire8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1086" title="claire8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/claire8.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a><a rel="attachment wp-att-1084" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1078/claire6"></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">She also loves to point at EVERYTHING! I love this picture I mean she's pointing at me, or the camera, doesn't get much better than that. Susie and Cliff were so great at laughing right along with me. You can't control kids and that's what makes their pictures so awesome!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1084" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1078/claire6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1084" title="claire6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/claire6.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">I know you're thinking the same thing as me. Why doesn't Cliff have his toes painted too? Don't forget to notice those adorable wrinkles on Claire's legs. Perfection!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1080" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1078/claire2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1080" title="claire2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/claire2.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">We finished our shoot with a cake. Everything in life should end with cake! Some kids love cake some don't...</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1079" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1078/claire1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1079" title="claire1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/claire1.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a>Claire loves cake! I love the balloon in the pic! Want one for your next shoot? Just let me know, there is a secret place in downtown Blue Springs that can balloon anything.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is Claire...</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1087" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1078/claire9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1087" title="claire9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/claire9.jpg" alt="" width="399" height="600" /></a></p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Children Photography~Kansas City</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1090</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 20 Jul 2010 15:36:28 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1090</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a rel="attachment wp-att-1094" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1090/bon4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1094" title="bon4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/bon4.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Prepare yourself! It's the Bondi boys, and they are even more adorable in person than they are in these pics!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is Charlie and the shoot was really all about him, even though his brother was more than happy to jump in and share the spotlight. Both boys have the brightest personalities, they are all over the place and happy so so happy.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1098" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1090/bon8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1098" title="bon8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/bon8.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Michael decided he should hang from a tree. Check out those awesome teeth. He did this when the camera wasn't ready, so I had him redo it, and he did. Just like that. Sometimes it's moments like this when you realize how fast time flies. I remember taking Michael's pics when he wasn't walking, now he's hanging form trees.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1099" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1090/bon9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1099" title="bon9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/bon9.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Ok this pic is not wall worthy, but it's hilarious. To me it looks like they're on a roller coaster.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1095" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1090/bon5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1095" title="bon5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/bon5.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Thank you Charlie for being so near perfection. Even your cowlick is perfect.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1097" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1090/bon7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1097" title="bon7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/bon7.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">He thought it would be fun to run off into the deep dark woods alone. Brave little boy!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1096" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1090/bon6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1096" title="bon6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/bon6.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is one of my favs from the shoot. I knew the rocks would be the perfect spot, but the light was all patchy coming through the trees, so I snapped a few off just because. Just as I did the clouds handed me a gift by covering up the sun and acting as a softbox. I clicked a few more. As it turns out I like the patchy light ones better. Sometimes as a photographer you just never know.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1092" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1090/bon2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1092" title="bon2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/bon2.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I'll title this one "Little boys and their scars"!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1093" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1090/bon3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1093" title="bon3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/bon3.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This willow tree was gorgeous, just had to share a pic of it.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1100" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1090/bon10"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1100" title="bon10" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/bon10.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Felicia and Michael, thank you so much for having such beautiful boys. I know they may make you tired with their endless energy, but they are perfect inside and out!</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Newborn Photography~ Kansas City</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1108</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 22 Jul 2010 15:43:50 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1108</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a rel="attachment wp-att-1109" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1108/well1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1109" title="well1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/well1.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Baby Hunter at just a week old. I know newbies can't smile on purpose, but I swear this little guy is.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1112" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1108/well4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1112" title="well4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/well4.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">The newborn "style" is the sleepy baby all curled up in a basket with their eyes closed. I love that look, and I know that most the time newborn have googly eyes because their muscles have not yet developed, but I like pictures of newborns with their eyes open, and closed. Especially when we can get them both looking the same direction.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1113" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1108/well5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1113" title="well5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/well5.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Just notice the sock fuzz on his itty bitty toes.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1110" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1108/well2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1110" title="well2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/well2.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">You may be thinking Hunter looks like a peaceful little guy, but I have a feeling he's going to be a tough guy someday. His dad Travis competes in strong man competitions and he's no little guy. But, holding Hunter he melted like butter.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1114" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1108/well6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1114" title="well6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/well6.jpg" alt="" width="467" height="700" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">I love the hammock shot but a lot of people out there seem to think I just hang the little tike in midair. Not the case, for you worried mommas out there. Actually Sarah is holding the bottom of the hammock and Travis is holding the top and his back. Jon is the backup. Safety with the newborns is always my first concern.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Don't forget to notice the little monkey toes.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1111" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1108/well3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1111" title="well3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/well3.jpg" alt="" width="467" height="700" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I love this last shot, and I love that I got to work with such an awesome family. I feel like I've known Sarah forever, I look forward to many more photo sessions.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Kid Photography~ Kansas City</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1123</link>
		<pubDate>Sun, 01 Aug 2010 16:01:11 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1123</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a rel="attachment wp-att-1127" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1123/clem4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1127" title="clem4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/clem4.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is little Oliver and he really is this cute!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1126" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1123/clem3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1126" title="clem3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/clem3.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="467" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">These are his crazy brothers Jonah and Hayden. Jonah is all about having fun, he is a free spirit that loves to smile. His brother is a much more serious kid, it's probably safe to say they're opposite. But just as this picture shows they are buddies. Competitive, but mostly friends. Jonah is more worried about sports and how to have fun, while Hayden is all about learning. Only in first grade and already reading and comprehending Little House on the Prairie, Hayden is a book worm. He even had a mad science birthday party where they did fun and crazy experiments. Sounds pretty fun to me. Oh did I mention he's polite, like from another time polite. I was impressed, however I can really relate to Jonah more. I did not memorize the periodic table just for fun.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>


<a rel="attachment wp-att-1125" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1123/clem2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1125" title="clem2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/clem2.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This post is really about Oliver since he was the man of the hour. It's hard to say which direction Oliver's personlity will go, being he's only one. There is however one obvisous fact. He's got a personality, a BIG one! And he loves cookies. He was surrounded by cookies the whole time. Any face you see that isn't smiling is him asking for more cookies. HAHA During shoots we give kids cookies. Keeping them happy is kinda important, and eventually they'll be older and cookie negotiation will be a non issue.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1128" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1123/clem5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1128" title="clem5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/clem5.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">These are his dynamic parents Jill and Mark.  With three boys under the age of 8 you gotta give them props for being so much fun. They are laid back and loving, just trying to let their boys become whoever, or whatever they want to become.  Jill also introduced me to Tea Drops <a href="http://www.teadrops.us/">http://www.teadrops.us/</a> and bubble tea so I will love her forever!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I can't wait to watch these boys grow up from behind my camera.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1124" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1123/clem1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1124" title="clem1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/clem1.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Big Dreams, and firsts for me.</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1131</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 27 Jul 2010 04:48:12 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1131</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[It's so easy when you're a kid to say that ya wanna do this, ya wanna do that, ya wanna change the world.  But something happens as we get older. I think the world handicaps us with the agreements we start to make. We start to think that only the beautiful, intelligent, super talented, and "special" people do those things the rest of us dream about. I am just as guilty as the majority of the world, and every day I still battle those nasty agreements. I call it head trash, but it really just boils down to excuses that keep me from feeling the guilt that follows failure. I don't know how far I've come, but I know every day I wake up and try to do something that brings me closer to my ultimate goals. Slowly the little goals build until I am accomplishing a big goal. My first art gallery opening is my second big goal! Someday I hope it's just one of those little goals, but for now, today, it's big. With this accomplishment comes more fear and head trash to boggle my mind. Getting the gallery, and artwork together was easy. Now I have to worry about how to get people to come, how much wine to buy, what to wear, and how to be "that girl" you know the artist. That last one makes me sweat. Knowing I'll be surrounded by my incredible, supportive friends eases the anxiety, but I'm still pretty sure I won't sleep Thursday the 5th. :)

I hope you can come out and enjoy the crazy festivities that we call "First Fridays" here in KC. My signature pieces will be for sale, but I'll also have smaller 8x10 and 5x7 prints for sale as well.  The gallery is just a few doors down form Lulu's noodle house, I'll have a sign out front. Come by and say hi, get a glass of wine, and maybe even find something that will look good on your wall. Oh, and please invite your friends, remember that little bit of head trash I mentioned a second ago.

I can't wait to see you Friday the 6th. :)

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1133" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1131/postcard1w"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1133" title="postcard1w" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/postcard1w.jpg" alt="" width="738" height="538" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1134" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1131/postcard2w"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1134" title="postcard2w" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/postcard2w.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Children Photography~Kansas City</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1146</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 27 Jul 2010 18:00:52 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1146</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">Adorable....nuff said!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1140" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?attachment_id=1140"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1140" title="glas1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/glas1.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is Annie, and she is just about as perfect as perfect can be.  As you can see she's super photogenic, but what you can't see is that she is so patient, understanding, and willing to do everything her mom Melissa and I asked.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1144" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?attachment_id=1144"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1144" title="glas5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/glas5.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">She is also super good with her little brother Sam.  Sam is quiet and patient too, but he wasn't last time we took pics.  Last time he was scared, this time he was perfect just like his sister.  I mean it was really too easy.  Picking pics to share with you was a real challenge.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1143" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?attachment_id=1143"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1143" title="glas4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/glas4.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">And then Sam gave me this little jewel.  He's a serious little boy by nature, but he also loves to laugh.  I was just changing up my lights and he just stood waiting.  I feel like I can see right into his soul in this picture.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1142" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?attachment_id=1142"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1142" title="glas3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/glas3.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">I said Annie is good with her brother, but I didn't tell you that Sam loves his sister!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1145" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?attachment_id=1145"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1145" title="glas6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/glas6.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">See what I mean...</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1141" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?attachment_id=1141"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1141" title="glas2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/glas2.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a>Melissa I always love our time together!  I hope Ben loved his father's day gift as much as I liked taking them!</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Newborn pics and even more ~ Kansas City Photographer</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1150</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 30 Jul 2010 15:01:01 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1150</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">Today is the last day of July which is so very hard to believe. This summer is going by way too fast. I love summer, I mean I really love summer, and I don't want it to end. So today I'm thinking it's time to take a sec and think about the little moments. The ones that really matter. To show you what I mean I picked the Hendrickson family.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1158" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1150/hen8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1158" title="hen8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/hen8.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is Abby and her newborn baby brother Bob. I like to look at this picture because it makes me wonder what she's thinking. I tried to guess, but it just didn't feel right. So I'll leave those thoughts to you.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1157" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1150/hen7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1157" title="hen7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/hen7.jpg" alt="" width="467" height="700" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This picture is all about the moments daddys share with their little girls. There is such a special bond. I was happy to capture this moment because truly Abby is her daddy's little girl.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1154" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1150/hen4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1154" title="hen4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/hen4.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Danielle is such a beautiful mom, she was a natural. It can be frightening for new moms to bring their week old baby in for pics. It's just downright stressful, but Danielle was born to be a mom, so it was easy. Just as easy as it is for her to love her baby Bob.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1153" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1150/hen3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1153" title="hen3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/hen3.jpg" alt="" width="467" height="700" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1156" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1150/hen6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1156" title="hen6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/hen6.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1155" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1150/hen5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1155" title="hen5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/hen5.jpg" alt="" width="467" height="700" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1152" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1150/hen2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1152" title="hen2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/hen2.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1151" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1150/hen1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1151" title="hen1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/hen1.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I know it's my job to capture the faces of the people my clients want to remember. I embrace the responsibility and cherish the opportunitiy to work with amazing people. What I love about my job it capturing the moments.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Maternity Pictures~ Kansas City</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1168</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 02 Aug 2010 20:57:41 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1168</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a rel="attachment wp-att-1169" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1168/tb1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1169" title="tb1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/tb1.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="550" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is Buddy and Tara, and they are as in love as them seem to be in these pics.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I've know these two cool cats since college. They went to William Woods University too. They were both jocks in school, Tara played softball, and Buddy was a volleyball player. He was also in the same fraternity as Jon, and they were good buddies. The cool thing about Buddy and Tara is that they haven't changed. They are both the same fun-loving, outgoing people they were in school. I will admit seeing Tara with a belly was a bit freaky. It's always weird when your friends get pregnant for the first time. It's hard to imagine them as a momma, but Tara will be perfect.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1171" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1168/tb3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1171" title="tb3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/tb3.jpg" alt="" width="467" height="700" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1170" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1168/tb2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1170" title="tb2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/tb2.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">When I shared the pics with Tara she was absolutely glowing with pride and excitement. We talked about what it will be like in those first few moments when she becomes a mom and looks down at her little creation. She told me that she saw a new newborn recently and just wanted to hold it so bad. I took that as a sign of someone as ready as they'll ever be.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1172" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1168/tb4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1172" title="tb4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/tb4.jpg" alt="" width="467" height="700" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I'm happy to report that baby Adalynn Kay Smith has arrived and is doing so well! Tara and Buddy are parents now, and they are doing a fabulous job!</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Non-Thanksgiving Thanks?</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1176</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 04 Aug 2010 07:28:38 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1176</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[I know it's not Thanksgiving or anything, but every now and then a little soft spot in my heart cries out thank you, thank you, and insists on being heard. And I'm getting so close to my gallery opening, and it's 2 in the morning, and who really thinks clearly at 2 in the morning anyway.

So here goes.

Thank you Jon for giving so much of your free time to this gallery opening. You have totally revamped my website, designed a poster for the sign outside the door, and you read all my crazy text about each piece, even though you lived it. Being supportive isn't always easy, but you make it look like it is. And sorry for not putting the computer down tonight when you were dancing around the living room trying to get my attention. I should have stopped and danced with you.

Thank you Cara for being the most supportive friend I have! You helped me pick out pics, talked strategy until you were blue in the face, and helped me put together matted pics even when I didn't ask. Oh and you're going to help with wine and sales the night of. (you probably didn't know that one yet) I don't know where I would be without you. I guess I need to also thank Ian in advance for filming the event. Ian you're a cool guy and I'm really happy Cara is marrying you.

Thank you Justin for helping with sound and video production. You've been so awesome. I can tell you care, and caring people are cool, especially caring people with a band. <a href="http://http://www.guskc.com/">http://www.guskc.com/</a> Thanks for letting me sing with you even though I can't sing. Next time it's best to pick out a song that is mostly shouting.

Thank you to all the friends that reposted info about my gallery opening. So many of you have shared the info with your friends on facebook. I love you, love you for doing that. And of course thank you for coming. Especially my fam from the other side of the state! Much love!!!

Let the countdown begin...

Oh and no post is complete without a pic. Here's another one that will be featured at the event this Friday. It's perfect for this post.

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1177" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1176/purity"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-1177" title="Purity" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/Purity-600x900.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="675" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Purity</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>The night before...</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1184</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 06 Aug 2010 03:43:04 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1184</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1187" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1184/gla1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1187" title="gla1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/gla1.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">So it's here, the dreaded night before. I'm going over and over my to do/remember list, in hopes that I'll get everything I've forgotten. Haha!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">So I thought maybe my friends could help me. Here goes...</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">Art</span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">Business cards </span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">Food and wine</span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">Music- </span>live music is from 7-10</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Music for non live music times</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">portrait art slideshow</span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">attire for me</span> thanks sista sista for coming over today and helping me accessorize</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">attire for Jon</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">haircut for jon</span>- he didn't understand why he needed a haircut and cute oufit. BOYS!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1186" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1184/gal3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1186" title="gal3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/gal3.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">website- here he is working on it at 10. He's pretty frustrated right now. I guess writing code is hard.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">small prints</span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="text-decoration: line-through;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1188" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1184/gal4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1188" title="gal4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/gal4.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a></span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">
</span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">print stands</span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">cups</span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">napkins and toothpicks- UGH almost forgot</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">Easel </span> this will be outside the front door on the sidewalk</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1185" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1184/gal2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1185" title="gal2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/gal2.jpg" alt="" width="466" height="700" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">did I mention the art?</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I guess lastly I'll need a good night sleep! Night Night everyone. I hope I don't dream of tomatoes.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">

	<item>
		<title>Maternity Photography~Kansas City</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1191</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 11 Aug 2010 03:19:28 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1191</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a rel="attachment wp-att-1192" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1191/car1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1192" title="car1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/car1.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="350" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">I recently saw an article in a professional photographer's magazine about maternity pics. First of all they were kinda creepy, too posed, and well just blah. I love doing maternity pics and not to toot my own horn TOOT TOOT, but I think my maternity pics are some of the best! I have to admit I'm lucky because I work with tons of beautiful women like Carroll. Beautiful, fun-loving couples that make it easy to capture their love.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1194" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1191/car3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1194" title="car3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/car3.jpg" alt="" width="466" height="700" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Really Carroll can you be more gorgeous? Brian you are one lucky guy.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1193" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1191/car2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1193" title="car2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/car2.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">I have to admit Carroll is lucky too. Brian is obsessed with her, and their future baby. I think they'll make a splendid team!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1195" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1191/car5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1195" title="car5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/car5.jpg" alt="" width="467" height="700" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Thanks you two for being adorable, in love, and so easy to work with! I couldn't even begin to pick the pics to share.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Children Photography~ Kansas City</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1201</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 11 Aug 2010 13:28:34 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1201</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">When I'm sitting on the floor with my clients they give me the most peculiarlooks. Take for example baby Izzy. First she was cautious, then curious, then befuddled. I love the faces kids make when they are just being kids. Makes me laugh out loud when I'm editing.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1202" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1201/iz1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1202" title="iz1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/iz1.jpg" alt="" width="720" height="288" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Izzy not only has a big personality, but also a beautiful face. I mean really. She's a dream.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1204" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1201/iz3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1204" title="iz3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/iz3.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Izzy is also one of the most chilled out babies ever. She comes over to my house most Mondays to watch episodes of the bachelor. She is most happy being passed around, or just sitting in her mom's lap.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1203" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1201/iz2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1203" title="iz2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/iz2.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">You've probably inferred that Izzy's mom Heidi is also one of my good good friends. I've known Heidi forever, and she's an amazing friend, but an even more amazing mom. Some people are meant to be mom's and Heidi is one of them. I've never seen her happier than she is with Izzy.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1205" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1201/iz4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1205" title="iz4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/iz4.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Izzy I love you so much, and can't wait to be there to capture your years as you grow into an amazing woman.</p>]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>
		<wp:post_id>1201</wp:post_id>
		<wp:post_date>2010-08-11 08:28:34</wp:post_date>
		<wp:post_date_gmt>2010-08-11 13:28:34</wp:post_date_gmt>

	<item>
		<title>Chapter 134~ More of my head trash...</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1209</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 12 Aug 2010 20:28:47 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1209</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Guilty! I'm guilty, I admit it, I'm not proud, but I compare my work to that of other artisits. Sometimes I think I'm better, sometimes I know they're better. It's such a natural human thing to do. I try really hard to compete only with myself, but we're surrounded with amazing photography, it's everywhere. The digital camera has taken some of the novelty out of photography. So I like need to get to the point, right?

My point.

Tuesday I took the day to hang with Cara at the pool. Her last day of summer before the start of school, and I'll admit I needed a day off. Anyway, she saw in my bag a professional photography magazine and said "oh that's a creepy picture". I immediately grabbed the magazine, curious. I really value Cara's opinion. To my surprise it was a picture of a newborn. Now I hate to pull this exact cover up because this photographer in my opinion is amazing. But Cara thought it looked unnatural, awkward, and well creepy. It's kinda the style right now to take beautiful, sleepy, little newborns and put them in weird settings, and poses. This particular baby was folded over itself with it's hands under it's head and it was smiling. Now you know it wasn't really smiling, but the photographer was good and captured a moment. So the point...I really need to focus on my style. Get back to feeling the moment and capturing it. Here I was trying to recreate that style, the "in" style, when I really needed to focus on what I'm good at. Capturing the emotion. Mostly between parents and their newborns. Mostly love. So if everyday has a lesson, today mine would be to love my work with the understanding that photography really is an art and everyone has a style.

Check out these pics and you'll see what I mean. If these don't make you feel something you might need to go the ER right away for CPR.

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1214" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1209/par1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1214" title="par1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/par1.jpg" alt="" width="467" height="700" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1215" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1209/par2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1215" title="par2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/par2.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1217" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1209/par4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1217" title="par4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/par4.jpg" alt="" width="467" height="700" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">I just can't stop looking at this pic! It's hilarious and awesome.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1216" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1209/par3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1216" title="par3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/par3.jpg" alt="" width="467" height="700" /></a>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Marketing Tips</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1223</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 16 Aug 2010 16:13:02 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1223</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[A few weeks ago Jon looked up from his mac and said "you're a little marketing facebook wizard". My immediate response, "Does that mean I can go to Hogwarts?"

Recently I've been getting tons of comments about my marketing techniques, and some requests for info. My first reaction is yah right 90% of the time I have no idea what I'm doing. But since Jon thinks I'm a wizard, I guess I'll give this a go. I can't guarentee that any of these techniques will work for you, I just know what works for me.  I'm a list maker so that's what you're gettin'. Here goes.

1. <strong>Branding-</strong> You gotta have a brand. When I say brand I mean your look, your logo, even you personal image is important. In my bus. I am my product for the most part. So everything is important, how I dress, what I say, it's all part of the package. That's not to say any look goes, I'm just saying if I showed up to a shoot wearing hiking boots, and a khaki shirt with tons of pockets, I'm giving people a different impression than perhaps the one I want. So brand carefully. My brand in the simplist form is the AC you see on everything. Now that I've taken on the fine art in my bus. the AC is what will tie it all together.

2. <strong>Social Media</strong>- Most of you know how I market in this department. I think there's a fine line between just enough and way too much. I want to be present on your facebook page, but I don't want to be in your face. Haha The last thing you want people to do is hide you. eek. It's also important to blog regularly. 2 reasons, it keeps your clients up on your most recent work, and it helps your ratings in the google dept. So blog and blog often. You can't blog too much. Go for it. Just be sure to tag each and every blog you write. You can see what words are searched most often if you google keywords. See<a href="http://http://www.google.com/search?source=ig&amp;hl=en&amp;rlz=1G1GGLQ_ENUS270&amp;q=keywords&amp;aq=f&amp;aqi=&amp;aql=&amp;oq=&amp;gs_rfai="> http://www.google.com/search?source=ig&amp;hl=en&amp;rlz=1G1GGLQ_ENUS270&amp;q=keywords&amp;aq=f&amp;aqi=&amp;aql=&amp;oq=&amp;gs_rfai=</a>

3. <strong>Google</strong>- Gotta let google see you and make it easy for them to read you. Wordpress is great for now, but that could change. I've heard that blogger is no good for google to read, but google ownes them so who knows. By changing over to wordpress you'll lose blogger followers, but you might possibly get higher on the google pages. It's a give and a take I tell yah, and sometimes I just throw my hands up. My whole page is wordpress with some jquery.

4. <strong>Website</strong>- Speaking of wordpress, it's great, but I had a flash site before, and was at the top of most pages forKansas City newborns, maternity, and babies! Then I switched to wordpress and lost that ranking. No idea why. Google is a mystery, and I think they like it that way. You can try to web optomize by tagging, updating your page regularly, and being old, the site I mean. Even still it's a bit of a mystery. If you really want to get to the top, hire someone, but be careful, some companies are dirty and they'll get you kicked off of google. Give Justin over at Cowtown a buzz. He'll take care of you.<a href="http://http://cowtownmarketing.com/"> http://cowtownmarketing.com/</a> They can build your website too.

<strong>5. Advertising</strong>- Ugh! So hard to know what works. I've tried a variety of things, but what I've found that works best is google ads, facebook ads, and word of mouth. You can sign up for both google and facebook ads and only pay for clicks on your ads. That's awesome. But it can get expensive too. And it's really hard to track clicks that turn into customers.

<strong>6. Peeps</strong>- The last bit of advice I give you is to be yourself and love your people. Show them your true colors. Hold nothing back, share your up times and your down times. Celebrate and cry with your fans. They'll love you more for it. Probably the hardest thing I've had to learn to do. I'm a private person (pause for sarcastic laughter) and sharing my failures is hard to swallow, but it's getting easier. Be you, be loving, and reward your peeps for sharing you.

I hope these tidbits help. If you have your own tips I'd love to hear them just comment below. If you have a question you can comment that too.

Much love my friends!]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Headshots, Opera, and Cute Kids</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1224</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 13 Aug 2010 13:18:13 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1224</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1231" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1224/jo8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1231" title="jo8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/jo8.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Ever been to an Opera? Me neither, but I think it would be cool. That's why I'm going to go this year to the Lyric theatre to watch Joanna perform. Joanna contacted me to take some new headshots for her upcoming perfomance. I'm so happy for her. I know how hard she's worked to get to this place. People that follow their dreams warm my heart.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1230" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1224/jo7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1230" title="jo7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/jo7.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="751" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is her beautiful daughter Kylee. It's hard to believe she's gotten so big. I remember when she was an itty bitty baby still just as beautiful as she is now.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1228" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1224/jo4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1228" title="jo4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/jo4.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1226" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1224/jo2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1226" title="jo2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/jo2.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is Kylee's little sister and they couldn't be more different. Kylee is quiet, reserved and easy going. Her sister is wild, opinionated, and always smiling and ready for fun. Both girls are super sweet.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1229" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1224/jo5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1229" title="jo5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/jo5.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="1550" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Both girls are also so very very beautiful! I had a lot of fun taking their pictures and already look forward to the next time.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Wedding Photography ~ Kansas City</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1249</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 17 Aug 2010 17:40:42 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1249</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">This love started with a boy and a girl. A boy not sure of marriage, and a girl sure of love. And sure enough they found each other!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">It wasn't coincidence, it wasn't by chance, it wasn't a random meeting at a bar, this relationship was fate. Let me explain. Amber is a teacher, and at parent teacher conferences one of her parents, Cheryl, tried to hook her up with her handsome cousin Sean. Amber was all no way, so of course she didn't pursue. Then a year later while coaching cross country, Cheryl again tried to convince Amber that dating her cousin was the best idea ever. Amber must have given in because Sean called her and they had a fateful first date. I guess the rest is history because after 5 years of fun, they are now married.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">The day started flawlessly. A warm breeze in the air, blue skies, and Amber with all her besties getting ready for her big day.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1250" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1249/attachment/1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1250" title="1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/1.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="700" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">The dress was perfect.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1251" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1249/attachment/2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1251" title="2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/2.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="750" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">The flowers were perfect! This is the 3rd wedding I've seen use <a href="http://http://www.hy-vee.com/">Hy-Vee</a> and each time the flowers have been this good!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1252" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1249/attachment/3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1252" title="3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/3.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="750" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Minus the fact that she had a few butterflies, Amber was perfect!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1253" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1249/attachment/4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1253" title="4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/4.jpg" alt="" width="800" height="450" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Her bridesmaids were gorgeous and ready.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1254" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1249/5-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1254" title="5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/5.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Makeup and hair...Perfect! Thanks to Alecia and Shannon at Shag Salon.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1255" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1249/6-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1255" title="6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/6.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="700" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">But then the skies went from blue to <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">grey </span>black. And sheets of rain started coming down. While everyone followed the Doppler radar, I prayed to the rain gods. Amber wasn't so worried about the rainbecause she knew at the end of the day she would be married to the man of her dreams, her best friend, Sean.  So while the rain poured down I headed to see Sean as he prepared for his big day.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1256" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1249/attachment/7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1256" title="7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/7.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="700" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Just as we arrived at the chapel the Gods granted my request because the sun was out and there was a big blue sky. It was hot, sweaty, humid, did I mention it was horribly hot, but it wasn't raining. And the bride and groom were glowing.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1257" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1249/attachment/8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1257" title="8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/8.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="700" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">The picture below was taken by my mighty assistant Cara Doumitt! She is so talented!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Amber and her momma are so close, so this is picture perfect.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1258" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1249/attachment/9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1258" title="9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/9.jpg" alt="" width="465" height="700" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">The chapel was perfection! <a href="http://http://www.pilgrimchapel.org/">Pilgram Chapel</a></p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1259" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1249/attachment/10"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1259" title="10" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/10.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="700" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1260" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1249/attachment/11"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1260" title="11" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/11.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="700" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">And as they exited there were bubbles.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1261" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1249/attachment/12"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1261" title="12" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/12.jpg" alt="" width="900" height="400" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1262" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1249/attachment/13"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1262" title="13" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/13.jpg" alt="" width="466" height="700" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1263" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1249/attachment/14"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1263" title="14" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/14.jpg" alt="" width="800" height="364" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1265" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1249/attachment/16"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1265" title="16" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/16.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="700" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1264" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1249/attachment/15"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1264" title="15" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/15.jpg" alt="" width="800" height="343" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">The bridal party was fab! They were up for anything like walking down the middle of a Kansas City street.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1266" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1249/17-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1266" title="17" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/17.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1267" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1249/18-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1267" title="18" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/18.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Typically the grooms are ready to get to the reception in a hurry, but Sean loves photography so we were able to get some fabulous pictures.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">They are so in love that taking beautiful pictures on their wedding day was easy.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1268" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1249/attachment/19"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1268" title="19" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/19.jpg" alt="" width="800" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This one might be my fav! There was this most perfect golden light coming in and hitting Amber perfectly! Not to mention their expressions are magazine quality! Kudos!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1269" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1249/attachment/20"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1269" title="20" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/20.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1270" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1249/attachment/21"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1270" title="21" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/21.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="750" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1272" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1249/attachment/23"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1272" title="23" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/23.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1271" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1249/attachment/22"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1271" title="22" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/22.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">You know I can't resist a cute baby!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1273" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1249/attachment/24"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1273" title="24" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/24.jpg" alt="" width="710" height="474" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Amber you are absolutely gorgeous!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1274" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1249/attachment/25"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1274" title="25" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/25.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Amber and her mom are close like sisters, act like sisters, and look like sisters! So cool!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1275" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1249/attachment/26"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1275" title="26" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/26.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Boulevard beer, wine, Italian cookies, and cake. This is the perfect night for me.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1278" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1249/attachment/29"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1278" title="29" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/29.jpg" alt="" width="582" height="700" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">The reception was at <a href="http://http://www.boulevard.com/wp-content/themes/boulevard960/ageverify.php?r=http://www.boulevard.com%2Fbeers%2Fabout-our-beers%2F">Boulevard Brewery</a>. I'm so proud of this Kansas City landmark so I was excited to shoot the reception. The weather was flawless so everyone stood out on the balcony most of the night.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1277" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1249/attachment/28"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1277" title="28" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/28.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="700" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Amber and Sean I have no doubt you will have an amazing life together! Full of love, babies, and adventures to remember.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1276" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1249/attachment/27"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1276" title="27" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/27.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">It's a good thing this girl was able to convince this boy that marriage was for him because they make a perfect team.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">If you or someone you know is interested in booking a 2011 wedding, please have them contact me. I only take on 10 weddings a year and currently have 6 scheduled for 2011. :) That way I can give my brides my whole heart!</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Maternity Photography~Kansas City</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1284</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 20 Aug 2010 17:48:24 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1284</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a rel="attachment wp-att-1285" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1284/vin1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1285" title="vin1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/vin1.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Meet Sarah and Matthew. Two happy people, happy to be in love, and even more happy to be pregnant.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1287" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1284/vin3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1287" title="vin3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/vin3.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Some women seem to be nervous when they're pregnant, or anxious, or just down right scared. That would be me. But Sarah was at ease and so very excited to be a mom. I think you can tell from the pictures that she has definitely got the love gene. She has so much to give. Matthew just soaks it up. During our sometimes I felt like they didn't even notice I was there. They are a real unit, and little Tavin is lucky to have them as parents.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1286" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1284/vin2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1286" title="vin2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/vin2.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Sarah and Matthew I wish you the best of luck as parents not that you'll need it. Just keep loving eachother the way you already do!</p>]]></content:encoded>
