	<item>
		<title>Children photography~ Kansas City</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1292</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 25 Aug 2010 14:39:01 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1292</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a rel="attachment wp-att-1295" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1292/wil3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1295" title="wil3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/wil3.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Meet most perfect adorable Colton and Keira! As you can see they are a perfect pair. This is one of my favorite shots to take of the siblings when the little one is still too young to sit up by themselves. However, it doesn't always turn out this perfectly! Notice the contrast in eyes!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1300" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1292/wil8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1300" title="wil8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/wil8.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Keira is a spicy, fun-loving ,little girl that adores life like she adores her momma and daddy. Here she's smiling at her mom Devin camera left.</p>


<a rel="attachment wp-att-1297" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1292/wil5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1297" title="wil5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/wil5.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Colton is the typical chilled out second child. He's chubby, happy, and makes faces like this! I love it!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1299" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1292/wil7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1299" title="wil7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/wil7.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This picture should remind us all the close our eyes every now and then and take it the perfection we call life.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1293" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1292/wil1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1293" title="wil1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/wil1.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1298" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1292/wil6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1298" title="wil6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/wil6.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Kids love to try to see me through the lens. I love the pics I get in the process.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1296" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1292/wil4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1296" title="wil4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/wil4.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1294" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1292/wil2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1294" title="wil2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/wil2.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">When you're 3 and adorable you can do things like dance around the studio in nothing but a crown and tutu.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Jason, Devin, Keira, and Colton thanks again for allowing me to capture these fleeting moments. I cherish them, and look forward to the next time.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Les Bourgeois Wine, and Small town Rocheport</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1303</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 27 Aug 2010 17:40:56 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1303</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[It started with a photo shoot or two. My awesome cooperating teacher from my student teaching days wanted me to take pictures of her adorable 5 year old daughter Stella. I was all, absolutely, but they live in Fulton. 2 hours away, in our old college town. But another client wanted to do pics in St. Louis as well, so I planned on stopping in Fulton taking pics and then driving to St. Louis for another shoot. Then we would get to see Jon's fam. Perfect right? Not quite my St. Louis client had to reschedule due to unexpected business travel, so I was going to have to reschedule Kara's shoot as well. I was disappointed with a capital D. Whenever something disappointing or discouraging comes up I try to turn it into something even better. So I thought hmmm...and then it hit me, Jon and I hadn't celebrated our anniversary, in fact, we hadn't had alone time in FOREVER. We constantly joke about the date night that never seems to happen. So I decided to book a b and b in small town Rocheport and enjoy an afternoon sipping wine at the A frame at Les Bourgeois winery. The day was even more perfect than originally planned. I love when something expected turns into something wonderfully unexpected. Perfection with a capital P.

I hope that after seeing the pics you are excited to take your own trip to little Rocheport where the wine goes down easy and the light is always golden. Let me tell you more about my day.

At about noon after scoping out some great spots we started our shoot with the Wagner clan. They are a happy bunch and Stella is about as photogenic as they get. Here are just a few from our shoot. I really couldn't pick because there were somewhere around 60 perfect pictures! But here are some favs, maybe later I'll post the rest on a slide show.

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1306" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1303/wag3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1306" title="wag3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/wag3.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Stella wasn't afraid to work it. No coaching was involved. This little one is oozing with confidence. Hold on to it girl, you rock!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1311" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1303/wag8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1311" title="wag8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/wag8.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">For sure Daddy's little girl.  Stella adores Jason</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1305" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1303/wag2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1305" title="wag2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/wag2.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">I just love it when kids do there thing. I'm just happy I had my camera ready to capture this Stella moment!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1310" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1303/wag7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1310" title="wag7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/wag7.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">If you know Stella this is her smile, warm and radiant. She doesn't mess around with grumpy.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1307" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1303/wag4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1307" title="wag4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/wag4.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">PS her toenails are purple too! LOVE IT! Sparkly purple toes are pretty close to perfection.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1308" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1303/wag5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1308" title="wag5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/wag5.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Kara and Stella have such a bond. I just know they'll always be close.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1309" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1303/wag6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1309" title="wag6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/wag6.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Stella was amazing the whole time, but I think by the time we were done she was pooped, but still smiling! Sometimes ya just gotta lay on a log.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1304" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1303/wag1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1304" title="wag1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/wag1.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I'm so happy we made this happen. Kara your family is great and I look forward to more pics with Stella in the future!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">After the shoot we headed back to Rocheport for some much needed down time. Of course I took my camera, even though Jon probably wouldn't have minded my leaving it in the car. I had to play with my new lens. Here are some pics I got. Ahh it's relaxing thinking about it. :)</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.missouriwine.com/">Les Bourgeois</a> is a fun winery and if you're ever driving through the state it's worth a stop off. You can sit under a tree at a picnic table high on the bluffs overlooking the Missouri river, drinking wine and eating cheese.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1319" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1303/roch8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1319" title="roch8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/roch8.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I love my hot hubby's mug! He has a great looking smirk.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1313" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1303/roch2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1313" title="roch2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/roch2.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">My favorite summer wine. Sweet and refreshing.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1316" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1303/roch5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1316" title="roch5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/roch5.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">After we checked into our little B and B, Jon needed a nap and I needed to catch some of this light before it was gone. So I took off down the street of this small town. The whole town is only a few blocks.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1315" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1303/roch4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1315" title="roch4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/roch4.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.rocheport.com/">Rocheport</a> isn't on the bluffs like the winery, it's down in the valley, right by the river. So the evening light comes in and fills the valley with this gooey golden light that makes everything look amazing. Even old chairs.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1318" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1303/roch7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1318" title="roch7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/roch7.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Everything in Rocheport is quaint and middle America. I wish I could have seen the town in it's booming railroad days. The railroad tracks are now a part of the 225 mile<a href="http://www.bikekatytrail.com/">Katy Trail</a>. You can walk it or bike it. I would love to go back and bike it this fall when the leaves are changing colors. There is an old railroad tunnel that totally gave me the creepers. I felt so unsafe walking through it. Obviously there isn't tracks, so no train was going to come through, but it sure felt like it. I regret not getting a picture of it.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1321" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1303/roch10"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1321" title="roch10" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/roch10.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is our bed and breakfast. The <a href="http://www.schoolhousebb.com/?tracker=googlelocal">Schoolhouse</a> was built in 1914, but you would never know. The owners have done a fabulous job of keeping it up, and thinking of every little detail to make the stay memorable. The bed was great, the heart shaped jacuzzi was better, and I loved the breakfast. We will definitely come back for another stay in a different room.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1320" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1303/roch9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1320" title="roch9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/roch9.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Old is cool!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1314" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1303/roch3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1314" title="roch3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/roch3.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I didn't get a pic of <a href="http://abigails-restaurant.com/">Abigail's</a> but I want to give them a shout out for the great meal. It's the only place to eat on a Sunday evening, but I would go back any day of the week. Everything was made fresh, in fact, the menu was on a white board with things scratched out as they ran out. And our dessert menu was handed to us on an index card.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1317" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1303/roch6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1317" title="roch6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/roch6.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is one of the most perfect spots for pictures the light was gorgeous. I told Jon we had to take a pic. So I se my camera up on a gate and focused and hoped for the best. I really want someone to get married in Rocheport so we can do pics here!!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1312" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1303/roch1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1312" title="roch1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/roch1.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Jon and I had a great time, but I'm ready to go back. There's something appealing about the simple life of a small town.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>The energy of a 2 year old ~ Kansas City Photographer</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1325</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 30 Aug 2010 22:28:45 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1325</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a rel="attachment wp-att-1327" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1325/1year2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1327" title="1year2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/1year2.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is Jacob and by lookng at this picture you're probably thinking he is totally posing. Well, think again. Jacob is two, and 2 year olds don't sit still, let alone pose for the camera. I didn't even know I had captured this most perfect expression of Jacob's until I was working in post production. You see Jacob was running around the back of our yard exploring every nook and cranny. Totally ignoring the fact that I was chasing him, or that his dad was asking him to do things. Two year olds have one objective and that is to discover the world one touch, one smell, one taste, and one question at a time.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1326" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1325/1year"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1326" title="1year" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/1year.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is Jacob with his awesome dad Nathan. As you can see both boys have great camera smiles!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1328" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1325/1year3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1328" title="1year3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/1year3.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">If only we could bottle the energy our little two year olds seem to have endless supply of, we would be soooo rich! Photographing two year olds is an adventure of my own, but I love it!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Jacob I loved taking your pictures. You are always welcome back to explore my yard some more!</p>]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>
		<wp:post_id>1325</wp:post_id>

	<item>
		<title>One year old pics~ Kansas City Photographer</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1340</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 01 Sep 2010 13:32:16 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1340</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">In the first year of life, babies change so much. I only get to see the babies in my life (my clients) about every 3 months that first year, so it amazes me how fast they change. They go from scrawny, bony, newborns, that can't even control the direction of their eyes. To pudgy, happy, wiggly babies that mostly just want to eat and witness the world around them. Before I know it they're crawling and pictures become a teeny bit more difficult, because now they want to become a part of the world. They explore, touch, taste, and want to learn. By the time they are one they are still rather reckless, but they are now entering childhood, no longer babies. Ready to walk and start learning to talk. They still have their adorable baby features, but their adult face is starting to take shape as is their personality.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is baby Keaton. An adorable little one year old ready to make the transition into childhood. And while newborns turn into children fast, I think children turn into adults even faster.</p>


<a rel="attachment wp-att-1355" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1340/1year7-4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1355" title="1year7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/1year73.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">His perfectly soft little feet will soon start getting calloused from walking, running, and tripping.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1352" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1340/1year4-3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1352" title="1year4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/1year42.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">His little hands will soon be capable of throwing a ball hard, catching frogs, and getting very dirty.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1354" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1340/1year6-3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1354" title="1year6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/1year62.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This little look will be for a girl and not the camera. He had the most grown up seriouscamera face, but I'm not going to lie he liked me. While shooting in the studio he would crawl over and into my lap. I would pick him up and he would laugh. It's hard to believe he'll be bigger than me someday.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1353" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1340/1year5-3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1353" title="1year5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/1year52.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Soon he'll be too cool to hug his mom, or sit on his dad's lap.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1356" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1340/1year8-3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1356" title="1year8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/1year82.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">And then there's little Sophi. Also one, and probably the happiest baby in the world! Seriously, she never stopped smiling. It was sooo easy.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1357" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1340/1yr9-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1357" title="1yr9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/1yr91.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">But eventually she'll stop wanting stuffed animals and start wanting name brand clothes.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1360" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1340/1yr12-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1360" title="1yr12" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/1yr121.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Eventually she won't want to sit around topless with a tutu on. Haha so cute!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1359" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1340/1yr11-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1359" title="1yr11" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/1yr111.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">She'll learn to be less violent when she kisses. She's seriously giving her cat a kiss. Hilarious!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1358" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1340/1yr10-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1358" title="1yr10" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/1yr101.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">And unfortunately she'll start caring what others think of her, although with Sophia I think she might be the exception. It seems to me the only thing she cares about is having fun, and maybe being the center of attention. While I was talking to her mom Bethany, she would randomly squeal. We would look at her and she would smile. This one might have potential for the silver screen. Seriously!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1350" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1340/1yr13"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1350" title="1yr13" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/1yr13.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Life goes by fast, enjoy the ride, and take lots of pictures along the way!</p>]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>
		<wp:post_id>1340</wp:post_id>
		<wp:post_date>2010-09-01 08:32:16</wp:post_date>

	</item>
	<item>
		<title>Baby Love~ Newborn Photography Kansas City</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1385</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 07 Sep 2010 17:56:20 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1385</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a rel="attachment wp-att-1392" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1385/joel7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1392" title="joel7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/joel7.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Baby Love: A great song by The Supremes, but also the special way new parents feel about their new arrivals. Baby Love.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1391" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1385/joel6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1391" title="joel6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/joel6.jpg" alt="" width="467" height="700" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Meet Ainsley the proud baby of parents Jenni, and Joel. Her parents have hard core baby love syndrome. They are the definition of obsessed. I don't think I need to say much about these newborn pictures, because the photos do their emotions justice.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1388" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1385/joel3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1388" title="joel3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/joel3.jpg" alt="" width="650" height="480" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">I do want to say that Jenni is a gorgeous momma. Red hair is my absolute favorite to photograph. Perfection!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1390" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1385/joel5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1390" title="joel5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/joel5.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Funny story, Joel and I swam on the same swim team as kids. He didn't know I was Allison McIntosh until he got to my house and we started taking pictures. Halfway through the shoot he made the connection and I remembered. Pretty funny how things work out. Joel was quite the swimmer as a kid now he's quite the daddy.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1393" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1385/joel8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1393" title="joel8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/joel8.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Ok not my most perfect picture but I couldn't resist. I just wished the bunny would have cooperated more. He refused to look at little Ainsley.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1386" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1385/joel1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1386" title="joel1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/joel1.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1389" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1385/joel4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1389" title="joel4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/joel4.jpg" alt="" width="466" height="700" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Ainsley was such an easy baby to photograph. Not sleepy, but definitely willing to let us take a pic of her pretty mug.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1387" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1385/joel2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1387" title="joel2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/joel2.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I can't wait to see Ainsley grow up. And I have no doubt her parents will always have baby love for her.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Newborn Photography~Kansas City</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1399</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 10 Sep 2010 02:07:20 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1399</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">This story starts like any good newborn story, with a belly.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1406" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1399/hor7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1406" title="hor7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/hor7.jpg" alt="" width="666" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1408" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1399/hor9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1408" title="hor9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/hor9.jpg" alt="" width="713" height="500" /></a>A perfect belly, beautiful really. This belly belongs to Colleen, she's one of those pretty pregnant people. I mean I think all pregnant women are glowing and beautiful, but some just seem to get lucky, and Colleen is one of those women.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1407" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1399/hor8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1407" title="hor8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/hor8.jpg" alt="" width="713" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is her baby Greyson, he's not so much a baby anymore and much more like a boy. He didn't really know what he was getting into when his parents told him he was going to be a big brother in a month. I'm sure ideas of a little playmate where first on his mind. Even though Lyla may not have met Greyson's expectations entirely, he loves her all the same.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">By the way Greyson is at that fun age for photogs when they like to make the cheese smile. It only lasts about a year, but man it's hard to get a genuine smile. I feel so fortunate to have captured this shot. This is Greyson's REAL smile. :)</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1405" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1399/hor6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1405" title="hor6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/hor6.jpg" alt="" width="715" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">I tried several times to type something about this pic, but words can't describe. It's soooo hard to get a good newborn /sibling pic. I usually warn parents about the bad odds, but on this day the odds were in our favor. Aww I can see this on their senior slidshow.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1402" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1399/hor3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1402" title="hor3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/hor3.jpg" alt="" width="713" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1404" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1399/hor5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1404" title="hor5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/hor5.jpg" alt="" width="715" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1403" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1399/hor4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1403" title="hor4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/hor4.jpg" alt="" width="666" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Colleen and Greg are such natural parents taking pictures was easy. Newborn shoots require patience, endurance, creativity...and milk.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1400" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1399/hor1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1400" title="hor1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/hor1.jpg" alt="" width="713" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1401" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1399/hor2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1401" title="hor2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/hor2.jpg" alt="" width="713" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Little Lyla you couldn't have been born into a better family. You will have so much love in your life!</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Maternity Pictures~Kansas City Photographer</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1412</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 16 Sep 2010 20:33:28 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1412</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a rel="attachment wp-att-1415" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1412/jeno3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1415" title="jeno3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/jeno3.jpg" alt="" width="749" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">I've been absent on the blog lately. Partly because I'm busy, partly because it's takes time I don't have, but mostly because I don't feel like I have the words to accurately describe the amazing people I get to work with. That was definitely the case with Jen. This is my third shoot with Jen this year and to say I think she's awesome would be an understatement. The first was boudoir where she bravely agreed to go with her sister in law, the second was for fun with her husband downtown, and now she's got this amazing belly.  Also she's got amazing Angelina Jolie lips. Jealous.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1416" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1412/jeno4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1416" title="jeno4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/jeno4.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">I stuggle with her story , because Jen was one of the many women who couldn't get pregnant. Tried for years, but nothing happened.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1418" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1412/jeno5-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1418" title="jeno5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/jeno51.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">She had several failed in vitro attempts. Which cost her a lot of money and even more heartache. On her final attempt, it took. Her pregnancy has been oh so much easier than the actual getting pregnant part. I didn't know Jen before she was pregnant, but she smiles all the time.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1414" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1412/jeno2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1414" title="jeno2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/jeno2.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">There's no way for me to put into words the feelings and emotions Jen must go through on a daily basis when she looks down at her round belly. I've never been there, and maybe it's even hard for Jen to put into words the power of these pictures. Here's what she wrote to me in an email after seeing her gallery.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">"I LOVE them! I had a big smile on my face the whole time I was looking at them. They make me very happy. You did a great job! I might not be able to choose which are my favorites! Lots of people are already commenting on them on facebook. I am so glad I did it. We've waited so long for this little guy and I know that in the future, as well as now, that I'll treasure these pictures. For a long time we didn't know if I'd even get pregnant so these pictures are a huge celebration and a reminder of the blessings we've been given."</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1413" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1412/jeno1">
<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1413" title="jeno1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/jeno1.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Newborn Shoot~ Kansas City Photography</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1425</link>
		<pubDate>Sun, 12 Sep 2010 21:06:01 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1425</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">A surprise, a gift from the heavens, an angel passed into the arms of special people lucky enough to have the responsibility. That is what a newborn baby is, and for Heather, that was a gift she had given up thinking she'd ever receive. Until she found out about baby Gianna!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1432" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1425/gia2-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1432" title="gia2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/gia21.jpg" alt="" width="742" height="500" /></a>I won't reveal Heather's age, I'll just say she looks amazing. But then you can see that for yourself. I was shocked when she revealed her true age to me in a casual conversation, as she stared, oozing love adoringly at her daughter. She explained that her age is making this life change easy.  Even at one week her favorite thing to do is cuddle with Gia on the couch. From my perspective, she just filled the hole in her heart she didn't know was there. Daddy Sammy is just as gaga. Sammy and I went to high school together, and I guess I never really pictured him as a dad. Well, he's a natural, he made it look easy. I was totally impressed.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1429" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1425/gia4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1429" title="gia4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/gia4.jpg" alt="" width="699" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Sammy told me his brain has been spinning with the possibilities for his little girl. The awesome stuff, and scary stuff. I don't think those feelings will ever go away.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1436" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1425/gia6-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1436" title="gia6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/gia61.jpg" alt="" width="742" height="500" /></a>These are the moments that count. The yawns, the kisses, and even the dirty diapers that let you know your baby is healthy. Heather seems to enjoy it all.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1435" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1425/gia3-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1435" title="gia3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/gia31.jpg" alt="" width="742" height="500" /></a>Taking pictures of Gianna, Sammy and Heather was so much fun for me.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1434" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1425/gia1-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1434" title="gia1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/gia11.jpg" alt="" width="699" height="500" /></a>Gia you are a beautiful little girl, I look forward to watching you grow up.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1433" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1425/gia5-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1433" title="gia5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/gia51.jpg" alt="" width="742" height="500" /></a>]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>
		<wp:post_id>1425</wp:post_id>

	<item>
		<title>Family Portraits~Kansas City Photographer</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1448</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 17 Sep 2010 14:03:16 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1448</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">It was the most perfect day. You know when the weather is so good you don't even notice it. Not to cold, not to hot, that kind of good. Golden light, blue skies, perfect temperature, and a family excited to have their pictures taken. Life was good, and I was happy. Long story short the Trober had the hook up, they know the owners of Stephenson's apple orchird. The owners suggested we take pics at their old hunting cabin down by the pond. I'm all sure, sounds good, right? Well, minus the crazy adventure it was good, more than good, it was perfect.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">The only real downfall was that it's not easy to get to. I'm just saying, it was a good thing Christina had her 4 wheel drive because the drive to the cabin was not a smooth one. We off roading it, which has it's perks, we saw a flock of wild turkeys, and some deer.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">When we pulled up to the log cabin I was in creative, photographer, heaven. It was small, tiny really, just 2 rooms, but the rustic old logs, and the golden light pouring in made this location a dream. Not to mention the ivy growing off the roof, and the tall natural Missouri grasses growing all around. Ahh, I could go on and on.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">The shot below is backlit. I turned their backs to the sun and exposed for their skin tones. It blows the sky out, but in this situation it's ok, because it looks great.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1450" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1448/tro2"><img class="size-full wp-image-1450    aligncenter" title="tro2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/tro2.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I'm lovin' the door in the background. Looks eery, but cool.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1454" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1448/tro6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1454" title="tro6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/tro6.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Maya just lost here teeth, isn't it awesome! I'm so proud of her for giving me her full grin!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1456" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1448/tro8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1456" title="tro8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/tro8.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1453" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1448/tro5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1453" title="tro5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/tro5.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1457" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1448/tro9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1457" title="tro9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/tro9.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">I love love love the light in these pics.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1449" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1448/tro1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1449" title="tro1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/tro1.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Wowzer! Christina your are fiercely hot.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">For this shot I stood Christina out of the direct window light, it's too hot.  For window light shots stand your subject just out of the direct light.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1458" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1448/tro10"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1458" title="tro10" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/tro10.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1451" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1448/tro3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1451" title="tro3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/tro3.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1455" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1448/tro7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1455" title="tro7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/tro7.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1452" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1448/tro4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1452" title="tro4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/tro4.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">I plucked this picture out of magazine, for real, they look hot.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">We did deal with quite a bit of nature, but it was so worth it. The big guy on the right was like 3 inches long. I had to destroy his web to get this shot. I also almost backed into a nest of about 5 spider eggs. Nasty!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1459" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1448/tro11"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1459" title="tro11" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/tro11.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>This shoot was more than memorable. I loved my time out in nature with the Trobers. Thanks guys, I'm already looking forward to next time!</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Golden light IS the good stuff! ~ Kansas City Photographer</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1467</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 23 Sep 2010 13:11:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1467</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">I was excited about the shoot because the day before Jon and I had scoped out the location, and we knew it was going to be killer. But at 6:00 pm, I wasn't so sure as I drove down I-70. With my clients following, I was watching the sun slowly set while hiding behind the clouds. I needed the sun, and I needed it to stay in the sky. My "oh no" radar started sounding, and that's about the time I missed the turn off and had to weave back through the city to get back and try again. No worries, I was back on track with an hour of light. Be fast Allison was the only thought I could really focus on. Well, fast and creative. I stopped the car, hopped out, smiled at my clients. They probably thought I was crazy, or maybe they thought they were crazy for trying to follow me. Remember I'm not the best driver, according to Jon anyway. Lucky for me, Peggy, Mackenzie, and Kylie are the sweetest people ever, and totally understanding. It didn't even seem to phase them. That's probably why we were able to capture some of the most amazing pics ever!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">We started in this field just off the road. The setting sun was still hiding in the clouds, which was great, it was like a diffuser for me.  These pics are right out of camera. Peggy is gorgeous which makes my job Easy! Most the time it takes people a few shots to warm up to the camera, but Peggy was good to go right off the bat!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1479" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1467/peg12"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1479" title="peg12" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/peg12.jpg" alt="" width="693" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Sometimes it's the moments between the pictures that matter most. These 3 are so close.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1478" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1467/peg11"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1478" title="peg11" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/peg11.jpg" alt="" width="742" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">After working the field it was time to move on so I took the girls to the dark tree covered road, where I was looking for the juicy light. You know the kind that makes people look amazing. I think I found it. It was super golden which is why their skin is a little orangish, but I love warm light. It's real.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1477" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1467/peg10"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1477" title="peg10" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/peg10.jpg" alt="" width="693" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Hands down one of my most favorite shots of all time! LOVE LOVE LOVE! It's not just the setting either. These girls have a powerful connection.</p>


<a rel="attachment wp-att-1476" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1467/peg9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1476" title="peg9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/peg9.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1475" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1467/peg8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1475" title="peg8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/peg8.jpg" alt="" width="744" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Kylie was feeling fierce! Rawr! I can't wait to take her senior pics in 2 years, I can't even begin to imagine how amazing her pics will be.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1474" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1467/peg7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1474" title="peg7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/peg7.jpg" alt="" width="743" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1473" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1467/peg6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1473" title="peg6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/peg6.jpg" alt="" width="693" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">One of the reasons I brought the girls to this location was to shoot in front of the waterfall. Haha. Right as I got the girls set up the thing shut off! I'm not even joking. Just turned off. We laughed and I kept right on going. When we scoped the location out there was a guy on the side of the road cleaning his car with water from the waterfall. Pretty funny.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1480" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1467/peg13"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1480" title="peg13" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/peg13.jpg" alt="" width="693" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">We ended our shoot in front of this castle looking house, with the coolest doors ever! Lucky for me the owners were out so I asked if I could use their front steps, and gorgeous flowers for some shots. They were happy to share. In fact their son is a headshot photographer in LA so they were very understanding. I sat and talked to the owner Serena for 45 minutes after the shoot. I mean I had to, she owns the only castle in KC.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1469" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1467/peg2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1469" title="peg2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/peg2.jpg" alt="" width="693" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Seriously Peggy you are one lucky lady!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1471" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1467/peg4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1471" title="peg4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/peg4.jpg" alt="" width="693" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Mackenzie was one of my students my last year teaching. That class was one of my favorites, partly because she was in it, partly because it was my last, but mostly because I had a fun group. Mackenzie loves to play sports, wear her hair in a ponytail, and give me a hard time. She does not like to have her pics taken, however, I think she did a great job!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1468" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1467/peg1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1468" title="peg1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/peg1.jpg" alt="" width="744" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">The pic above was the last one I took of the night. I squeezed every last ounce out of the sun to get the shot. I shot with my 50 mm 1.4 with 800 ISO.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1470" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1467/peg3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1470" title="peg3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/peg3.jpg" alt="" width="744" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This last pic pretty much sums up our time together. I had a blast!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1472" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1467/peg5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1472" title="peg5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/peg5.jpg" alt="" width="744" height="500" /></a>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Art for me, or art for you?</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1483</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 27 Sep 2010 18:31:50 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1483</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">My portrait business is a big part of my livelihood, because I love the people I get to meet and often they become friends. It's awesome, and right now there isn't anything else in the world I'd rather be doing. But I know my job is going to have to evolove. I'm a creature of change, and I want to grow as a professional photographer. So I've been dabbling in all sorts of photography genre's. One of which is art shows. I remember when I would walk the streets of the Plaza Art Fair and think someday I want to be here, doing this. But it was one of those dreams you quickly tuck away and disregard. Because the people in those art shows, they are brave, and I am not. But slowly I've taken steps to make that dream a reality. A couple weekends ago I had my Indonesia work on display in my tent at the Zona Rosa Art Festival. I was finally one of those brave artists. And it was awesome! People came, they looked, they OOOhhhed, and Ahhhed. They talked to me about my work, but I didn't sell any of my big pieces. :( I was really sad and frustrated. I started to wonder if it was my work, if it was me, I started to feel the brave artist melting away with my drive to follow my dreams. I questioned what's important, to be an artist that has something to share, or to be an artist that has something to sell. I still don't have the answers, but I do know I need my work to represent the person I am, the life I've lived, and the experiences I've had. Staying true to my passion is what I'll do for now. I'll pick my head up, and look ahead because I might not be brave, but I'm tough.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Here are my 3 big ones. These are all 36x46. Buddha sit by my at work.</p>


<a rel="attachment wp-att-1485" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1483/dawnofnewbegninngsb"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1485" title="dawnofnewbegninngsb" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/dawnofnewbegninngsb.jpg" alt="" width="625" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1486" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1483/goldenb"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1486" title="goldenb" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/goldenb.jpg" alt="" width="560" height="700" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1487" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1483/romanceinthemorningb"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1487" title="romanceinthemorningb" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/romanceinthemorningb.jpg" alt="" width="625" height="500" /></a>]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>
		<wp:post_id>1483</wp:post_id>
		<wp:post_date>2010-09-27 13:31:50</wp:post_date>
		<wp:post_date_gmt>2010-09-27 18:31:50</wp:post_date_gmt>
		<wp:comment_status>open</wp:comment_status>
		<wp:ping_status>open</wp:ping_status>
		<wp:post_name>art-for-me-or-art-for-you</wp:post_name>

	<item>
		<title>Puppy pictures! ~ Kanasas City Photographer</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1491</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 28 Sep 2010 15:04:03 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1491</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a rel="attachment wp-att-1502" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1491/har11"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1502" title="har11" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/har11.jpg" alt="" width="721" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Meet Harry! Harry Winston! He's a Chinese Crested champion show dog! Retired already at the age of 2. He now spends his days cuddled up with his mom Samantha, mostly being spoiled.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I am a dog lover, so when Samantha contacted me to take pictures of her kid, Harry, I jumped at the chance. Harry started the shoot just like the above picture, a little skeptical, a little unsure, a little nervous, but it didn't take long for him to warm up, and start flashing us those champion dog good looks.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I think he looks a little like a Fragglerock. Loved that show!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1501" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1491/har10"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1501" title="har10" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/har10.jpg" alt="" width="673" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Apparently this is how Harry sleeps, on his back. Seriously, this picture cracks me up, how adorable!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Harry might be adorable, but Samantha is gorgeous inside and out! I just love when a new client comes in and I immediately bond with them. The more we talked the more we realized we like all the same things. One of the best perks of my job is all the cool people I meet and become friends with. I just know this is the case with Sam.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1499" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1491/har8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1499" title="har8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/har8.jpg" alt="" width="722" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is one of my favorites! Dramatic!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1500" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1491/har9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1500" title="har9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/har9.jpg" alt="" width="721" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Fragglerock maybe, later I realized he's really a mini horse. I was surprised to find out Sam doesn't trim him. His hair naturally grows this way. Like a horse, he's got a mane, a tail, and fluff around his feet. The hair on his back would be comparable to a mans beard, but it's really soft. The best part is that Chinese Crested puppies are hypo allergenic. For more information read<a href="http://www.akc.org/breeds/chinese_crested/"> here</a>.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1494" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1491/har3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1494" title="har3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/har3.jpg" alt="" width="721" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">I asked Samantha what voice she would give Harry if he could talk. She thought surfer originally, but he's too classy for that. We both agreed George Clooney. He's sophisticated, grey, and too cool for words. He also totally snubbed my girls when we let them out to visit.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1493" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1491/har2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1493" title="har2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/har2.jpg" alt="" width="673" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Did I mention he also runs like a horse.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1498" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1491/har7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1498" title="har7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/har7.jpg" alt="" width="770" height="535" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">I'm not sure Harry isn't human in this picture. I mean it's so obvious he loves Samantha as much as she loves him!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1497" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1491/har6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1497" title="har6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/har6.jpg" alt="" width="721" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1492" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1491/har1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1492" title="har1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/har1.jpg" alt="" width="721" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1495" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1491/har4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1495" title="har4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/har4.jpg" alt="" width="673" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">His hair really does look this good. I wish my hair had that much volume.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1503" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1491/har12"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1503" title="har12" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/har12.jpg" alt="" width="721" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Samantha and Harry, I loved our time together, in fact I was sad when you left. Feel free to come by anytime!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Allison! HOLY COW.
You are an absolute GENIUS!! I literally cried today when I saw that one with Harry's eyes closed when I was kissing him! LOVE IT!! Love it, Love it!! I could not have been happier with the 10 that you put on facebook AND THEN when I saw the whole lot of them... breathtaking! I LOVE THEM ALL!!!
I really cant thank you enough. You captured exactly what I was looking for plus some! And that is an amazing feat as I really had no idea what I was looking for! :)</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1496" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1491/har5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1496" title="har5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/har5.jpg" alt="" width="721" height="500" /></a>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Wedding Photography ~ Kansas City</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1509</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 29 Sep 2010 20:48:15 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1509</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">She didn't want someone else to do her hair, or her makeup. The fact that she was putting on makeup at all was going to be enough. She knew Brice would love her no matter what she looked like, he always had. As she got ready she would occationally check the clock, but other than that you would never guess it was her wedding day. Her confidence was amazing.</p>


<a rel="attachment wp-att-1510" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1509/lin1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1510" title="lin1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/lin1.jpg" alt="" width="673" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Lindsay arrived at the church in just enough time to walk down the aisle. She got married at little Rosedale church, a very urban chuch where Brice coached a basketball team for boys that don't have much else. Both Lindsay and Brice are big givers in their own way. Brice is a devote Christian, and true to the Christian message he gives back. I know he always will. Lindsay is a dog lover and spends her weekends driving around the city, finding homeless dogs and then finding homes for them. Lindsay has also made her career all about helping others. She's a social worker, we should all give thanks. Combined these two have enough love in their hearts for the whole world.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1512" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1509/lin3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1512" title="lin3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/lin3.jpg" alt="" width="673" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1513" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1509/lin4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1513" title="lin4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/lin4.jpg" alt="" width="721" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Lindsay has a heart of gold, but she's also got some spunk. Check out these rockin blue shoes!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1514" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1509/lin5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1514" title="lin5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/lin5.jpg" alt="" width="722" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">I hope you can see the glow in these pics!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1515" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1509/lin6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1515" title="lin6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/lin6.jpg" alt="" width="673" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1517" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1509/lin8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1517" title="lin8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/lin8.jpg" alt="" width="721" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Love Love Love</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1518" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1509/lin9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1518" title="lin9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/lin9.jpg" alt="" width="673" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Lindsay's mom with her nephew, and Brice's parents. Happy.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1519" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1509/lin10"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1519" title="lin10" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/lin10.jpg" alt="" width="673" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This kiss lasted quite awhile and then they exited with joy!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1520" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1509/lin11"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1520" title="lin11" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/lin11.jpg" alt="" width="673" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1521" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1509/lin12"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1521" title="lin12" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/lin12.jpg" alt="" width="721" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Went across the street to an old run down house that had ivy growing up the side. Gorgeous light and gorgeous couple.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1522" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1509/lin13"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1522" title="lin13" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/lin13.jpg" alt="" width="673" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1523" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1509/lin14"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1523" title="lin14" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/lin14.jpg" alt="" width="721" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Lindsay and Brice had a morning wedding, so their reception was all about brunch. They had their reception at <a href="http://thecashew.com/">The Cashew</a>, which I'm pretty sure has the most amazing light in the city. With one whole wall of windows facing the north it was a photographer's dream. Check it out!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1535" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1509/lin26"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1535" title="lin26" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/lin26.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="498" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Lindsay you are gorgeous. Thanks for letting me be your little paparazzi during this pics.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1534" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1509/lin25"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1534" title="lin25" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/lin25.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="498" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1532" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1509/lin23"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1532" title="lin23" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/lin23.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="498" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1531" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1509/lin22"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1531" title="lin22" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/lin22.jpg" alt="" width="721" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Ummm did I mention her dress was gorgeous!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1533" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1509/lin24"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1533" title="lin24" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/lin24.jpg" alt="" width="754" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">They did this A LOT! Too cute.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1530" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1509/lin21"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1530" title="lin21" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/lin21.jpg" alt="" width="721" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">The best part was the root beer floats. What an awesome idea! I think Jon enjoyed two.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1528" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1509/lin19"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1528" title="lin19" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/lin19.jpg" alt="" width="721" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Lindsay was on the dance floor waiting for Brice, when he got there she threw her arms around him and smiled and kept smiling the whole dance. Brice just held on...tight!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1529" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1509/lin20"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1529" title="lin20" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/lin20.jpg" alt="" width="673" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Lindsey with her girls.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1526" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1509/lin17"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1526" title="lin17" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/lin17.jpg" alt="" width="721" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Brice you're a stud, thanks for being so awesome!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1527" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1509/lin18"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1527" title="lin18" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/lin18.jpg" alt="" width="673" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">It was sunny, 100 and noonish, but the two rocked the shades while we tromped around the plaza.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1524" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1509/lin15"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1524" title="lin15" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/lin15.jpg" alt="" width="673" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1525" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1509/lin16"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1525" title="lin16" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/lin16.jpg" alt="" width="721" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Lindsay and Brice I'm not going to say the obvious here, but I really really want to. You two are a great team, and without a doubt will change the world!</p>]]></content:encoded>
