	<item>
		<title>Southern Plantation Wedding~ Kansas City Photographer</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1542</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 06 Oct 2010 16:00:18 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1542</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">I remember I was walking around Costco the first time Brooke brought up Justin's name in conversation. She said it casually, "I met a boy". I jumped at the opportunity to hear more because, well Brooke is always guarded with her heart, when it comes to men. "What? Tell me more." As though my enthusiasm was a reminder of her heart she quickly brushed it off as no big deal. I didn't stop though, I forced her to tell me how they met, what he was like, and how long this had been going on. She made it seem simple, no big deal, but I could hear her smiling through the phone. I knew this boy had broken down a wall.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">So when I met Justin for the first time, it was no surprise Brooke was glowing. He constantly showered her with attention and affection. She was being treated like a queen, as she should be.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">A few years later, and many memories it's their wedding day.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I was the lucky photographer, and because Brooke and Justin are perfection, and the location was amazing, this wedding was a photographer's dream. Here's the story of their wedding day.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1543" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1542/br1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1543" title="br1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/br1.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">On the right is David, the owner of the plantation, a fine southern gentleman, and as refined as the genuine silver you see below. He's all about following the rules of etiquette, anything less is not suitable for his house. He was also Brooke's wedding coordinator, and one of my favorite people at the wedding. When I left, I thanked him for a great day, and he told me I had met the wildest man in the south. I don't doubt that for a second.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1544" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1542/br2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1544" title="br2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/br2.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Audrey, Brooke's mom was a rockstar. She was cool, calm and collected. She was gorgeous, helpful, and loving. I guess I now know where Brooke gets it.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1545" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1542/br3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1545" title="br3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/br3.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">David took care of the flowers, the cake, food, and planning.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1546" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1542/br4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1546" title="br4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/br4.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">When we first arrived at the plantation we quickly realized Brooke's dress did not make the drive over. So we waited, for about 35 minutes. But, Brooke was a rockstar with no stress at all. The dress did eventually arrive, but the shoes did not.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1547" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1542/br5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1547" title="br5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/br5.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">No one could find the missing shoes. So while we funbled around trying to find a solution, David came to the rescue. He pulled these white shoes from his very on closet. Women's size 8, Brooke's size. We had a lot of laughs about this one. But in the end David really did save the day.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1548" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1542/br6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1548" title="br6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/br6.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">The flowers were gorgeous, as was the house, and of course the bride!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1549" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1542/br7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1549" title="br7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/br7.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Brooke has the most loving friends, all of the bridesmaids were a dream to work with.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1550" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1542/br8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1550" title="br8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/br8.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Brooke and Justin opted to have a first look, so we were able to get some amazing photos before the ceremony. The one on the right is their first hug after seeing eachother.</p>
<a style="text-decoration: none;" rel="attachment wp-att-1551" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1542/br9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1551" title="br9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/br9.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1552" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1542/br10"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1552" title="br10" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/br10.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Ohhh the light...bless you!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1554" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1542/br12"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1554" title="br12" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/br12.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1555" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1542/br13"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1555" title="br13" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/br13.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">The boys looking very GQ.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1556" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1542/br14"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1556" title="br14" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/br14.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">The light in the greenhouse was something fierce, bouncing all over the place, and making Brooke look like an angel.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1557" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1542/br15"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1557" title="br15" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/br15.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Did I mention the bridesmaids were great!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1558" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1542/br16"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1558" title="br16" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/br16.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1559" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1542/br17"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1559" title="br17" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/br17.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1560" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1542/br18"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1560" title="br18" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/br18.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">There were a lot of these smiles during the ceremony on the steps of the plantaion.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1561" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1542/br19"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1561" title="br19" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/br19.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Didn't even notice the teal ceiling until post production.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1562" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1542/br20"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1562" title="br20" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/br20.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is Riley, Brooke's brother.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1564" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1542/br22"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1564" title="br22" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/br22.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1563" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1542/br21"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1563" title="br21" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/br21.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Hello Bling!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1569" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1542/br27"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1569" title="br27" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/br27.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1565" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1542/br23"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1565" title="br23" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/br23.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Justin is everything Brooke described him to be.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1566" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1542/br24"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1566" title="br24" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/br24.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">The house had a garden with perfectly trimmed hedges well over Jon's head. And the field on the right was just to the left of the house, there were actual cows out there.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1567" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1542/br25"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1567" title="br25" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/br25.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1568" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1542/br26"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1568" title="br26" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/br26.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1570" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1542/br28"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1570" title="br28" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/br28.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1571" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1542/br29"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1571" title="br29" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/br29.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1572" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1542/br30"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1572" title="br30" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/br30.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1573" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1542/br32"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1573" title="br32" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/br32.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1574" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1542/br33"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1574" title="br33" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/br33.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">After a perfect wedding, on a perfect day, with the most perfect bride and groom, these were the last shots of the day. Just looking at these pics I can feel the closeness. Congrats Mr. and Mrs. Gantt!</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Baby Love~ Newborn,Maternity photography</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1580</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 07 Oct 2010 18:25:02 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1580</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a rel="attachment wp-att-1585" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1580/stan5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1585" title="stan5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/stan5.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Sometimes people get lucky, lucky to find love, lucky to find happiness, and lucky to look this good 8 months pregnant.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">For Justin and Stephani all of these are true. I think you'll see it for yourself when you view these pics.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1583" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1580/stan3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1583" title="stan3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/stan3.jpg" alt="" width="673" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Actually their story started with luck. In college Stephani was friends with Justin's brother and when he came to visit KU where both Justin and Stephani went to school, he stopped by to visit. Immediately the sparks went flying. Being the confident woman Steph is, she didn't hesitate to call. They met out later that night, and I guess you see the rest is history.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1584" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1580/stan4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1584" title="stan4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/stan4.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1582" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1580/stan2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1582" title="stan2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/stan2.jpg" alt="" width="673" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1586" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1580/stan6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1586" title="stan6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/stan6.jpg" alt="" width="673" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">LOVE LOVE LOVE!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1581" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1580/stan1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1581" title="stan1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/stan1.jpg" alt="" width="673" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Their luck didn't stop with finding love because now they have this little bug. Evelyn is a precious little darlin'. Sorry there are so many pics, I just couldn't stop myself.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1589" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1580/stan9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1589" title="stan9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/stan9.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1591" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1580/stan11"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1591" title="stan11" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/stan11.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>

<a style="text-decoration: none;" rel="attachment wp-att-1590" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1580/stan10"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1590" title="stan10" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/stan10.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1594" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1580/stan14"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1594" title="stan14" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/stan14.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1588" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1580/stan8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1588" title="stan8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/stan8.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1587" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1580/stan7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1587" title="stan7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/stan7.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">The picture below is the reason I love taking pictures of newborns. It's totally unpredictable!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1593" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1580/stan13"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1593" title="stan13" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/stan13.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Justin has a band, and he's a really talented singer and guitarist. He performs weekly all over the KC area with his band GUS. Check them out <a href="http://www.guskc.com/">here</a>!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">So of course we had to get some pics of little Evie on the guitar. This one was a fluke, but I had to share . Notice the peace sign and the microphone hand. I think she's going to rock out like her daddy! haha</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1596" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1580/stan16"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1596" title="stan16" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/stan16.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">And then I love this one. Wall worthy!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1595" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1580/stan15"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1595" title="stan15" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/stan15.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Evelyn is all about faces. Here are just a few she made right in a row. Perfection!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1597" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1580/stan17"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1597" title="stan17" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/stan17.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="1997" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Stephani and Justin thank you for letting me be the lucky photographer to capture these precious moments!</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Old Fashioned Love, and a Smokin&#039; Hot Couple ~ Kansas City Wedding Photographer</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1605</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 13 Oct 2010 21:22:50 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1605</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">When Allison walked into the hospital room where Matt was working on a patient, it got a little bit hotter. His attraction was immediate despite the situation. He was busy repairing someones backside, when Allison came in to assist. She noticed him too, but it wasn't until later that SHE got up the nerve to ask him out. They went to a Chiefs game, and afterwards got cozy in the corner of a restaurant, where Matt says they embarrassed the patrons with their nuzzling. Their relationship started with fire and it hasn't fizzled. Their chemistry is obvious and it was so easy to capture. I think you'll agree these pictures are all so fiery hot!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1617" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1605/am12"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1617" title="am12" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/am12.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Matt says something funny, Allison laughs. Repeat and follow up with a kiss.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">By the way this car belongs to Matt's dad. Thank you Thank you Thank you!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1616" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1605/am11"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1616" title="am11" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/am11.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">A classic car for a classic couple.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1613" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1605/am8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1613" title="am8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/am8.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Allison is a classy chic! She found this vintage inspired dress online. There's really only one thing to say about this dress. SMOKIN' HOT! I told you these pics were on fire.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1615" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1605/am10"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1615" title="am10" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/am10.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Allison is an occupational therapist and she recently made the transition from the hospital world to the school setting. Bless her for all she does every day.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1611" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1605/am6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1611" title="am6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/am6.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1618" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1605/am13"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1618" title="am13" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/am13.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I wanted to find a vintage location to go with the vintage car, and the vintage dress. So why not, Town Topic Burger. We took some pics then went inside. Matt and Jon couldn't resist the mouthwatering smells of burgers and had to get some. I had a strawberry shake that was near flawless. We ate, and laughed. I've never taken a break in the middle of a shoot like that, but I loved it! What great memories!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1619" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1605/am14"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1619" title="am14" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/am14.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Love love the fierce pic on the left!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1612" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1605/am7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1612" title="am7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/am7.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1608" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1605/am3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1608" title="am3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/am3.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">I love KC!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1610" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1605/am5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1610" title="am5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/am5.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1609" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1605/am4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1609" title="am4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/am4.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1607" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1605/am2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1607" title="am2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/am2.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1606" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1605/am1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1606" title="am1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/am1.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1614" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1605/am9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1614" title="am9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/am9.jpg" alt="" width="752" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">On the car ride downtown I asked them if they had ever taken acting classes. They laughed and told me no. After spending our time together I can so clearly see that acting is not in their future because their love is real!</p>]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Engagement Pictures ~ Kansas City Photographer</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1627</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 15 Oct 2010 14:12:56 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1627</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a rel="attachment wp-att-1638" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1627/ci11"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1638" title="ci11" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/ci11.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">They share a love for music, sushi, books, and experiences. She doesn't like to clean the house, but he doesn't mind asking her for help. He doesn't like to be off his planned schedule, but she doesn't mind leaving early. It's a give and a take in their love, but in the end they both like to have experiences that are memorable and fun. They make their friends a priority, but more importantly they make each other the first priority. Their love is a strong one. I know this, because I've known Cara since 6th grade. Don't aah, because we weren't friends, she didn't like me, but not without good reason. I moved to a new school in 6th grade, and the only way I knew how to fit in was to be funny. It was like I learned to be funny over night. I guess the cool kids thought I was funny too because they accepted me, and for the first time I fit in.  So when one of the cool kids told Cara she needed windshield wipers for her glasses because she spit when she talked, I laughed. At the time I didn't realize how badly I had hurt Cara, one laugh really can scar someone. So for the next 10 years Cara wrote me off, literally scratched me out of her yearbook. We even shared mutual friends, but never shared more than casual pleasantries.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Then in my 3 year teaching she was placed at my school teaching the same grade as me. God wasn't giving up on us! It wasn't until the second year we taught together that we became unseperable. I'm just so happy she's in my life, and now Ian too. They are perfect for eachother. I love the way Cara smiles when she's with him.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1629" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1627/ci2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1629" title="ci2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/ci2.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">We spent the evening roaming around the city taking random pics in random places. Wherever the light was good.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">The pic below was taken in the bottom floor of Revolution, a cool old warehouse. The owner Patrick told us we could go in and check out his collection of antiques from all across the country. Then he invited us upstairs, where someone was throwing a fundraiser event for young architects, or something like that. He took us to the bar and forced us to get drinks and told us to stay and eat and drink. We didn't, but we wanted to, it's just we were running out of light. The funny thing is that Cara and Ian have been searching the city for a cheap, unique place for their reception, I think we might have stumbled upon something great.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1632" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1627/ci5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1632" title="ci5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/ci5.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Remember that smile I talked about...here it is.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1636" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1627/ci9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1636" title="ci9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/ci9.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Cara, I am so proud of you! Your really worked it! Seriously!!!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1630" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1627/ci3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1630" title="ci3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/ci3.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Just two cool cats hanging out in an alley!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1634" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1627/ci7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1634" title="ci7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/ci7.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1633" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1627/ci6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1633" title="ci6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/ci6.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is one of my favorites.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1635" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1627/ci8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1635" title="ci8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/ci8.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">You really can't tell from the pictures, but Ian Hates having his pictures taken. He had to have 2 beers before the shoot. I think he kinda likes it now. Maybe...</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1631" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1627/ci4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1631" title="ci4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/ci4.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">As you can see, there was lots of kissing! They just couldn't keep their hands off each other. Especially once Cara put that short dress on!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1628" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1627/ci1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1628" title="ci1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/ci1.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I love you two so much! I just can't wait for your wedding in Mexico! xoxo</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>High School Sweethearts~ Kansas City Photographer</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1645</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 21 Oct 2010 14:40:57 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1645</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">They fell in love roaming the halls of their high school. Their love was real back then, but like many young loves it didn't last. They both moved on and moved away from each other. But seven years ago when Sharon's brother passed away, they were reunited. The timing was right, and they fell right back into the easy rhythmn of love they had in high school. They've been going strong ever sense.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1648" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1645/ell3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1648" title="ell3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/ell3.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I meet Sharon through Silpada. She's the most amazing rep. and I fell in love with not only the jewelry, but also Sharon. Sometimes you just know you're meant to be friends with someone.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1652" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1645/ell7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1652" title="ell7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/ell7.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">It wasn't until later I met Tony. He works for the KCPD. That alone wins him some big points with me, so when Sharon told me the story of the t-shirt he moved right up to the top where I keep Buddha, Dali Lama, Jesus, and Maggie. Here's the story, I guess they were shopping at Cargo Largo. Those of you from Eastern Jackson County totally know what I'm talking about. For everyone else, it's a warehouse with lots and lots of random leftovers companies don't want anymore. I guess Tony came over to Sharon all excited with this T-shirt with a camera on it telling her they needed to get it for me. It's the same shirt you see on my facebook page. Thanks Tony! I love that shirt!!!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1646" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1645/ell1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1646" title="ell1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/ell1.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1649" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1645/ell4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1649" title="ell4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/ell4.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1647" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1645/ell2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1647" title="ell2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/ell2.jpg" alt="" width="752" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Typically guys lose interest in pictures about 30 minutes in, but Tony was game the whole time. He did a great job of making Sharon giggle at all the right times. And he loves photography. I guess he's worked with enough forensic photographers that he really understands light. He kept explaining to Sharon why certain shots wouldn't work. Pretty Funny.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1650" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1645/ell5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1650" title="ell5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/ell5.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1651" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1645/ell6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1651" title="ell6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/ell6.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Here's where it gets real. I've gotten to know Sharon this last year, and her strength comes from overcoming many obstacles in her life.  Obstacles most of us never dream of. I can't even get into them all here, you'll just have to have a Silpada party and see for yourself. <a href="http://www.mysilpada.com/sharon.ell"> Click Here</a>!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I will tell you this, even though I don't want to cause it hurts, and because I don't think I can adequately describe her strength. Sharon's dream of a family was almost a reality when she lost her baby in the 3rd trimester. The shock of the loss left her empty, but being as resilient as she is, she filled the void with the love from her dogs. It's amazing how animals can fill the empty spots that even loved ones can't. Her babies make her family complete.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1653" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1645/ell8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1653" title="ell8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/ell8.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1654" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1645/ell9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1654" title="ell9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/ell9.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Rocky is 17 years young. He's been there for Sharon in times when she was all alone. Their bond is something special.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1655" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1645/ell10"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1655" title="ell10" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/ell10.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">I'm always in awe of strong people like Sharon that are so willing to expose the soft, tender, still aching spots in their heart. This is something I'm not good at. Sharon and Tony I'm lucky to know you!</p>]]></content:encoded>

			<wp:comment_content><![CDATA[Dear Allison,

"Thank-you" for not just being a GREAT photographer, but a true friend who has helped me grow as a leader and as a person. Tony and I appreciate every ounce of energy you poured into your photography, to make our pictures "perfect!"  We absolutely LOVE our pictures!  Most of all we'd like to thank God for allowing our paths to cross. You are an amazing woman and we are SO honored to call you friend.     

Our thanks, love and gratitude,
Tony and Sharon Ell

	<item>
		<title>Wedding Photography ~ Kansas City</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1661</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 22 Oct 2010 14:40:07 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1661</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">Their first memory of each other is vague. Nick remembers a horsey girl (ponytail, boots, maybe a little dirty) out in the middle of the arena barking orders to kids to prepare them for the show. He didn't really notice her at all because he was really there to watch his sister compete, after all Elizabeth was just his sister's trainer. But later when they met face to face it was a whole different story. He thought she was beautiful, and she thought he was hot. But, they were both dating someone else at the time, so nothing happened.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Four years later when they were both single again, a friend suggested they get together. They dated, and quickly fell in love, whether they knew it or not. When Elizabeth went away to train with another Arabian trainer for 3 weeks in a different state it became obvious to Nick that he couldn't, wouldn't live without this girl. They talked constantly, so when she got home he asked ,"When are you movin' to Marshall?" Her response, "When are you gonna ask?"</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1678" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1661/th18"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1678" title="th18" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/th18.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">They're day was full of joy. That's really the only way I can describe it. They are both pretty laid back, down to Earth and all about fun!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1675" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1661/th15"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1675" title="th15" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/th15.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Poor Nick. The Saturday before the wedding I got an email from Elizabeth saying that Nick broke his leg and that I needed to prepare to be creative for pics. I guess the morning of the accident Elizabeth had told Nick to be careful on his 4 wheeler. He was, but a freak accident left his 4 wheeler looking like this, and his leg in a full cast. I guess he's lucky, cause the 4 wheeler is not. We're also lucky his pants fit over the cast.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1677" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1661/th17"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1677" title="th17" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/th17.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1676" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1661/th16"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1676" title="th16" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/th16.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">After they got ready at the church we went to Nick's old family mansion. This house was built sometime in the early to mid 1800's. During the civil war it was used as a hospital. In fact Nick's family had to sand down the wood floors to get the blood stains out. If you look to the right you'll see a note that is written on the wall dated 1876. It's a letter to someone saying their going to church, they will return if nothing happens to prevent. It's kinda scary like they were going to go to church in the middle of a blizzard. Really cool! Also, the goomsmen that have stayed the night there are convinced it's haunted. I guess they would wake up in the middle of the night hearing billiards being played downstairs, but there is no pool table. eeeewwww!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1674" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1661/th14"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1674" title="th14" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/th14.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Elizabeth and Nick opted for the first look which allowed us to get some fantastic pictures!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1672" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1661/th12"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1672" title="th12" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/th12.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1671" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1661/th11"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1671" title="th11" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/th11.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1669" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1661/th9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1669" title="th9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/th9.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">They thought I wasn't looking! They did this kind of adorable stuff all day!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1670" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1661/th10"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1670" title="th10" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/th10.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1667" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1661/th7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1667" title="th7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/th7.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This picture on the left is one of my favorites!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1666" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1661/th5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1666" title="th5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/th5.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1673" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1661/th13"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1673" title="th13" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/th13.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Elizabeth was working it all day long!!!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1668" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1661/th8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1668" title="th8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/th8.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1664" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1661/th3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1664" title="th3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/th3.jpg" alt="" width="752" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Nick was such a trooper he hobbled up and down the steps for the pics.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1665" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1661/th4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1665" title="th4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/th4.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is Nick's corvette. After the ceremony the sped away in it!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1663" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1661/th2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1663" title="th2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/th2.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">See what I mean...workin it f' real!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1662" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1661/th1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1662" title="th1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/th1.jpg" alt="" width="753" height="500" /></a><a rel="attachment wp-att-1673" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1661/th13"></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1681" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1661/th21"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1681" title="th21" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/th21.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1682" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1661/th22"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1682" title="th22" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/th22.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1680" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1661/th20"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1680" title="th20" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/th20.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is little Axel and I've been taking his pictures since he was a newbie. He is always this happy!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1683" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1661/th23"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1683" title="th23" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/th23.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1679" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1661/th19"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1679" title="th19" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/th19.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1684" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1661/th24"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1684" title="th24" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/th24.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1685" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1661/th25"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1685" title="th25" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/th25.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Nick and Elizabeth compliment each other in all the right ways. I was lucky to get to be there to help them remember this substantial day.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1686" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1661/th26"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1686" title="th26" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/th26.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Love you guys!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">d</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>So much LOVE!!! ~ Kansas City Family Photographer</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1690</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 28 Oct 2010 17:07:03 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1690</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">When Nikki contacted me a few months ago about doing pictures, she was excited, nervous, and a little unsure. I could hear it in her emails, so when she told me her son was born with EEC syndrome, and explained that he's missing some fingers and toes, and was also born without tear ducts, I understood why. She also told me he's a shy little boy and she wasn't real sure how the pictures were going to go.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Well let me just say I think I'm in love with Brady. He smiled, laughed, grinned, and worked the camera like it was his job. I think or maybe hope he had a little crush on me. Most of the pictures I captured that day are of him grinning ear to ear, but I picked this one to share.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">You see, Brady might be handicapped physically because he doesn't have all his fingers and toes, but his heart is full of enough love to make up for it. When I took this picture I got chills, but at the time I didn't know why. When I opened it I realized he was looking right through the camera at me. He didn't let the camera act as a barrier like most people. He connected with me. Brady has the special ability to really see people.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1692" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1690/nik2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1692" title="nik2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/nik2.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">His big sister Morgan is the most loving, supportive sister anyone could ask for.  I'm sure it's hard for her at times being the sister of a brother with EEC, but she didn't seem to mind...at all.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1697" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1690/nikk5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1697" title="nikk5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/nikk5.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">See...</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1696" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1690/nik7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1696" title="nik7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/nik7.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">And the kids aren't the only ones that make this family special. Mike and Niki were all laughs. I decided to vote Mike top male model of the month. For real, check it out! And Niki, you're a strong beautiful woman!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">PS these are untouched in photoshop. They really just look that good.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1691" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1690/nik1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1691" title="nik1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/nik1.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Talk about beautiful. Mike couldn't keep his hands off his wife. He kept saying, "Man you are gorgeous, you are so hot". What a lucky lady.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1694" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1690/nik4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1694" title="nik4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/nik4.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1693" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1690/nik3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1693" title="nik3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/nik3.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Some families just have it, and the Voight family is one of those lucky families. Enough said.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1695" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1690/nik5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1695" title="nik5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/nik5.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Twin photography ~ Kansas City</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1704</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 29 Oct 2010 13:36:26 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1704</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">The following pictures make me feel like a great photog. That doesn't always happen, and it feels incredible! I can't take credit though, it wasn't my expensive camera or lens, it wasn't the rustic awesome setting, it was the girls. Twin girls! They made this shoot flawless.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">The pic below is right out of a fairytale. I'm picturing a new version of Little Red Riding Hood. I guess it would be Little Red Riding Hoods.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1706" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1704/scr2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1706" title="scr2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/scr2.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Meet Jenna and Janae.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1712" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1704/scr8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1712" title="scr8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/scr8.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">They started the shoot shy and reserved, but that didn't last long. Soon they realized having their picture taken was all about having fun.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1708" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1704/scr4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1708" title="scr4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/scr4.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1711" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1704/scr7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1711" title="scr7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/scr7.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">They are identical twins, but there are slight differences, both physical and in their presonalities.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1707" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1704/scr3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1707" title="scr3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/scr3.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Jenna is a little more brave, a little more outgoing, and a little more bold. Janae is more independent, and slow to trust, but once she does, she's all love.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1713" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1704/scr9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1713" title="scr9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/scr9.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Both are alike in so many ways, but different too.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1710" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1704/scr6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1710" title="scr6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/scr6.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Twins have an undeniable connection that keeps them close forever.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1714" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1704/scr10"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1714" title="scr10" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/scr10.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Their parents Joy and Tom have done a wonderful job of fostering their twin connection, but also showing them they are independent people. What a fine balance.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I met Joy my second year as a teacher. I guess you could say she was a mentor, but that would be an understatement. She was so much more. She's an amazing teacher to this day, but I remember when she and Tom were struggling trying to get pregnant. Like me she put off having kids, so it took a long time. Just as she was about to give up she got the news. I'll never forget the joy she had when she found out she was pregnant, and with twins! She was so happy! I'm so happy for her. It's so clear Joy's and Tom's life wouldn't be complete without these girls.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1709" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1704/scr5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1709" title="scr5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/scr5.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">THIS is my favorite. I mean at the end of the day what's important?</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1705" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1704/scr1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1705" title="scr1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/scr1.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Joy, Tom, Jenna, Janae, thank you soooo much for letting me take your pics. Words can't describe.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Engagement pictures~ Kansas City</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1720</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 03 Nov 2010 20:11:19 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1720</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">Selena contacted me last January and told me she wanted to give her boyfriend a special gift/hint for Valentines day. Boudoir photos, with a twist! I love twists, so of coures I was intrigued. She wanted me to take a hot pic of her in her special undies that said hint hint. She had been dating her boyfriend Johnny for awhile and wanted to let him know she was ready to be with him forever. Well, it worked because now the two are tying the knot this spring.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I think the hot gesture is just the beginning for these two. First of all they are hot! Both have dabbled in modeling, which made my job oh so easy, and fun. Second, their love is hot. I think you'll see it's clear they can't keep their hands off each other. But the coolest thing is that Selena looks so different when she's with Johnny. I mean she's gorgeous, but when she's with Johnny she has a little extra glow, a little bigger smile, and she laughs all the time. I love that he makes her feel so good about herself, and that he laughs at my jokes, even when they aren't funny.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I tried hard to capture their chemistry in these pics, but you just gotta see it in person to really feel it.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1729" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1720/sj9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1729" title="sj9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/sj9.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">They just seem to fit together well.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1726" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1720/sj6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1726" title="sj6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/sj6.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">In the pic on the right there was this little perfect patch of light that was so glam. No flash here folks, just good ol' fashion sun. The pic on the left is my attempt to challenge myself. I'm really trying to reach inside and figure out who I am as an artist. I love it, the process, and the product.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1728" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1720/sj8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1728" title="sj8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/sj8.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a><a rel="attachment wp-att-1733" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1720/sj13"></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">I think they should name their first born fierce.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1733" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1720/sj13"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1733" title="sj13" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/sj13.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1724" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1720/sj4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1724" title="sj4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/sj4.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1732" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1720/sj12"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1732" title="sj12" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/sj12.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1730" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1720/sj10"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1730" title="sj10" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/sj10.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">The pic on the left was taken under a huge cypress tree. Not really sure if that's what kind it was, but it was gorgeous. It swallowed them whole with thegooey golden light.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1722" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1720/sj2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1722" title="sj2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/sj2.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1725" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1720/sj5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1725" title="sj5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/sj5.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1723" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1720/sj3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1723" title="sj3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/sj3.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1721" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1720/sj1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1721" title="sj1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/sj1.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1727" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1720/sj7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1727" title="sj7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/sj7.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1731" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1720/sj11"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1731" title="sj11" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/sj11.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Selena and Johnny I had a great time taking these pics. Your love is real, and I feel lucky to be the one getting to capture it!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">xoxo, AL</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>I heart bellies and babies! ~ Kansas city photog</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1739</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 05 Nov 2010 14:40:27 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1739</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Meet Desiree, and David. Two cops having a baby. Sounds like a sitcom, but their relationship is anything but a funny daytime TV show.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1758" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1739/des4-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1758" title="des4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/des41.jpg" alt="" width="742" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Desiree is the type of person that makes everyone feel important. During her maternity shoot she was brave, confident, and willing to be silly with me.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1757" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1739/des3-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1757" title="des3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/des31.jpg" alt="" width="693" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">David did everything he could to make Desiree feel beautiful. During maternity shoots it's not really about the boys, their job is to admire their glowing wife. I would say David was pretty obsessed with Desiree during the shoot.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1756" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1739/des2-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1756" title="des2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/des21.jpg" alt="" width="693" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Desiree looked and felt beautiful, and it shows in these pics.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1755" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1739/des1-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1755" title="des1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/des11.jpg" alt="" width="693" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1759" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1739/des5-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1759" title="des5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/des51.jpg" alt="" width="693" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">A few months later and a little early, baby Audrey was born. Bright-eyed and strong.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1754" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1739/aud10"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1754" title="aud10" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/aud10.jpg" alt="" width="743" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1753" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1739/aud9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1753" title="aud9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/aud9.jpg" alt="" width="742" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Typically newborn shoots are interrupted with feedings, diaper changes, and breaks with mom to chill. Audrey rocked the whole shoot with just one diaper change. She barely whined, and gave me all her best looks. She was amazing!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1749" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1739/aud5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1749" title="aud5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/aud5.jpg" alt="" width="742" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1751" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1739/aud7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1751" title="aud7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/aud7.jpg" alt="" width="693" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1752" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1739/aud8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1752" title="aud8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/aud8.jpg" alt="" width="742" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">I know I usually only share the really cute pictures of newborns, where the little baby is sleeping, or looking at the camera deep in thought. But today, I couldn't resist posting the next pic. We'll title this one, The Scream. Inspired by artist Munch. She's not actually screaming, just yawning, but I thought it was too funny to pass up. Not to mention those rolls on the knees. Perfection!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1748" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1739/aud4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1748" title="aud4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/aud4.jpg" alt="" width="743" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Desiree is always so good at giving me her beautiful camera face. She's such a natural. Like mother like daughter.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1750" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1739/aud6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1750" title="aud6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/aud6.jpg" alt="" width="743" height="500" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1746" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1739/aud2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1746" title="aud2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/aud2.jpg" alt="" width="743" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Do newborns chillax? Audrey is starting a new trend.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1747" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1739/aud3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1747" title="aud3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/aud3.jpg" alt="" width="744" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">David and Desiree, as always I enjoyed our time together. It just feels like I've been a part of the family forever. Audrey is a beautiful baby and you two are perfect parents. You were obssessed with Audrey before she arrived, and now, even more so. Love Love Love!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1745" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1739/aud1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1745" title="aud1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/aud1.jpg" alt="" width="693" height="500" /></a>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Finding Joy</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1770</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 11 Nov 2010 00:58:19 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1770</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[My dogs have found their joy. It comes in the form of little brown pellets that smell nasty, but apparently taste delicious to them.  Every day from 2-4 anytime I get up to do anything they are at my feet, hoping it's time to get a little bit of their joy. Lucy spins wreckless circles, and Layla jumps up and down repeatedly on her hind legs. It's annoying to me, and most days I look at them and say "not yet"! But sometimes, I just laugh. When it is finally dinner time they gobble up the food in seconds, go outside, come back in, and lick the bowls, just in case.

Watching them every day gets me thinking about joy, and how easy it is to have it taken away, and how hard it can be to find. I recently let someone steal my joy, but just for a little second. I felt bad, and even worse, bad about myself. Like I had failed. It was all in my head of course, but for that half day my joy was gone. So, I did some reflecting, some yoga, and then decided that in 5 years I wouldn't even remember this situation. If only it was as easy as pouring some brown pellets in a bowl. I was indeed able to reclaim my joy fairly fast, but it was all on me, and for some I know it's not that easy. Right now, during this crazy holiday season joy is all around us. I love the family time, the parties with friends, the decorations, the food, but when all that's gone and the deep gray winter sky settles in, it's easy to lose sight of what's important... my joy!

So, to help me remember here is a little list.

Jon, puppies, family, friends, PHOTOGRAPHY, my work, wait is that the same?, Diamond horse, a clean house, travel, reading, eating, I love food, making new friends, learning about a new culture, helping someone in need

That's a pretty good list, I'm pretty sure there are lots of other things, I'll just have to add as I go. I have a lot to be thankful for, and when I look at this list there is no reason I should ever let someone take my joy! I hope you do the same.

xoxo

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1771" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1770/ind_2106">
<img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-1771" title="IND_2106" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/IND_2106-900x598.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="299" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1773" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1770/mac5"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-1773" title="mac5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/mac5-598x900.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="677" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1772" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1770/mac3"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-1772" title="mac3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/mac3-900x598.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="299" /></a>]]></content:encoded>
