	<item>
		<title>Family Pictures ~ Kansas City Photographer</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1777</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 12 Nov 2010 16:08:07 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1777</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">Some people sparkle, not because they are a vampire in twilight, but because they have so much inner beauty they just glow without even trying, even in the dark.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Trisha is one of those people. You walk in the room and she immediately takes over with her glowing, shining beautiful nature. I met Trisha by coincidence, well not really. She married Bobby Guffey. Prepare yourself for some giggles, we were in 4H together! Yup I use to show and actively participate in 4H. 4H forever baby!!!! We didn't raise cows, or knit, but we did show horses together. I was there when Bobby showed his horse Traveler for the first time, got his first truck, and his first kiss. Time passed and we lost touch. Until this summer when he was at a wedding I was shooting. Trisha was in the wedding. Funny how things work out. Trisha and I hit it off immediately. Both of us girls that just like to have fun! Long story shorter, she let me take her family pictures this fall. I think you'll understand the whole sparkle thing after seeing these pics. The whole bunch loves to laugh and have fun, and so did I!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1787" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1777/gu11"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1787" title="gu11" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/gu11.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Bobby with his parents. They've known me forever, but haven't seen me in years, so when I walked in and Bob told me I hadn't changed, at all, I wanted to give him a big smackaroo!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1782" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1777/gu6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1782" title="gu6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/gu6.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Gage with his grandma. Look at those sweet little hands. Don't let him fool you in these pics, he's all boy. In fact he reminds me of those sour patch kid commercials. One second he's shooting you down with his stick gun, and the next he's giving you a huge hug.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Trisha gets her inner glow from her mom Sheila. When I got to their house she came out to help me and offered me a bowl of chili and iced tea because she knew I'd been shooting all day. Now that's a mom!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1784" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1777/gu8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1784" title="gu8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/gu8.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Timeless</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1781" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1777/gu5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1781" title="gu5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/gu5.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1783" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1777/gu7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1783" title="gu7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/gu7.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I imagine Trisha spends most of her time like this. Those boys are obsessed with her, so it was easy for my to take their pictures.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1786" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1777/gu10"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1786" title="gu10" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/gu10.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1779" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1777/gu2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1779" title="gu2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/gu2.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Gage you were perfect!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1785" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1777/gu9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1785" title="gu9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/gu9.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">So Bobby and Trisha...</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1780" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1777/gu3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1780" title="gu3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/gu3.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1778" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1777/gu1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1778" title="gu1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/gu1.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Wow! Words can't describe how much fun I had taking these family pictures! Trisha and Bobby your family is like hot chocolate on a cold day. Sweet and comforting. Thanks for letting me capture its beauty!</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>A classic family ~ Kansas city photographer</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1793</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 17 Nov 2010 01:40:24 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1793</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">There are some families that have been with me from the beginning. I hold these special people close to my heart. In my early years as a photographer they gave me a chance, they believed in me, they supported and encouraged me, and to this day they come to me to capture their ever changing precious moments. The Habiger family is one of those families, and I love them more than peanut butter. I've been taking their pictures for years now, and I hope to never stop.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Chris and Karri are the parents that gently hold eachother and weap while they view their pictures because they are so in awe of the amazing kids their love was able to create. Just look.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1799" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1793/hab6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1799" title="hab6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/hab6.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Their kids Rudy and Ella are little lively bundles of joy.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1800" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1793/hab7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1800" title="hab7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/hab7.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Chris and Karri believe strongly in encouraging independence because they want their kids to someday be able to stand on their own two feet.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1797" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1793/hab4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1797" title="hab4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/hab4.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1798" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1793/hab5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1798" title="hab5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/hab5.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1796" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1793/hab3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1796" title="hab3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/hab3.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">They like to have fun!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1794" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1793/hab1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1794" title="hab1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/hab1.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1801" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1793/hab8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1801" title="hab8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/hab8.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1795" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1793/hab2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1795" title="hab2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/hab2.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1802" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1793/hab9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1802" title="hab9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/hab9.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">And they always make each other a priority. A first priority, because they understand that they are the foundation of their family, and without a strong foundation there is nothing to build on. I feel lucky to know this family, and to be their family photographer.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>What if...</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1806</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 18 Nov 2010 21:15:10 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1806</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[What if we're all here for a reason? What if we all have this amazing potential to create our own reality? What if life is more than a collection of memories, but a choice? I'm always soul searching. Looking for the answers. Yesterday I stumbled on Oprah's show, and I haven't watched it in years but I thought I should try to start since it's her last season. I watched, listened, absorbed and turned the TV off, but it stuck like a good book or movie that you ponder for hours afterwards. Without telling you everything, I'll just say it's about miracles. Do you believe? Maybe not, and maybe that's why you're stuck. I think achieving greatness is a bit of a miracle. You have to believe. I struggle with this daily, but remedy the struggles by reminding myself that I am worthy of greatness, of happiness, of complete joy. I have attached the bits that stuck with me, but you can read the whole article <a href="http://http://www.oprah.com/spirit/Do-You-Believe-in-Miracles_1/1">here</a>.

"I believe the power of belief, the power of the mind, are far more powerful than we have begun to explore," he says."I believe that's an unexplored wilderness in terms of research."

In terms of his own experience with John of God, Dr. Rediger says it's been life-changing."Perhaps the real heart within us is not just a pump, he says."Perhaps the real heart within us is about love and faith. Perhaps the physical body is not who we really are. Perhaps we are these invisible souls walking around, and the body is just an instrument or metaphor for something we are trying to learn."

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1807" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1806/q3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1807" title="q3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/q3.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1808" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1806/ba3-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1808" title="ba3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/ba3.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1812" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1806/earn9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1812" title="earn9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/earn9.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1813" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1806/ed3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1813" title="ed3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/ed3.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>

<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1821" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1806/w10"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1821" title="w10" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/w10.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I don't know what I believe... but I know I believe in you... and me... and love.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>My little Elf...</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1824</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 29 Nov 2010 03:55:40 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1824</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">Photography is my passion, my air, my dream, my reality. Not so much Jon's. But it doesn't stop him from helping me any chance he gets. Most the time it's on location or in the studio, carrying gear, holding reflectors, adjusting light stands and moving backdrops and props around. But, really his biggest job is to bounce around behind the camera getting the attention of kids and adults of all ages. He's pretty much a natural, and I can always count on his beautiful mug to bring out a smile with even the most serious babies. They love him. He's a bit of a kid magnet. And I love that about him. Even more than all his free time he puts in to help me with my business even though he doesn't have to.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Here's a picture taken this weekend! The little guy insisted Jon come over and sit by him.</p>


<a rel="attachment wp-att-1826" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1824/ind_3698-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1826" title="IND_3698" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/IND_36981.jpg" alt="" width="466" height="700" /></a>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Twins ~ Kansas city photographer</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1829</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 30 Nov 2010 22:59:01 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1829</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a rel="attachment wp-att-1834" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1829/mur5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1834" title="mur5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/mur5.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">When Brooke contacted me and told me she wanted photographs of her twin identical babies and 2 year old I was all excited for the challenge. Then it occured to me that maybe I was taking on more than I could handle, especially without Jon around to help. Until I meet Brooke, her mom Judy, and her girls!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">As with any and all twin photo shoots you get one quiet and content and the other starts wailing. And, these girls were convinced the studio was way too much fun to sleep. Brooke and Judy were amazing and so patient. Brooke had two goals...a pic of the girls together and and a pic with the sisters together in their tutu's. I think it's always a good idea when you're working with kids this age to come in with a goal. So smart.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is big sister Reagan. She was awesome through 90 percent of the shoot, and then the last little 10 percent she acted like a 2 year old. Sassy, confident, and opinionated. So cute.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1835" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1829/mur6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1835" title="mur6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/mur6.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">It's funny I just noticed how similar these smiles really are. Love it! Alana was so chilled out, she loves having her pictures taken.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1833" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1829/mur4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1833" title="mur4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/mur4.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">You may have noticed they don't actually look identical, and I'm not crazy, they are. It's just they were premature, and Delaney is smaller than her sister. They both are still teeny tiny even at 12 weeks.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1832" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1829/mur3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1832" title="mur3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/mur3.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Oh and sometimes twins cry together. There is a whole series of these pics where they are literally moving their arms around in perfect mirror form.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1831" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1829/mur2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1831" title="mur2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/mur2.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">At the end of the shoot little Delaney decided sleeping in her sisters arms was perfect a perfect idea. And so did I.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1830" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1829/mur1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1830" title="mur1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/mur1.jpg" alt="" width="752" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I love these girls! I hope I get to capture ther beautiful little mugs forever!</p>]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Children Portraits ~ Kansas City Photographer</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1845</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 08 Dec 2010 15:23:41 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1845</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">I've known Alice since college, in fact I was one of the first people she met on campus as her Freshman orientation assistant. Unlike many freshman Alice was confident, outgoing, and oh so happy, she wasn't afraid to show it and share it.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">If I had to pick one word for Alice it would be passionate. She had passion for the people in her life, her religion, and her theatre practice. It should come as no surprise that she was a rock star on stage. Years later I'm happy to report Alice is still sharing that passion and zest for life. In fact, she is even more in love with life now that she has two beautiful babies! I had the honor of capturing some tender moments with her kids on a cold December day.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1851" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1845/lar6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1851" title="lar6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/lar6.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1850" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1845/lar5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1850" title="lar5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/lar5.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Her hubby Josh owns a pedal company. Something musically oriented so way out of my league, but you can check it out <a href="http://www.jhspedals.com/jhspedals/Home.html">here</a>. He's kinda a big deal in the music world.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1847" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1845/lar2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1847" title="lar2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/lar2.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1846" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1845/lar1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1846" title="lar1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/lar1.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1849" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1845/lar4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1849" title="lar4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/lar4.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1848" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1845/lar3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1848" title="lar3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/lar3.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Little Emma is practicing her mothering skills. At just three she already so good with her baby brother Eliott. While we were getting ready to bring him over for the shot she was all "come here little guy, it's ok". Too cute for words!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1852" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1845/lar7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1852" title="lar7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/lar7.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Alice it was a joy working with your kids! They are perfection!</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Obvious Love ~ Engagement pictures, Kansas City</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1856</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 14 Dec 2010 13:26:05 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1856</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">They'd been friends for a long time, but Samantha was secretly pineing over Chris. And, there was always the mutual attraction, but it wasn't until recently that they were able to truly admit their love. That's when Chris decided to propose, and she said yes. From behind the camera their love was obvious. Their connection was magnetic, when he moved, she moved, when she moved, he moved. Ok, so I stole that from Eclipse, but their love might just be as good as Edward and Bella's. Seriously. We tooled around the city Thursady afternoon, looking for all the best light, not that we needed it. Samantha was glowing.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1864" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1856/sam8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1864" title="sam8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/sam8.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Did I mention Chris was awesome! He was so up for anything. Loved it!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1863" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1856/sam7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1863" title="sam7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/sam7.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Sam, you're hot. Seriously you worked it!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1861" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1856/sam5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1861" title="sam5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/sam5.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is a little planning and a lot of luck!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1862" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1856/sam6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1862" title="sam6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/sam6.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Gorgeous!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1868" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1856/sam12"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1868" title="sam12" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/sam12.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1866" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1856/sam10"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1866" title="sam10" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/sam10.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Chris's family owns <a href="http://eskewjewelers.com/">Eskew</a> jewelry, and he runs the store in Indep. So you can imagine how gorgeous the ring was. Huge perfect solitaire, and 2 yellow diamonds on the side. Custom design for Sam. Very pretty!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1858" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1856/sam2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1858" title="sam2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/sam2.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1865" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1856/sam9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1865" title="sam9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/sam9.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1860" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1856/sam4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1860" title="sam4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/sam4.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">So, I'm kinda crazy. Which is probably why I decided to sing a creepy song for them while they danced around during these pics. I can't sing so it came out more as a collection of weird noises. Whatever, it made them laugh, and it's a great memory we won't every forget!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1859" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1856/sam3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1859" title="sam3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/sam3.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">This pic sums it up! Taken at <a href="http://www.kansascitymenus.com/harryscountryclub/">Harry's Country Club</a>, one of my favorite restaurants! They both have those googley eyes. I love it!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1857" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1856/sam1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1857" title="sam1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/sam1.jpg" alt="" width="752" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is on the wall at Harry's. Hilarious.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1870" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?attachment_id=1870"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1870" title="sam13" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/sam13.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Sam and Chris, I had a blast taking your engagment pictures! I'm already looking forward to your exotic wedding next year!!!!</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>My favorite Christmas gifts...EVER!</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1874</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 24 Dec 2010 03:55:59 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1874</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a rel="attachment wp-att-1875" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1874/mad3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1875" title="mad3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/mad3.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">So this post was inspired by one of my most favorite clients, little Eva from Arkansas. Here is the facebook message I received today titled "You have competition".</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">"Allison - Eva got a "pink camera" for Christmas (Santa came early to our house as we are leaving for Boston tmw). She has been quite a shutterbug ever since - truly hilarious. By about 9 am, she had taken 200 photos. Of which, 20 were good. My favorites were the pictures of the TV while she was watching her new Tinkerbell movie. We've also enjoyed holding one of her toys while she takes a picture of it. This may be her calling.... :)"</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">So having shared this I was inspired to post a list of the gifts that left their mark on me. I'll try to keep this short because I know all of you have your own presents to unwrap.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">My top 10 favorite Christmas presents of all time...</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">10. A sewing machine - My brother James gave me a pretty hard time about this one. He thought I was nerdy, I thought I was finally free.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">9. A wicker vanity- Ok, this one wasn't that great when I finally realized it was furniture, but the under tree suspense was huge, because the boxes were out of this world big and wrapped.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">8. A leather jacket- My mom totally had me crying at that Christmas because I thought I hadn't gotten it only to watch her pull it out...after Christmas. I was pretty snotty at that gangly age of 13 and probably deserved it.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">7. Plastic white bouncey horse- I don't remember this one much but the home videos are evidence enough that I really really loved it! Even bonked my mouth on the hard plastic mane and kept on riding.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">6. A funeral package - I'm not lying, my dad bought Jon and I plots and funeral packages. Apparently it's a big investment. I told him it was the gift of eternity.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">5. Stuffed reindeer - Every year my mom would put a reindeer in my stocking. I was a stuffed animal buff and loved it when I would see that little fuzzy head sticking out of my stocking. I'm still hoping she brings that tradition back someday.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">4. G.I. Joes, homemade guns, and barbies, I couldn't pick.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">3. A mixed music casette tape my brother made for me by copying off his own collection. I don't remember all the songs, but I do remember "Desperado" and "Allison's Road".</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">2. My engagement ring - Jon had it all wrapped up in a nice story of our relationship. Pure perfection.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">1. Money - Sorry for the serious anticlimatic nature of this one, but need I say more? Really?</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">This wasn't an easy task because really I've been blessed with so many gifts over the years, it's hard to pick favorites, but these were the first to come to mind. Nowadays, Jon and I don't even exchange gifts. We buy trips around the world, furniture, and tennis lessons, to share together. When I look back my favorite gifts have nothing to do with the actual gift, the unwrapping, or the suspence of opening them, rather, I remember the moments in time that these material objects help me remember. Isn't that what it's really about, a moment in time marked with a feeling of joy and complete happiness. I wish all of you joy and complete happiness this holiday season.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I have so much love in my heart for all of you!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Happy Holidays!!!!!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1876" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1874/ind_0497"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-1876" title="IND_0497" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/IND_0497-900x599.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="299" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Boudoir Photography ~ Kansas City</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1883</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 03 Jan 2011 03:07:59 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1883</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">With the holidays barely behind us it's time to start thinking about the next holiday. One of my favs...Valentine's Day! I love the candy, flowers, dinner dates, pink and red galore, the basic concept, and of course the cards. I don't even care that it's a very successful Hallmark marketing scheme. What I don't love is coming up with a good gift for Jon. That's mostly why I love taking BOUDOIR photos and making the daunting task of shopping for hubby easy. Super easy. Here are a few of the pics I recently took. I wish I could share more, but privacy is important. She was super ecstatic to share the pics, because she loved how she looked. You should know she's around 40. I'll just leave it at that.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">There is just a few thing you should know about my boudoir photography.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">1. All the pics are tastefully done, I like to consider them art. Really hot art.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">2. The shoots last about an hour and a half.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">3. I'll help you with wardrobe.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">4. It really helps if you get your makeup professionally done.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">5. You can drink wine and bring a friend.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">6. I promise to make you look and feel your very best, inside and out.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">7. Yes, I will airbrush you to perfection. :)</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">8. Ultimately you control the shoot, but I will guide you through poses and coach you on how to look sexy. Don't worry smiles are also so sexy, if you're like me and look ridiculous being serious.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">9. Lastly, I love doing these boudoir pictures. They are some of my favorite shoots to take.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1886" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1883/bou3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1886" title="bou3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/bou3.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1885" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1883/bou2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1885" title="bou2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/bou2.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="399" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1888" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1883/bou5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1888" title="bou5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/bou5.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="399" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1884" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1883/bou1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1884" title="bou1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/bou1.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="399" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1887" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1883/bou4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1887" title="bou4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/bou4.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="399" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Here are some of the comments a few of my lovely ladies have given me about their experience.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">"My boudoir session was AMAZING! I was so apprehensive about doing it because, I am not a fan of my body, but I wanted to do it for my husband to have on our wedding day. When I left your studio, I was so confident with myself and the curves I have. You made the session so comfortable and truly made me feel beautiful with all of my curves!! When I saw the pictures, it made me look at myself in a new way. Not only did I like my body but you captured parts of my that I would have never seen as beautiful. I was amazed!!! These pictures did so much for my self image! Oh yeah, and my husband loves them too!!"</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">"Allison is a wonderful photographer. After having some fantastic pictures taken of our 2 month old I decided a boudoir shoot would be a great Christmas present for my husband. Being a little hesitant, as I had only given birth 13 weeks ago and wasn't quite back to pre-baby body, I called her up and scheduled a shoot. It was so much fun! You lose all sense of being self-conscious. She makes you feel like a supermodel! I highly recommend to all women, not only as a great gift for your significant other, but also as an intense self-esteem booster."</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">"I decided my boyfriend of two years needed a little motivation to take the next step. I asked Allison to take some sexy pics of me in my 'hint hint' panties and she helped make my dream come true. My pictures were not only beautiful but a work of art, I've never looked or felt more beautiful. My boyfriend must of felt the same because he took the 'hint' and we're currently engaged."</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>My 2011 Goals</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1893</link>
		<pubDate>Sun, 02 Jan 2011 00:26:34 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1893</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Last year I made a list of goals. It was really more of a 5 year plan. Little did I know that when I put my mind to something, great things can happen, and sometime saying it out loud does help. So before I go into my 2011 goals I need to take a look back.  These were posted exactly one year ago today.

1.<span style="text-decoration: line-through;"> Grow my business, I mean really grow my business. That means following up with clients, asking them for referrals, and being brave enough to put myself out there. Part of this will come from being a part of a business networking group.<strong> </strong></span><strong> I have indeed grown my business, I need to work on the referral thing, but I get better every day about putting myself out there. The networking group is doing so amazing. I really wouldn't even call it that now, it's more of a business growth group. We all push eachother to achieve more every month. Love it!</strong>

2. <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">Have my first gallery opening! There are really 2 sets of photos I want to have gallery openings for. The first Indonesia, </span>and the second women, beautiful women, normal women. You get the idea. Photography is my passion, my art and I need to make that form of my expression a priority. <strong>The gallery opening was a huge success. I can now mark that one off my bucket list. I look forward to sharing my work more in 2011. Right now it's on display at Cafe Sophia, and in just a couple days it will be on display at Dean and Deluca in Overland Park. I also participated in some art shows. </strong>

3. <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">Have over 150 shoots. </span><strong> I blew this one away. Haven't stopped to count, but I think it's more around 200! </strong>

4. <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">Run a photography workshop, I want to share what I know with others, and hopefully learn something too. </span><strong>YES! I held my workshop and it was great. I will be hosting more of these in 2011.</strong>

5. S<span style="text-decoration: line-through;">ome small stuff, shopping cart for proof page, new blog, new pics on website (almost done with that one YES), you get the idea, for most of this stuff I need Jon's help. </span><strong>New website should be posted soon.</strong>

6. G<span style="text-decoration: line-through;">et 1,000 fans on my facebook page. I'm not sure if this directly results in new clients, but it can't hurt. Just 500 to go. Yikes that's a lot! Please suggest my page to friends, that would be awesome, and help a lot!</span><strong> Actually just recently reached 2,000. Thank you so much for suggesting my page to your friends! I love communicating with my clients, fans, and fellow photography lovers.</strong>

7. I have 2 photography book ideas, but I have no idea where to start. This year I'm going to start and see what happens. <strong>This one will be on the 2011 list, I dabbled, but didn't touch.</strong>

8. Finally I want to start a charity organization that takes pictures of kids in poverty. I've seen those kids, I've worked with those families and those kids deserve good pictures too! <strong>I didn't get the charity started, but I did donate over 2,300 in sittings to great charity events!</strong>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="font-weight: normal;">Only two to move on! Not bad. Looking at these goals now I see that I need to reach for bigger and better things. I need to stretch myself thin. Here goes nothin'!</span></strong></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><strong><span style="font-weight: normal;">1. Photography books</span></strong></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><strong><span style="font-weight: normal;">2. I want to become more active in a charity that helps families that can't afford high end portraits. </span></strong></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><strong><span style="font-weight: normal;">3. Attend a workshop with a fabulous photog that can help me define my style. I'm getting close, but I know I can get closer.</span></strong></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><strong><span style="font-weight: normal;">4. I've been dabbling in all things portrait photography. This year I want to push myself to look into other industries. I'm really loving fashion photography right now. I like to study the lighitng techniques.</span></strong></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><strong><span style="font-weight: normal;">5. I would like to do more travel with my photography. Not just for weddings, but for family/kid shoots. I think Texas will be my first trip. </span></strong></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><strong><span style="font-weight: normal;">6. Hire my first employee. This one scares me, but I'm most excited about it. I want someone reliable, but also creative, and supportive. </span></strong></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><strong><span style="font-weight: normal;">7. Continue to show my Indonesia series around the city, and someday I want to have a gallery opening in NYC!</span></strong></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><strong><span style="font-weight: normal;">8. I want to put together a collection of powerful images of kids with handicaps. My good friend Karren is going to write their stories, and together we want to help raise awareness for these special kids. I also have an idea for a series of pictures about women and their challenges. The map has been made now I just need to make it happen.</span></strong></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><strong><span style="font-weight: normal;">9. I'm going to get organized with my time, establish some real guidelines for myself and my clients.</span></strong></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><strong><span style="font-weight: normal;">10. Still need to do better with follow up. I need to show the clients I love and adore how much they mean to me.</span></strong></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><strong><span style="font-weight: normal;">11. Read a book that will help me grow professionally every month.</span></strong></p>
<p style="text-align: left;">12. Blog regularly, 3 times a week ideally. I also want to get better about blogging about the photography business.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>There they are! Get ready 2011, I'm taking this year by storm.</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Happy New Year's everyone! May all your dreams come true in the next 12 months!</strong></p>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>How to take group pictures of kids...tips that sometimes work.</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1898</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 05 Jan 2011 02:54:33 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1898</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">There's really only one thing harder than herding cats...taking pics of 5 kids four years old and younger, and getting them to smile, and getting them to look at the camera, and getting them to sit still.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Ok, in truth, there are probably a lot of things harder, like brain surgery, or building a spaceship, but for me, this is my challenge. I have very little control of these shoots, but the little control I do have I want to share with you.  The itty bitty things I've learned along the way that make it more likely to get a good shot. I promise these methods won't work every time, in fact they'll only work some of the time and sometimes none of the time. I think I might have gotten wordy, but you get the point. It's hard, real hard. So without further adieu here are my tips for herding cats, I mean um... taking pictures of cute kids.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1907" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1898/car9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1907" title="car9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/car9.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Tip #1 - I usually don't jump right in and start taking pics the second the families arrive, I like to build a little repore with the kids by talking to them. I try to make eye contact with them and not their parents. While chatting it up about Santa, candy, and favorite sports I try to assess the kids and their attitudes towards pictures, and more importantly me.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1903" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1898/car5-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1903" title="car5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/car5.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Tip #2- I always start with the hardest picture, in this case it was the group picture. I usually have very limited time with the limited attention span at this age, so I have to be sure to use my time wisely. Get the hard one over with. It's much easier to get one kid focused than 5.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Tip #3- It took me a long time to figure out that it's really best to only have one parent in the room. For this family shoot, there were two families, so 4 adults, 2 grandparents, 5 kids, and Jon and I crowded into my small studio. With all those people the kids get overwhelmed, it gets loud, and the kids don't know where to look because everyone is trying to get them to smile. I just ask the parents to pick one person that they think would do the best at nurturing the scared ones, while making the serious ones laugh. Between the 3 of us we can usually cover it.</p>
<a style="text-decoration: none;" rel="attachment wp-att-1904" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1898/car6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1904" title="car6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/car6.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Tip #4- Kinda goes with tip 3. I try to make sure the people that are in the room with me understand that I want the kids to look at the camera, so toward me. Parents are awesome at getting their kids to smile, so I usually just ask them to get real close to me. Or even play peek a boo behind my head. Jon and I do all kinds of crazy things to get kids to look. Layla has sat on my head many a time!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1905" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1898/car7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1905" title="car7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/car7.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Tip #5- I never put my camera down unless I think I've got the shot. I'm always always waiting for that perfect expression of the kids personality.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1906" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1898/car8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1906" title="car8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/car8.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Tip #6- I don't wait for the smiles. Sometimes the in between moments are even more precious. Like the pic below.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1900" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1898/car2-2">
<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1900" title="car2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/car2.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Tip #7- If kids do get upset and cry I don't fret, I just work with their sibling, or parents. They usually come around, because everyone wants to be the center of attention. :) Even kids!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1899" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1898/car1-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1899" title="car1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/car1.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1901" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1898/car3-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1901" title="car3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/car3.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1902" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1898/car4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1902" title="car4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/car4.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I love that my job is unpredictable, I love that my tricks don't always work. It keeps me on my toes. I guess that's what this post is really about. Stay on your toes, stay ready, and have fun! Happy shooting!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">By the way I picked THE CUTEST KIDS EVER for this post. The Carlisle kids! Thanks guys for being so much fun, and sharing so much of yourselves with me!</p>]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>

		<wp:status>publish</wp:status>
		<wp:post_parent>0</wp:post_parent>

	<item>
		<title>FAQ~ cameras and business programs</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1911</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 06 Jan 2011 19:47:59 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1911</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">Sometimes my body lay awake in my bed at night, usually 4am, eyes closed, my mind a racin', but my person trying my darnest to go to sleep. Yes, I did indeed describe my mind as a separate entity. If you know me AT ALL you know my mind is not always there. I'm right brained, let's just go with that excuse for now. So I lay awake and think about everything like when to get the carpets cleaned, or new dog collars, to answering questions for my fans on my blog. The carpets and collars can wait, today I want to answer a few questions.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Question #1</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>What is a good camera for a professional/advanced amateur?</strong> This is such a loaded question because it depends on the following answers. What do you like to shoot Nikon, or Cannon?  What is your price range? When do you want to upgrade? What are you using it for?</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Having given a disclaimer here are my recommendations for Nikon, which is what I shoot. I think the D90 is great for an entry level camera, I think the <a href="http://imaging.nikon.com/products/imaging/lineup/digitalcamera/slr/d7000/index.htm">D7000</a> is even better, but it's more expensive. It has gotten great reviews. You are looking to spend 1,00-2,000 for a serious amateur camera.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Next level would be the D700. I'm hoping with my whole heart that Nikon comes out with a replacement camera this spring. I wouldn't recommend buying one of these unless you get it used. You're going to want to upgrade to a camera with high def video capabilities soon enough. Around 2,000</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Then there's my camera the D3. There is also the D3x a little cooler and a lot more costly, and the D3s which has video and I want one...bad. But I'm waiting. I just have a hunch, more is to come. These cameras are around 5,000- 8,000</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Here's the thing...camera's don't take pictures you do! So you don't have to have the biggest and best. For those of us that do it all day, everyday, it's nice to have the good stuff because it just makes like easier. For everyone else I say save the money on the body and spend it on the lens. AKA glass.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Lenses are so important! Don't ever settle for the lens that comes in the package. They are usually included cheaper for a reason. Unfortunately, in the lens world, more expensive does mean better. A good lens usually costs around 800-2,000. You can get some decent non zoom lenses for 300-500. My favorite lens is the Nikon 24-70 2.8. It's great for portraits but would really suck for sports. So consider the subject matter when you go shopping.  Also in my experience name brand matters. I've heard some good things about Tamron, I've never used one. I have used a Sigma, let's just say I don't anymore.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Question #2</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>I have so many questions about starting my business. Do you think I should enroll in an online course or something?</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Everyone learns differently, and honestly if you can afford it there are are some nicely packaged programs out there that professional photogs have put their heart and soul into. I say go for it. However, if you have the time and not the money everything you need to know is right on the web. Check out <a href="http://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=photography&amp;aq=f">you tube</a>, read blogs, and get on forums. I spent a lot of time early on submitting photos to a <a href="http://www.picturesocial.com/">photography social network </a>. The people on there are knowledgeable and helpful. Just ask. There are tons of other forums and blogs. I would start there unless you are the type of person who can't stand searching the web. Then I would get package.  The cool thing is that you can make your education your own and it's free. Happy knowledge hunting.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Ok, that's long! DANG!!! Sorry...</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I'll end with a picture that explains why I was dreaming about dog collars. I guess the girls didn't like them after all.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1912" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1911/collar"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1912" title="collar" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/collar.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Maternity/Newborn Photography ~ Kansas City</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1917</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 07 Jan 2011 20:43:18 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1917</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a rel="attachment wp-att-1919" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1917/lob2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1919" title="lob2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/lob2.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">When Lauren contacted me for maternity pictures she told me she had been talking to another photographer that hadn't gotten back in touch with her. What a great loss for that photographer and a great gain for me because I love the Lobner family!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1920" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1917/lob3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1920" title="lob3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/lob3.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">With Lauren's heart of gold that shows in everything she says and does and JR's boyish good looks their maternity shoot was a huge success. We laughed, and then laughed some more. Lauren was up for anything, and totally worked it in front of the camera. JR did what all good hubbies do during a maternity shoot, he sat back and admired his glowing wife. And made her laugh.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1918" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1917/lob1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1918" title="lob1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/lob1.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Then just a few shorts weeks later and a few 3 weeks early baby Jackson arrived. They decided to wait to find out if they were having a boy or girl. So hard, but so cool! I like to imagine the scene in the delivery room when the doctor gets to yell it's a boy! They the boys go outside and smoke cigars wrapped in baby blue paper that says "It's a Boy". Ok this might only happen in the movies, but it's dreamy non the less.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1921" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1917/lob4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1921" title="lob4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/lob4.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">JR must help a lot because he was great with this little tiny 2 week old. I wonder if Jackson's hands will someday be bigger than JR's.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1924" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1917/lob8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1924" title="lob8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/lob8.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Love this hat! Lauren when Jackson outgrows this I'll buy it from you!!!!! LOVE LOVE!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1922" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1917/lob5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1922" title="lob5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/lob5.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1923" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1917/lob7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1923" title="lob7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/lob7.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Capturing moments is what I do, and I love it. Especially these precious first ones!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Love you guys, I can't wait to be there to capture all of Jackson's personality in the future.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Maternity and Newborn pictures ~ Kansas City Photographer</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1930</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 11 Jan 2011 01:20:10 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1930</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a rel="attachment wp-att-1931" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1930/ti2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1931" title="ti2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/ti2.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">It was her laugh that I noticed first. During our shoot Tish just had a way of making me smile when she laughed. Not because it was big, or obnoxious, or silly, but it was real, and I could tell. That's what I noticed first, then I noticed how Jermaine always noticed. He smiled too.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1933" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1930/ti5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1933" title="ti5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/ti5.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Maybe the glowing came from the fact that this pregnancy was a true blessing for them, or, maybe they just glow when they're together. They tried for a long time before realizing they needed help. This story is unfortunately all too common in my studio, but I love all the success stories I get to witness. In those precious moments when clients expose their hearts and hardships to me I am humbled. But to Jermaine it's just a miracle to get pregnant at all.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1932" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1930/ti1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1932" title="ti1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/ti1.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Then came baby!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">A BIG BABY!!!!! So big in fact Tish had to have a c-section.  Beautiful, perfect Malachi was born into the arms of two very excited and very loving parents. Just a few days later I got to meet him. For an hour and a half we admired the ahh of a newborn baby. It never really gets old.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1936" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1930/garth3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1936" title="garth3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/garth3.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">See what I mean? BIG!!!!!!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1935" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1930/garth2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1935" title="garth2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/garth2.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Malachi was special because he would do these little smiles the whole time. And he's strong! He was holding his head up like crazy. It was great. I have a feeling he'll be walking way sooner than he should.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1940" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1930/garth7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1940" title="garth7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/garth7.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Cankles are so cute, for real!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1939" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1930/garth6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1939" title="garth6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/garth6.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Baby lint is too!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1937" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1930/garth4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1937" title="garth4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/garth4.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">I loved my time with this wonderful family. I hope I get to be a part of it FOREVER!!!!!</p>


<a rel="attachment wp-att-1938" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1930/garth5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1938" title="garth5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/garth5.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Snow days are great for dreaming!</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1943</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 11 Jan 2011 17:30:59 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1943</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">It's the jumping off part that's scary. You're standing on the edge with the lightness of possibility in front of you and the darkness of what you know to be true behind you. You know the darkness isn't the life you would choose given the choice, but jumping still seems harder. There is no safety net, no one comforting you or guaranteeing you'll be ok, and you know you'll fall. So do you jump?</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is exactly how I felt when I decided to leave my comfortable teaching career to pursue my dream. As it turns out I didn't fall to my demis, instead every fall, stumble, or lost way, lead me to a greater understanding that I was indeed doing the right thing, and that I would be ok. Even as I write these words there is a little voice saying, no one wants to hear this, they'll just say dreams are for dreamers. I have to hush those voices EVERY DAY! So today I'm going to write these words and push send in the hopes that someone will read this and think dreams do come true, and happiness is a choice.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Taking pictures makes me happy so today I snapped a few of the snow.  The weatherman says if feels like -15 so I didn't even leave my deck, but I can't post without pics. :) Happy Tuesday everyone!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1944" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1943/winter1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1944" title="winter1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/winter1.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">The puppies are only outside for about 30 seconds at a time. They made a path down the side of the fence where the snow is shallower. They walk about halfway down the fence where their path ends go to the bathroom and walk back along the path to the house. Spoiled.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1945" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1943/winter2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1945" title="winter2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/winter2.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1946" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1943/winter3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1946" title="winter3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/winter3.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="700" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1947" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1943/winter4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1947" title="winter4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/winter4.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Large Family Photos ~ Kansas City Photographer</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1951</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 20 Jan 2011 14:44:38 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1951</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">Right now I'm in sunny Florida helping the one and only <a href="www.maggiestolzberg.com">Mags</a> celebrate her 30th b-day. I wanted to get some focused work done while I was here, but instead I've started every day with puppy chow, gone on a 5 mile walk down the beach, and out to eat at least once a day. To say I'm overindulging is an understatement. The fun ends tomorrow so today I'm going to get some of that intended work done.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Today's post is about large family photos. These pics were taken right around the holidays so it was cold outside. In the most favorable situation I would do big family pictures outside where the light can be controlled. My studio is way too small for 20 people so in the winter the challenge becomes all about the where. I knew I wanted a location with good natural light. Lighting this many people evenly with speedlights can be tricky, and with kids tricky means I'll run out of time. So I settled on <a href="http://www.unionstation.org/">Union Station</a>, tons of beautiful filtered window light comes in and makes it a perfect location for pictures. It was perfect, minus the ridiculous photographers fee of $75. But, with a family this size the fee was necessary to get the shots.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">The trickiest part about large family photos isn't really the location or the lighting. It's really all about getting something creative which was another perk to shooting in Union Station. Here are a few of the more creative shots I was able to capture. The family was amazing, and so very easy to work with, which really makes the whole experience more fun for everyone. Lots of laughing during the shoot.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">One of the family members actually suggested this picture, and man I'm happy they did. The ceiling looks amazing! The challenge was keeping that window to the right out of the frame, and not disturbing the patrons in the restaurant. I just tell my clients to put a big smile on their faces and look like they know what they're doing. And I have to be quick.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1952" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1951/kitts1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1952" title="kitts1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/kitts1.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1953" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1951/kitts2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1953" title="kitts2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/kitts2.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Grandma with her grand kids.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1955" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1951/kitts4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1955" title="kitts4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/kitts4.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Below is a picture of the Kitts. Jon and I played tennis with Nancy and Steve this summer. They are such great people, I feel lucky to know them! And look at their beautiful family!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1954" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1951/kitts3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1954" title="kitts3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/kitts3.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">And of course when shooting a large family you always need to take the safe shot. Some people actually prefer this more formal looking picture, so I'm always sure to include it.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1956" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1951/kitts5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1956" title="kitts5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/kitts5.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">A few things to keep in mind when you are taking large family photos.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">* scope out your locations before your family gets there</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">* think about lighting and set up, I brought the bench you see to give variety</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">* be goofy behind the camera, people look better when they are actually laughing, even if it means they are laughing at you</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">* start arranging people by putting the most important people or person in the middle then work your way outward by families or couples put the kids in last</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">* don't stress, just have fun, most the time the people are already stressing</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Thanks to the Kitts family for making this an awesome shoot!</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>3 month baby pictures ~ Kansas City Photographer</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1959</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 24 Jan 2011 03:51:40 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1959</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">In Julie's words "it all happened so fast". She's talking about love, marriage, and the baby. Julie had settled into life, content with the idea that her dream of someday having kids was never going to happen. Then she met Constantin online and everything changed, and FAST! Their love was like drugs and Julie was addicted. At first I thought her stories were all to wonderful, and maybe too good to be true. Until I met Constantin, and saw for myself how much he adored her. Couldn't keep his hands off her in fact. And he knew how to make her laugh. Big, real big! It's no surprise their joy was able to make such a little slice of perfection. Meet Emma.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1961" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1959/sas2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1961" title="sas2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/sas2.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">It was so warm Emma just couldn't hold her little eyes open.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1964" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1959/sas5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1964" title="sas5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/sas5.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Gonna go ahead and say it...she's a poser!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1965" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1959/sas6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1965" title="sas6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/sas6.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Julie your affection is warm and refreshing like the sun after a week of rain.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1966" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1959/sas7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1966" title="sas7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/sas7.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1962" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1959/sas3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1962" title="sas3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/sas3.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1960" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1959/sas1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1960" title="sas1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/sas1.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">These 2 pics are exactly why no one should ever skip 3 month pics!!!!! They are so different than newborns or 6 monthers.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1963" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1959/sas4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1963" title="sas4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/sas4.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">There were 82 pictures in this collection, 82 beautiful faces, 82 little memories to hold on to forever. I'm humbled by my job, I take it very seriously, but love it fiercely!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>]]></content:encoded>
