	<item>
		<title>Newborn Photography ~ Kansas City</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1970</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 25 Jan 2011 22:12:08 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1970</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">23 eggs. There were 23 eggs in the beginning, but slowly they started to parish. One by one, until there were only 5, then 4, then 3, then 2, and finally one. One egg. One chance, that's all they had. In vitro is risky enough, but with just one egg the odds weren't in Pam and Scott's favor. But as it turns out, one egg is enough. In fact it's the perfect amount. I didn't get to meet Pam and Scott before they were pregnant, but I know they must have been changed forever when they finally got the good news after years of trying.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I guess dreams do come true...</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">meet lucky Gavin! He's the one and only, and the lucky boy to have landed in the arms of two very appreciative parents!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1973" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1970/siems3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1973" title="siems3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/siems3.jpg" alt="" width="752" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">So strong!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1975" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1970/siems5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1975" title="siems5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/siems5.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I'm not that into airplanes, but Scott flies the plane on Gavin's onsie in this picture. It's the one that flies over the Chiefs stadium. I think that's pretty cool! I think he's going to want to be just like his Daddy when he gets a little older.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1977" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1970/siems7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1977" title="siems7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/siems7.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Giddy! That's how I would describe these new parents. Pam didn't even seem tired, just happy.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1976" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1970/siems6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1976" title="siems6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/siems6.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a><a rel="attachment wp-att-1972" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1970/siems2"></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">If he seems a little chunky that's because he downed 4 ounces of milk before he was happy. I think he's going to be a big boy! Dang, you go Gavin!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1972" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1970/siems2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1972" title="siems2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/siems2.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Big appetite and big hands. Yup, I see ball sports in his future.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1974" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1970/siems4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1974" title="siems4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/siems4.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1971" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1970/siems1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1971" title="siems1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/siems1.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Scott, Pam and Gavin, I am touched forever by your story. Thank you so much for coming to me for your maternity and newborn pictures. I look forward to many more laughs in the studio, and 4 ounce feedings. :)</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Me...and the big apple!</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1985</link>
		<pubDate>Sun, 13 Feb 2011 03:06:25 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=1985</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">The anticipation had been building for weeks. The original phone calls/ emails, writing the proposal and then the anticipation of whether or not I would even get the job. But I did. And I'm here. In New York City, downtown Manhattan, shooting an ad campaign for a high end <a href="http://www.artistictile.com/">tile company</a>.  It took packing the studio and getting on the plane for the reality to sink in. I thought I would be overwhelmed, nervous, and maybe even scared. But I'm not. I'm confident, excited, and in LOVE with this city. It's nothing and everything I expected and then some. Today Jon and I spent the whole day roaming the streets. I carried my D3 in my purse and got to capture a little bit of what I was feeling. Lovely energy...everywhere.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Our view from our teeny tiny room. And our lunch location. Jon was lovin the pastries.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-2000" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1985/ny15"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2000" title="ny15" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/ny15.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1998" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1985/ny13"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1998" title="ny13" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/ny13.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">I'll title this one hotdog head!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1997" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1985/ny12"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1997" title="ny12" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/ny12.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Some weird ceremony going on in the middle of times square. Never did figure it out, but the line was really long. I just loved the video ad in the background.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1996" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1985/ny11"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1996" title="ny11" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/ny11.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Some guys walked over and pulled these two flamingos out of the dirt just as I was getting ready to snap the pic. So, I asked them to put them back for a picture, they did, and told me they were taking a little vacation. Haha!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1995" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1985/ny10"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1995" title="ny10" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/ny10.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">I didn't know he saw me. I was really trying to get the pretzels. Oh the smells on the streets. Hot greasy food.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1994" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1985/ny9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1994" title="ny9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/ny9.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Our little snack. A reece's pieces pastry. And, as good as it looks.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1992" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1985/ny7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1992" title="ny7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/ny7.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">The guy in the pizza shop is smiling at me. Didn't know that until later when I downloaded them.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1993" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1985/ny8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1993" title="ny8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/ny8.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1991" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1985/ny6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1991" title="ny6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/ny6.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Musicians make central park so speical, the music, and their love for it.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1990" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1985/ny5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1990" title="ny5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/ny5.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1989" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1985/ny4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1989" title="ny4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/ny4.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1988" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1985/ny3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1988" title="ny3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/ny3.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-1986" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1985/ny1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1986" title="ny1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/ny1.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">I turned around and snapped this one off just in time.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1987" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1985/ny2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1987" title="ny2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/ny2.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Even Jon loves this big city. There's just something special here. I hope tomorrow brings even more creativity and lovely energy.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-1999" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/1985/ny14"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1999" title="ny14" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/ny14.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Home Sweet Home</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2003</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 16 Feb 2011 17:34:25 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=2003</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">I'm home and so happy to be able to catch up on some processing, but first I wanted to share a pic Jon took with our new <a href="http://shop.usa.canon.com/webapp/wcs/stores/servlet/product_10051_10051_255917_-1">powershot G12</a> at the shoot on Sunday.  It's a great little camera to keep in my purse and it has good glass and high ISO capabilites. So excited to see what this little guy can do out and about. Maybe I'll stop lugging my D3 around in my purse.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">So the shoot was even more perfect than I expected. We arrived about 10AM and since we had set up the lights the night before we didn't have much to do while the models Jess and Danielle got their hair and makeup done. We wandered around the huge showroom looking at the tile backdrops they wanted to shoot in front of. Jess was the first to be ready and her dress fit her like a glove despite the fact that it was made of tile. The back was all open which was great because it showed off her beautiful back and perfect profile. The front wasn't finished and she couldn't lift her arms up, but she worked it. I really only had 2 posing options for her so I used the light to make the shots interesting and diverse.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Eduardo is adjusting Jess's dress, he made it! When I asked him if it's hard to make clothes out of tile he said no. He makes clothes for photo shoots all the time, and man he's talented! I was so happy to have him there, along with a whole slew of wonderful people that were always helping make sure the dress layed right and their hair looked perfect.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-2006" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2003/at2">
<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2006" title="at2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/at2.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Unfortunately, we didn't get many shots of the shoot because Jon was super busy, moving my lights, finding outlets, and changing from beauty dish, to strip light, to octobox. We changed tile backgrouds a lot too which meant sometimes we shot with a shiny background. I couldn't have done it without him.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Danielle the other model had a sexy low cut tuxedo jacket on. It was hot, to say the least. Both girls had individual looks that I can't wait to share. We wrapped up around 5 and celebrated with some wine. Later, as Jon and I were taking the elevator up to our hotel room he looked at me and said that I totally rocked it. Man I love my job!</p>]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Newborn Photograpy ~ Kansas City</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2015</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 23 Feb 2011 21:13:57 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=2015</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">I met Rebecca while watching Jon and her hubby Mike play volleyball for corporate challenge. We hit it off and made plans to do lunch with the boys downtown someday. Well someday never came, but a couple years later Rebecca contacted me ready to get together...for maternity pictures!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I was more than excited because I knew they had been trying since I saw her at the volleyball game. Like so many other couples I get to know, getting pregnant was not as easy as expected.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">But they did! And they now have a little bundle of joy! Meet baby Roman!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2017" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2015/sin2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2017" title="sin2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/sin2.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Like many little newbies, Roman likes to cry, but only when he's not eating. But in the sweet moments when Roman was feeling peaceful we were able to capture the obious love this family has!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2020" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2015/sin5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2020" title="sin5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/sin5.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Rebecca and Mike are naturals and oh so relaxed!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2019" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2015/sin4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2019" title="sin4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/sin4.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2016" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2015/sin1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2016" title="sin1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/sin1.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2018" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2015/sin3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2018" title="sin3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/sin3.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Baby Roman you are so close to perfection it's scary. I have a feeling you're a little heartbreaker in the making!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>A baby story ~ Kansas City Photographer</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2023</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 25 Feb 2011 00:49:01 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=2023</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2025" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2023/re2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2025" title="re2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/re2.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">When I meet a new client, there is always a level of anxiety that I try to mask with my smile and constant conversation. I want the clients that come into my home, into my studio, to like me, feel comfortable with me, and most importantly I want to bring it for them. I want my creative energy to be uber powerful, so I can turn out the best pictures for them.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">What I sometimes forget is that my clients are equally nervous.  They are coming to a strangers house, and being asked to get pretty much naked. Geez, I thought I was nervous, but never having had this experience I can't imagine what my beloved clients must go through.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Rebecca was sent to me by her friend Pam who also just had a baby. I knew Pam would only send me the coolest people in the world, and I was right. Rebecca came in the studio nervous, but left a friend.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">We clicked.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I think I even managed to get her hubby Mike to enjoy getting his pics taken.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">They haven't ever really had professional pics taken, but I would have never guessed that. They look like models. Adorable!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2024" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2023/re1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2024" title="re1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/re1.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2028" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2023/re5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2028" title="re5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/re5.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2027" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2023/re4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2027" title="re4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/re4.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2026" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2023/re3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2026" title="re3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/re3.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Meet baby Julie...</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2030" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2023/ju2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2030" title="ju2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/ju2.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I didn't have to pull out many tricks for this shoot, all Julie wanted to do was sleep. Alex her big sister was also so so awesome!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2032" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2023/ju4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2032" title="ju4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/ju4.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">As you can see there is no shortage of kisses for Julie. I think she's going to be a little spoiled.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2034" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2023/ju6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2034" title="ju6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/ju6.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Loooonnnngggg fingers! Oh and she's a serious sucker. If she ever finds her thumb she'll be so happy!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2031" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2023/ju3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2031" title="ju3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/ju3.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Sisters! Alex was like my little assistant during this shoot. The two Al's working together!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2029" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2023/ju1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2029" title="ju1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/ju1.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2033" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2023/ju5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2033" title="ju5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/ju5.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a>I am so so happy Pam sent the Schriever's my way. I just love this family and can't wait to watch baby Julie grow up!</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Baby Photography ~ Kansas City</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2037</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 25 Feb 2011 17:14:03 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=2037</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">I'm proud to announce I have my first protege. Little Eva! She received her first camera for Christmas and hasn't stopped shooting since. Hundreds of pictures later she's developing some real talent. Already I can see she's good at filling the frame, getting in close, and finding interesting angles. Not to mention the subject matter she chooses is superb! You might think I'm joking, but I'm not. During our shoot little Eva took a few minutes to run through some of her shots on her little 2 eye ball Fischer price camera. Some of the moments I spend in my studio are indeed priceless.</p>


<a rel="attachment wp-att-2043" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2037/madi6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2043" title="madi6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/madi6.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">This family is one of my FAVORITES for many reasons. #1 They come all the way up from Fayetteville AK to see me. This makes me feel more than loved if that's even possible. #2 Angie and I are cut from the same cloth so when I see her it's like catching up with an old friend. #3 The kids are perfect in every way, and Tim's cool too. :)</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2045" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2037/madi8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2045" title="madi8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/madi8.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2040" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2037/madi3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2040" title="madi3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/madi3.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2042" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2037/madi5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2042" title="madi5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/madi5.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">"Have you seen my clubs?"</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2044" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2037/madi7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2044" title="madi7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/madi7.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2041" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2037/madi4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2041" title="madi4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/madi4.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">This is a what dude moment!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2046" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2037/madi9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2046" title="madi9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/madi9.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2038" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2037/madi1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2038" title="madi1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/madi1.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2047" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2037/madi2-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2047" title="madi2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/madi21.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Eva you're a doll, Gavin your little fat rolls are to die for cute. I love love loved our time together! Much love to this fam!</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Adorable baby props</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2050</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 08 Mar 2011 20:45:22 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=2050</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">Lynn the owner of <a href="http://www.facebook.com/pages/DizzliciousCreations/106159336120367?ref=ts&amp;sk=wall">Dizzlicious Creation</a>s came by today and made this dark gloomy day oh so much better! She brought me a bag of loot for my newborn sessions.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I just met Lynn a couple weeks ago, but I already love her for so many reasons. #1 She's an artist through and through. #2 She's so fast, and I'm fast, so I kinda love fast people. #3 She's affordable. #4 She can make anything on etsy and then some.! I love etsy, but I avoid it because it just gets me in trouble.  I find it's really hard to afford all the adorable stuff I want, and I want it all. Lynn makes that possible.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Find something on etsy and drop Lynn an email, she'll make if for you! dizzliciouscreations@gmail.com</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">SO SO SO happy!!!!! Below are just a few of the goodies she brought me. I also got an owl hat, but I'll keep that one a surprise for later this week!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Ooohh lala!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2051" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2050/bunny2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2051" title="bunny2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/bunny2.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2052" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2050/football"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2052" title="football" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/football.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>

	<item>
		<title>Home...</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2057</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 10 Mar 2011 23:13:30 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=2057</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">It's been a few days since I got home from the workshop in Santa Fe, and I'm still feeling the thrill of it all. I guess I haven't blogged about it yet because it's hard to put the experience I had into words. I met a lot of awesome poeople that I can now call friends, I learned a ton, and I had fun too. But I guess what I will most remember is the instructor Peter. I don't think I had unrealistic expectations for Peter, I just assumed he would be a little more, I don't know, fullof himself, distant, too cool for school. Ok he's cool, but he's one of the most humble, real, open, awesome people I've ever been around. He wanted to share everything and then some! He came to dinner with us every night, he gave up an afternoon off to follow us around downtown Santa Fe and offer support. He was more than a teacher, he became a friend, and a mentor, and I think the world of him. It's no wonder he gets all the most awesome shoots, it's easy to love him!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.peteryang.com">www.peteryang.com</a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2059" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2057/peter2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2059" title="peter2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/peter2.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Some of the stuff I learned.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">* Fill light is important. I love dramatic light, but my stuff could definitely benefit from some fill light.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">* That I love Flan, and can indeed get tired of mexican food.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">* The higher the kicker light or hair light the less fall off. So that's what inspired the studio search. PS I think I might have found something awesome!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">* High noon full sunlight is awesome. And I can shoot in it without blowing out the background.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">* That it's better to shoot on f8, f11 when using a strobe. I love to shoot wide open as much as possible, but it really is easier to go high.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">* Scrims (a big white sheet) rock! Even I am smart enough to use one.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">* Jajajajaja is hahahaha in South Amerca.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">* Prophoto 7b's are the way to go. I'm gonna have to start saving all my pennies.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">* That hobby photogs have have way better gear than professionals. Sigh...</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">* That I really love beauty, fashion photography. I love to be close.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">* That my favorite light modifier is a soft box with a grid. I thought it was a beauty dish.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">* That sometimes a long focal length is better.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">* That I can evenly light a subject and then take light away.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">* That I know a lot, but have so much more to learn!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Newborn pictures ~ Kansas City Photographer</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2063</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 11 Mar 2011 21:24:31 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=2063</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">It had been over a week since I'd held a newborn baby in my arms. I'm not gonna lie, I missed it. Kind of scary thing to say out loud since I am so not ready to have kids. I just love the feeling when a new mom walks in with her itty bitty baby. I love their tiny hands, the baby smell, and the fact that they are so fragile, and needy. I've gotten really good at finding rhythmn during these shoots. Not something I could say last year. I know how to comfort them, when to shoot, when to feed, and when to go ahead and change their diaper. I even have a whole slew of trips on how to quite them. Ok, maybe I'm a little more ready, but that's a whole nother blog.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Meet Griffin...</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2064" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2063/c1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2064" title="c1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/c1.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">And his sis Delaney. She's 2 and a firecracker! I love that she totally bonded with me. I got some great expressions, and she has amazing big blue eyes!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2068" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2063/c5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2068" title="c5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/c5.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2071" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2063/c8"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2071" title="c8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/c8.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Unlike his sister, Griffin is totally chilled out all the time. He slept, and slept, and slept. I LOVED it!!!!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2066" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2063/c3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2066" title="c3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/c3.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2070" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2063/c7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2070" title="c7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/c7.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">The new hat on the right is from <a href="http://www.facebook.com/DizzliciousCreations?ref=ts">Dizzilicious Designs</a>.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a style="text-decoration: none;" rel="attachment wp-att-2072" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2063/c9"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2072" title="c9" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/c9.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">This monkey hat too! I love the pic on the left.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2069" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2063/c6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2069" title="c6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/c6.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">How do you get a 2 year old to cooperate during pictures? You're lookin' at it! We held that sucker over her head for a whole hour.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2065" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2063/c2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2065" title="c2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/c2.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2067" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2063/c4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2067" title="c4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/c4.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Kacey, and Levi I'm so happy you are friends with Jen, and I'm so happy you live here, and I'm so happy you found me!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I can't wait for more pics to come! What a blast!</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Infertility Awareness</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2076</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 14 Mar 2011 15:36:13 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=2076</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">It's becoming more and more common for women to come to my studio with stories of the challenges of getting pregnant. When I see them, they are overcome with joy, they love everything about their bodies. Just relieved to finally be pregnant. They are the happiest pregnant people.  But their stories make me realize just how much luck goes into having a baby. So when Allison Spencer one of my amazing, awesome, clients told me she was going to start an infertility support group, I was more than excited to share this with my friends and followers. It's just been a few months, and already Allison and her group have a free conference planned. There are going to be speakers, panels, and give aways, including a sitting with me. I look forward to watching as great things come from this group.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.facebook.com/pages/Kansas-City-Infertility-Awareness/161714753875691?ref=ts">Facebook</a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2077" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2076/img217"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-2077" title="img217" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/img217-694x900.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="583" /></a></p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Photo workshop 101 ~ April 30th</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2080</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 15 Mar 2011 21:30:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=2080</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/the-workshop">Workshop</a> time! Calling all hobby/amatuer photogs ready to take better pics. This workshop is for all ya'll that look at your photos and think "what the?". I'll be putting my teaching shoes on for another day of fun. Below are a few shots Jon boy snapped last fall. If the content is boring I promise I will not be.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">We'll be learning all the technical mumbo jumbo in the morning, I'll give you a few creative guidelines and you'll have time to shoot. Last time I was uber impressed with the quality of work the class turned out. They were artists in the making.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Sign up <a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/the-workshop">here</a>.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-2082" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2080/ws1"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-2082" title="ws1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/ws1-900x673.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="336" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Jon boy was our model last time, but this time I think I'll have some real models. Or just hot friends.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-2084" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2080/ws3"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-2084" title="ws3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/ws3-900x673.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="336" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Hopefully I'll be able to answer all your questions.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-2083" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2080/ws2"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-2083" title="ws2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/ws2-675x900.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="600" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2085" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2080/ws4"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-2085" title="ws4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/ws4-900x673.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="336" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">See you at the <a href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/the-workshop">workshop</a> on April 30th! Just a few spots left!</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Newborns, Newborns, Newborns!      Newborns, Newborns, Newborns!</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2092</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 17 Mar 2011 03:21:44 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=2092</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">I have made it annoyingly obvious that I love newborns, but I can't say it enough. I love how I get to hold them, and cuddle with them, and then hand them back when they get stinky diapers. Right now I would say 75% of my clients are newborns. It's awesome. I can't get enough!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Here's a little guy I got to hang out with yesterday! Meet Braeden...</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2094" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2092/br2-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2094" title="br2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/br2.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">These are his adorable parents Addam and Lindsay! I loved how they oohhed and Ahhed when I showed them the pics on the back of my camera. Even Addam.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Oh and looking at this pic you might think Braeden is like a 3 month old. Nope, he's 2 weeks and huge!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2097" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2092/br5-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2097" title="br5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/br5.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I love when this happens! Maybe next time I'll be able to see both of their dimples.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2095" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2092/br3-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2095" title="br3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/br3.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2096" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2092/br4-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2096" title="br4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/br4.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a><a rel="attachment wp-att-2093" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2092/br1-2"></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">What a wonderful baby and even more wonderful family! I absolutely loved my time with them. It's funny how often I feel like I've known my clients forever even after just a few hours. Sigh...I love my job!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2093" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2092/br1-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2093" title="br1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/br1.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Braeden, you are perfection!</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Newborn photography...Kansas City</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2100</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 22 Mar 2011 03:16:41 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=2100</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">They met in college at K-state, back when they were wild college kids. I think they are still kinda wild, and I know they are always busy which is why they probably didn't have time to tell the world they were expecting. So when I posted the pics on facebook their loving friends went wild with excitement. They are so very loved, and I can see why!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2106" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2100/ma1-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2106" title="ma1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/ma1.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Even though Jonas was sick with chills, but he didn't show it. He wins the hubby of the year award for sure!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2107" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2100/ma2-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2107" title="ma2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/ma2.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Mary just kept smiling.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2108" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2100/ma5-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2108" title="ma5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/ma5.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I get the feeling these two will make a great team.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2109" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2100/ma3-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2109" title="ma3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/ma3.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Then came Henry!  Henry is adorable, cuddly, and strong, and hungry.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-2101" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2100/jonas1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2101" title="jonas1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/jonas1.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Oh, and lucky! Mary and Jonas love being parents and are so very in love with this little man! Check out his knees.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-2104" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2100/jonas4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2104" title="jonas4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/jonas4.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">I said sleepy right?</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-2102" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2100/jonas2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2102" title="jonas2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/jonas2.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>

&nbsp;

<a rel="attachment wp-att-2103" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2100/jonas3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2103" title="jonas3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/jonas3.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>

&nbsp;
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2105" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2100/jonas5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2105" title="jonas5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/jonas5.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Henery, Jonas and Mary I had a blast during our time together. What a great family!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">xoxoxoxoxo</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Newborn Pictures~ Kansas City Photography</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2113</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 25 Mar 2011 17:51:09 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=2113</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">Meet darling Amy!  She's a new mom, and a military mom at that. When we did her maternity pictures she was so much fun. Since it was just the two of us it was some seriously good girl time!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2121" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2113/amy1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2121" title="amy1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/amy1.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">He hubby Isaiah was in Afghanistan during the session. In fact, he was fighting a war the whole time she was pregnant. That is why I think Amy is one of the strongest women...ever!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2124" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2113/amy4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2124" title="amy4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/amy4.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I mean, she didn't have anyone to pamper her, to listen to her complain about the troubles of pregnancy, to get her midnight ice cream, or to yell at just because. I know I couldn't do it, but Amy was good real good. Happy even. That's what I love about her.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2123" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2113/amy3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2123" title="amy3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/amy3.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Luckily Isaiah was able to come home for the delivery of his first born. But not by much. Little baby did not want to come out, and Amy was induced just a week before Isaiah was scheduled to go back to war. In fact we took baby Aden's newborn pictures the day before he was scheduled to return.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Meet Aden.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-2115" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2113/gaan2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2115" title="gaan2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/gaan2.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">I'm so happy we were able to get their pictures done, because Isaiah is such a nice guy, and a great dad! It was so fun watching these new parents adore their baby. In fact, I had to tell them to stop looking at the baby and look at the camera. Pretty funny. Ok look here. Click. They immediately look down. Hilarious.</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-2120" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2113/gaan7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2120" title="gaan7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/gaan7.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a>
<p style="text-align: center;">Remember how I said Amy was strong. Yah I wasn't kidding she delivered Aden naturally. Not because she wanted to prove something, but because she was just moving through labor without much problem. Then she decided anepiduralwas a good idea, but it was too late. She was 9.5 and ready to push. WHAT A WOMAN!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2118" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2113/gaan5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2118" title="gaan5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/gaan5.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">There are about 20 amazing pics of Aden and Isaiah. I feel so lucky to have gotten to capture these amazing moments!</p>
<a rel="attachment wp-att-2119" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2113/gaan6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2119" title="gaan6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/gaan6.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a>

<a rel="attachment wp-att-2116" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2113/gaan3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2116" title="gaan3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/gaan3.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a>

&nbsp;
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2117" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2113/gaan4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2117" title="gaan4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/gaan4.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I love funny people and Amy is definitely funny.  We were talking about how Aden is a bit jaundice and Amy's response was that he's even more yellow than normal.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Pretty funny!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2114" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2113/gaan1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2114" title="gaan1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/gaan1.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Aden was such a perfect little model, I finished the shoot feeling totally spoiled. I loved all my time with this family, and look forward to many more.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Isaiah my thoughts are with you and I'm wishing you a quick and safe return! xoxo</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Newborn Photography</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2137</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 31 Mar 2011 14:59:33 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=2137</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">The plan was to do maternity pics first, but that plan was busted when baby Michael Vernon arrived early. Donna was disappointed, but I'm sure a little relieved to have the pregnancy over. By the time I see women, they are over being pregnant. Let me back up, Donna started her family later in life. Her first daughter Alexis was a perfect accident. But a few years later when she wanted to try to have another child she couldn't. By that time she was entering her 40's, and doctors were discouraging. She didn't listen and it's a good thing because now she's got a beautiful boy! Meet Michael!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2138" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2137/witt1-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2138" title="witt1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/witt11.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Michael is the perfect newborn to photograph. He didn't need to eat all the time, he didn't cry much, and all he really wanted to do was sleep!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2140" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2137/witt3-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2140" title="witt3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/witt31.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">His mom is a teacher in the Kansas City School District, which makes her an angel in my eyes. Teaching in poverty is the hardest job in the world!  Bless the good people willing to do it everyday.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2142" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2137/witt5-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2142" title="witt5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/witt51.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Big Sis Alexis!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2139" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2137/witt2-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2139" title="witt2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/witt21.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2141" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2137/witt4-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2141" title="witt4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/witt41.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Daddy Mike owns his own window tinting business. I love the contrast of hands.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2143" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2137/witt6-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2143" title="witt6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/witt61.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2145" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2137/witt8-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2145" title="witt8" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/witt81.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2144" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2137/witt7-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2144" title="witt7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/witt71.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">What a perfect day I got to spend taking pictures with this family! I loved every second of it, and look forward to many more.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>The start...</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2149</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 21 Apr 2011 16:17:08 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=2149</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I've been reading a lot of self help type books lately, OK I can't lie, I'm always reading those kind of books. I love getting the advice of others, some is good and some is so so, but all is worth hearing. Sometimes it sticks, like sap on my car hood. I can't get rid of it no matter what, and that's when I know it's worth acknowledging. The recent advice that stuck was to be invisible. Not literally, like the invisible man, but in my business. I guess I need to show everyone everything. My first reaction puts a sour taste in my mouth. It's that voice in my head again. No not the crazy one, the one I call head trash that says, "Why would anyone want to hear anything about your life?" I stomp on that voice and push on, I guess that's why I'm here writing this. To prove to myself and my head trash that I can feel the fear and do it anyway. So I'm starting at the beginning. My journey into becoming an open book, invisible.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I get asked all the time how long I've been taking pictures, and the answer varies depending on my mood. Sometimes it's since high school, or college, or since I started my business. But most recently I've been saying forever, because well, it has been forever, my forever anyway. I remember being on vacation with my family when I was young. Not sure how young, but I want to say 8ish. I wanted to take pictures of everything and anything. I guess I bugged my parents enough to get my own camera. It was blue and took 110 film. And cheap, I mean the camera. It was brave for them to buy me a camera now that I think about it because they had to buy film, and then pay to process the film. Dang it was kinda expensive. Maybe they thought it was another one of my quick loves. You know the ones that fade with the season.  Yup, I'm one of those people. But photography stuck.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I wish I still had that little blue camera and maybe I do tucked away in the drawers of my childhood room.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">It looked something like this only ocean blue.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2152" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2149/31nd3zznvfl-_sl500_aa300_"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2152" title="31ND3ZZNVFL._SL500_AA300_" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/31ND3ZZNVFL._SL500_AA300_.jpeg" alt="" width="300" height="300" /></a> I took hundreds of rolls of film with that little beauty. In fact I wouldn't go on vacation without it. I remember packing my little Royals bag with this and that, but always my camera.  It went on every family vacation with us for years. Then I used it in 6th grade to take pictures for a photo contest. That's when things started to change for me. It's wasn't just about the memories anymore.  Every day on my way home from school I would stop at the pond by my house where 2 swans lived. They would come over to the dock because they knew I had saved them part of my pbj sandwich. I must have taken a dozen rolls of film trying to get the perfect shot. Most of them were exactly the same. But one of those pictures was THE SHOT.  I titled it "the perfect family" even though I was pretty sure they were the same sex. But with birds, eh who knows. That's when I realized I was in love with photography, and maybe a little nerdy.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2151" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2149/camera-2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2151" title="camera" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/camera1.jpg" alt="" width="475" height="400" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I went on to take many more pictures in high school. I had two photography teachers. Mr. Zinger was my first and kinda make me feel bad about my work. In the end I think it pushed me to get better, but at the time it was hard to swallow the criticism. He was always telling me my pics were to gray. I guess that's why I like lots of contrast now. Later I had Mrs. Gaverth. She was awesome! She helped build my ego right back up. In high school I shot with my dad's old camera. I mostly shot with TMAX 400. I learned how to process the film and develop the pictures. I learned that making pictures is like magic when the plain white paper hits the fixer. I also learned I loved the smell of fixer on my fingers. It never goes away, so it's a good thing I liked it.</p>
&nbsp;
<p style="text-align: center;">Then in college I did a mentorship class with the photography teacher because I took all the photog classes. He was the teacher that encouraged me to go to art school. I was waaaayyy too in love with Jon to leave William Woods, but I'll never forget his confident words. In college I learned I didn't like studio work, or using tripods, they were both stifling, or so I thought. But I started to identify my style....close.  I mean I didn't know that then, but I do now. I didn't go to school for photography, but it was alwasys there. And who knows maybe I would have ended up in the same place.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I was still shooting film back then, and I shot with a Nikon F5. Digital was just getting introduced, and I remember Mr. Elliott let me use his digital camera my senior year. Man that thing was slow and I think only 4 mega pixels.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2169" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2149/nikonf5front80mm"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2169" title="NikonF5front80mm" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/NikonF5front80mm.jpeg" alt="" width="432" height="422" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Once I was out of college I focused on my career at a teacher, but the desire to take pictures was always there. My dad continued to quietly support my passion. So as soon as I could I built a studio in my house. That was 6 years ago.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I guess the rest is yet to come. Every day I want to grow, learn and get better. I don't have a desire to be "the best" or famous. Right now I just want to reach my goals one at a time.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">In writing this I realize just how in love with photography I've always been.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Because I feel like I should give my current camera some love here's a pic of my big baby.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2170" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2149/zbeauty"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-2170" title="ZBEAUTY" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/ZBEAUTY-841x900.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="481" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Boudoir, Bellies, then Babies!</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2153</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 16 Apr 2011 18:03:49 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=2153</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">I think bellies, babies and boudoir just sounds better so that's why I have it in that order on my website, but really, it should go boudoir, bellies, then babies. That's the order Erin chose to get her pics taken.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I'll leave the boudoir photos for Greg, but I would like to share a little bit about the belly and baby!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">It started a few years back when Jon handed me gift certificates for free massages, I was a little more than stoked. But that's before I even met Erin and learned that she's a passionate business <a href="http://www.caringtouchmassage.biz/">owner</a>, always looking to better herself and her business. She was working at the NAIC with Jon at the time, but wan't happy. Her heart was in massage. So when she decided to jump ship, and go out on her own, I was in awe and oh so inspired! We would spend our time together talking about how it felt to be self- employed, sharing ideas for what's working, and what's not. Always with a smile, she would quietly encourage me to "just do it". She's an outstanding massage therapist, but an even better friend. She really inspired, and pushed me to go for my dreams. She made it seem doable. I noticed her whole person changing when she went full time into massage therapy, and dreamt of the day I would have that glow.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">We didn't always talk about business, sometimes we talked about babies. We shared a fear of motherhood. Both of us worried we just weren't going to be good enough. Erin again jumped ship. And again I am so proud. Maybe not as inspired just yet, but definitely happy for her.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2165" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2153/erin4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2165" title="erin4" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/erin4.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Her pregnancy was a nasty one. She was sick for her first 2 trimesters. She actually lost weight getting pregnant!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2164" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2153/erin3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2164" title="erin3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/erin3.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">She was still glowing but for a whole different reason. Baby! Oh and I didn't mention that she's kinda obsessed with Greg her husband. I swear I've seen her staring at him countless times with a smile that looks a lot like a school girl with a crush.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2162" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2153/erin1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2162" title="erin1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/erin1.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Then baby Autumn arrived! Unlike the pregnancy the delivery was a smooth one. Just 15 minutes of pushing. All the mommas out there that pushed for 2 hours are now allowed to groan.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2156" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2153/aut2"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2156" title="aut2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/aut2.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Oh course I was dying to hear everything! Erin made it seem way to easy. And she said it was because she had so much love for Autumn.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">But honestly if I'm going to give credit to someone it's Greg. He was like the baby whisperer! Seriously impressive!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2160" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2153/aut6"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2160" title="aut6" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/aut6.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2155" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2153/aut1"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2155" title="aut1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/aut1.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a><a rel="attachment wp-att-2157" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2153/aut3"></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Newborns don't giggle and laugh but this kinda looks like she is. Love it!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2157" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2153/aut3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2157" title="aut3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/aut3.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2159" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2153/aut5"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2159" title="aut5" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/aut5.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Happy Easter everyone!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2161" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2153/aut7"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2161" title="aut7" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/aut7.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Thank you so much for letting me take pictures of your little Autumn. I look forward to watching her grow into a big girl! And I look forward to Erin getting back to work. I need a <a href="http://www.caringtouchmassage.biz/">massage</a>! :)</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>A tile dress, my first national ad campaign, and reality.</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2186</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 25 Apr 2011 20:11:36 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=2186</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">
I think I come off confident, fearless, and maybe even arrogant. But...I'm really not. I mean I use to say that I was fearless. And I am, when it comes to public speaking, rock climbing, snakes, meeting new people, and trying new things. But I'm not when it comes to my photography.  There are so many more talented photogs out there, for me to compare myself to, that often I feel lost, like a single stalk of wheat in a huge field, just trying to be big enough to see what's goin' on. So today, when I received my<a href="http://www.interiordesign.net/">Interior Design</a> magazine with one of my picture as a full page ad I felt, well, the same. It's funny, I thought some of those insecurities would dissolve. But I'm still just Allison, a Kansas City girl, who loves to play tennis, and gets to do what she loves everyday as her job! I'm still looking forward, and hoping that someone out there likes my work. This week I hope to release my new commercial website and I'm eager but anxious. Here's the ad. So excited to share!!!!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2187" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2186/at1-4"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2187" title="at1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/at11.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2188" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2186/at2-3"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2188" title="at2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/at21.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a></p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title></title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2127</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 31 Mar 2011 14:48:14 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=2127</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">The plan was to do maternity pics first, but that plan was busted when baby Michael Vernon arrived early. Donna was disappointed, but I'm sure a little relieved to have the pregnancy over. By the time I see women, they are over being pregnant. Let me back up, Donna started her family later in life. Her first daughter Alexis was a perfect accident. But a few years later when she wanted to try to have another child she couldn't. By that time she was entering her 40's, and doctors were discouraging. She didn't listen and it's a good thing because now she's got a beautiful boy! Meet Michael!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2128" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?attachment_id=2128"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2128" title="witt1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/witt1.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="499" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2130" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?attachment_id=2130"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2130" title="witt3" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/witt3.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="499" /></a></p>]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>
		<wp:post_id>2127</wp:post_id>

		<wp:post_date_gmt>2011-03-31 14:48:14</wp:post_date_gmt>

	<item>
		<title>Tile dress, big city, and my first national ad campaign</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2182</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 25 Apr 2011 20:04:13 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=2182</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I think I come off confident, fearless, and maybe even arrogant. But...I'm really not. I mean I use to say that I was fearless. And I am, when it comes to public speaking, rock climbing, snakes, meeting new people, and trying new things. But I'm not when it comes to my photography.  There are so many more talented photogs out there for me to compare myself to that often I feel lost, like a single stalk of wheat in a huge field, just trying to get big enough to see what's goin on. So today when I received my <a href="http://www.interiordesign.net/">Interior Design</a> magazine with one of my picture as a full page ad I felt, well, the same. It's funny, I thought some of those insecurities would dissolve. But I'm still just Allison, a Kansas City girl, who loves to play tennis, and gets to do what she loves everyday as her job! I'm looking forward, and hoping that someone out there likes my work. This week I hope to release my new commercial website and I'm eager but anxious.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2183" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?attachment_id=2183"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2183" title="at1" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/at1.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2184" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?attachment_id=2184"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2184" title="at2" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/at2.jpg" alt="" width="751" height="500" /></a></p>

	<item>
		<title>Workflow</title>
		<link>http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2191</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 28 Apr 2011 20:27:20 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.allisoncarenza.com/?p=2191</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;">I'm kinda a right brain person. I go with the flow. I throw things together at the last minute. I use kitchen utensils for repairing the car when we don't have the right tool. Ok I've never repaired the car, but you get the point. I just like to think outside the box. Scratch that, I like to live outside the box. Which is why I probably love my job so much. Having said that, there is a big part of a photography business that is so not right brain friendly. The books, the taxes, the workflow. Out of those 3, workflow is the least miserable, so I'll start there.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I am random, but I like to work fast, and be efficient. This is probably not the best, but right now it's the best for me. My pics go from camera to client in about a week to 2 weeks. Today I'll just cover the computer part.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Step 1: I take the pictures.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Step 2: I download the pics to my computer in<a href="http://www.adobe.com/products/bridge.html"> adobe bridge</a>. I have an AC2011 file that has each month in it. I'm supposed to burn a CD each month at the end of the month and delete it from my computer, but yah I'm way behind. In the month file, I have each shoot labeled with a date and family name. So a shoot done today would be labeled like this. AC2011/April/4-28-11 Moore</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Step 3: Once they are on the computer I import them into Lightroom where I process the RAW files. Once I'm done I export them back to the same file under edited.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">AC2011/April/4-28-11 Moore/edited</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Step 4: I back up those edited files on my external hard drive which is set up in a similar way. I then delete the RAW files. Notice I have not cleared my card until they are backed up in a second place.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Step 5: I do a quick run through the images in Bridge to see if any need <a href="http://www.adobe.com/products/photoshop.html?sdid=FIGGA&amp;skwcid=TC|22182|CS4%20photoshop||S|b|7503287058">photoshopping</a>. This step can add a lot of time if the images need a lot of work.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Step 6: I upload a small preview to facebook and then the rest to my site for the clients to view. Sometimes I do a blog, and sometimes I don't have time.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Step 7: I email the clients the link and yay I'm done!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">7 steps that take about 2 hours give or take from start to finish. Slower sometimes because I daydream. Being right brained can be so frustrating.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">I hope some other random right brained peeps out there find this useful, please share with your photog friends. If you have any questions don't hesitate to post them.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Much Love and Happy Shooting my friends!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">No blog is complete without a pic. My Papa on his 90th with my aunt Martha, and cousin Courtney.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2192" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2191/pap90th"></a><a rel="attachment wp-att-2192" href="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/archives/2191/pap90th"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-2192" title="pap90th" src="http://www.allisoncarenza.com/studio/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/pap90th-900x605.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="302" /></a></p>]]></content:encoded>
